#. [race], id=AE_roswellian
#: .\units\archaic_units\menagerie_race.cfg:70
msgid ""
"The Magnellian civilization reached great heights and enlightenment, despite "
"some flaws. They dared to reach out and touch the stars, and the first alien "
"civilization they encountered was a race of bald, bug-eyed, rubbery dwarves, "
"who seemed to lack any gender or emotion. Yet they must have some emotion, "
"for once the two peoples could communicate, the Magnellians couldn't help but"
" detect a hint of good humor when the rubbery dwarves explained that they "
"were 'Roswell Greys'. The Magnellians had no idea what that meant, but the "
"name stuck, and the 'little green men' were hence known as 'Roswellians'\n"
"\n"
"Outerspace is vast, empty, and dangerous, so the Roswellian and Magnellian "
"civilizations did not assimilate quickly.  When the Magnellians stumbled "
"across the Destroyer, and were subsumed into the terrible force of "
"destruction that keeps the universe free of galactic empires, the Roswellians"
" had but a small outpost exposed.  A handful of Roswellian workers and "
"soldiers were swept up in the enslavement of the Magnellians, but the rest of"
" their civilization was able to sever ties and flee the trap of the "
"Destroyer."
msgstr ""

