#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Orcish_Destrier, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Destrier.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The elite members of the orcish cavalry have reached a great level of prowess"
" and notoriety upon the battle field, but are expensive to maintain for both "
"orc and mount must be in top physical shape. As a result, they do not try to "
"become warlords, but seek warlord patrons who will pay their upkeep in "
"exchange for the long and strong arm they can provide."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Orcish_Drifter, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Drifter.cfg:4
msgid "Orcish Drifter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Orcish_Drifter, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Drifter.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Some orcs have finer features and less physical strength, it's not clear they"
" are even of the same species. These Drifters move from clan to clan, helping"
" their hosts with esoteric arts not otherwise available to the orcish clans. "
"They are also messengers of higher-level, inter-clan, messages. They are "
"essentially diplomats and observers, and have learned how to deal with the "
"ghosts that roam the northern drifts."
msgstr ""

#. [heals], id=healing
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Drifter.cfg:22
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Traveler.cfg:45
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Vagrant.cfg:23
msgid "medicine"
msgstr ""

#. [heals], id=healing
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Drifter.cfg:23
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Traveler.cfg:46
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Vagrant.cfg:24
msgid ""
"This unit uses esoteric herbal remedies to heal units on the battlefield "
"(including itself) and slow poison.\n"
"A unit cared for by this healer may heal up to 4 HP per turn, or slow poison."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Orcish_Firebreather, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Firebreather.cfg:4
msgid "Orcish Firebreather"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Orcish_Firebreather, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Firebreather.cfg:17
msgid ""
"After some experience with wielding a torch as a weapon, the upper-level "
"Fireline searched for another advantage to exploit. Orcs are not known for "
"thinking about the long-term health consequences of their actions, so the "
"upper-level Fireline have no reservations about filling their mouths with "
"whatever light oils were available and spitting through their torch, into the"
" face of their opponent. Hence the name, 'Firebreather'."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Firebreather.cfg:45
msgid "fire"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Orcish_Fireline, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Fireline.cfg:5
msgid "Orcish Fireline"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Orcish_Fireline, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Fireline.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The Orcish Fireline is a development that arose from the arms race between "
"the northern orcs and the Ukians. The Ukian signal corps combined a torch and"
" an axe for both long range communication and diverse armament. The orcs knew"
" nothing of the long range communication, but found the torch and blade "
"combination could indeed be effective."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Orcish_Foreman, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Foreman.cfg:4
msgid "Orcish Foreman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Orcish_Foreman, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Foreman.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Goblins can be corralled into labour by sheer force, but that does not work "
"as well with orcs themselves. These field-captains manage the lower-ranking "
"orcs through a mixture of persuasion and coercion that might seem crude to "
"some outsiders, but it does work."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Frost_Goblin, race=goblin
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Frost-Goblin.cfg:15
msgid "Frost Goblin"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Frost_Goblin, race=goblin
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Frost-Goblin.cfg:29
msgid ""
"Frost Goblins are a subset of Goblin Impalers that have acquired more "
"sensible clothing for the cold, so they are not as helpless on the snow."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Goblin_Drummer, race=goblin
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Frost-Goblin.cfg:109
msgid "Goblin Drummer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Goblin_Drummer, race=goblin
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Frost-Goblin.cfg:123
msgid ""
"Braying and howling like an idiot may pass for leadership amongst the "
"southern goblins, but for the goblins of the ice and tundra, a more "
"thoughtful approach has proven successful. The drum-beats provide a sense of "
"purpose and assurance in those vital moments before battle, so there is no "
"fear in the hearts of commrades. "
msgstr ""

#. [leadership], id=drumbeat
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Frost-Goblin.cfg:132
msgid "drumbeat"
msgstr ""

#. [leadership], id=drumbeat
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Frost-Goblin.cfg:133
msgid "female^drumbeat"
msgstr ""

#. [leadership], id=drumbeat
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Frost-Goblin.cfg:134
msgid ""
"This unit can offer reassurance to allies, counteracting a time-of-day "
"penalty during daylight hours."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Orcish_Hunter, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Hunter.cfg:4
msgid "Orcish Hunter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Orcish_Hunter, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Orcish_Slinger, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Orcish_Stalker, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Hunter.cfg:16
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Slinger.cfg:17
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Stalker.cfg:39
msgid ""
"The Hunters have an ability to stay at least one step ahead of the scouts and"
" explorers, for whatever the target may be. They are also often employed to "
"complement patrols of the more powerful orcish banners."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Orcish_Overseer, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Overseer.cfg:4
msgid "Orcish Overseer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Orcish_Overseer, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Overseer.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The successful battle-field leaders gain more power and authority, as would "
"be expected. Perhaps it is a comment on orcish politics that these leaders "
"have also learned a theif's knife-play."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Orcish_Ox_Rider, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Oxrider.cfg:4
msgid "Orcish Ox-Rider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Orcish_Ox_Rider, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Oxrider.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Despite their reputation for stupidity, the orcs do learn tactics from their "
"enemy. The more observant orcs note the utility of the human cavalry, and "
"note that certain large animals have no trouble keeping their footing on "
"snow."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Orcish_Raider, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Raider.cfg:4
msgid "Orcish Raider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Orcish_Raider, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Raider.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The Raiders wear an ugly bronze mask to make themselves more fearsome to the "
"easily frightened humans. They also wear a large number of trinkets, given to"
" them by the drifters and wanderers, designed to ward off the poisons and "
"chills often encountered in the north."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Cave_Dragoon, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Rat_Dragoon.cfg:4
msgid "Cave Dragoon"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Cave_Dragoon, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Rat_Dragoon.cfg:30
msgid ""
"The northern cave rat is a semi-aquatic mammal about the size of a wolf. It "
"has a large flat tail for swimming and powerful incissors for biting through "
"tree roots, as it lives underground and near water. They are social animals, "
"like wolves, so they have similarly been approached by the more determined "
"goblins.\n"
"The dragoons are veteran lancers, and have continued to scavenge better "
"armor.  Their relationship with the rat has paid dividends for the rodent, "
"for the goblins practice their spearing by hunting smaller animals, and while"
" the rats will eat anything, they benefit from the richer diet of a predator."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Rat_Dragoon.cfg:107
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Rat_Lancer.cfg:106
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Rat_Rider.cfg:94
msgid "tail-slap"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Cave_Lancer, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Rat_Lancer.cfg:4
msgid "Cave Lancer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Cave_Lancer, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Rat_Lancer.cfg:29
msgid ""
"The northern cave rat is a semi-aquatic mammal about the size of a wolf. It "
"has a large flat tail for swimming and powerful incissors for biting through "
"tree roots, as it lives underground and near water. They are social animals, "
"like wolves, so they have similarly been approached by the more determined "
"goblins.\n"
"The lancers have an improved understanding with their mount, so they can use "
"their thighs and heels to communicate, freeing their hand to hold a spear.  "
"They've also scavenged better pieces of armor."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Rat_Lancer.cfg:118
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Rat_Rider.cfg:106
#: .\units\archaic_units\south-seas\Rover.cfg:44
#: .\units\archaic_units\south-seas\Wolf.cfg:52
msgid "dart"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Goblin_Rat_Rider, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Rat_Rider.cfg:4
msgid "Goblin Rat-Rider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Goblin_Rat_Rider, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Rat_Rider.cfg:29
msgid ""
"The northern cave rat is a semi-aquatic mammal about the size of a wolf. It "
"has a large flat tail for swimming and powerful incissors for biting through "
"tree roots, as it lives underground and near water. They are social animals, "
"like wolves, so they have similarly been approached by the more determined "
"goblins.\n"
"The riders have established a working relationship with the rats, but still "
"need to keep one hand on the scruff of the animal's neck, so they only carry "
"a wooden shield and no weapon."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Orcish_Knave, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Serf.cfg:4
msgid "Orcish Knave"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Orcish_Knave, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Serf.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Although most labour can be and is in fact done by goblins, projects that "
"must be completed on a stricter time-table or under greater threat, such as "
"seizure of timber or the construction of a front-line fortress, are carried "
"out by the stronger hands of these orcs."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Orcish_Slinger, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Slinger.cfg:4
msgid "Orcish Slinger"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Orcish_Stalker, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Stalker.cfg:4
msgid "Orcish Stalker"
msgstr ""

#. [advancement], id=amla_drifter
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Stalker.cfg:20
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Traveler.cfg:20
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Wanderer.cfg:21
msgid "Max HP bonus +2, Max XP +10%, Damage +1"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Stork_Master, race=goblin
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Stork_Master.cfg:4
msgid "Stork Master"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Stork_Master, race=goblin
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Stork_Master.cfg:34
msgid ""
"As time goes by, the bird and goblin come to understand each other, so that "
"their movement and response is better coordinated."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Marabou_Stork, race=goblin
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Stork_Rider.cfg:4
msgid "Marabou Stork"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Marabou_Stork, race=goblin
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Stork_Rider.cfg:33
msgid ""
"Marabou storks are carrion eaters with bald heads. A heavily feathered "
"variety lives in the North and follows the orcish tribes, feasting upon the "
"corpses and carcasses the orcs leave in their wake. Much like the wolf "
"riders, some goblins try to escape their pitiful fate and master the skys on "
"the backs of one of these birds. Of course, the birds do not want to fly with"
" some other animal on their back, but over time, the birds learn that there "
"is more food to be had if they tolerate the cargo. The long avian feet and "
"oily feathers allow the bird and rider to traverse water terrain with great "
"ease."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Orcish_Terror, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Terror.cfg:4
msgid "Orcish Terror"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Orcish_Terror, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Terror.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The Terror has added horns to the mask and helmet, because they seem to scare"
" the humans. The Terror has also spent enough time in the cities and "
"settlements to have become well aware of how to use the surroundings to his "
"advantage. Tired of the ragging he's been getting from his warrior commerads "
"for not using a blade like a real orc, he modifies his weapon, and wishes he "
"thought to do this sooner."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Terror.cfg:36
msgid "chain flail"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Orcish_Traveler, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Traveler.cfg:4
msgid "Traveler"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Orcish_Traveler, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Traveler.cfg:39
msgid ""
"The orcs that most of the denizens of Wesnoth are familiar with are the "
"teaming masses forced out of the Northlands. But the orcish societies are "
"more complicated in those Northlands. Orcs with less physical strength, but "
"greater intelligence, can survive in their own unique niches. Orcish "
"Travelers have spent years moving between various orcish, and sometimes even "
"dwarvish, cities and strongholds, gaining exposure to a wide variety of "
"practices and arts. In general, they are competent warriors, as any orc would"
" be, but each individual can have unique capabilities."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Vagrant, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Vagrant.cfg:4
msgid "Vagrant"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Vagrant, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Vagrant.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The orcs that most of the denizens of Wesnoth are familiar with are the "
"teaming masses forced out of the Northlands. But the orcish societies are "
"more complicated in those Northlands. The Vagrants are skilled at travelling "
"through the Northland terrain, and while not much more powerful than the "
"common grunt, they are swifter and harder to kill."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Wanderer, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Wanderer, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Wanderer, race=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarf
#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Wanderer, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Wanderer, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Wanderer.cfg:4
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\e1_Wanderer.cfg:5
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Wanderer.cfg:4
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Wanderer.cfg:5
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Wanderer.cfg:5
msgid "Wanderer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_orcs_Wanderer, race=AE_arc_race_north_orc
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Wanderer.cfg:39
msgid ""
"The Wanderers move from clan to clan, helping their hosts with esoteric arts "
"not usually available to the orcish clans. They are also messengers of "
"higher-level, inter-clan, messages. They are essentially diplomats and "
"observers, and have learned how to deal with the ghosts that roam the "
"northern drifts."
msgstr ""

#. [heals], id=healing
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Wanderer.cfg:45
msgid "improved medicine"
msgstr ""

#. [heals], id=healing
#: .\units\archaic_units\orcs\Wanderer.cfg:46
msgid ""
"This unit uses esoteric herbal remedies to heal friendly units on the "
"battlefield (including itself) and slow poison.\n"
"A unit cared for by this healer may heal up to 6 HP per turn, or slow poison."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_phantom_Divine_Jay, race=AE_arc_phantom_spirit
#: .\units\archaic_units\phantom\Divine_Jay.cfg:4
msgid "Divine Jay"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\archaic_units\phantom\Divine_Jay.cfg:87
#: .\units\archaic_units\phantom\Spirit_Dove.cfg:79
#: .\units\archaic_units\phantom\Spirit_Jay.cfg:83
