#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Royal_Herdsman, race=human
#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Royal_Spotter, race=human
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Royal_Horseman.cfg:19
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Royal_Spotter.cfg:19
msgid ""
"The mounted patrol of the northern kingdom ride the massive equine peculiar "
"to the frozen north, and carry a pannier of smoldering coals. They use the "
"coals to keep warm on their long patrols, and also to heat branding irons. "
"The irons are intended for marking animals as the king's property, but they "
"also make decent weapons."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Northern_Ranger, race=human
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Royal_Ranger.cfg:4
msgid "Northern Ranger"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Northern_Ranger, race=human
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Royal_Ranger.cfg:19
msgid ""
"The cold of the far north robs the fingers of their dexterity and makes a bow"
" too hard to use. For this reason, the Northern Rangers favor spears, which "
"do not require nimble fingers, over the bow. These fighters must move alone "
"in the harsh north, away from the warmth of camp or even a horse, so they are"
" relatively unfazed by the touch of cold."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Royal_Rider, race=human
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Royal_Rider.cfg:4
msgid "Northern Rider"
msgstr ""

