#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Royal_Warrior.cfg:4
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Northern_Warrior.cfg:5
msgid "Northern Warrior"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Northern_Warrior, race=human
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Royal_Warrior.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Fierce as the biting winds of his homeland, the Northern Warrior is a "
"testament to the terrific demands nature makes of those who would prosper in "
"the frozen heath. Clad in the finest plate armor worn by any infantry in his "
"kingdom and the pelts of great wolves and bears, he deals death with his "
"fierce blade, while himself nearly invulnerable to steel and cold alike. But "
"he is not invincible: though mighty, he is greatly slowed by his equipment, "
"and those nimble warriors well suited to range over the frigid wastes have "
"been known to wear him to death, by and by, with nothing more than simple "
"spears and stones."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Archer, race=AE_arc_race_ukian, gender=female
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Archer.cfg:4
msgid "Ukian Archer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Archer, race=AE_arc_race_ukian, gender=female
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Archer.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Due to the need for everyone to be able to fend off an orc, all Ukian women "
"learn archery."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Attack_Dog, race=AE_arc_race_dogukian
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Attackdog.cfg:4
msgid "Attack Dog"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Attack_Dog, race=AE_arc_race_dogukian
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Attackdog.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Attack Dogs are highly valued by the Ukians for their proven loyalty and "
"strength, so they are given leather and plates to cover their throats and "
"spines (anything more would be too restrictive). They are not usually used as"
" scouts anymore because of their value at the offensive line. If given the "
"signal, they will throw themselves at the enemy in a fight-to-the-death fury."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Attackdog.cfg:55
#: .\units\EFM_units\Darklanders\f1_Malice.cfg:34
#: .\units\EFM_units\Darklanders\f2_Wrath.cfg:34
#: .\units\EFM_units\Darklanders\f3_Vengence.cfg:29
#: .\units\EFM_units\Darklanders\f4_Judgement.cfg:30
msgid "fury"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Civilian, race=AE_arc_race_ukian
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Civilian.cfg:4
msgid "Ukian Civilian"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Civilian, race=AE_arc_race_ukian
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Civilian.cfg:20
msgid ""
"It used to be the case that everyone had to fight, but those who grew up "
"under the reign of the former King had had reason to believe there was more "
"to life."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Civilian.cfg:25
msgid "punch"
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Civilian.cfg:89
msgid "female^Ukian Civilian"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Commander, race=AE_arc_race_ukian
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Commander.cfg:4
msgid "Ukian Commander"
msgstr ""

#. [advancement], id=amla_commander_sword
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Commander.cfg:21
msgid "Max HP bonus +2, Sword Damage +1, Max Exp penalty 30%"
msgstr ""

#. [advancement], id=amla_commander_crossbow
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Commander.cfg:50
msgid "Max HP bonus +2, Crossbow Damage +1, Max Exp penalty 30%"
msgstr ""

#. [advancement], id=amla_commander_crossbow2
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Commander.cfg:79
msgid "Max HP bonus +2, Crossbow Marksmanship, Max Exp penalty 40%"
msgstr ""

#. [advancement], id=amla_commander_shield
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Commander.cfg:111
msgid "Max HP bonus +2, Shield Damage +2, Impact Resistance 5%, Max Exp penalty 40%"
msgstr ""

#. [advancement], id=amla_commander_armor
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Commander.cfg:148
msgid "Max HP bonus +2, Blade &amp; Pierce Resistance 5%, Max Exp penalty 40%"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Commander, race=AE_arc_race_ukian
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Commander.cfg:184
msgid ""
"Commanders are the military leaders of the Ukians. They get the few crossbows"
" preserved from the old days, and heavier armor. They have the best shields, "
"made of steel, which provide greater protection and cause more damage upon "
"impact."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Commando, race=AE_arc_race_ukian, gender=male
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Commando.cfg:4
msgid "Ukian Commando"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Commando, race=AE_arc_race_ukian, gender=male
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Commando.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Commandos are accustomed to operating alone, and as a result have learned to "
"carry a wide variety easy-to-carry weapons. They've had plenty of practice at"
" evading orcs under the cover of night, they can become almost invisible."
msgstr ""

#. [leadership], id=leadership
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Commando.cfg:30
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Courrier.cfg:30
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Runner.cfg:36
msgid "dog female^trainer"
msgstr ""

#. [leadership], id=leadership
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Commando.cfg:31
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Courrier.cfg:31
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Runner.cfg:37
msgid ""
"Dog Trainer:\n"
"This unit can lead Ukian Dogs that are next to it, making them fight better."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Courier, race=AE_arc_race_ukian, gender=male
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Courrier.cfg:4
msgid "Ukian Courier"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Courier, race=AE_arc_race_ukian, gender=male
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Courrier.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Runners who have proven themselves are given more allowance for supplies "
"because they are entrusted with more important correspondenses. Still, they "
"travel light, so the sling is their weapon of choice."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Deadeye, race=AE_arc_race_ukian, gender=female
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Deadeye.cfg:4
msgid "Ukian Deadeye"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Deadeye, race=AE_arc_race_ukian, gender=female
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Deadeye.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Ukian Deadeyes have been roaming the forrest for a long time and can move "
"about undetected. They can launch many missiles, or they can take a tactic "
"from the orcs and launch more destructive (but slower to load) fire arrows."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Dog, race=AE_arc_race_dogukian
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Dog.cfg:4
msgid "Dog"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Dog, race=AE_arc_race_dogukian
#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Harrier, race=AE_arc_race_dogukian
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Dog.cfg:18
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Harrier.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Dogs are not high maintanence and are useful allies when hunting or scouting."
" Ukian Dogs are weak but fast and nimble so they are good at causing havoc "
"behind enemy lines, but not so good at holding a line. The life of a dog is "
"often short, but they do get tougher with experience."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Flareman, race=AE_arc_race_ukian
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Flareman.cfg:4
msgid "Ukian Flareman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Flareman, race=AE_arc_race_ukian
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Flareman.cfg:90
msgid ""
"Flaremen are elite Signalmen who carry brighter flames, for greater broadcast"
" strength. The brilliance of the flames made combat with orcs a little "
"easier. They've grown accustomed to the heat, so they have a resistance to "
"flame attacks."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Harrier, race=AE_arc_race_dogukian
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Harrier.cfg:4
msgid "Harrier"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Hawkeye, race=AE_arc_race_ukian, gender=female
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Hawkeye.cfg:4
msgid "Ukian Hawkeye"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Hawkeye, race=AE_arc_race_ukian, gender=female
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Hawkeye.cfg:19
msgid ""
"It's not that easy to accurately fire a bow, the Hawkeyes' secret is their "
"ability to fire off so many shots. They can also take a tactic from the orcs "
"and launch more destructive (but slower to load) fire arrows."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Officer, race=AE_arc_race_ukian
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Officer.cfg:4
msgid "Ukian Officer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Officer, race=AE_arc_race_ukian
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Officer.cfg:25
msgid ""
"The Ukian Officers are veteran Regulars, the Ukians didn't have a class "
"structure before the arrival of the King."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Regular, race=AE_arc_race_ukian
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Regular.cfg:4
msgid "Ukian Regular"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Regular, race=AE_arc_race_ukian
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Regular.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Ukian Regulars carry a spear because spears are relatively inexpensive. Like "
"all Ukians, they are accustomed to life on the tundra, and know how to "
"maintain their footing in the snow.\n"
"Special Notes:"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Runner, race=AE_arc_race_ukian, gender=male
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Runner.cfg:4
msgid "Ukian Runner"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Runner, race=AE_arc_race_ukian, gender=male
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Runner.cfg:25
msgid ""
"Because there were no horses in Ukiah, the scouts and messengers travelled by"
" foot, learning to keep pace even over icy terrain. To avoid being spotted, "
"they prefer to travel under the cover of darkness. They can't carry heavy "
"armor and supplies while maintaining their agility, so they are experts at "
"the sling, a weapon for which they don't need to carry the ammunition. "
"Because they are front-line scouts, they often must work with the dogs, and "
"as a result, they have some influence on the moral of their canine "
"colleagues."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Seal, race=AE_arc_race_dogukian
#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Seal, race=monster
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Seal.cfg:4
#: .\units\imperial_units\animals\Seal.cfg:4
msgid "Seal"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Seal, race=AE_arc_race_dogukian
#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Iceblade_Seal, race=AE_arc_race_dogukian
#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Ice_Seal, race=AE_arc_race_dogukian
#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Lion_Seal, race=AE_arc_race_dogukian
#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Pack_Seal, race=AE_arc_race_dogukian
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Seal.cfg:19
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Seal_Blade.cfg:20
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Seal_Ice.cfg:18
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Seal_Lion.cfg:20
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Seal_Pack.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Seals are less attuned to human interaction than are dogs, but they can be "
"trained, and are better at swimming in the deep, cold water often encountered"
" in the north. The Ukians also use tame seals to trick the wild seals they "
"sometimes hunt, which doesn't seem to bother the tame seals."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Iceblade_Seal, race=AE_arc_race_dogukian
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Seal_Blade.cfg:5
msgid "Iceblade Seal"
msgstr ""

#. [hides], id=snow_hide
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Seal_Blade.cfg:44
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Seal_Blade.cfg:46
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Seal_Ice.cfg:42
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Seal_Ice.cfg:44
msgid "snow blend"
msgstr ""

#. [hides], id=snow_hide
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Seal_Blade.cfg:45
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Seal_Blade.cfg:47
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Seal_Ice.cfg:43
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Seal_Ice.cfg:45
msgid "female^snow blend"
msgstr ""

#. [hides], id=snow_hide
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Seal_Blade.cfg:48
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Seal_Blade.cfg:51
msgid ""
"This unit can hide in snow, and remain undetected by its enemies.\n"
"\n"
"Enemy units cannot see this unit while it is on snow or snow hills (but not "
"ice), except if they have units next to it. Any enemy unit that first "
"discovers this unit immediately loses all its remaining movement."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Ice_Seal, race=AE_arc_race_dogukian
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Seal_Ice.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Seal"
msgstr ""

#. [hides], id=snow_hide
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Seal_Ice.cfg:46
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Seal_Ice.cfg:48
msgid ""
"This unit can hide in snow, and remain undetected by its enemies.\n"
"Enemy units cannot see this unit while it is on snow or snow hills (but not "
"ice), except if they have units next to it. Any enemy unit that first "
"discovers this unit immediately loses all its remaining movement."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Lion_Seal, race=AE_arc_race_dogukian
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Seal_Lion.cfg:5
msgid "Lion Seal"
msgstr ""

#. [leadership], id=sealpack
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Seal_Lion.cfg:46
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Seal_Pack.cfg:44
msgid "sealpack"
msgstr ""

#. [leadership], id=sealpack
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Seal_Lion.cfg:47
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Seal_Pack.cfg:45
msgid "female^sealpack"
msgstr ""

#. [leadership], id=sealpack
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Seal_Lion.cfg:48
msgid ""
"This unit fights better when adjacent to other members of the seal pack (any "
"seal of the same team); its attacks do 25% more damage."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Pack_Seal, race=AE_arc_race_dogukian
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Seal_Pack.cfg:4
msgid "Pack Seal"
msgstr ""

#. [leadership], id=sealpack
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Seal_Pack.cfg:46
msgid ""
"This unit fights better when adjacent to other members of the seal pack (any "
"seal of the same side); its attacks do 25% more damage."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Seeress, race=AE_arc_race_ukian, gender=female
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Seeress.cfg:4
msgid "Ukian Seeress"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Seeress, race=AE_arc_race_ukian, gender=female
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Seeress.cfg:19
msgid ""
"So much knowledge was lost during the orcish raids, the Seeresses have had to"
" start from the beginning. While they can't completely form and control a "
"missile, they can send out a shockwave that will stun the enemy if it "
"connects. They are also students of the healing arts."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=ranged
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Seeress.cfg:42
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Witch.cfg:100
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Witch.cfg:367
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Witch.cfg:504
msgid "shockwave"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Signalman, race=AE_arc_race_ukian
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Signalman.cfg:4
msgid "Ukian Signalman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Signalman, race=AE_arc_race_ukian
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Signalman.cfg:92
msgid ""
"Ice, snow, and rough terrain can make it too slow or treacherous to send "
"messages via Runner. Flames can be seen from a distance, so Signalmen send "
"coded messages by waving a torch and passing their axe in front. Standing on "
"top of a hill waving a torch attracts a lot of unwanted attention, so the "
"signal corps is composed of strong fighters."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Subcommander, race=AE_arc_race_ukian
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Subcom.cfg:4
msgid "Ukian Subcommander"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Subcommander, race=AE_arc_race_ukian
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Subcom.cfg:33
msgid ""
"Successful Officers become Subcommanders, and lead greater numbers of "
"fighters. They also carry more substantial shields, which may be used not "
"only to frustrate enemy strikes, but to stun the enemy."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Veteran, race=AE_arc_race_ukian
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Veteran.cfg:4
msgid "Ukian Veteran"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Veteran, race=AE_arc_race_ukian
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Veteran.cfg:19
msgid ""
"The core of the Ukian infantry is the spearman, so not every experienced "
"fighter can leave to join the Officers or Signalmen. The veteran spearmen lay"
" claim to better equipment, and give up the basic throwing knives for the "
"heftier hatchets."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=ranged
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Veteran.cfg:47
msgid "throwing axe"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_War_Hound, race=AE_arc_race_dogukian
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Wardog.cfg:4
msgid "War Hound"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Witch, race=AE_arc_race_ukian, gender=female
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Witch.cfg:4
msgid "Ukian Witch"
msgstr ""

#. [advancement], id=AE_green_witch
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Witch.cfg:20
msgid "Choose path of nature. Max HP bonus +2, Max XP +20%"
msgstr ""

#. [advancement], id=AE_black_witch
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Witch.cfg:49
msgid "Focus on war-time skills. Max HP bonus +2, Max XP +20%"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_arc_ukians_Ukian_Witch, race=AE_arc_race_ukian, gender=female
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Witch.cfg:76
msgid ""
"Ukian Witchs are both proficient in the healing arts and resistent to the "
"elements. Magic attacks are of a different nature, it is difficult to be "
"masters of them as well. Nevertheless, they have managed to control the "
"unformed blast into an electric strike. The uncontrolled blast is easiest to "
"form, so they have not abandoned it."
msgstr ""

#. [variation], id=green
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Witch.cfg:292
msgid "Ukian Green Witch"
msgstr ""

#. [advancement], id=AE_green_adv
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Witch.cfg:310
msgid "Increase Shockwave damage +1, Max HP bonus +2, Max XP +30%"
msgstr ""

#. [variation], id=green
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Witch.cfg:338
msgid ""
"Ukian Witches are both proficient in the healing arts and resistent to the "
"elements. Magic attacks are of a different nature, it is difficult to be "
"masters of them as well. Nevertheless, they have managed to control the "
"unformed blast into an electric strike. The uncontrolled blast is easiest to "
"form, so they have not abandoned it.\n"
"The Green Witches focus on improving their shockwave attack, have better "
"defense in forest and fungus terrains, and are more resilient to arcane "
"attacks.  They are more vulnerable on the artificial castle terrains, "
"however."
msgstr ""

#. [variation], id=black
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Witch.cfg:442
msgid "Ukian Black Witch"
msgstr ""

#. [advancement], id=AE_black_adv
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Witch.cfg:460
msgid "Increase Strike damage +2, No HP bonus or healing, Max XP +30%"
msgstr ""

#. [variation], id=black
#: .\units\archaic_units\ukians\Ukian_Witch.cfg:475
msgid ""
"Ukian Witches are both proficient in the healing arts and resistent to the "
"elements. Magic attacks are of a different nature, it is difficult to be "
"masters of them as well. Nevertheless, they have managed to control the "
"unformed blast into an electric strike. The uncontrolled blast is easiest to "
"form, so they have not abandoned it.\n"
"The Black Witches focus on improving their strike attack, have better defense"
" in artificial terrains (village and castle), and are more resilient to some "
"physical attacks.  They are not as resilient to heat and cold, however."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes.cfg:9
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes.cfg:11
msgid "race^Anakes"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes.cfg:10
msgid "race+female^Anakes"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes.cfg:15
msgid ""
"This race is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"The Anakes are legendary demons, personifications of death and corruption "
"whose only goal is to prepare the Prime Material Plane to be recreated by "
"their god Ba'al and the other Dark Gods.\n"
"Even the bravest warriors hesitated when they faced these war machines "
"without emotions firmly decided to accomplish the will of their god to whom "
"they are fanatically loyal.\n"
"The most terrifying feature of these demons is their ability to canalize the "
"negative energy of the souls of their dead enemies to create new demons who "
"join their legions.\n"
"The Anakes come from a plane known as Muspellsheimr or Avernus, a corrupted "
"wasteland in which they settled their kingdoms and where they were exiled "
"millennia before the arrive of the elves on the Great Continent.\n"
"The majority of the creatures hate and fear those demons and usually try to "
"avoid them. However, some necromancer who worship the Dark Gods of the Anakes"
" cooperated with those demons and sometimes they also turned into demons."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians.cfg:9
msgid "race^Calydonian Human"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians.cfg:10
msgid "race+female^Calydonian Human"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians.cfg:11
msgid "race^Calydonian Humans"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians.cfg:15
msgid ""
"This race is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"Hellenic people get together in the calydonian Hegemony after many centuries "
"of war between city-state. The calydonian domination transformed the hellenic"
" people in a warlike population, perfectly organized in a warlike and "
"expansionist society.\n"
"Thanks to a strong feeling of belonging to the state and a good organisation "
"of the conscription and training of the soldiers, Calydonians managed to "
"establish themselves as rulers of the other population of Hellas: Thracians "
"and Dardanians.\n"
"The relationships between the Calydonians and the other civilisations have "
"always been difficult because of the xenophobia of this population which has "
"fought lots of wars which turned the Calydonians into terrific fighters: firm"
" and disciplined on the battlefield, they often manage to defeat even "
"well-organized armies.\n"
"Despite the strong feeling of belonging to the native country that unites all"
" the Calydonians, the calydonian Hegemony allowed the populations who live in"
" the small islands near Hellas to be independent if they gave military "
"support to the Hegemony. The same relationship of cooperation was then "
"established with the other populations living in Hellas and nowadays all the "
"island is controlled, directly or indirectly, by the calydonian Hegemony."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_bem_wood_warriors_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\wood-warriors.cfg:9
msgid "race^Wood Warrior"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_bem_wood_warriors_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\wood-warriors.cfg:10
msgid "race+female^Wood Warrior"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_bem_wood_warriors_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\wood-warriors.cfg:11
msgid "race^Wood Warriors"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_bem_wood_warriors_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\wood-warriors.cfg:14
msgid ""
"This race is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"Wood Warriors are a quite variegated population. Indeed, this faction isn't "
"composed by only one race but by some different ones with some common "
"traits.In addition to their shy and lone nature (that makes them very skilled"
" in hiding and ambushes), these warriors have in common the choice of the "
"forest as their habitat; some forced to it, others for their own will.The "
"members of this group are mainly legendary creatures, whose existence is "
"still ignored by some. Indeed those who had met this army rarely had such a "
"long life to be able to tell it!Many legends are told about some of them, "
"wherein sometimes they are evil wizards who draw their prey where they can be"
" lethal (into the wood), other times they are told as good creatures living a"
" nature-friendly and cheerful life. However, wise travelers usually avoid "
"those places where the shadow of the trees eats the light and thousands "
"glittering eyes are seen in the dark: sometimes to reveal the hidden in "
"legends arcane can be a fatal error."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Alastor, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Alastor.cfg:4
msgid "Alastor"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_anakes_Alastor, race=AE_bem_anakes_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\anakes\Alastor.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
"\n"
"Alastor, that means 'Avenger', was the name of one of the four demigods "
"instructed by the Dark Gods to lead the Anakes in the ancient wars against "
"the Gods of Light. Alastor controlled storms and winds and he used his powers"
" to create the Stormbringers. For this reason, the most powerful "
"Stormbringers, who are instructed to lead other demons in battle, are usually"
" called Alastors."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Cretan_Toxotes, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Cretan_Toxotes.cfg:5
msgid "Cretan Toxotes"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Cretan_Toxotes, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Cretan_Toxotes.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"Even if a small part of the Calydonians chooses to use the bow and become a "
"Toxotes, the Calydonian army often needs better trained archers. In these "
"cases, Strategoi usually recruit some Cretan mercenaries: the island of Crete"
" is well-known for its skilled archers, who use their bows with a deadly "
"precision."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Dardanian_Pillager, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Dardanian_Pillager.cfg:5
msgid "Dardanian Pillager"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Dardanian_Pillager, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Dardanian_Pillager.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
"\n"
"Barbarians often show great abilities when sack cities and an unbelievable "
"cruelty when treat prisoners. These savage warriors are called 'Pillagers' by"
" the Calydonians."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Dardanian_Ravager, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Dardanian_Ravager.cfg:5
msgid "Dardanian Ravager"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Dardanian_Ravager, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Dardanian_Ravager.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
"\n"
"Among the barbarian troops, some veterans have developed special techniques "
"to sack and destroy cities and villages. Skilled and cruel, these warriors "
"are dangerous enemies and should be dealt with the highest level of care."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Dardanian_Warrior, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Dardanian_Warrior.cfg:5
msgid "Dardanian Warrior"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Dardanian_Warrior, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Dardanian_Warrior.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
"\n"
"Sometimes some barbarous warriors join the Calydonian army to gain some money"
" and sack cities and villages. Strategoi usually allow only the best "
"Dardanian warriors to join the army permanently."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Diarch, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Diarch.cfg:5
msgid "Diarch"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Diarch, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Diarch.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"Diarchs are the political chiefs of the Calydonian Hegemony and they "
"generally remain in the capital, Calydon. However, they often take part in "
"important campaigns. Diarchs are skilled warriors, who can deal with every "
"enemy and face every situation. Their enemies should always be very careful "
"when they fight them."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Diarch.cfg:53
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Epihipparch.cfg:57
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Hetaroi.cfg:47
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Hipparch.cfg:57
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Hippikon.cfg:42
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Hoplite.cfg:42
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Polemarch.cfg:52
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Prodromoi.cfg:44
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Strategos.cfg:41
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Tassiarch.cfg:40
msgid "xiphos"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Dioian_Swordmaster, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Dioian_Swordmaster.cfg:5
msgid "Dioian Swordmaster"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Dioian_Swordmaster, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Dioian_Swordmaster.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
"\n"
"Some Dioi not only manage to survive, battle after battle, but also "
"distinguish themselves for bravery and strength. These warriors are called "
"'Swordmasters' by the majority of the people, even if this rank doesn't exist"
" in the Dioian society, which doesn't recognize differences between these "
"warriors and the common swordsmen. However, when these extraordinary fighters"
" are recruited by the Calydonian army, they receive an higher salary than the"
" swordsmen and the veterans, which allow them to buy heavy armors and "
"shields."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Dioian_Swordmaster.cfg:62
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Dioian_Swordsman.cfg:60
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Dioian_Veteran.cfg:55
msgid "rampage"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Dioian_Swordsman, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Dioian_Swordsman.cfg:5
msgid "Dioian Swordsman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Dioian_Swordsman, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Dioian_Swordsman.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
"\n"
"Among the barbarous people of the Thracian, there is a tribe of men, called "
"Dii or Dioi, who are famous for their bravery and their ability as swordsman."
" Even if the Calydonian army is not keen on recruit barbarians, the Dioian "
"Swordsmen are often recruited because of their great skills. Armed only with "
"a long sword, these strong and savage warriors are feared by every enemy."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Dioian_Veteran, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Dioian_Veteran.cfg:5
msgid "Dioian Veteran"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Dioian_Veteran, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Dioian_Veteran.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Dioi are fearless and strong warriors, but they are not immortal and many"
" of them die fighting. Nevertheless, some swordsmen manage to survive, battle"
" after battle. These great warriors are admired by both their allies and "
"their enemies. Even if the veterans rarely change their weapons, their "
"experiences have made them more careful, so they usually use more protective "
"armors than the ones wore by the swordsmen."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Epihipparch, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Epihipparch.cfg:5
msgid "Epihipparch"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Epihipparch, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Epihipparch.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"The commander of two hipparchia is called Epihipparch and is the highest "
"cavalry official in the Calydonian army. Epihipparchs have great tactical "
"abilities and can face almost every situation."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Gymnet, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Gymnet.cfg:5
msgid "Gymnet"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Gymnet, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Gymnet.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"Armed only with slings and with the protection of leather armors and wooden "
"shields, Gymnets rely only on their mastery with the sling and their bravery "
"to defeat the enemies: throwing stones with great precision, they damage "
"armors and shields and often break enemy's bones."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Hetaroi, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Hetaroi.cfg:5
msgid "Hetaroi"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Hetaroi, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Hetaroi.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"The Hetaroi are a class of skilled knights known for their strength and their"
" bravery. The Hetaroi are usually members of the Calydonian aristocracy who "
"have devoted themselves to the warfare. Entirely loyal to their homeland, the"
" Hetaroi are known to be dangerous enemies and precious allies, who never "
"retreat from a battle."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Hipparch, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Hipparch.cfg:5
msgid "Hipparch"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Hipparch, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Hipparch.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
"\n"
"In the Calydonian army, a Hipparch is the commander of a hipparchia, a group "
"of 500 horsemen. Hipparchs are expert warriors with uncommon tactical "
"abilities, which allow them to lead the soldiers. The Hipparchs don't use "
"spears, but they are all trained at sword."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Hippikon, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Hippikon.cfg:5
msgid "Hippikon"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Hippikon, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Hippikon.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"The name Hippikon is given to the veteran riders of the Calydonian army. "
"Hippikons are better trained and armed than the Prodromoi and their charges "
"can easily defeat every kind of enemy, with the only exception of spearmen "
"and archers."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Hoplite, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_imperialists_Hoplite, race=AE_efm_imperialists_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_refugees_Hoplite, race=AE_mrc_refugees_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Hoplite.cfg:5
#: .\units\EFM_units\Imperialists\a2_Hoplite.cfg:5
#: .\units\ME_units\refugees\g2-hoplite.cfg:5
msgid "Hoplite"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Hoplite, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Hoplite.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"Hoplites are the staple of the Calydonian army: soldier wearing a heavy armor"
" and armed with a spear and a short sword, called Xiphos. Brave and "
"well-trained, Hoplites usually are dangerous enemies for every type of "
"soldier."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Peltast, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Peltast.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
"\n"
"In the Calydonian army, a Peltast is a soldier armed with spears and equipped"
" with a wooden shield, called Pelta. Peltasts run across the battlefield and "
"throw their spears toward the enemy, but usually don't engage the enemy in "
"melee fights."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Polemarch, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Polemarch.cfg:5
msgid "Polemarch"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Polemarch, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Polemarch.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"In the Calydonian army, a Polemarch is a magistrate who takes care of the "
"warfare and commands a Mora, a group of 600 soldiers. Polemarchs are great "
"soldiers who have demonstrated uncommon strength and bravery. These "
"extraordinary warriors can use spears and Xiphos with a deadly ability and "
"are very dangerous in every situation."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Prodromoi, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Prodromoi.cfg:5
msgid "Prodromoi"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Prodromoi, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Prodromoi.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"The Prodromoi are the horsemen of the Calidonian army. Usually used as "
"explorers, the Prodromoi, armed with both a spear and a Xiphos, are brave and"
" skilled warriors. Prodromoi are a serious danger for light infantrymen, "
"especially if these enemies have broken formation. However, Prodromoi don't "
"represent a real danger for heavy infantrymen and well trained warriors."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Rhodian_Slinger, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Rhodian_Slinger.cfg:5
msgid "Rhodian Slinger"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Rhodian_Slinger, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Rhodian_Slinger.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"Often recruited to strengthen groups of Gymnets, the Rhodian mercenaries are "
"known to be the best slingers in the Calydonian Hegemony. These soldiers "
"usually don't throw stones as the other slingers, but use weights of lead "
"which injure seriously the enemies. Even if these soldiers coming from Rhodes"
" aren't good in melee fighting, they represent a great danger for every kind "
"of soldier."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Strategos, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Strategos.cfg:5
msgid "Strategos"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Strategos, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Strategos.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"The rank of Strategos is the highest in the Calydonian army. Every Strategos "
"have a huge experience in warfare and a great leadership. Strategoi have also"
" a strong political influence and often they take important decisions on the "
"foreign policy of the Calydonian Hegemony."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Tassiarch, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Tassiarch.cfg:5
msgid "Tassiarch"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Tassiarch, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Tassiarch.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"In the Calydonian army, the name Tassiarch is given to the commander of a "
"Taxis, which is a group of Lochoi, that are groups of 200 soldiers. "
"Tassiarchs have great tactical abilities who allow them to lead efficiently "
"other soldiers and are also trained at sword."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Teti, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Teti.cfg:5
msgid "Teti"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Teti, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Teti.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"Not everyone can afford an armor such as the one wore by the Hoplites: these "
"kind of people are called 'Teti' and represent one of the lowest social class"
" in the Calydonian Hegemony. Nevertheless, many Teti join the Calydonian "
"army, armed with a sling and a dagger and without a specific training; these "
"soldiers usually support the Hoplites throwing stones at the enemy."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Thracian_Peltast, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Thracian_Peltast.cfg:5
msgid "Thracian Peltast"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Thracian_Peltast, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Thracian_Peltast.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
"\n"
"Thracian mercenaries are famous for their ability as Peltast: faster than any"
" other infantryman in the Calydonian army, these terrific warriors can spot "
"unprotected archers and light infantrymen with great precision, attack the "
"target and retreat before heavy infantrymen and horsemen reach them."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Toxotes, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Toxotes.cfg:5
msgid "Toxotes"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Toxotes, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Toxotes.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
" \n"
"In the Calydonian army archery has been marginal for a long time and the "
"archers, called Toxotai, were used only to defend cities and fortresses. "
"Still recently archery has become more important, mainly because of the "
"experiences of the Calydonian army in fighting well-trained archers. The "
"Toxotai, armed with a bow and a dagger, now represent a considerable part of "
"the Calydonian army."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Veteran_Peltast, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Veteran_Peltast.cfg:5
msgid "Veteran Peltast"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_calydonians_Veteran_Peltast, race=AE_bem_calydonians_race
#: .\units\BEEM_units\calydonians\Veteran_Peltast.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from BEEM. Its coding and art were done by Voodoo, Baro_st, "
"Tydeus, Dibs, and various others.\n"
"\n"
"Peltasts who survived some battles are called 'Veterans'. Experienced and "
"deadly warriors, Veteran Peltasts move rapidly across the battlefield "
"attacking light infantrymen who have broken formation or unprotected archers."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_bem_wood_warriors_Adventurer_Puck, race=AE_bem_wood_warriors_race, gender=male
