msgid ""
"Drenched in the blood of its enemies, an abomination bears little resemblance"
" to the mutation it was created from. Enemy generals have been known to order"
" full blown retreats at the mere sight of such a monster. An abomination's "
"giant pus-laden body can withstand a dizzying amount of punishment, making it"
" almost impossible to take down. This, combined with incredible raw strength,"
" has turned abominations into veritable killing machines, something their "
"chaos masters delight in."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Blood_Knight, race=human
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Blood_Knight.cfg:5
msgid "Blood Knight"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Blood_Knight, race=human
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Blood_Knight.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Ultimate mastery comes with the greatest sacrifice. Dark Knights open their "
"veins and let their blood flow. If taste of their blood satisfies the Chaos "
"Lords, they promote them to the rank of Blood Knights, supreme warriors of "
"Chaos."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Daemon, race=AE_ext_chaos_demon_race
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Chaos_Daemon.cfg:5
msgid "Chaos Daemon"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Daemon, race=AE_ext_chaos_demon_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Greater_Daemon, race=AE_ext_chaos_demon_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Lesser_Daemon, race=AE_ext_chaos_demon_race
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Chaos_Daemon.cfg:21
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Greater_Daemon.cfg:22
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Lesser_Daemon.cfg:21
msgid ""
"The lesser demons are the gift of the Gods of Chaos to those who have shown "
"to be worthy enough to recieve aid from their sides, though barely any "
"tougher than the average human the lesser demons can easily turn the tide of "
"a battle due to the combination of their nible movement and tough fighting..."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Chaos_Daemon.cfg:117
msgid "female^Chaos Demon"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Dark_Knight, race=human
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Dark_Knight.cfg:5
msgid "Dark Knight"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Dark_Knight, race=human
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Dark_Knight.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Tougher than the average chaos follower, the Dark Knight attempts to confuse "
"its opponent by wielding a different weapon in each hand, he lets his style "
"on combat alter depending on the situation which makes him a tough warrior to"
" fight."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Demonologist, race=human
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Demonologist.cfg:5
msgid "Demonologist"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Demonologist, race=human
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Demonologist.cfg:27
msgid ""
"The mastery of daemons lies in the changing into daemon oneself. "
"Demonologists are daemonic minds entrapped in human body. What is left of "
"human in these creatures are only bodies and memories of invokers and magi, "
"who finally achieved the true power of their lords."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Demonologist.cfg:41
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Invoker.cfg:36
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Magus.cfg:53
msgid "chaos blast"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Demonologist.cfg:53
msgid "infernal storm"
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Demonologist.cfg:163
msgid "female^Demonologist"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Doom_Guard, race=human
#. [unit_type], id=AE_chs_chaos_empire_Doom_Guard, race=human
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Doom_Guard.cfg:5
#: .\units\EoC_units\human-chaos\Chaos_Doom_Guard.cfg:5
msgid "Doom Guard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Doom_Guard, race=human
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Doom_Guard.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Daemons know that, the only thing than can stop a tidal wave is a powerful "
"wall. Doom Guards are such wall, wall of living flesh and steel. Devoid of "
"bloodlust, their aggression is changed into fanatic loyalty. Doom Guards are "
"not the ones to fight, they are the ones to stand against every possible "
"enemy."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Evil_Crab, race=AE_ext_chaos_demon_race
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Evil_Crab.cfg:5
msgid "Evil Crab"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Evil_Crab, race=AE_ext_chaos_demon_race
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Evil_Crab.cfg:23
msgid ""
"The corruption of chaos is a subtle and slow process. Even animals as "
"harmless as crabs can be unwittingly twisted and warped far beyond their "
"ordinary nature. Evil crab's are one all too unfortunate result of this "
"process, as the merfolk and naga can attest to."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Evil_Crab.cfg:36
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Hell_Crab.cfg:39
msgid "evil eye"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Greater_Daemon, race=AE_ext_chaos_demon_race
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Greater_Daemon.cfg:5
msgid "Greater Daemon"
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Greater_Daemon.cfg:118
msgid "female^Greater Demon"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Greater_Mutation, race=AE_ext_chaos_demon_race
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Greater_Mutation.cfg:5
msgid "Greater Mutation"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Greater_Mutation, race=AE_ext_chaos_demon_race
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Greater_Mutation.cfg:22
msgid ""
"It came as a great surprise to the Magus who created them that Mutations "
"would over time increase in both stature and strength. It seems the act of "
"killing feeds these bloodthirsty beasts on some innate level. There are few "
"soldier's brave or indeed foolish enough to face off against such a creature,"
" especially when night falls."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Headhunter, race=human
#. [unit_type], id=AE_chs_chaos_empire_Headhunter, race=human
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Headhunter.cfg:5
#: .\units\EoC_units\human-chaos\Chaos_Headhunter.cfg:5
msgid "Headhunter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Headhunter, race=human
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Headhunter.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Given their souls to daemons, these lifeless scouts appear in the places, "
"that will be infested with the daemonic plague. They are the ones to spread "
"fear and message of daemonic invasions."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Hell_Crab, race=AE_ext_chaos_demon_race
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Hell_Crab.cfg:5
msgid "Hell Crab"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Hell_Crab, race=AE_ext_chaos_demon_race
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Hell_Crab.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Within each species there are often freakishly strong and powerful "
"aberrations born through seemingly blind chance. Successful servants of chaos"
" can find their bodies shifting and growing as these latent traits are "
"brought out. The Hell Crab is a powerful example of the potential all Evil "
"Crabs carry inside them."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Hell_Guardian, race=human
#. [unit_type], id=AE_chs_chaos_empire_Hell_Guardian, race=human
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Hell_Guardian.cfg:5
#: .\units\EoC_units\human-chaos\Chaos_Hell_Guardian.cfg:5
msgid "Hell Guardian"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Hell_Guardian, race=human
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Hell_Guardian.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Only the toughest of armorers are worthy of greatest armors, that are forged "
"in burning pits of daemonic homeworld. It is said, that if they were "
"commanded to, they could easily withstand the avalanche without stepping "
"back."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Hound, race=monster
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Hound.cfg:5
msgid "Hound"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Hound, race=monster
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Hound.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Trained hunting dog are ferocious animals, eager to attack in an uncontrolled"
" frenzy."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Flesh_Hound, race=monster
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Hound_Flesh.cfg:5
msgid "Flesh Hound"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Flesh_Hound, race=monster
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Hound_Flesh.cfg:23
msgid ""
"A hound that becomes a host for a lesser daemon turns into a flesh hound. The"
" unnatural fusion gives them a strange half dog, half human. With a daemons "
"cunning and a dog's senses, these muscled berserkers follow the stench of "
"blood."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Rabid_Hound, race=monster
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Hound_Rabid.cfg:5
msgid "Rabid Hound"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Rabid_Hound, race=monster
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Hound_Rabid.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Dog infused with chaotic magic turn rabid. The magic degrades their mind and "
"turns them into slavering beasts that hunger for bloodshed."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Warp_Hound, race=monster
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Hound_Warp.cfg:5
msgid "Warp Hound"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Warp_Hound, race=monster
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Hound_Warp.cfg:20
msgid ""
"With time, Rabid Hounds become mutated by the insidious magic of chaos "
"flowing through their bodies. They grow horns and other demonic traits, "
"becoming Warp Hounds. Their only desire is to rend their enemies with teeth "
"and claw."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Invader, race=human
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Invader.cfg:5
msgid "Invader"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Invader, race=human
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Invader.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Chaos warriors share the common believe that any goverment and any god is "
"corrupt by default, by this thought they fufill the bidding of chaos lords "
"who do not suger coat their reign and let their men face the harsh truth."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Invoker, race=human
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Invoker.cfg:5
msgid "Invoker"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Invoker, race=human
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Invoker.cfg:22
msgid ""
"You can spot them at the first line of Chaos flood. Standing with small "
"groups of warriors, these adepts of fiery arts of Chaos command the vanguard "
"hordes of chaos, seeking the best opportunity to advance in the ranks of "
"Chaos. At this point, their mind can be still compared to the mind of the "
"mortal. The only difference is they have no soul, for they sold theirs to "
"their daemonic Gods."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Invoker.cfg:117
msgid "female^Invoker"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Lesser_Daemon, race=AE_ext_chaos_demon_race
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Lesser_Daemon.cfg:5
msgid "Lesser Daemon"
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Lesser_Daemon.cfg:107
msgid "female^Lesser Demon"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Lesser_Mutation, race=AE_ext_chaos_demon_race
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Lesser_Mutation.cfg:5
msgid "Lesser Mutation"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Lesser_Mutation, race=AE_ext_chaos_demon_race
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Lesser_Mutation.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Myriad and ever-changing the forces of chaos recognize the need for staying "
"power within their ranks. Thus in dark labs filled with screams the Mutations"
" were created. These warped monstrosities were gifted with a self healing "
"body whose very touch other races find poisonous."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Magus, race=human
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_oracles_Magus, race=AE_mrc_oracles_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Magus.cfg:5
#: .\units\ME_units\oracles\e2-magus.cfg:5
msgid "Magus"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Magus, race=human
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Magus.cfg:26
msgid ""
"It is they, who rally with the larger groups of chaos warriors, supporting "
"them with magic. As daemonic essence touches chaotic mages, they gain the "
"sharpness of mind and way of thinking more resembling daemons, than human "
"beings. Being trapped between human and daemon life form, they seek no "
"turning back, but aspire to lose their humanity and succumb to the very core "
"of Chaos."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Magus.cfg:140
msgid "female^Magus"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Marauder, race=human
#. [unit_type], id=AE_chs_chaos_empire_Marauder, race=human
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Marauder.cfg:5
#: .\units\EoC_units\human-chaos\Chaos_Marauder.cfg:5
msgid "Marauder"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Marauder, race=human
#. [unit_type], id=Wose
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Marauder.cfg:21
#: .\units\EoC_units\elves-wood\a1-Wose.cfg:9
msgid ""
"This unit is from Extended Era. Its coding and art were done by the Various "
"people who created Extended Era."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Overlord, race=human
#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Overlord, race=AE_stf_minotaurs_race
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Overlord.cfg:5
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Gore_Overlord.cfg:5
msgid "Overlord"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Overlord, race=human
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Overlord.cfg:25
msgid ""
"Overlord is a title earned, not given. For such a rank to be claimed, blood "
"knights of Chaos must undergo the harshest and most brutal of trials in order"
" to appease their dark gods. Charred remains and broken bones attest to the "
"difficulty of such tests, yet every year at least one warrior will make the "
"(perhaps foolish) attempt. In the annals of history, only a select few have "
"ever emerged from the trials alive. Granted unholy strength, inhuman "
"resilience and a demonic mount, these are blood knights no longer but "
"Overlords of Chaos."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Soulhunter, race=human
#. [unit_type], id=AE_chs_chaos_empire_Soulhunter, race=human
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Soulhunter.cfg:5
#: .\units\EoC_units\human-chaos\Chaos_Soulhunter.cfg:5
msgid "Soulhunter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Winged_Daemon, race=AE_ext_chaos_demon_race
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Winged_Daemon.cfg:5
msgid "Winged Daemon"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_chaos_Winged_Daemon, race=AE_ext_chaos_demon_race
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Winged_Daemon.cfg:29
msgid ""
"Some daemons are given with power, some are given with speed. Winged Daemons "
"are the messengers and vanguard of the Daemonic Corpus, who always take "
"pleasure at sudden strikes and appearing in the place, that no one could "
"expect them."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EE_units\chaos\Winged_Daemon.cfg:117
msgid "female^Winged Demon"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Captain, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_ele_Centaur_Captain, race=AE_ele_centaur, gender=male
#. [unit_type], id=AE_chs_aragwaith_Captain, race=AE_chs_aragwaith
#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Captain, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Captain.cfg:5
#: .\units\ELE_units\wild-centaurs\Centaur_Captain.cfg:5
#: .\units\EoC_units\human-aragwaithi\Aragwaith_Captain.cfg:5
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\f3-Captain.cfg:4
msgid "Captain"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Captain, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Captain.cfg:22
msgid ""
"These Elves have been an example to their fellow soldiers, and have gained "
"the rank of Captain. Although they can never become Lords, they still strive "
"to do their best to defend the Matron Mother with their swords and short "
"spears."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Cleric, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race, gender=female
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Cleric.cfg:5
msgid "female^Cleric"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Cleric, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race, gender=female
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Cleric.cfg:22
msgid ""
"A Cleric is adapt at both their magical abilities and the use of their maces,"
" as the Dwarves have found out. They have the cure ability, a tool they use "
"for their sadistic pleasure. Terribly seductive, they are both feared and "
"admired for their beauty and cruelty."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Cleric.cfg:39
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Enchantress.cfg:31
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Sorceress.cfg:35
msgid "magic torture"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Corsair, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_mercenaries_Corsair, race=AE_mrc_mercenaries_race
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Corsair.cfg:5
#: .\units\ME_units\mercenaries\g3-Corsair.cfg:5
msgid "Corsair"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Corsair, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Corsair.cfg:18
msgid ""
"No single being can stand before a Dark Elf Corsair. If you every see one, "
"run. With they're razor sharp swords, they can splice and dice a dwarves "
"beard."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Enchantress, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race, gender=female
#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Enchantress, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race, gender=female
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Enchantress.cfg:5
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\e2-Enchantress.cfg:4
msgid "female^Enchantress"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Enchantress, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race, gender=female
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Enchantress.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The women of the Dark Elves often join the Order of the Clerics at a very "
"young age. They start of as an Enchantress, with limited physical and magical"
" abilities, and have just began practicing their torture techniques. Through "
"the guiding of the Clerics, someday they will become a mighty Sorceress."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Fighter, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_ele_Centaur_Fighter, race=AE_ele_centaur, gender=male
#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Cavernei_Fighter, race=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_dark_legion_Fighter, race=human
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Fighter.cfg:5
#: .\units\ELE_units\wild-centaurs\Centaur_Fighter.cfg:5
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Fighter.cfg:5
#: .\units\misc_units\dark_legion\Dark_Fighter.cfg:4
msgid "Fighter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Fighter, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Fighter.cfg:24
msgid ""
"The initiates in their House army, many Fighters die because of lack of "
"training. Dark Elves believe that only the best should have the honor of "
"fighting for the Matron Mother."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_High_Lord, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\High_Lord.cfg:5
msgid "High Lord"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_High_Lord, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\High_Lord.cfg:21
msgid ""
"When in his castle, the High Lord watches his slaves, feeds the lizards, and "
"other duties. They wear simple purple robes, and keep their hair combed. "
"However, when on the battlefield, they are as bold and daring as anyone. "
"After years of experience, they know every trick of their trade. Their men "
"follow them fearlessly, confident that through their Lords guidance, none can"
" stand before them."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Hunter, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_highlanders_Hunter, race=AE_efm_highlanders_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Therian_Hunter, race=AE_myh_therian, gender=male
#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Hunter, race=goblin
#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Hunter, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Hunter, race=AE_imp_marauder_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_mercenaries_Hunter, race=AE_mrc_mercenaries_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_tribe_Hunter, race=AE_mrc_tribe_race, gender=male
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mie_thelian_hunter, race=AE_mie_thelian
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Hunter.cfg:5
#: .\units\EFM_units\Highlanders\b1_Hunter.cfg:5
#: .\units\EoM_units\therians\d1_Hunter.cfg:5
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Goblin_Hunter.cfg:4
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Hunter.cfg:5
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Hunter.cfg:5
#: .\units\ME_units\mercenaries\b1-Hunter.cfg:5
#: .\units\ME_units\tribe\d2-hunter.cfg:5
#: .\units\MiE_units\human-thelians\1_Hunter.cfg:6
msgid "Hunter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Hunter, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Hunter.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Lurking in the ever dark depths of the caves, the Hunters move around with "
"out a sound, except for the twang of their crossbows."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Lizard_Master, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_free_saurians_Lizard_Master, race=AE_stf_free_saurians, gender=male
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Lizard_Master.cfg:5
#: .\units\EOS_units\saurians\Lizard_Master.cfg:5
msgid "Lizard Master"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Lizard_Master, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Lizard_Master.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Though the Lizards are not as fast as horses, they are much more powerful. "
"Many an Dwarf has been cut in two by its strong jaws. It would be well to "
"recruit several of these powerful units."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Lizard_Master.cfg:28
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Lizard_Rider.cfg:23
msgid "deathlance"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Lizard_Rider, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_free_saurians_Lizard_Rider, race=AE_stf_free_saurians, gender=male
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Lizard_Rider.cfg:5
#: .\units\EOS_units\saurians\Lizard_Rider.cfg:5
msgid "Lizard Rider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Lizard_Rider, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Lizard_Rider.cfg:18
msgid ""
"From childhood, they have been training with their beast, feeding it, healing"
" it, and sleeping with it. It is their duty to scout ahead into the unknown, "
"to go where no Dark Elf has gone before. Some day, they will become Master of"
" the Lizard."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Lord, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Lord, race=AE_fut_welkin
#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Cavernei_Lord, race=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Lord, race=AE_imp_marauder_race
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Lord.cfg:5
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Lord.cfg:5
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Lord.cfg:5
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Lord.cfg:5
msgid "Lord"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Lord, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Lord.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Highly decorated, These men have gained the title of Lord through their "
"cunning, their prowess, bravery, and strength. They command their provinces, "
"lead their men in battle, and hold the law with an iron grip. They lead as an"
" example to the life of a warrior in the realm of the Dark Elves."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Marshal, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Marshal, race=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarf
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Marshal.cfg:5
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Marshal.cfg:4
msgid "Marshal"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Marshal, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Marshal.cfg:22
msgid ""
"These Elves have proven themselves on and off the battle field with their "
"character and demeanor. They have earned for themselves the rank of Marshal. "
"Although they can never become Lords, they still strive to do their best to "
"defend the Matron Mother with their swords and short spears."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Noble, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_chs_wild_humans_Noble, race=human, gender=male
#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Noble, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Noble.cfg:5
#: .\units\EoC_units\human-wild\Noble.cfg:4
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\c2_Noble.cfg:5
msgid "Noble"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Noble, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Noble.cfg:20
msgid ""
"The young Lords are rash and brave. They have spent their entire childhood "
"training with the sword, and have been taught from the best Marshals "
"battlefield tactics. They have highly decorative shields that they use in "
"battle to attack and encourage their troops."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Shadow, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Shadow.cfg:4
msgid "Shadow"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Shadow, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Shadow.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Staying hidden safe in the shadows of the caves, they will hit you when you "
"least expect it. Despite their frailty, they can inflict great damage either "
"by thrusting their daggers in the back of their target or by shooting fast a "
"lot of bolts from their crossbow."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Sorcerer, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race, gender=male
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_oracles_Sorcerer, race=AE_mrc_oracles_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Sorcerer.cfg:5
#: .\units\ME_units\oracles\d3-sorcerer.cfg:5
msgid "Sorcerer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Sorcerer, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Sorcerer.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Sorcerers are Wizards that have gone deeper into the studying of the arcane "
"arts. Their research consumes them in a quest for more power, leading them "
"down a path toward the dark arts practiced by the Necromancers and Lichs. "
"Their mighty cold blast can freeze any foe that dares to cross their path."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Sorcerer.cfg:38
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Warlock.cfg:41
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Wizard.cfg:24
msgid "dark wave"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Sorceress, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race, gender=female
#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Sorceress, race=AE_efm_pygmies, gender=female
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Sorceress.cfg:5
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\f3_Sorceress.cfg:5
msgid "Sorceress"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Sorceress, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race, gender=female
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Sorceress.cfg:22
msgid ""
"The women of the Dark Elves often join the Order of the Clerics at a very "
"young age. These have gained the rank of Sorceress, and have nearly mastered "
"the art of healing, torturing, and healing their captives again and again. "
"Very soon, they will become Clerics, the terribly seductive sadistic "
"torturers."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Stalker, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Stalker.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Cunning, agile warriors, the Stalkers are powerful in both the use of their "
"daggers and crossbows. They are completely hidden in the caves, only the thud"
" of a dead body tells you they are near."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Warlock, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Warlock.cfg:5
msgid "Dark Elf^Warlock"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Warlock, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Warlock.cfg:19
msgid ""
"The best of their kind, these Warlocks have immense power, rivaling even that"
" of the Arch Mage. They have discovered the secrets of the dark arts, and "
"have the power to drain life from their opponents with a single touch, and "
"add it to their own."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Warrior, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Warrior.cfg:17
msgid ""
"These Warriors have devoted themselves totally to mastering the use of dual "
"weapons. With their balanced blades, they can shave a Dwarf. Only few become "
"Corsairs."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Wizard, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race, gender=male
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_oracles_Wizard, race=AE_mrc_oracles_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Wizard.cfg:5
#: .\units\ME_units\oracles\d1-wizard.cfg:5
msgid "Wizard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Wizard, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EE_units\dark_elves\Wizard.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Some Dark Elves prefer studying the arcane arts over close-combat. Usually "
"they are left to the lesser duties of the House, such as upkeep, watching the"
" slaves, and other such things. However, in time of conflict, they can do "
"great damage, even though they lack any training in close-combat."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_drake_Apprentice, race=drake, gender=female
#: .\units\EE_units\drakes\a1-Apprentice.cfg:4
msgid "Drake Apprentice"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_drake_Apprentice, race=drake, gender=female
#: .\units\EE_units\drakes\a1-Apprentice.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The Drake Magi are fresh members of the Obsidian Citadel, who have been bound"
" to and mutilated by the cult. Although they have undergone training harsh "
"enough to kill any human or orc, they are inexperienced, and thus can only "
"safely wield a weaker form of their feared fireball spell. However, they also"
" share the weaknesses of the High Magi."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_drake_Druid, race=drake, gender=female
#: .\units\EE_units\drakes\a2-Druid.cfg:4
msgid "Drake Druid"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_drake_Druid, race=drake, gender=female
#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_drake_Master_Druid, race=drake, gender=female
#: .\units\EE_units\drakes\a2-Druid.cfg:18
#: .\units\EE_units\drakes\a3-Masterdruid.cfg:19
msgid ""
"The Drake High Magi are elite members of an order of magic-using drakes who "
"spend their days in the Obsidian Citadel, honing their powers for use in "
"times of crisis. They can summon blasts of intense cold with a gesture, and "
"can hurl powerful fireballs across great distances. However, due to the "
"extensive mutilations that are required of drakes to harness and use these "
"powers, they are frail and slow."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_drake_Master_Druid, race=drake, gender=female
#: .\units\EE_units\drakes\a3-Masterdruid.cfg:4
msgid "Drake Master Druid"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: .\units\EE_units\drakes\a3-Masterdruid.cfg:39
msgid "ice shot"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_drake_Sword_Drake, race=drake
#: .\units\EE_units\drakes\b2-Sword.cfg:4
msgid "Sword Drake"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_drake_Sword_Drake, race=drake
#: .\units\EE_units\drakes\b2-Sword.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Sword Drakes are drake warriors of the fighter caste who have taken a "
"different path from that of the Warriors. They eschew the traditional drakish"
" war blade in favor of a slightly lighter sword. A sword is not as "
"hard-hitting as a war blade, so they deal less damage, but they consider this"
" tradeoff justified because they can strike more often. Drakes using this "
"fight style are slower but toughter as well they have focused more in melee "
"training and less at fire breath. By design drakish swords can also be used "
"as blunt weapons without breaking even if you are as strong as a drake."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_drake_Sword_Master, race=drake
#: .\units\EE_units\drakes\b3-Swordmaster.cfg:4
msgid "Drake Swordmaster"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_drake_Sword_Master, race=drake
#: .\units\EE_units\drakes\b3-Swordmaster.cfg:20
msgid ""
"In drakish society, the term ‘blademaster’ is reserved for those who have "
"mastered the deadly drakish war blade. Meanwhile, the golden-armored "
"Swordmasters have chosen a different specialty. Their attacks may be slightly"
" weaker than those of their Blademaster counterparts, but by using a lighter "
"sword these drakes are able to wear heavier armour and yet still retain "
"enough agility to strike more often than a Blademaster can manage. By design "
"drakish swords can also be used as blunt weapons without breaking even if you"
" are as strong as a drake."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_drake_Ranger, race=drake
#: .\units\EE_units\drakes\c2-Adventurer.cfg:5
msgid "Drake Ranger"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_drake_Ranger, race=drake
#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_drake_Golden, race=drake
#: .\units\EE_units\drakes\c2-Adventurer.cfg:18
#: .\units\EE_units\drakes\c3-Golden.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This drake is a light weaponed fighter. He has been trained as well to fight "
"at night and in caves."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_drake_Ranger
#: .\units\EE_units\drakes\c2-Adventurer.cfg:87
msgid "Drake Adventurer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_drake_Ranger
#: .\units\EE_units\drakes\c2-Adventurer.cfg:88
msgid ""
"Where did this drake come from? Maybe it will disapear again, maybe it will "
"replace the Ranger, who is fancying with a higher level. For now it exists "
"and is on the hunt to master a dungeon. Only the folks who go deep enough in "
"the code encounter this drake."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_drake_Golden, race=drake
#: .\units\EE_units\drakes\c3-Golden.cfg:4
msgid "Golden Drake"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dwarves_Dwarvish_Flamethrower, race=dwarf
#: .\units\EE_units\dwarves\b2-Flamethower.cfg:5
msgid "Dwarvish Flamethrower"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dwarves_Dwarvish_Flamethrower, race=dwarf
#: .\units\EE_units\dwarves\b2-Flamethower.cfg:20
msgid ""
"It is said that the Dwarven Flamethrowers have strange staves of wood and "
"iron, similar to those of the flamethrowers. But instead of making a "
"thunderous noise shooting a projectile, their weapon generates a continous "
"tongue of flame."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\EE_units\dwarves\b2-Flamethower.cfg:39
msgid "firestick"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dwarves_Dwarvish_Steamwheel, race=dwarf
#: .\units\EE_units\dwarves\c1-Steamwheel.cfg:5
msgid "Steamwheel"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dwarves_Dwarvish_Steamwheel, race=dwarf
#: .\units\EE_units\dwarves\c1-Steamwheel.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Some Dwarves use strange vehicles that can move fast without a horse. It is "
"said that these great wheeled vehicles are powered by invisible steam genies,"
" thus they are called 'Steamwheels'."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dwarves_Dwarvish_Thunderwheel, race=dwarf
#: .\units\EE_units\dwarves\c2-Thunderwheel.cfg:5
msgid "Thunderwheel"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dwarves_Dwarvish_Thunderwheel, race=dwarf
#: .\units\EE_units\dwarves\c2-Thunderwheel.cfg:19
msgid ""
"With the help of one more steam genie, those noisy vehicles are able to move "
"faster than horses."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dwarves_Dwarvish_Warwheel, race=dwarf
#: .\units\EE_units\dwarves\c3-Warwheel.cfg:5
msgid "Warwheel"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dwarves_Dwarvish_Warwheel, race=dwarf
#: .\units\EE_units\dwarves\c3-Warwheel.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Warwheels are faster and more heavily armored than Steamwheels, and can "
"breach enemy lines with their fearsome charge."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dwarves_Dwarvish_Gyrocopter, race=dwarf
#: .\units\EE_units\dwarves\d1-Gyrocopter.cfg:5
msgid "Gyrocopter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dwarves_Dwarvish_Gyrocopter, race=dwarf
#: .\units\EE_units\dwarves\d1-Gyrocopter.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Some dwarves have crafted strange machines they call 'Gyrocopters'. Capable "
"of flight, they need space to manoeuvre, thus they cannot be used "
"underground. Gyrocopters are hard to control and are not suited to close "
"combat. Instead, their drivers throw strange eggs they call 'bombs', that "
"explode with the sound of thunder. None know what strange beast lays such "
"eggs."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=ranged
#: .\units\EE_units\dwarves\d1-Gyrocopter.cfg:36
#: .\units\EE_units\dwarves\d2-Steamcopter.cfg:36
msgid "bomb"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dwarves_Dwarvish_Steamcopter, race=dwarf
#: .\units\EE_units\dwarves\d2-Steamcopter.cfg:5
msgid "Steamcopter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dwarves_Dwarvish_Steamcopter, race=dwarf
#: .\units\EE_units\dwarves\d2-Steamcopter.cfg:20
msgid ""
"With the aid of steam genies, Steamcopters are able to move faster and carry "
"more bombs than Gyrocopters."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Boreal_Wyrm, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_wyrm_race, gender=female
#: .\units\EE_units\ice_wyrms\Boreal.cfg:5
msgid "Boreal Wyrm"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Boreal_Wyrm, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_wyrm_race, gender=female
#: .\units\EE_units\ice_wyrms\Boreal.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from Unknown. Its coding and art were done by ???.\n"
" \n"
"Ancient wyrms so rarely seen that many regard them as legends, Boreal Wyrms "
"are evolved from Mistral Wyrms that have lived for over a century. Viciously "
"powerful and unbelievably fast, sightings of these creatures are made even "
"rarer by the fact that Boreal Wyrms attack on sight. Only the most powerful "
"of champions can face these creatures and survive."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: .\units\EE_units\ice_wyrms\Boreal.cfg:40
#: .\units\EE_units\ice_wyrms\Frost.cfg:39
#: .\units\EE_units\ice_wyrms\Ice.cfg:35
#: .\units\EE_units\ice_wyrms\Mistral.cfg:39
#: .\units\EE_units\ice_wyrms\Rime.cfg:40
msgid "cold breath"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Frost_Wyrm, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_wyrm_race, gender=female
#: .\units\EE_units\ice_wyrms\Frost.cfg:5
msgid "Frost Wyrm"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Frost_Wyrm, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_wyrm_race, gender=female
#: .\units\EE_units\ice_wyrms\Frost.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Unknown. Its coding and art were done by ???.\n"
" \n"
"Ice wyrms that live in the sea become more serpentine, turning into Frost "
"Wyrms. Named for the powerful icy blasts they emit, frost wyrms prefer to "
"freeze their enemies from afar. When cornered, they use their powerful tails "
"to pummel their enemies."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Ice_Wyrm, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_wyrm_race, gender=female
#: .\units\EE_units\ice_wyrms\Ice.cfg:5
msgid "Ice Wyrm"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Ice_Wyrm, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_wyrm_race, gender=female
#: .\units\EE_units\ice_wyrms\Ice.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Unknown. Its coding and art were done by ???.\n"
" \n"
"Cold-blooded reptiles from the north, ice wyrms are the youngling form of "
"creatures that can live centuries. Despite their relative youth, they are "
"already twice the size of the common man. Frightening creatures to encounter,"
" they are capable of blasting enemies with their icy breath, or lashing them "
"with their tail. Even worse, their scaly hide offers them natural protection "
"against a warrior's blade. It is fortunate that their natural environment has"
" made them ill-suited to face fire."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Mistral_Wyrm, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_wyrm_race, gender=female
#: .\units\EE_units\ice_wyrms\Mistral.cfg:5
msgid "Mistral Wyrm"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Mistral_Wyrm, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_wyrm_race, gender=female
#: .\units\EE_units\ice_wyrms\Mistral.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Unknown. Its coding and art were done by ???.\n"
" \n"
"Ice Wyrms that dwell high in the mountains eventually grow wings and become "
"capable of flight. Called Mistral Wyrms, they are far stronger and more "
"capable than Ice Wyrms. One would do well to avoid these creatures."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Rime_Wyrm, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_wyrm_race, gender=female
#: .\units\EE_units\ice_wyrms\Rime.cfg:5
msgid "Rime Wyrm"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dark_elves_Rime_Wyrm, race=AE_ext_dark_elves_wyrm_race, gender=female
#: .\units\EE_units\ice_wyrms\Rime.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from Unknown. Its coding and art were done by ???.\n"
" \n"
"Unlike humans, wyrms only grow stronger and more powerful with age. Rime "
"wyrms are elder frost wyrms: stronger and capable of a more savage breath "
"attack."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Fire_Wisp, race=AE_ext_monsters_elemental
#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Fire_Wisp, race=AE_myh_elemental
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Fire_Wisp.cfg:5
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\a2_Fire_Wisp.cfg:5
msgid "Fire Wisp"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Fire_Wisp, race=AE_ext_monsters_elemental
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Fire_Wisp.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Fire Wisps are spirits of smoke and flame summoned by powerful mages. When "
"not being ordered around, they like to frolic in pools of lava and take great"
" delight in burning anything they can reach."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Tentacle_of_the_Deep, race=AE_ext_monsters_seacreatures
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Tentacle.cfg:4
msgid "Sneaky Tentacle"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Tentacle_of_the_Deep, race=AE_ext_monsters_seacreatures
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Tentacle.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Tentacles of the Deep are the appendages of some greater monster that lurks "
"below the waves."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Undead_Dragon, race=undead
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Undead_Dragon.cfg:4
msgid "Undead Dragon"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Undead_Dragon, race=undead
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Undead_Dragon.cfg:32
msgid ""
"Long ago one of the mightiest living creatures, the feared Dragon has become "
"only bones and dark sinew. Long after its death, it was raised through the "
"dark powers of necromancy, which it now serves."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Dark_Wolf, race=wolf
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Wolf_Dark.cfg:5
msgid "Dark Wolf"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Dark_Wolf, race=wolf
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Wolf_Dark.cfg:22
msgid ""
"The Dark Wolves are stuff for various legends and fairy tales. All races have"
" their own stories about creepy shadows that haunt the woods and as most of "
"the phantoms victims just simply disappear many people believe that they have"
" been taken by bad spirits. The Dark Wolves are also called Wolf Phantoms "
"however are lone hunters, but sometimes even these loners find themselves "
"within a strong pack in a valuable position amongst the other wolves, feared "
"and loved by their own kind."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Wolf_Dark.cfg:75
msgid "pounce"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Wolf_Howler, race=wolf
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Wolf_Howler.cfg:4
msgid "Wolf Howler"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Wolf_Howler, race=wolf
#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Wolf_Terror, race=wolf
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Wolf_Howler.cfg:17
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Wolf_Terror.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Wolves are aggressive animals that hunt in packs. Although weak individually,"
" a wolf pack can kill even the strongest man in minutes."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Wolf_Howler.cfg:49
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Wolf_Terror.cfg:73
#: .\units\EoC_units\animals\Demon_Wolf.cfg:62
msgid "howl"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Wolf_Terror, race=wolf
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Wolf_Terror.cfg:4
msgid "Wolf Terror"
msgstr ""

#. [advancement], id=dire_howl
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Wolf_Terror.cfg:128
msgid "Dire howl: add magical ability to howl attack"
msgstr ""

#. [advancement], id=fangstrikes
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Wolf_Terror.cfg:158
