#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_orcs_Naga_Guardian, race=naga
#: .\units\EE_units\nagas\a1-Guardian.cfg:5
msgid "Naga Guardian"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_orcs_Naga_Guardian, race=naga
#: .\units\EE_units\nagas\a1-Guardian.cfg:23
msgid ""
"These heavy fighters are slower and more heavily armored than most naga and "
"wield huge maces which they use to crush their enemies. They mostly guard "
"naga outposts, but occasionally participate in offensive raids."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_orcs_Naga_Warden, race=naga
#: .\units\EE_units\nagas\a2-Warden.cfg:5
msgid "Naga Warden"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_orcs_Naga_Warden, race=naga
#: .\units\EE_units\nagas\a2-Warden.cfg:23
msgid ""
"These heavy fighters are the elite guards of the naga. They are slower and "
"more heavily armored than most naga and wield huge maces which they use to "
"crush their enemies. They mostly guard naga outposts, but occasionally "
"participate in offensive raids."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_orcs_Naga_Sentinel, race=naga
#: .\units\EE_units\nagas\a3-Sentinel.cfg:5
msgid "Naga Sentinel"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_orcs_Naga_Sentinel, race=naga
#: .\units\EE_units\nagas\a3-Sentinel.cfg:24
msgid ""
"These heavy fighters are elite guards of the naga, choosen by their "
"dedication and skill, their purpose is to defend their sleeping brethen from "
"any menace or guarding their hidden cities from outside invasors until the "
"great awake of their civilization arrive. These nagas are mostly unknow in "
"Wesnoth since they can only be found near Naga cities."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_orcs_Naga_Hunter, race=naga
#: .\units\EE_units\nagas\b1-Hunter.cfg:5
msgid "Naga Hunter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_orcs_Naga_Hunter, race=naga
#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_orcs_Naga_Assassin, race=naga
#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_orcs_Naga_Striker, race=naga
#: .\units\EE_units\nagas\b1-Hunter.cfg:19
#: .\units\EE_units\nagas\b2-Assassin.cfg:19
#: .\units\EE_units\nagas\b3-Striker.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Naga Hunters are Naga who are skilled at hunting with a bow. Since the naga "
"are naturally resistant to poison, they have no qualms about hunting with "
"poisoned arrows. These two foot long shafts, tipped with a potent poison, "
"have been known to slay many kinds of prey."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_orcs_Naga_Assassin, race=naga
#: .\units\EE_units\nagas\b2-Assassin.cfg:5
msgid "Naga Assassin"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_orcs_Naga_Striker, race=naga
#: .\units\EE_units\nagas\b3-Striker.cfg:5
msgid "Naga Striker"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_orcs_Naga_Depthprowler, race=naga
#: .\units\EE_units\nagas\c2-Depthprowler.cfg:5
msgid "Naga Depthprowler"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_orcs_Naga_Depthprowler, race=naga
#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_orcs_Naga_Depthstalker, race=naga
#: .\units\EE_units\nagas\c2-Depthprowler.cfg:20
#: .\units\EE_units\nagas\c3-Depthstalker.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Some nagas, whether through cowardice or cunning, develop a knack for "
"surviving in darker depths of the water. After special training, this "
"knowledge can develop into an entirely different branch of combat, although "
"it is just as deadly. Naga Depthstalkers are especially valued as brood "
"guardians, where they keep watch over eggs laid in hidden caves."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EE_units\nagas\c2-Depthprowler.cfg:177
msgid "Nagini Depthprowler"
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EE_units\nagas\c2-Depthprowler.cfg:179
#: .\units\EE_units\nagas\c3-Depthstalker.cfg:100
msgid ""
"Some naganis, whether through cowardice or cunning, develop a knack for "
"surviving in darker depths of the water. After special training, this "
"knowledge can develop into an entirely different branch of combat, although "
"it is just as deadly. Nagani Depthstalkers are especially valued as brood "
"guardians, where they keep watch over eggs laid in hidden caves."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_orcs_Naga_Depthstalker, race=naga
#: .\units\EE_units\nagas\c3-Depthstalker.cfg:5
