#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_outlaws_Princess, race=human, gender=female
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\b2-Princess.cfg:4
msgid "Outlaw Princess"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_outlaws_Princess, race=human, gender=female
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\b2-Princess.cfg:21
msgid ""
"A noble by birth, the Outlaw Princess has learnt swordplay with the greatest "
"generals, but she is the product of a failed aristocracy who has opted for "
"the life of an Outlaw. She dreams of founding her own Queendom with the "
"plunder she finds on the road."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_outlaws_Queen, race=human, gender=female
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\b3-Queen.cfg:4
msgid "Outlaw Queen"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_outlaws_Queen, race=human, gender=female
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\b3-Queen.cfg:29
msgid ""
"A noble by birth, the Outlaw Queen has learnt swordplay with the greatest "
"generals and battle tactics with the greatest sages, making her both a great "
"combatant and leader. However, she is the product of a failed aristocracy who"
" has opted for the life of an Outlaw. She dreams of founding her own Queendom"
" with the plunder she finds on the road, and she is ever so close to that "
"goal."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_outlaws_Raider, race=human
#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_seastates_Raider, race=AE_efm_seastates_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Raider, race=AE_efm_whites
#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Raider, race=AE_imp_marauder_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_dark_legion_Raider, race=human
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\c2-Raider.cfg:5
#: .\units\EFM_units\SeaStates\d2_Raider.cfg:5
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\e2_Raider.cfg:5
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Raider.cfg:5
#: .\units\misc_units\dark_legion\Dark_Raider.cfg:4
msgid "Raider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_outlaws_Raider, race=human
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\c2-Raider.cfg:26
msgid ""
"After a four or five robbings any Brigands that last that long will usually "
"find a sword of some type. Usually this is a saber because fencers are their "
"most regular prey as they often wander around lonely backroads looking for a "
"fights most of the time. They also usually build or buy (or steal) a better "
"crosbow and their accuracy and skill have both improved with practice."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_outlaws_Arsonist, race=human, gender=male
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\Outlaw_Arsonist.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This is custom unit. Its coding and art were done by IPS and various others. "
"Arsonists are hordes of pillagers that destroy everything in their way. They "
"murder every living creature in their way, and set the villages on fire."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\Outlaw_Arsonist.cfg:58
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\Outlaw_Pyromaniac.cfg:64
msgid "thrown torch"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_Pyromaniac, race=human, gender=male
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\Outlaw_Pyromaniac.cfg:5
msgid "Pyromaniac"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_Pyromaniac, race=human, gender=male
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\Outlaw_Pyromaniac.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This is custom unit. Its coding and art were done by IPS and various others. "
"Pyromaniacs set fire to everything just because they like it. They have "
"stolen the firebomb techniques of the dwarves, and have perfected these "
"methods to kill and destroy."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_outlaws_Troublemaker, race=human, gender=male
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\Outlaw_Troublemaker.cfg:5
msgid "Troublemaker"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_outlaws_Troublemaker, race=human, gender=male
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\Outlaw_Troublemaker.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This is custom unit. Its coding and art were done by IPS and various others. "
"Troublemakers are just people that hang around the tavern, get drunk, and "
"make trouble with anyone for any reason. They are the scum of society, and a "
"real pest to the enforcers of the law."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_undead_Death_Baron, race=undead
#: .\units\EE_units\undead\a2-Death_Baron.cfg:5
msgid "Death Baron"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_undead_Death_Baron, race=undead
#: .\units\EE_units\undead\a2-Death_Baron.cfg:42
msgid ""
"This unit is from Invasion from the Unknown. Its coding and art were done "
"mainly by Shadowmaster and Kitty.\n"
"\n"
"Sometimes the mightiest warriors and generals, cursed with hate and angst, "
"come back to this world as Death Knights. Death Barons serve them whilst "
"accruing enough unholy power to become Death Knights. In the process they "
"pick up a good deal of the Knight's power, including the ability to command "
"underlings."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Great_Ogre, race=ogre
#: .\units\EE_units\unused\Great_Ogre.cfg:5
msgid "Great Ogre"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Great_Ogre, race=ogre
#: .\units\EE_units\unused\Great_Ogre.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Great Ogres are larger than the ordinary ogre, possess more strength and "
"stand taller than an adult Wose. They live in the wilderness and are "
"xenophobic, so if you ever encounter one, then run."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_efm_dalefolk
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk.cfg:5
msgid "race^Dalemen"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_efm_dalefolk
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk.cfg:6
msgid "race^Dalefolk"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_efm_dalefolk
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk.cfg:7
msgid ""
"Easily the most peaceful people on the continent are those who live high in "
"the mountains where it is so cold that no other people dain to dwell there. "
"It is said that the cold air addles their minds and gives rise to an "
"unnatural number of hedge mages, mad inventors, and tameless wild men. "
"However the power of their legendary machines and their fine crafts of metal "
"have brought the occasional attempt to raid them and their stout hearted "
"militia have never failed to rally to fight them off. In battle the dalefolk "
"use their strange machines and magics, as well as a bit of wild lore."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_efm_darklanders
#: .\units\EFM_units\Darklanders.cfg:5
msgid "race^Darklander"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_efm_darklanders
#: .\units\EFM_units\Darklanders.cfg:6
msgid "race^Darklanders"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_efm_darklanders
#: .\units\EFM_units\Darklanders.cfg:8
msgid ""
"The Darklanders are a loose confederation of jungle tribes. Known for their "
"callous cruelty and harsh ways most other nations leave them alone. This has "
"backfired during the rare occasions when one of their priests has convinced "
"an entire army to come with him and attempt to slay everyone in the world but"
" none of them have ever gotten anywhere. As an odd quirk the darklanders are "
"also known for their skill in metalwork and art. In battle the darklanders "
"fare much better in their home terrain than in the open. The mad aura of "
"their priests and the frenzy of their warriors makes a powerful combination."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen.cfg:5
msgid "race^Freeman"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen.cfg:6
msgid "race^Freemen"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen.cfg:8
msgid ""
"The free men are so named after the first impression they gave the explorers "
"who found them. After more formal relations were established many started to "
"find the name ironic but it has stuck around anyway and the freemen "
"themselves seem to appreciate it. They are tough people who inhabit the "
"northern deserts. What few cities there are are renown for the remarkable "
"shows of wealth that are commonplace in them. Many of them live in the cities"
" under the guidance of the aristocracy and priests but many more of them live"
" in the desert as nomads and owe little allegiance to anything other than "
"family."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_efm_highlanders_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Highlanders.cfg:5
#: .\units\EFM_units\Highlanders.cfg:6
msgid "race^Natives"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_efm_highlanders_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Highlanders.cfg:8
msgid ""
"The Natives are a nomadic people who have never developed metal working. They"
" have a very strong sense of spirituality to their culture and have been "
"known to walk with many beasts (most famously the mighty elephant). They give"
" great honor to both the herder and the hunter; both the warrior and the "
"wiseman. Although they tend to grow larger and stronger than the men of most "
"other nations the lack of armor tends to balance things out. They are much "
"more adept at fighting in the hills than in the open."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_efm_imperialists_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Imperialists.cfg:5
msgid "race^Imperialist"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_efm_imperialists_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Imperialists.cfg:6
msgid "race^Imperialists"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_efm_imperialists_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Imperialists.cfg:7
msgid ""
"The imperialist empire is the largest power on the continent. Starting as a "
"mere city state it discovered a new brand of tactics that allowed it to "
"spread outward. Its conquests and power have made it proud and even though "
"its expansion has slowed it continues to spread the idea that its culture is "
"superior. It widely regards itself as doing a favor to the slaves that it "
"captures and promotes the virtues of patriotism. In battle the imperialists "
"are most adept at fighting in the plains. Their discipline and high moral "
"gives their formations a great deal of resilience but the strictness of their"
" training inhibits their aggressive capabilities."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_efm_pygmies
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies.cfg:5
msgid "race^Pygmy"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_efm_pygmies
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies.cfg:6
msgid "race^Pygmies"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_efm_pygmies
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies.cfg:8
msgid ""
"The name pygmy means small people which describes these jungle dwellers quite"
" accurately. They are a strange and secretive people who mostly leave "
"everyone else alone. On the rare occasion when they have been attacked their "
"methods of battle could be described as nothing short of unusual. As there "
"are many many poisonous creatures and dangers in their native environment "
"almost all of them know herb lore and first aid."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_efm_seastates_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\SeaStates.cfg:5
msgid "race^Statesman"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_efm_seastates_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\SeaStates.cfg:6
msgid "race^Statesmen"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_efm_seastates_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\SeaStates.cfg:8
msgid ""
"The sea states are a fairly large number of mercantile city states. The sea "
"states compete with each other through intricate intrigues, alliances, "
"economic games, and outright war. The cities tend to be run by the economic "
"elite who can afford to fiance the merchants that help make the land "
"prosperous, pay the artists and craftsmen who can make cities beautiful, and,"
" most importantly, hire the hordes of mercenaries that come to the region "
"looking for work. In battle the sea states troops tend to be well equipped "
"and trained but expensive."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_efm_whites
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites.cfg:5
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites.cfg:6
msgid "race^Whities"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_efm_whites
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites.cfg:8
msgid ""
"Hailing from a different continent these savage warriors are named after the "
"peculiar colour of their skin. Little is known about their culture however in"
" battle they are known for their ability to move over most types of terrain "
"easily and their magicians have the ability to control weather."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_dalefolk_Miner, race=AE_efm_dalefolk
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_slavers_Miner, race=AE_mrc_slavers_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\a1_Miner.cfg:5
#: .\units\ME_units\slavers\a2-miner.cfg:5
msgid "Miner"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_dalefolk_Miner, race=AE_efm_dalefolk
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\a1_Miner.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The dalefolk live in the creases between mountains and have always had a "
"strong industry in their mining. During times of war miners have been rounded"
" up to form a surprisingly effective militia. Hardened by their work and "
"already armed they will bravely defend their people."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_dalefolk_Delver, race=AE_efm_dalefolk
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\a2_Delver.cfg:5
msgid "Delver"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_dalefolk_Delver, race=AE_efm_dalefolk
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\a2_Delver.cfg:18
msgid ""
"A few miners come to love the mines so much that they rarely leave. Their "
"appearance changes, they come to see better in the dark than under the sun, "
"and they become uncanny adept at traveling in caves."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_dalefolk_Foreman, race=AE_efm_dalefolk
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\a2_Foreman.cfg:5
msgid "Foreman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_dalefolk_Foreman, race=AE_efm_dalefolk
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\a2_Foreman.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The foremen who lead the miners in digging their mines also tend to lead them"
" in combat."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_dalefolk_Herder, race=AE_efm_dalefolk
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\b1_Herder.cfg:5
msgid "Herder"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_dalefolk_Herder, race=AE_efm_dalefolk
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\b1_Herder.cfg:17
msgid ""
"One of the major industries and traits of the dalesfolk is their goat "
"herding. They regularly send their bravest lads out into the mountains alone "
"seeking land for their flocks to graze in. Over time these boys have become "
"quite adept at seeking sheep and fighting predators. In times of war they are"
" called in to serve as light skirmishers for the dalesfolk."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_dalefolk_Mountaineer, race=AE_efm_dalefolk
#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Mountaineer, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\b2_Mountaineer.cfg:5
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Mountaineer.cfg:5
msgid "Mountaineer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_dalefolk_Mountaineer, race=AE_efm_dalefolk
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\b2_Mountaineer.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Occasionally after a former herder has grown old enough to be relieved of "
"shepherd duties he will head into the mountains to make his own way. These "
"mavericks are however still loyal to their people and will return to defend "
"them."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_dalefolk_shifter
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\c1_Shifter.cfg:23
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\c1_Shifter.cfg:339
msgid "Shifter"
msgstr ""

#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\c1_Shifter.cfg:26
msgid ""
"When the scientifically minded dalefolk heard stories about witches turning "
"princesses into frogs and other such tales they undertook to learn how it "
"worked. They were successful to an extent. Although they could not figure out"
" how to turn someone else into a beast they did eventually learn how to do it"
" to themselves. It is a rare talent and much in demand for both domestic and "
"militaristic problems. The downside of this magic is that those who initiate "
"themselves with this power cannot seem to control it and thus their form is "
"determined by their landscape."
msgstr ""

#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\c1_Shifter.cfg:69
msgid "Shifter(bear)"
msgstr ""

#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\c1_Shifter.cfg:72
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\c2_Wilderman.cfg:70
msgid "The bear form of the shifter is the most physically strong."
msgstr ""

#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\c1_Shifter.cfg:115
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\c2_Wilderman.cfg:113
msgid "Shifter(BigHornedSheep)"
msgstr ""

#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\c1_Shifter.cfg:118
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\c2_Wilderman.cfg:116
msgid ""
"The big horned sheep form is a dauntless defender of mountains and attacks "
"with a devastating ram attack."
msgstr ""

#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\c1_Shifter.cfg:169
msgid "Shifter(Beaver)"
msgstr ""

#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\c1_Shifter.cfg:172
