#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_dalefolk_Channeler, race=AE_efm_dalefolk
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\d1_Channeler.cfg:5
msgid "Channeler"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_dalefolk_Channeler, race=AE_efm_dalefolk
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\d1_Channeler.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Among the dalesfolk are those who study the theory of magic. Through careful "
"experimentation they have discovered a devastatingly deadly way to attack "
"with it. By touching something or someone they can channel its heat directly "
"into the ground. Though there are many peaceful applications for such "
"magicians the most famous use of it was in a siege where a group of them made"
" the base of a stone wall so brittle that the wall could be smashed through "
"with a hammer."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_dalefolk_Beacon, race=AE_efm_dalefolk
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Beacon, race=AE_mrc_cult_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\d2_Beacon.cfg:5
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\d3-beacon.cfg:5
msgid "Beacon"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_dalefolk_Beacon, race=AE_efm_dalefolk
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\d2_Beacon.cfg:18
msgid ""
"There is a special knack to channeling that will allow it to be done at a "
"distance. It takes constant practice and conditioning to do it for any real "
"amount of energy so most channelers don't bother. The rare few who specialize"
" in it are of great use in a few industries."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\d2_Beacon.cfg:43
msgid "draw"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_dalefolk_Mediator, race=AE_efm_dalefolk
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\d2_Mediator.cfg:5
msgid "Mediator"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_dalefolk_Mediator, race=AE_efm_dalefolk
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\d2_Mediator.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Given time and practice a channeler can also draw heat from the ground and "
"transfer it to a person he touches. It is equally devastating but for very "
"different reasons."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_dalefolk_Conduit, race=AE_efm_dalefolk
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\d3_Conduit.cfg:5
msgid "Conduit"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_dalefolk_Conduit, race=AE_efm_dalefolk
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\d3_Conduit.cfg:18
msgid ""
"A daleman who becomes truly skilled at the magic arts becomes a conduit in "
"complete control of the flow of energy around him."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_dalefolk_Rocketeer, race=AE_efm_dalefolk
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\e1_Rocketeer.cfg:5
msgid "Rocketeer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_dalefolk_Rocketeer, race=AE_efm_dalefolk
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\e1_Rocketeer.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Other nations hold the rockets (of which the dalefolk seem so fond) in a "
"mixture of amazement and bemusement. They have no understanding of these "
"strange weapons nor of why anyone would use such an unreliable weapon. The "
"dalesfolk value them for their range but also just seem to love things that "
"go boom."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#. [attack], type=fire, range=artillery
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\e1_Rocketeer.cfg:37
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\e1_Rocketeer.cfg:46
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\e2_Bombadier.cfg:37
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\e2_Bombadier.cfg:46
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\e3_Battery.cfg:34
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\e3_Battery.cfg:43
msgid "rocket"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_dalefolk_Bombadier, race=AE_efm_dalefolk
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\e2_Bombadier.cfg:5
msgid "Bombadier"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_dalefolk_Bombadier, race=AE_efm_dalefolk
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\e2_Bombadier.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Most rocketeers are fairly strong men as their weapons take quite a bit of "
"endurance to carry. As they get stronger they can carry even heavier rockets "
"though there is a practical limits to what sizes are effective."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_dalefolk_Battery, race=AE_efm_dalefolk
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\e3_Battery.cfg:5
msgid "Battery"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_dalefolk_Battery, race=AE_efm_dalefolk
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\e3_Battery.cfg:18
msgid ""
"A master rocketeer can aim, prep, and launch rockets quickly making up for "
"their inherent inaccuracy with volume."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_dalefolk_Raven, race=monster
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_avians_Raven, race=AE_mrc_avians_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\f0_Raven.cfg:5
#: .\units\ME_units\avians\e3-Raven.cfg:5
msgid "Raven"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_dalefolk_Raven, race=monster
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\f0_Raven.cfg:17
msgid ""
"When the dalesfolk discovered that ravens were unusually intelligent they set"
" about training them. Though not overly useful as hunting birds they could be"
" taught to mimic or carry messages. This was enough to have them around at "
"first but eventually a mage discovered a pattern to their warning cries that "
"could be used to get more precise information. Since then the dalelanders "
"have used them as spies and scouts."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_dalefolk_Mynah, race=monster
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\f1_Mynah.cfg:5
msgid "Mynah"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_dalefolk_Mynah, race=monster
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\f1_Mynah.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Mynah birds are even larger and more intelligent than ravens. As a result "
"their warning patterns are a little more complex and it takes a more cunning "
"mage to decipher them."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_dalefolk_Herbalist, race=AE_efm_dalefolk
#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Herbalist, race=AE_fut_brungar_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\g1_Herbalist.cfg:5
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Herbalist.cfg:5
msgid "Herbalist"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_dalefolk_Herbalist, race=AE_efm_dalefolk
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\g1_Herbalist.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Many strange and interesting plants grow on the side of the mountains. "
"Herbalists make their living by knowing which ones are helpful and which are "
"harmful. This knowledge makes them useful support for the dalesfolk militias."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: .\units\EFM_units\Dalefolk\g1_Herbalist.cfg:37
msgid "carkroot fumes"
msgstr ""

