#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Amir, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\a2_Amir.cfg:5
msgid "Amir"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Amir, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\a2_Amir.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The title Amir frequently denotes a great deal of personal prowess and "
"bravery but it can just as oft represent a talent for scheming or use of "
"'underhanded' methods. Most frequently though, a mix of both."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Vizier, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\a2_Vizier.cfg:5
msgid "Vizier"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Vizier, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\a2_Vizier.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Although the Amir tend to be the officers of the armies they are rarely the "
"planners, tacticians, or strategists. The people who fill these roles tend to"
" prefer background positions as 'advisors'."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Caliph, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\a3_Caliph.cfg:5
msgid "Caliph"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Caliph, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\a3_Caliph.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Caliph is one of the two terms commonly given to the ruler of an entire city."
" It is a generally more militant term such as might be used for the cities "
"conqueror or one who rules by virtue of force."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Sultan, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\a3_Sultan.cfg:5
msgid "Sultan"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Sultan, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\a3_Sultan.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Sultan is one of the two terms commonly used for the ruler of an entire city."
" It is generally considered to be less militant, to be used for a ruler who "
"inherited or achieved power through other peaceful means. It is worth noting "
"however, that although the means of inheriting are called 'peaceful' they "
"frequently come at the cost of the 'untimely demise' of many other potential "
"inheritors. It is also worth noting, that the mind that can scheme its way "
"into control of a city is frequently good at military tactics as well."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Sand_Walker, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\b1_Sandwalker.cfg:5
msgid "Sand Walker"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Sand_Walker, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\b1_Sandwalker.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The streets of most cities are rough places and most men who live there grow "
"up to be tough and light on their feet. It is quite common for masses of such"
" people to pressed or bribed into armies in times of war. Most desert "
"militiamen carry a sling as a second weapon."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Ensnarer, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\b2_Ensnarer.cfg:5
msgid "Ensnarer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Ensnarer, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\b2_Ensnarer.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Bolas are another popular hunting tool of the freemen to be used on larger "
"prey."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Guardsman, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Cavernei_Guardsman, race=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\b2_Guardsman.cfg:5
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Guardsman.cfg:5
msgid "Guardsman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Guardsman, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\b2_Guardsman.cfg:17
msgid ""
"A man who proves his metal might be kept on as guard for a wealthy sultan or "
"caravan."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Goun, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\b3_Goun.cfg:5
msgid "Goun"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Goun, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\b3_Goun.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Goun is the name for the elite of the guard. These feared warriors are "
"expected to be able to defend caravans against the many or treasuries agains "
"the cunning."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Camel_Rider, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_fanatics_Camel_Rider, race=AE_mrc_fanatics_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\c1_CamelRider.cfg:5
#: .\units\ME_units\fanatics\c2-camelrider.cfg:5
msgid "Camel Rider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Camel_Rider, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\c1_CamelRider.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Despite their ungainly look, camels are actually quite swift mounts and can "
"easily match pace with horses. This and the fact that they need little water "
"make them the preferred mount and pack animal for the freemen."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Mehariste, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\c2_Mehariste.cfg:5
msgid "Mehariste"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Mehariste, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\c2_Mehariste.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Mehariste means camel cavalry which is about all that needs be said about "
"them."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Sand_Rider, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\c2_SandRider.cfg:5
msgid "Sand Rider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Sand_Rider, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\c2_SandRider.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Most people who travel the desert would choose the camel as their mount for "
"they are swift and do not need much water. But there is a rare breed of men "
"who prefer the rare breed of horse that lives in the desert. The horsemanship"
" of these few is the stuff of great praise and the horses are renowned for "
"their strength."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Adventurer, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\c3_Adventurer.cfg:5
msgid "Adventurer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Adventurer, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\c3_Adventurer.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Stories are told of a proud few who ride through the desert on great black "
"horses seeking adventure. Tales of their incredible horsemanship and prowess "
"in battle and the many strange things they find amuse and amaze foreigners "
"who hear them. Most foreigners doubt the validity of these tales but the "
"freemen know them to be true."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Zunbooruch, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\c3_Zunbooruch.cfg:5
msgid "Zunbooruch"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Zunbooruch, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\c3_Zunbooruch.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Zunbooruch was a mehariste officer who famously sniped the enemies sultan "
"from his camel mount at a range of a hundred yards with a crossbow after "
"calling the shot. Since then whenever a successful mehariste has saved up "
"enough for a crossbow (very expensive purchase in the freelands) people will "
"call them after said officer."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Muezzin, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\d1_Muezzin.cfg:5
msgid "Muezzin"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Muezzin, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\d1_Muezzin.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Although the term generally refers simply to the person who gives the call to"
" prayer it can also refer to low ranking members in the militant clergy "
"though the 'prayer' they call people to can hardly be called reverent. As "
"potential mullah they are generally held to be quite valuable and thus are "
"frequently gifted with expensive armor from southern lands however as members"
" of their caste you can fully expect to see them putting their life at risk "
"anyway. They also serve a second calling as healers."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Mufti, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\d2_Mufti.cfg:5
msgid "Mufti"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Mufti, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\d2_Mufti.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Not quite a full mullah yet but well versed in their doctrine and likely a "
"veteran of battle as well, a mufti is a respected man in freeman society."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Mullah, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\d3_Mullah.cfg:5
msgid "Mullah"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Mullah, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\d3_Mullah.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Mullah are the primary teachers and scholars of the freelands as well as its "
"priests. They are men of great power and influence and many of them are "
"warriors or magicians as well. They are easily identified by the halo that "
"they somehow create that illuminates the area about them."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Wanderer, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\e1_Wanderer.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Those that wander the desert are rarely unprepared to scuffle for their lives"
" if need be. Chakaram are one of their preferred weapons for they are are "
"more reusable than arrows but can still be used to hunt game at a distance. "
"As a result of years of life-style enforced practice most of them are a deft "
"hand with it. Although they do not live in forests, mountains, or other such "
"diverse terrains, they have become quite adept at moving through them "
"swiftly."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Derwish, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\e2_Dervish.cfg:5
msgid "Dervish"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Derwish, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\e2_Dervish.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The dervishes are an order of freemen who undertake to guard and support the "
"mullah (religious scholars) in their efforts. It is not a role that pays well"
" if at all but there are still plenty of them about."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Nomad, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_equestrians_Nomad, race=AE_mrc_equestrians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\e2_Nomad.cfg:5
#: .\units\ME_units\equestrians\h2-nomad.cfg:5
msgid "Nomad"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Nomad, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\e2_Nomad.cfg:17
msgid ""
"A foreigner once asked an Amir about the nomads and this was the mans reply, "
"'those who travel hard lands all their days are likely to become hard men. "
"Those who wander wild lands all their days are likely to become wild. You "
"call us 'free men' because when first your people met with us you met these "
"among us. It is they who are strong enough to truly be free.'"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Immortal, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\e3_Immortal.cfg:5
msgid "Immortal"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Immortal, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\e3_Immortal.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The immortals are so named after how hard it is to kill them and how "
"intertwined they are to the religion they serve. They form the elite guard of"
" the important priests and other holy men."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Sheik, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\e3_Sheik.cfg:5
msgid "Sheik"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Sheik, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\e3_Sheik.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The leader of a nomad tribe is called a Sheik. Sheiks are chosen by a council"
" of elders for their ability to lead and the councils rarely choose poorly."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Chanter, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\g1_Chanter.cfg:5
msgid "Chanter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Chanter, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\g1_Chanter.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Among the freemen there is a strange order of magicians  who twist themselves"
" into forms that allow them to deliver devastatingly loud and powerful "
"screams. It is not the most dignified form of attack, but it has proved "
"itself to be quite effective on numerous occasions."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Howler, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\g2_Howler.cfg:5
msgid "Howler"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Howler, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\g2_Howler.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The actual titles of the chanter order are not known to outsiders. Among the "
"common soldier, they tend to merely get fitting nicknames."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Screecher, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\g3_Screecher.cfg:5
msgid "Screecher"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_freemen_Screecher, race=AE_efm_freemen_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Freemen\g3_Screecher.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The most terrible of chanters can use not just the volume and power of their "
"voice as a weapon but the resonance as well. A voice held at the perfect "
"pitch with enough volume can shatter the crystalline structures of stone and "
"make structures collapse."
msgstr ""

