#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Knat, race=AE_efm_pygmies
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\a0_Knat.cfg:5
msgid "Knat"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Knat, race=AE_efm_pygmies
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\a0_Knat.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Knat isn't what they call themselves infact as near as anybody can tell they "
"don't call themselves anything. They seem to assume that rounding up everyone"
" you can find and giving them blow guns is a natural state of things during "
"war. They are called knats by their enemies because they seem to come in "
"endless numbers and although easy to swat are incredibly annoying to fight."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\a0_Knat.cfg:37
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\a1_Fly.cfg:37
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\a2_Mudfoot.cfg:46
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\a2_Stinger.cfg:38
msgid "blow darts"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Fly, race=AE_efm_pygmies
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_hive_Fly, race=AE_mrc_hive_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\a1_Fly.cfg:5
#: .\units\ME_units\hive\e1-fly.cfg:5
msgid "Fly"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Fly, race=AE_efm_pygmies
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\a1_Fly.cfg:17
msgid ""
"During one invasion a sea state officer noted that some of the crazy little "
"people with blow guns were harder to kill than the rest. He decided to call "
"these groups 'flies' and the name has stuck for any of the more experienced "
"pygmy units."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Mudfoot, race=AE_efm_pygmies
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\a2_Mudfoot.cfg:5
msgid "Mudfoot"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Mudfoot, race=AE_efm_pygmies
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\a2_Mudfoot.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Knives are an important tool and symbol of status for pygmies. It is not "
"uncommon for a typical blow dart wielding warrior to steal a knife from a "
"fallen enemy and practice with it in secret. A wielder of the knife who "
"practices stealth kills rather than dueling is called a mudfoot. It is a "
"somewhat derogatory title but the insult is only to the methods chosen not "
"the results they get."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Stinger, race=AE_efm_pygmies
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\a2_Stinger.cfg:5
msgid "Stinger"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Stinger, race=AE_efm_pygmies
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\a2_Stinger.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Knats poison their darts to bring down their targets however they tend to "
"choose weak and commonly available poisons. The more experienced units who "
"are better at scrounging up nasty long lasting poisons are fearsome foes."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Piper, race=AE_efm_pygmies
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\b1_Piper.cfg:5
msgid "Piper"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Piper, race=AE_efm_pygmies
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\b1_Piper.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The instruments of the pygmy carry strange enchantments which can be quite "
"harmful if the musician is trained. One of these is the ability to summon and"
" to a certain extent control creatures. Insects are one of the most common "
"choices for they are simple to control and difficult to combat. No type of "
"armor and no type of defense known is effective at reducing this attack."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Charmer, race=AE_efm_pygmies
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\b2_Charmer.cfg:5
msgid "Charmer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Charmer, race=AE_efm_pygmies
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\b2_Charmer.cfg:18
msgid ""
"A famous trick that originated among the pygmies is the ability to charm "
"snakes. Ironically this ability requires no magic at all and can be practiced"
" by any brave man. It is said however that you should not anger the snake "
"charmer that carries a pygmy flute for even if no snake approaches you, you "
"may find yourself with a poisoned bite in an uncomfortable place."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Puma, race=AE_efm_pygmies
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\c1_Puma.cfg:5
msgid "Puma"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Puma, race=AE_efm_pygmies
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\c1_Puma.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The Pygmies export spider silk and a number of other things to the sea states"
" in exchange for tools and steel knives. A long knife may as well be a sword "
"in the hands of a pygmy but others have learned not to underestimate the "
"agility with which the little men can wield their weapons. In particular "
"their ability to dart around a mans guard is noted."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Lynx, race=AE_efm_pygmies
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\c2_Lynx.cfg:5
msgid "Lynx"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Lynx, race=AE_efm_pygmies
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\c2_Lynx.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The knife wielders who come back alive with a decent collection of scalps are"
" afforded great honor in pygmy society. They are admitted into a special "
"caste with associated privileges and will not have any problems finding "
"themselves a willing mate."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Saber_Cat, race=AE_efm_pygmies
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\c3_SaberCat.cfg:5
msgid "Saber Cat"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Saber_Cat, race=AE_efm_pygmies
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\c3_SaberCat.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Many lynxes are content to enjoy the position they have fought for but many "
"still compete with the rest for even more renown within their caste. The ones"
" who are considered serious competitors are called saber cats after the "
"legendary hunters. Incidentally, most of these pygmies are strong enough to "
"wield full sized sabers."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Spider_Rider, race=AE_efm_pygmies
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\d1_SpiderRider.cfg:4
msgid "Spider Rider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Spider_Rider, race=AE_efm_pygmies
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\d1_SpiderRider.cfg:16
msgid ""
"The most infamous thing about the pygmies military is their use of giant "
"spiders as mounts. Other nations regard this with a mixture of disgust and "
"horror for the giant spiders make very effective combat mounts."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Great_Spider, race=AE_efm_pygmies
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\d2_GreatSpider.cfg:4
msgid "Great Spider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Great_Spider, race=AE_efm_pygmies
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\d2_GreatSpider.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Giant spiders that eat well tend to grow very large to the point where they "
"dwarf others of their kind."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Web_Spitter, race=AE_efm_pygmies
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\d2_WebSpitter.cfg:4
msgid "Web Spitter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Web_Spitter, race=AE_efm_pygmies
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\d2_WebSpitter.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Amount the giant spiders is a verity that rather than building webs spits "
"masses of sticky silk at targets slowing them down to make theme easy prey."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Crocodile, race=AE_efm_pygmies
#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Crocodile, race=monster
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\e1_Crocodile.cfg:5
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Crocodile.cfg:5
msgid "Crocodile"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Crocodile, race=AE_efm_pygmies
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\e1_Crocodile.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Large portions of the jungle that the pygmies live in could be better "
"described as a swamp. Living in these swamps is a fearsome predator that "
"lurks in the swampy waters and ambushes the unweary. However even these "
"fearsome beasts are not beyond the ability of pygmies tamers."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Grand_Crocodile, race=AE_efm_pygmies
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\e2_GrandCrocodile.cfg:5
msgid "Grand Crocodile"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Grand_Crocodile, race=AE_efm_pygmies
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\e2_GrandCrocodile.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Most crocodiles can be mistaken for a floating log. There are however a few "
"that are so big that none would mistake them for anything other than an elder"
" crocodile."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Swamp_Witch, race=AE_efm_pygmies, gender=female
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\f1_SwampWitch.cfg:5
msgid "Swamp Witch"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Swamp_Witch, race=AE_efm_pygmies, gender=female
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\f1_SwampWitch.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Although most pygmies do not practice cannibalism like the rumors say there "
"are a few who do. Do not let your children play near the jungle else they may"
" fall victim to the devil witches who eat man and wield death and decay as "
"weapons."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\f1_SwampWitch.cfg:39
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\f2_ToadBreath.cfg:38
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\f2_Wyrd.cfg:39
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\f3_LizardEye.cfg:39
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\f3_Sorceress.cfg:40
msgid "jida"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Toad_Breath, race=AE_efm_pygmies, gender=female
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\f2_ToadBreath.cfg:5
msgid "Toad-breath"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Toad_Breath, race=AE_efm_pygmies, gender=female
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\f2_ToadBreath.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Should you encounter a jungle witch with the breath of a toad then ensure "
"that you do not end up at her mercy for she will turn you into a toad and "
"either eat you or dominate your will. For whatever reason these witches jida "
"does not cause decay."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Wyrd, race=AE_efm_pygmies, gender=female
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\f2_Wyrd.cfg:5
msgid "Wyrd"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Wyrd, race=AE_efm_pygmies, gender=female
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\f2_Wyrd.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Generally the stronger witches live deeper in the jungle. There they grow "
"mushrooms to leach trees for strength to provide them with power. This makes "
"them considerably stronger than those who have to try to catch children or "
"steal babies but it does not make them lose their taste for blood."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Lizard_Eye, race=AE_efm_pygmies, gender=female
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\f3_LizardEye.cfg:5
msgid "Lizard Eye"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Lizard_Eye, race=AE_efm_pygmies, gender=female
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\f3_LizardEye.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Lizard eyed witches are to be feared for much the same reason that those with"
" toad breath are. It has been speculated that living as a lizard might be "
"slightly more satisfying than living as a toad, though no one has gone "
"through the process and survived to comment."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Sorceress, race=AE_efm_pygmies, gender=female
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\f3_Sorceress.cfg:19
msgid ""
"In the deepest part of the jungle where the trees are so thick you might as "
"well be in a cave live powerful sorceresses. Ruminating in decay for years "
"gives their aura such deadly power that it can wilt men alive."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Toad, race=monster
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\z0_toad.cfg:18
msgid ""
"It is a truly horrible fate to be dominated by a witch and turned into a "
"toad. Even if they won't eat you they will carelessly send you off to fight "
"their enemies without the slightest care for the fact that you weigh a few "
"grams. You will not be able to stop yourself from throwing yourself head "
"first at your former friends but at the very least you probably won't have to"
" put up with it for long."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Lizard, race=monster
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\z1_lizard.cfg:5
msgid "Lizard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_pygmies_Lizard, race=monster
#: .\units\EFM_units\Pygmies\z1_lizard.cfg:18
msgid ""
"It is a truly horrible fate to be dominated by a witch and turned into a "
"lizard. Even if they won't eat you they will carelessly send you off to fight"
" their enemies without the slightest care for the fact that you weigh a few "
"grams. You will not be able to stop yourself from throwing yourself head "
"first at your former friends but at the very least you probably won't have to"
" put up with it for long."
msgstr ""

