#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Warrior, race=AE_efm_whites
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\a1_Warrior.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The whites live in vast and untamed lands and are well adapted to fighting in"
" the wild.. Axes are the favored armament for they are as much a tool as a "
"weapon."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Bard, race=AE_efm_whites
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\a2_Bard.cfg:5
msgid "Bard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Bard, race=AE_efm_whites
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\a2_Bard.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Deeply instilled in the whites culture is a love for tales of valor and for "
"the beating of drums. A class of warrior scholar developed to know such tales"
" and of musical arts."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Housecarl, race=AE_efm_whites
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\a2_HouseCarl.cfg:5
msgid "Housecarl"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Housecarl, race=AE_efm_whites
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\a2_HouseCarl.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The core of many a white army is the housecarl, a breed of professional "
"warrior. They serve the thanes for good or ill."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Balladier, race=AE_efm_whites
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\a3_Balladier.cfg:5
msgid "Balladier"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Balladier, race=AE_efm_whites
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\a3_Balladier.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Although there is a respect for those who can recite a ballad there is "
"greater respect still for those who write them. In a way, they become legends"
" in their own right, though none of them would write about themselves."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Thane, race=AE_efm_whites
#. [unit_type], id=AE_ele_Viking_Thane, race=AE_ele_viking, gender=male
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\a3_Thane.cfg:5
#: .\units\ELE_units\true-vikings\Viking_Thane.cfg:5
msgid "Thane"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Thane, race=AE_efm_whites
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\a3_Thane.cfg:18
msgid ""
"In general it is the responsibility of the thanes or other small nobilities "
"to protect their people and lead the armies against dangers. As a result "
"thanes tend to be chosen or bred from some of the finest warriors the whites "
"produce."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Bow_Girl, race=AE_efm_whites, gender=female
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\b0_BowGirl.cfg:5
msgid "Bow Girl"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Bow_Girl, race=AE_efm_whites, gender=female
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\b0_BowGirl.cfg:18
msgid ""
"When a white tribe gets desperate for extra warriors they will round up their"
" young girls who are strong enough to draw a war bow but not yet mothers and "
"use them as ranged support."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Keeper, race=AE_efm_whites, gender=female
#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Keeper, race=AE_myh_celestial
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\b1_Keeper.cfg:5
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\b2_Keeper.cfg:5
msgid "Keeper"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Keeper, race=AE_efm_whites, gender=female
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\b1_Keeper.cfg:18
msgid ""
"A woman who has fought bravely in battle is afforded the right to remain a "
"warrior. Those who keep their weapons are called 'keepers' and are considered"
" to be honorary men for legal purposes (including wergeld but excluding "
"marriage) until they become mothers."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Storm_Child, race=AE_efm_whites, gender=female
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\b1_Stormchild.cfg:5
msgid "Storm Child"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Storm_Child, race=AE_efm_whites, gender=female
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\b1_Stormchild.cfg:18
msgid ""
"A small portion of whitey women have the aptitude for magic. The most famous "
"and common magic that is known to the whites is the control of weather. "
"Although most commonly used to help farmers it is also commonly used in war. "
"Training for this magic must begin when the user is fairly young for them to "
"be able to achieve any sort of potency. Due to the danger of such magic you "
"will encounter far more 'storm children' than true storm witches."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Huntress, race=AE_efm_whites, gender=female
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\b2_Huntress.cfg:18
msgid ""
"A noted tendency is for women who keep their weapons is to become hunters. "
"This way they can keep their skills sharp and provide their village a useful "
"service at the same time."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Storm_Witch, race=AE_efm_whites, gender=female
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\b2_Stormwitch.cfg:5
msgid "Storm Witch"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Storm_Witch, race=AE_efm_whites, gender=female
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\b2_Stormwitch.cfg:18
msgid ""
"More devastating than even thunder bolts thrown with deadly precision are "
"sudden blizzards which devastate regions."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\b2_Stormwitch.cfg:46
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\b3_StormLady.cfg:46
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\b4_StormQueen.cfg:47
msgid "blizzard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Bow_Lady, race=AE_efm_whites, gender=female
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\b3_BowLady.cfg:5
msgid "Bow Lady"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Bow_Lady, race=AE_efm_whites, gender=female
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\b3_BowLady.cfg:19
msgid ""
"The bow girl tradition has occasionally produced legends of heroines brave as"
" any man and able to wield bows that most men would have a hard time drawing."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\b3_BowLady.cfg:44
msgid "long bow"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Storm_Lady, race=AE_efm_whites, gender=female
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\b3_StormLady.cfg:5
msgid "Storm Lady"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Storm_Lady, race=AE_efm_whites, gender=female
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\b3_StormLady.cfg:18
msgid ""
"An experienced witch can cause the very earth to rumble and ground to shake "
"by the might of her power."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=ranged
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\b3_StormLady.cfg:58
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\b4_StormQueen.cfg:59
msgid "earthquake"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Storm_Queen, race=AE_efm_whites, gender=female
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\b4_StormQueen.cfg:5
msgid "Storm Queen"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Storm_Queen, race=AE_efm_whites, gender=female
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\b4_StormQueen.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Beware the witch whose magic is so strong that it acts without attention. If "
"the witch's tears bring sudden showers then her anger will strike a man dead "
"or lay waste to entire villages."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Storm_Guard, race=AE_efm_whites
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\c1_Storm_Guard.cfg:5
msgid "Storm Guard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Storm_Guard, race=AE_efm_whites
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\c1_Storm_Guard.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Due to how rare and valuable storm children are a tradition of assigning "
"personal guards to them has developed. Men who would have a storm witch for a"
" wife must join said guard and prove themselves in battle. As having a storm "
"witch for a wife is a great honor there are usually many who try out and each"
" a highly motivated fighter. There is a downside to this tradition however "
"and that with such a tempting motivation and difficult competition, most "
"storm guard throw themselves recklessly into battle when chance comes instead"
" of picking off foes with bow before they reach their charge like they're "
"supposed to."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Heart_Guard, race=AE_efm_whites
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\c2_Heart_Guard.cfg:5
msgid "Heart Guard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Heart_Guard, race=AE_efm_whites
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\c2_Heart_Guard.cfg:17
msgid ""
"A man who is considered a serious contender for the heart of a storm child is"
" marked with a badge. Once a storm guard is badged they tend to be more "
"willing to demonstrate restraint as they've already marked themselves a notch"
" above most of his rivals."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Soul_Guard, race=AE_efm_whites
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\c3_Soul_Guard.cfg:5
msgid "Soul Guard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Soul_Guard, race=AE_efm_whites
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\c3_Soul_Guard.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Those actually chosen to be the storm witches mates are almost guaranteed to "
"be devoted and ferocious warriors."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Warder, race=AE_efm_whites
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\d1_Warder.cfg:5
msgid "Warder"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Warder, race=AE_efm_whites
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\d1_Warder.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Some villages do not benefit from the protection of thanes or other nobility."
" In these villages it is not uncommon for many of the men to practice "
"warcraft in their spare time. In particular they train to be able to encircle"
" and overwhelm stronger opponents. Traditionally they wield staves for these "
"are easy to produce."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Guardian, race=AE_efm_whites
#. [unit_type], id=AE_ele_Centaur_Guardian, race=AE_ele_centaur, gender=female
#. [unit_type], id=AE_chs_aragwaith_Guardian, race=AE_chs_aragwaith
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mie_thelian_guardian, race=AE_mie_thelian
#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_dark_legion_Guardian, race=human
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\d2_Guardian.cfg:5
#: .\units\ELE_units\wild-centaurs\Centaur_Guardian.cfg:5
#: .\units\EoC_units\human-aragwaithi\Aragwaith_Guardian.cfg:5
#: .\units\MiE_units\human-thelians\3_Guardian.cfg:6
#: .\units\misc_units\dark_legion\Dark_Guardian.cfg:4
msgid "Guardian"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Guardian, race=AE_efm_whites
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\d2_Guardian.cfg:17
msgid ""
"In the absence of a thane there will usually be at least a few men who put it"
" upon themselves to maintain order and law in a village."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Vigilante, race=AE_efm_whites
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\d2_Vigilante.cfg:5
msgid "Vigilante"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Vigilante, race=AE_efm_whites
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\d2_Vigilante.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Some villagers decide to take creating order and resisting dominion into "
"their own hands. Rather than join any organized group they keep a low "
"profile, blending in with the other villagers so as to be indistinguishable "
"until they pull out knives and try to end you."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Sentinal, race=AE_efm_whites
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\d3_Sentinal.cfg:5
msgid "Sentinal"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Sentinal, race=AE_efm_whites
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\d3_Sentinal.cfg:18
msgid ""
"A town that appears undefended may prove to have an unexpected guardian. A "
"group of simple men with staves has proved to be the downfall of many a "
"raiding party."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Scout, race=AE_efm_whites
#. [unit_type], id=AE_chs_aragwaith_Scout, race=AE_chs_aragwaith
#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Scout, race=AE_imp_marauder_race
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\e1_Scout.cfg:5
#: .\units\EoC_units\human-aragwaithi\Aragwaith_Scout.cfg:5
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Scout.cfg:5
msgid "Scout"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Scout, race=AE_efm_whites
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\e1_Scout.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Whites not strong enough to be used as warriors are frequently marathon "
"trained to act as scouts and messengers. Most of them practice with hatchets "
"so that they can contribute something to a fight without beings stuck in the "
"melee."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Raider, race=AE_efm_whites
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\e2_Raider.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Cattle raiding is a favored past time of bored white scouts. If one is quick "
"enough one can get in, silence the keepers, and get out again leaving your "
"victim with only a few corpses and many neboring villages to suspect. This "
"kind of behavior is one of the many reasons the whites will never be at peace"
" with each other."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Terror_Rider, race=AE_efm_whites
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\f1_TerrorRider.cfg:5
msgid "Terror Rider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Terror_Rider, race=AE_efm_whites
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\f1_TerrorRider.cfg:17
msgid ""
"In general the whites are not fond of fighting mounted. Though many massive "
"beasts roam the land they prefer to fight on their own two feet. There is one"
" exception in the mighty terror bird where the hight of the beast allows for "
"easier use of a flail."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Terror_Strider, race=AE_efm_whites
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\f2_TerrorStrider.cfg:5
msgid "Terror Strider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_efm_whites_Terror_Strider, race=AE_efm_whites
#: .\units\EFM_units\Whites\f2_TerrorStrider.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The terror birds are intimidating creatures and when properly trained make a "
"war mount more fearsome than a horse."
msgstr ""

