#. [unit_type], id=AE_chs_sylvians_Fire_Faerie, race=AE_chs_faerie, gender=female
#: .\units\EoC_units\faeries\Fire_Faerie.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Faeries are rarely seen on a battlefield, as they are usually pacific "
"creatures when not disturbed. And they are rarely disturbed, as most races "
"know already what the consequences can be if they dare defy a faerie, and "
"thus they choose to respect them and their homes. However, it is said that in"
" times of war and great need they can become powerful allies to those who "
"protect nature as much as they do. And the best race for that purpose are the"
" forest elves.\n"
"\n"
"The most experienced faeries have developed a fearsome mastery of the fire "
"element, which they can use to throw powerful fireballs to their opponents at"
" long range, or to burn them at close range with a single touch of their "
"hands. It is said that their very bodies start to burn, eventually leading "
"them to become non-corporeal spirits of nature made of pure fire."
msgstr ""

