#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Devlings are small red creatures that live for nothing more than to torment "
"others. They always live and travel in rather large extended families, and "
"due to their very frequent breeding will almost always appear in overwhelming"
" numbers. They are masters of chaos, and despite not being strong or tough, "
"have demonstrated their ability to cause massive damage. However their "
"chaotic ways tend to stop them from forming a large enough host to be a "
"serious threat to any well defended territory."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_myh_devling
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings.cfg:19
msgid " Devling leaders are stronger than their brethren."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_myh_elemental
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals.cfg:14
msgid ""
"The Elementals are the guardians of the World, spirits of the elements that "
"incarnate themselves to fight. They are reclusive, but can be quite fierce "
"and brutal, for as it is said, there is nothing more ruthless than nature."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_myh_elemental
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals.cfg:14
msgid ""
"Sometimes a random mage gains the power to summon Elementals and leads them "
"into battle."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_myh_therian
#: .\units\EoM_units\therians.cfg:7
msgid "race^Therian Human"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_myh_therian
#: .\units\EoM_units\therians.cfg:8
msgid "race+female^Therian Human"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_myh_therian
#: .\units\EoM_units\therians.cfg:9
msgid "race^Therian Humans"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_myh_therian
#: .\units\EoM_units\therians.cfg:13
msgid ""
"The Therians are a spiritual people, who are generally not very aggressive, "
"but believe in self-sufficiency, and self-defense. They pride themselves in "
"their development of many arts, most particularly that of shapeshifting, but "
"also of the spiritual arts, and the magics of their jungle homes. Therians "
"are one of the few human factions strong enough to resist the other races. "
"They are commonly peaceful with the Celestials and share a strange friendship"
" with the warg."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_myh_gargoyle
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires.cfg:5
msgid "race^Gargoyle"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_myh_gargoyle
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires.cfg:6
msgid "race+female^Gargoyle"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_myh_gargoyle
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires.cfg:7
msgid "race^Gargoyles"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_myh_gargoyle
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires.cfg:11
msgid "Vampires can animate stones with blood magics, the result are gargoyles."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_myh_vampire
#. [race], id=AE_mie_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires.cfg:18
#: .\units\MiE_units\vampires.cfg:11
msgid "race^Vampire"
msgstr ""

