#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong.cfg:23
msgid "race^Windsong Human"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_myh_windsong
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong.cfg:24
msgid "race^Windsong Humans"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_myh_windsong
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong.cfg:29
msgid ""
"The Windsong are a mysterious people, consisting completely of abducted "
"female humans. Their numbers are few, and their goals and motives obscure. "
"However they have demonstrated in the past that they are not to be trifled "
"with. They have strange powers, and massive libraries and towers full of "
"books of ancient lore. Their armies though few in number have defeated all of"
" the many who've attacked them, or whom they've decided to attack. Humans "
"hate them because they steal the most fit of their daughters right from under"
" their noses. Most other races distrust them."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Crusader, race=AE_myh_celestial
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_holy_order_Crusader, race=AE_mrc_holy_order_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\a1_Crusader.cfg:5
#: .\units\ME_units\holy_order\a2-crusader.cfg:5
msgid "Crusader"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Crusader, race=AE_myh_celestial
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\a1_Crusader.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Crusaders undergo rigorous martial training as well as rudimentary medicinal "
"training to help their injured allies on the field of battle. Crusaders' "
"swords are infused with the arcane energy of the Light Spirits - a tradition "
"that started during the Great Crusade against the vampires."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=melee
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\a1_Crusader.cfg:31
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\a2_Divine_Knight.cfg:32
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\a2_Quester.cfg:42
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\a3_Divine_Champion.cfg:34
msgid "blessed sword"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Divine_Knight, race=AE_myh_celestial
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\a2_Divine_Knight.cfg:5
msgid "Divine Knight"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Divine_Knight, race=AE_myh_celestial
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\a2_Divine_Knight.cfg:17
msgid ""
"A crusader who survives many fierce battles is granted the honor of "
"knighthood. At this time the knight receives a ceremonial mace he must carry "
"at all times."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Protector, race=AE_myh_celestial
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\a2_Protector.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Protector's swords have been magically enchanted with the power of Fire by "
"Celestial Wizards. Protectors also carry a large shield which they use to "
"bash and Slow their opponents."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Quester, race=AE_myh_celestial
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\a2_Quester.cfg:5
msgid "Quester"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Quester, race=AE_myh_celestial
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\a2_Quester.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Most Celestials don't ride horses, or wander alone, but some crusaders feel "
"the call to work abroad on their own. These celestials follow the 'quest' to "
"bring light to the world individually through works of valor. Knowing they "
"must travel great distances, they learn to ride horses, and adapt a lance for"
" devastating charge attacks. Although the quest is supposed to be an "
"individual thing, Questers have no problems grouping up with other people if "
"it helps them accomplish their task."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Divine_Champion, race=AE_myh_celestial
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\a3_Divine_Champion.cfg:5
msgid "Divine Champion"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Divine_Champion, race=AE_myh_celestial
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\a3_Divine_Champion.cfg:18
msgid ""
"For a Knight to be recognized as a Champion he must first commit at least two"
" Great Deeds and have shown his form to be exceptional to other Knights on "
"the battle field. Champions are reguarded as highly as Messengers, if not "
"perhaps even higher."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Holy_Sentinel, race=AE_myh_celestial
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\a3_Holy_Sentinel.cfg:5
msgid "Holy Sentinel"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Holy_Sentinel, race=AE_myh_celestial
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\a3_Holy_Sentinel.cfg:18
msgid ""
"These crusaders hold the line with flaming sword, and great sheild. They are "
"famous for their ability to bash their way forward and then hold the ground "
"they just earned."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Legionnaire, race=AE_myh_celestial
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\b1_Legionnaire.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Legionnaires are staunch defenders of the Celestial homelands. With extensive"
" studies in the arts of defensive combat, Legionnaires have good physical "
"resistancies."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Keeper, race=AE_myh_celestial
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\b2_Keeper.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Keepers are staunch defenders of the Celestial homelands. With stout hearts, "
"and hardened skin they will hold till death or relief comes."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Sentinel, race=AE_myh_celestial
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\b3_Sentinel.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The great guardians of important celestials are called Sentinels, for their "
"silent, but imposing presence, and their complete immunity to boredom."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Light_Spirit, race=AE_myh_celestial, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\c1_Light_Spirit.cfg:5
msgid "Light Spirit"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Light_Spirit, race=AE_myh_celestial, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\c1_Light_Spirit.cfg:26
msgid ""
"Light Spirits are a breed of faeries who possess an aura of arcane energy "
"that infuses their entire body with a radiant light. They share their energy "
"with the Celestials in return for protection, and to some extent worship."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\c1_Light_Spirit.cfg:50
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\c2_Lantern_Archon.cfg:50
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\c3_Master_of_Light.cfg:51
msgid "shock of light"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Lantern_Archon, race=AE_myh_celestial, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\c2_Lantern_Archon.cfg:5
msgid "Lantern Archon"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Lantern_Archon, race=AE_myh_celestial, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\c2_Lantern_Archon.cfg:25
msgid ""
"Lantern Archons are a breed of faeries who possess an aura of arcane energy "
"that infuses their entire body with a radiant light. Lantern Archons defend "
"themselves with powerful shocks of arcane energy at a distance; up close they"
" are quite defenseless."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Master_of_Light, race=AE_myh_celestial, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\c3_Master_of_Light.cfg:5
msgid "Master of Light"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Master_of_Light, race=AE_myh_celestial, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\c3_Master_of_Light.cfg:26
msgid ""
"A faerie who exercises her output of arcane energy may master using it as a "
"weapon to such a degree that they are named Masters of Light."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Messenger, race=AE_myh_celestial
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_refugees_Messenger, race=AE_mrc_refugees_race
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\d1_Messenger.cfg:5
#: .\units\ME_units\refugees\b2-messenger.cfg:5
msgid "Messenger"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Messenger, race=AE_myh_celestial
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\d1_Messenger.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Messengers are chosen as Celestial leaders for the simple and traditional "
"reason that their wings grow in adolescence rather than fall off or remain "
"vestigial. Unlike other Celestials, Messengers can fly over the battlefield "
"and give orders, granting a bonus to surrounding troops."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\d1_Messenger.cfg:90
msgid "female^Messenger"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Claimant, race=AE_myh_celestial
#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Claimant, race=AE_imp_nemidian_race
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\d2_Claimant.cfg:5
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-nemidians\Claimant.cfg:5
msgid "Claimant"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Claimant, race=AE_myh_celestial
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\d2_Claimant.cfg:22
msgid ""
"All winged Celestials were once named Claimants. They were called this by "
"their bretheren in the beginning days of Celestial society as they claimed to"
" be the natural leaders of the Celestial people. Claimants now exclusively "
"write Celestial law, which Messengers then spread to the people."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\d2_Claimant.cfg:90
msgid "female^Claimant"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Herald, race=AE_myh_celestial
#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Herald, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\d3_Herald.cfg:5
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Herald.cfg:5
msgid "Herald"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Herald, race=AE_myh_celestial
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\d3_Herald.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Heralds are the highest ranking officers, skilled with sword, and words they "
"inspire their troops to victory. They proclaim a message of hope to their "
"fellows, and a message of death to their foes."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Windsong_Herald, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\d3_Herald.cfg:58
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\c3_Herald.cfg:5
msgid "female^Herald"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Seraph, race=AE_myh_celestial, gender=male
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\d4_Seraphin.cfg:5
msgid "Seraph"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Seraph, race=AE_myh_celestial, gender=male
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\d4_Seraphin.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Exalted is the title given to the mightiest of winged celestials. They are "
"honored to the point where they are no longer considered officers in the "
"army, but rather the manifestation of glory. Few exist that fight with "
"greater strength, or with greater ability to inspire and lead."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\d4_Seraphin.cfg:59
msgid "female^Seraph"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Wizard, race=AE_myh_celestial
#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Acolyte, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\e1_Wizard.cfg:5
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Acolyte.cfg:4
msgid "Acolyte"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Wizard, race=AE_myh_celestial
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\e1_Wizard.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Celestials who lose their vestigial wings in adolescence are not allowed to "
"fight in the military. As a result, they must undertake other endeavors. The "
"practice of magic is one of such endeavors. Originally used to create the "
"everglowing lights in Celestial towns using Holy energy, some Wizards have "
"harnessed magical powers for more militaristic purposes in order to join "
"their bretheren in battle. The Celestial Heralds have allowed them this "
"honor."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\e1_Wizard.cfg:36
msgid "flare"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Battle_Wizard, race=AE_myh_celestial
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\e2_Battle_Wizard.cfg:5
msgid "Battle Wizard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Battle_Wizard, race=AE_myh_celestial
#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Great_Wizard, race=AE_myh_celestial
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\e2_Battle_Wizard.cfg:17
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\e2_Great_Wizard.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The wizards of the celestials have always harnessed the suns power for their "
"magic. Those who fight with the military for a while become adept at pulling "
"the suns power into rapid magical blasts."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Great_Wizard, race=AE_myh_celestial
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\e2_Great_Wizard.cfg:6
msgid "Great Wizard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Mystic, race=AE_myh_celestial
#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Mystic, race=AE_stf_minotaurs_race
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\e2_Mystic.cfg:5
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Mage_Mystic.cfg:5
msgid "Mystic"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Mystic, race=AE_myh_celestial
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\e2_Mystic.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Many celestial wizards focus on the study of spirits rather than raw sun "
"magic. These are known as mystics. Their skills in this area allow them to "
"aid the army in new ways."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Prophet, race=AE_myh_celestial
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_oracles_Prophet, race=AE_mrc_oracles_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\e3_Prophet.cfg:5
#: .\units\ME_units\oracles\a2-prophet.cfg:5
msgid "Prophet"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Prophet, race=AE_myh_celestial
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\e3_Prophet.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Mystics who become skilled enough in their arts develop the strange ability "
"to foretell events. No one is certain how they do this or when any of the "
"things they say will happen, records have shown prophecies thousands of years"
" old coming true. These wizards are also deadly warriors in combat."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Sage, race=AE_myh_celestial
#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Sage, race=AE_fut_welkin
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_oracles_Sage, race=AE_mrc_oracles_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\e3_Sage.cfg:5
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Sage.cfg:5
#: .\units\ME_units\oracles\g1-sage.cfg:5
msgid "Sage"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Sage, race=AE_myh_celestial
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\e3_Sage.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The celestials believe the power of a wizard is not measured by his skill "
"with magic, but by his wisdom of it's use. A wizard who has achieved both "
"power and wisdom is known as a sage."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Zealot, race=AE_myh_celestial
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\f1_Zealot.cfg:5
msgid "Zealot"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Zealot, race=AE_myh_celestial
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\f1_Zealot.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The celestial society tends to breed people who would fearlessly battle with "
"no regard for their own life or family. More in fact than they can support in"
" their standing army. However if the armies go marching off, a crowd of "
"zealots will almost always follow, and the armies although not accepting "
"these into their ranks, do not deny them the chance to fight."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\f1_Zealot.cfg:27
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\f2_Militant.cfg:28
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\f3_Sicarius.cfg:31
msgid "chakram slice"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=ranged
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\f1_Zealot.cfg:36
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\f2_Militant.cfg:37
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\f3_Sicarius.cfg:40
msgid "chakram throw"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Militant, race=AE_myh_celestial
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\f2_Militant.cfg:5
msgid "Militant"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Militant, race=AE_myh_celestial
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\f2_Militant.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The celestials have always had a very militant, and totalitarian mindset. "
"They believe that the battle with evil should be fought until it is over. As "
"a result there is no shortage of civilians who are willing to join and fight "
"for the army at a minutes notice. Some of them even practice in case such a "
"chance comes up."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Sicarius, race=AE_myh_celestial
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\f3_Sicarius.cfg:7
msgid "Sicarius"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Sicarius, race=AE_myh_celestial
#: .\units\EoM_units\celestials\f3_Sicarius.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Civilian warriors who have proven their worth time and time again, are "
"granted an honorary rank known as Sicarius. It is quite an honor in Celestial"
" society."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Flappers, race=AE_myh_devling
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\a1_Flappers.cfg:5
msgid "Flappers"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Flappers, race=AE_myh_devling
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\a1_Flappers.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Some devlings are of a slightly different breed, and grow wings, and can spit"
" fire."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\a1_Flappers.cfg:29
msgid "mini-glaive"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Flyers, race=AE_myh_devling
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\a2_Flyers.cfg:5
msgid "Flyers"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Flyers, race=AE_myh_devling
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\a2_Flyers.cfg:17
msgid "Devlings are dangerous without wings, and even more dangerous with."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Attackers, race=AE_myh_devling
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\a3_Attackers.cfg:5
msgid "Attackers"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Attackers, race=AE_myh_devling
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\a3_Attackers.cfg:18
msgid ""
"With uncanny speed, heated breath, and sharp weapons, even the smallest of "
"enemies is a threat."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Nailers, race=AE_myh_devling
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\b1_Nailers.cfg:5
msgid "Nailers"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Nailers, race=AE_myh_devling
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\b1_Nailers.cfg:24
msgid ""
"All craftsmen know that if they leave their tools lying about they will get "
"lost, though few know why. Though small devlings have a knack for doing lots "
"of damage with simple tools."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\b1_Nailers.cfg:54
msgid "nail 'em"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\b1_Nailers.cfg:63
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\b2_Spikers.cfg:63
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\b2_Spikers.cfg:72
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\b3_Staplers.cfg:64
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\b3_Staplers.cfg:73
msgid "club 'em"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Spikers, race=AE_myh_devling
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\b2_Spikers.cfg:5
msgid "Spikers"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Spikers, race=AE_myh_devling
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\b2_Spikers.cfg:24
msgid ""
"Devlings are small knaves. They often use tricks to distract their enemies "
"before taking a swing. They may be small but certainly not harmless carrying "
"around a large club or hammer."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\b2_Spikers.cfg:54
msgid "spiker 'em"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Staplers, race=AE_myh_devling
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\b3_Staplers.cfg:5
msgid "Staplers"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Staplers, race=AE_myh_devling
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\b3_Staplers.cfg:25
msgid ""
"There are few happier things, than a small sadistic creature, with a great "
"big hammer."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\b3_Staplers.cfg:55
msgid "staple 'em"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Overgrown_Devling, race=AE_myh_devling
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\c1_Overgrown.cfg:5
msgid "Overgrown"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Overgrown_Devling, race=AE_myh_devling
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\c1_Overgrown.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Some devlings grow to be almost as tall as a dwarf. These devlings are solid "
"fighters, and provide a bit of toughness to the devling arsenal."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Devling_Soldier, race=AE_myh_devling
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\c2_Soldier.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Much of devling philosophy is quite simple. Life is about hurting other "
"people as much as possible. Overgrown devlings may not be as bright as their "
"smaller kin, but after awhile they figure out they can hurt others more if "
"they pick up a pointy stick. Though, they might never figure out that they "
"are supposed to be stabbing with it rather than slicing..."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Devling_Warrior, race=AE_myh_devling
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\c2_Warrior.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Much of devling philosophy is quite simple. Life is about hurting other "
"people as much as possible. Overgrown devlings may not be as bright as their "
"smaller kin, but after awhile they figure out they can hurt others more if "
"they pick up a club."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Devling_Chief, race=AE_myh_devling
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\c3_Chief.cfg:19
msgid ""
"The Devlings Chiefs may look burly compared to their lesser kin but are "
"fierce warriors. Upon their bodies are hung trophies from their latest "
"battles. However they still have not figured out that spears are supposed to "
"be stabbing weapons, but more than make up for that with brute muscle."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Devling_Hero, race=AE_myh_devling
#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Hero, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\c3_Hero.cfg:5
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Hero.cfg:5
msgid "Hero"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Devling_Hero, race=AE_myh_devling
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\c3_Hero.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Eventually a deviling can become proficient enough to be revered by his "
"kindred as a hero. Unfortunately devlings tend to forget any hero who dies, "
"so he won't have a legacy, but while he lives he'll have a sort of ironic "
"glory."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Grand_Devling_Chief, race=AE_myh_devling
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\c4_Grand_Chief.cfg:5
msgid "Grand Chief"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Grand_Devling_Hero, race=AE_myh_devling
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\c4_Grand_Hero.cfg:5
msgid "Grand Hero"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Grand_Devling_Hero, race=AE_myh_devling
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\c4_Grand_Hero.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Only those who are able to continue to grow in the battle advance to Grand "
"Heros"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Sneak, race=AE_myh_devling
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\d0_Sneak.cfg:5
msgid "Sneak"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Sneak, race=AE_myh_devling
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\d0_Sneak.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Devilings small size allows them to swiftly slip around enemies, and stick "
"sharp objects into vulnerable places."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Lurker, race=AE_myh_devling
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Lurker, race=AE_mrc_cult_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\d1_Lurker.cfg:5
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\h2-lurker.cfg:5
msgid "Lurker"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Lurker, race=AE_myh_devling
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\d1_Lurker.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Devilings who practice sticking knives into peoples backs long enough get "
"even better at it."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Ninja, race=AE_myh_devling
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\d2_Ninja.cfg:5
msgid "Little Ninja"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Ninja, race=AE_myh_devling
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\d2_Ninja.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Some devlings which didn't let others kill them, gain weight, and so they do "
"more powerful damage."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Assassin # ? or magican?, race=AE_myh_devling
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\d3_Magican.cfg:5
msgid "Little Magican"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Cursers, race=AE_myh_devling, gender=male
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\e1_Cursers.cfg:5
msgid "Cursers"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Cursers, race=AE_myh_devling, gender=male
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\e1_Cursers.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Devlings may be small creatures, but they have big mouths. Filthy ones too. "
"The verbal component to deviling magic tends to be quite profane."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Blasphemists, race=AE_myh_devling, gender=male
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\e2_Blasphemists.cfg:5
msgid "Blasphemists"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Blasphemists, race=AE_myh_devling, gender=male
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\e2_Blasphemists.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Devilings have a way of saying taunting peoples beliefs to undermine their "
"internal security. Devilings also have magic that grips the heart like a "
"claw. Devilings like to combine the two."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Offenders, race=AE_myh_devling, gender=male
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\e3_Offenders.cfg:5
msgid "Offenders"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Offenders, race=AE_myh_devling, gender=male
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\e3_Offenders.cfg:18
msgid ""
"If you have any pride in your heart, then devilings will find a way to offend"
" it. In theory, if you have absolutely no pride they can't hurt you that way."
" Unfortunately that won't save you from their magics."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Abusers, race=AE_myh_devling, gender=male
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\e4_Abusers.cfg:5
msgid "Abusers"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Abusers, race=AE_myh_devling, gender=male
#: .\units\EoM_units\devlings\e4_Abusers.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Words can harm a person, and devilings have a knack for finding the right "
"words to harm someone with. Enough of this harm can abuse a person in a way "
"you could not with any physical weapon."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Fire, race=AE_myh_elemental
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\a1_Fire_Elemental.cfg:5
msgid "Fire Elemental"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Fire, race=AE_myh_elemental
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\a1_Fire_Elemental.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Fire spirits tend to inhabit rocks to give them form to fight in. This form "
"gives them decent power, and toughness."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Fire_Wisp, race=AE_myh_elemental
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\a2_Fire_Wisp.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Fire Wisps are spirits of smoke and flame. When not being ordered around they"
" like to frolic in pools of lava and take great delight in burning anything "
"they can reach."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Living_Furnace, race=AE_myh_elemental
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\a2_Living_Furnace.cfg:5
msgid "Living Furnace"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Living_Furnace, race=AE_myh_elemental
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\a2_Living_Furnace.cfg:22
msgid ""
"In the course of time, Fire Elementals grow into a larger and stronger form. "
"Their strength has also increased."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Fire_Ghost, race=AE_myh_elemental
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\a3_Fire_Ghost.cfg:24
msgid ""
"Fire Wisps take the form of a ghost when they have enough power. These ghosts"
" are composed of the fire element and breathe out fire."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Lava_Beast, race=AE_myh_elemental
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\a3_Lava_Beast.cfg:5
msgid "Lava Beast"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Lava_Beast, race=AE_myh_elemental
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\a3_Lava_Beast.cfg:24
msgid ""
"Eventually these spirits will grow to monstrous Lava Beast. Beware of them, "
"they'll burn you!"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Air, race=AE_myh_elemental
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\b0_Air_Elemental.cfg:5
msgid "Air Elemental"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Air, race=AE_myh_elemental
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\b0_Air_Elemental.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Air Elementals take the form of a purple cloud. It fights with the ice winds "
"of the north that can draw the living heat from your skin, and gales of wind "
"that slice through armor. However the magical form of the elemental is "
"fragile, and has no defense at close range."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Razorbird, race=AE_myh_elemental
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\b1_Razorbird.cfg:5
msgid "Razorbird"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Razorbird, race=AE_myh_elemental
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\b1_Razorbird.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Lightning is not an element, however some wind spirits can take a form where "
"they can control it. The body they need to develop from a younger form, known"
" as the Razorbird. These birds have razor feathers which can slice anything "
"but they need more energy to generate a lightning bolt."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Wind_Spirit, race=AE_myh_elemental
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\b1_Wind_Spirit.cfg:5
msgid "Wind Spirit"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Wind_Spirit, race=AE_myh_elemental
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\b1_Wind_Spirit.cfg:21
msgid ""
"As Air Elementals stay in their physical form, they grow stronger, as does "
"their power over winds. The advanced ability to control or herd winds allows "
"the elemental to attack with more force. In addition they are now strong "
"enough to hold a dagger."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Thunderbird, race=AE_myh_elemental
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\b2_Thunderbird.cfg:5
msgid "Thunderbird"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Thunderbird, race=AE_myh_elemental
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\b2_Thunderbird.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Using its metal feathers the Thunderbird is able to create powerfull sparks "
"that can be thrown at long range."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\b2_Thunderbird.cfg:55
msgid "thunderbolt"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Zephyr, race=AE_myh_elemental
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\b2_Zephyr.cfg:22
msgid ""
"A wind spirit who stays in form long enough gains great mastery over winds. "
"This grants him strength to his attacks, and toughness to his form."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Djinn, race=AE_myh_elemental
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\b3_Djinn.cfg:24
msgid ""
"For centuries, there have been tales about mighty wind spirits known as "
"djinns that are oft summonable with magical metallic objects of ethereal "
"origin. In many stories, these objects are oil lamps. Most of the tales "
"mention that if a djinn is summoned by these types of objects, the djinn is "
"obliged to carry out the wishes of the summoner. Due to this fact, the "
"abilities of djinns are often highly exaggerated, to the point of granting "
"any wish of the summoner. In reality, these spirits are only capable of "
"accomplishing feats within the limits of the power of the wind and "
"swordsmanship.\n"
"\n"
"Despite the reality of these creatures' abilities, many believe that djinns "
"are virtually omnipotent beings, thus they speculate what force or god "
"created the djinn and for what reason. Some even believe that a race of "
"divine beings created the djinn in order to serve them. Although these "
"theories could be true, djinns are often spawned by violent storms being "
"exposed to incredibly powerful magic or created by immensely powerful wind "
"mages."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Earth, race=AE_myh_elemental
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\c1_Earth_Elemental.cfg:5
msgid "Earth Elemental"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Earth, race=AE_myh_elemental
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\c1_Earth_Elemental.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Earth spirts take the form of moving rocks. In combat the contribute great "
"durability, and mediocre attacks."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Rock_Golem, race=AE_myh_elemental
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\c2_Rock_Golem.cfg:5
msgid "Rock Golem"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Rock_Golem, race=AE_myh_elemental
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\c2_Rock_Golem.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Rock Golems are the bodies of Earth spirits that have grown strong enough to "
"animate their hulking bodies. These creatures are incredibly tough, but weak "
"for their size."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Stone_Titan, race=AE_myh_elemental
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\c3_Stone_Titan.cfg:26
msgid ""
"Earth Spirits of immense power can animate immense bodies. Although not fast,"
" the shear mass of the monster can cause quite a bit of damage."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Water, race=AE_myh_elemental, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\d1_Water_Elemental.cfg:5
msgid "Water Elemental"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Water, race=AE_myh_elemental, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\d1_Water_Elemental.cfg:24
msgid ""
"Water elementals bodies are merely a mass of water. In water it is hard to "
"distinguish them from the water. This and their ability to restore their form"
" from the water makes them powerful when in water. However on land it takes "
"all the spirits power just to keep itself moving, and flowing, without "
"worrying about defending itself."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Ice_Crab, race=AE_myh_elemental, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\d2_Ice_Crab.cfg:5
msgid "Ice Crab"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Ice_Crab, race=AE_myh_elemental, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\d2_Ice_Crab.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Some water elementals decide to generate an aura of cold, to freeze their "
"form, and give them a solid body. Crabs are the favored for, because their "
"form is practical for both land, and sea travel, and can fight with spearlike"
" icicles."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\d2_Ice_Crab.cfg:49
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\d3_Ice_Shell.cfg:50
msgid "icicle"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\d2_Ice_Crab.cfg:58
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\d3_Ice_Shell.cfg:59
msgid "gelid aura"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Undine, race=AE_myh_elemental, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\d2_Undine.cfg:24
msgid ""
"In conserving more power, little water elementals become the more violent and"
" magnificent Undines. Not only have the Undines gained more power but they "
"seemed to have, for some unknown reason, taken the shape of a woman."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Ice_Shell, race=AE_myh_elemental, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\d3_Ice_Shell.cfg:5
msgid "Ice Shell"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Ice_Shell, race=AE_myh_elemental, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\d3_Ice_Shell.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Once ice crabs gather enough elemental power from the cold, they evolve into "
"a more stronger and taller sort of creature. Having icicle spikes for hands, "
"they prefer to thrive in the coldest regions of the world."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Tempest_Spirit, race=AE_myh_elemental, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\d3_Tempest_Spirit.cfg:5
msgid "Tempest Spirit"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Tempest_Spirit, race=AE_myh_elemental, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\d3_Tempest_Spirit.cfg:24
msgid ""
"Tempest Spirits are manifestations of water that is influenced by the likes "
"of a deadly storm, due to this these spirits weld very dangerous power and "
"are often subject to being angered easily. Due to this it is best to avoid "
"these spirits, unless you are certain you either have a way of reasoning with"
" them or can counter their awesome power."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Unicorn, race=AE_myh_elemental, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\e1_Unicorn.cfg:5
msgid "Unicorn"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Unicorn, race=AE_myh_elemental, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\e1_Unicorn.cfg:29
msgid ""
"These small, white, horse-like creatures proudly bear a horn in the middle of"
" their foreheads. Composed by light and life forces, they are so full of them"
" that its mere presence heals allied units around them."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Silver_Unicorn, race=AE_myh_elemental, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\e2_Silver_Unicorn.cfg:5
msgid "Silver Unicorn"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Silver_Unicorn, race=AE_myh_elemental, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\e2_Silver_Unicorn.cfg:30
msgid ""
"Gleaming with light, these exotic creatures bear a magical silvery horn in "
"the middle of their foreheads which can shoot rays of pure light. Composed by"
" light and life forces, they are so full of them that its mere presence heals"
" allied units around them."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Vine_Beast, race=AE_myh_elemental, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\f1_Vine_Beast.cfg:22
msgid ""
"The vine beasts are diffrent from most elementals. They are not an "
"incarnation of an elemental spirit, but rather a beast formed from wood, and "
"given life by magic."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Vine_Tiger, race=AE_myh_elemental, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\f2_Vine_Tiger.cfg:5
msgid "Vine Tiger"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Vine_Tiger, race=AE_myh_elemental, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\f2_Vine_Tiger.cfg:22
msgid ""
"The vine beasts grow in size as they live, and the larger forms are called "
"tigers after a beast that they resemble."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Vine_Monster, race=AE_myh_elemental, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\elementals\f3_Vine_Monster.cfg:5
msgid "Vine Monster"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Falcon, race=AE_myh_therian, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\therians\a1_Falcon.cfg:5
msgid "Falcon Therian"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Falcon, race=AE_myh_therian, gender=female
#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Prairie_Falcon, race=AE_myh_therian, gender=female
#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Gyrfalcon, race=AE_myh_therian, gender=female
#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Peregrine_Falcon, race=AE_myh_therian, gender=female
