msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Therian_Priest, race=AE_myh_therian
#: .\units\EoM_units\therians\x3_Priest.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Therian Priests are shamans who have become very skilled in the many skills "
"they have learned."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Blood_Apprentice, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\a1_Blood_Apprentice.cfg:5
msgid "Blood Apprentice"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Blood_Apprentice, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\a1_Blood_Apprentice.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Vampires have always had an obsession with blood and control. As such their "
"magic has always revolved around blood and souls. These vampires attack their"
" enemies by causing their blood to boil or by using their aura to disrupt the"
" auras of their enemies, thus being able to strike their souls. If the "
"vampire is attacking a non-living creature it can use its blood boiling magic"
" as a field of fiery aura to damage it."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\a1_Blood_Apprentice.cfg:36
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\a2_Blood_Manipulator.cfg:36
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\a2_Flesh_Artisan.cfg:47
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\a3_Sangel.cfg:37
#: .\units\MiE_units\vampires\1_Apprentice.cfg:34
#: .\units\MiE_units\vampires\2_Savant.cfg:34
#: .\units\MiE_units\vampires\3_Grandmaster.cfg:35
msgid "blood boil"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Blood_Manipulator, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\a2_Blood_Manipulator.cfg:5
msgid "Blood Manipulator"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Blood_Manipulator, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\a2_Blood_Manipulator.cfg:17
msgid ""
"It is horrifying what an skilled manipulator of blood can do to you. He can "
"cause your every vein to burn. He can strip you of food, or cause you to "
"vomit, or burn through your brain. Horrifying as as that is what he can do to"
" your spirit is worse."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\a2_Blood_Manipulator.cfg:48
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\a3_Sangel.cfg:49
msgid "wipe"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Flesh_Artisan, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\a2_Flesh_Artisan.cfg:5
msgid "Flesh Artisan"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Flesh_Artisan, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\a2_Flesh_Artisan.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Some vampires who take up blood magic prefer to work on themeseleves rather "
"than their enemies. They turn themselves into monsters, and can fight well "
"both in melee and at a distance."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Sangel, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\a3_Sangel.cfg:5
msgid "Sangel"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Sangel, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\a3_Sangel.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Any vampier who has earned the title Sangel can do things with your blood and"
" soul too horrible to contemplate."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Bloodborn, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\b0_Bloodborn.cfg:7
msgid "Bloodborn"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Bloodborn, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\b0_Bloodborn.cfg:27
msgid ""
"Vampires do not bear many natural children. Most vampires are spawned by a "
"bite from another vampire. The curses and strengths of vampires are spread as"
" the vampire sucks the blood from his prey, and replaces it with magic. "
"People new to the blood are made weak by it, and have not enough mastery over"
" their mind to resist an order of the one who bit them. Eventually, they will"
" grow used to it, and learn how to use the strength it provides them, but "
"until then they are much as oversized children."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\b0_Bloodborn.cfg:54
msgid "female^Bloodborn"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Malborn, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\b1_Malborn.cfg:5
msgid "Malborn"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Malborn, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\b1_Malborn.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Some people are simply to weak to handle the blood, and it leaves them a "
"mindless mess. This gives the vampire lord complete control over what is left"
" of them. Because of this control, the vampire lord is quite willing to arm "
"these creatures with poisoned daggers. Unlike his other servents, these ones "
"cannot rebel."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#. [attack], type=blade, range=ranged
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\b1_Malborn.cfg:29
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\d3_Twilight_Walker.cfg:33
#: .\units\EOS_units\eventide\EventideAlchemist.cfg:54
#: .\units\EOS_units\eventide\EventideHerbalist.cfg:41
#: .\units\EOS_units\eventide\EventidePoisoner.cfg:61
msgid "poisoned dagger"
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\b1_Malborn.cfg:54
msgid "female^Malborn"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Fledgeling, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\c1_Fledgeling.cfg:5
msgid "Fledgeling"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Fledgeling, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\c1_Fledgeling.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Most vampires are weak ones in service of the lords and more powerful ones, "
"hoping and waiting that they will rise into a position of power for "
"themselves. Until then they serve him in exchange for blood. When there are "
"no more humans or bloodborn, these vampires are the next most expendable "
"thing a vampire lord has."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\c1_Fledgeling.cfg:71
msgid "female^Fledgeling"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Duelist, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\c2_Duelist.cfg:5
msgid "Duelist"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Duelist, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\c2_Duelist.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Vampires have always had a somewhat upper-class manner. This transfers over "
"to their style of fighting too. The vampires without the family or leadership"
" to become lords make themselves useful to a lord that can ensure they always"
" have a fresh supply of blood. Those who do this are known as duelists. Their"
" masters use them as guards and assassins. They wear not armor, but focus on "
"rapid pinpoint fencing which they carry out with inhuman accuracy."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\c2_Duelist.cfg:74
msgid "female^Duelist"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Noble, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\c2_Noble.cfg:19
msgid ""
"The vampires with family or leadership make themselves lord over whatever "
"land they can hold. They use charm, terror, and ruthlessness to uphold their "
"reign. They will surround themselves with their loyal vampires, whom they "
"keep in check with the promise of continual blood, and subject any lesser "
"creature to be the surfs of their society, and to provide blood or "
"cannon-fodder in an emergency. They do not feed on them directly in most "
"circumstances, because that tends to lead to rebellion, but rather force the "
"surfs to provide animals for their weekly blood."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\c2_Noble.cfg:75
msgid "female^Noble"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Sire, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\c3_Sire.cfg:5
msgid "Sire"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Sire, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\c3_Sire.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Some vampires grow strong enough to subject other vampire lords to "
"themselves. In exchange for protection (from whom is not always mentioned), "
"the other lords provide a tithe of their tax to the Sire."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\c3_Sire.cfg:52
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\c4_Methusalem.cfg:53
#: .\units\MiE_units\vampires\3_Count.cfg:49
#: .\units\MiE_units\vampires\4_Prince.cfg:50
msgid "dementia gaze"
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\c3_Sire.cfg:101
msgid "female^Mistress"
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\c3_Sire.cfg:105
msgid ""
"Some of the beautiful vampiresses who are as powerful as a Sire and are "
"capable of winning the love of one are given the title of 'Mistress'. These "
"vampiresses are capable of unleashing a world of pain and suffering upon "
"their enemies with their twin daggers and their dementing gaze. The minions "
"and mercenaries which serve her fight significantly better whenever they "
"around her, sometimes it is unknown whether she is leading them or the "
"mercenaries and minions are protecting her in order to protect themselves "
"from the wrath of the Mistress husband."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Sword_Dancer, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\c3_Sword_Dancer.cfg:5
msgid "Sword Dancer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Sword_Dancer, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\c3_Sword_Dancer.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Vampires live a long time, and have time to develop many social graces, "
"including dance. Duelists who have spent extended amounts of time fighting, "
"and dancing see similarities between the two, and combine them into a "
"devastating and accurate form of fighting that cuts through defenses."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\c3_Sword_Dancer.cfg:83
msgid "female^Sword Dancer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Methusalem, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\c4_Methusalem.cfg:5
msgid "Methusalem"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Methusalem, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\c4_Methusalem.cfg:20
msgid ""
"You may only see one such vampire every thousand years, but when you do you "
"know war is coming. These vampires have grown so old, and so powerful, that "
"they believe it is time to fill the vampire manifest destiny, and subject "
"every other race. With their terrible power, charisma, and the promise of an "
"eternity of free blood, they can gather the support of most vampire lords and"
" lieges. Those who won't join them they destroy ruthlessly."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\c4_Methusalem.cfg:102
msgid "female^Duchess"
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\c4_Methusalem.cfg:106
msgid ""
"A Duchess is a powerful, yet elegant vampiress who is often the wife of a "
"Methusalem. Even though a Duchess is feared for all the minions she "
"controlls, she is capable of ravaging her enemies with her graceful "
"swordsmanship and her dementing gaze; in addition she has a powerful bite. It"
" is wise not to get in her way due to her dreadful power and the vast number "
"of minions she controls."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Thin_Blood, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\d1_Thin_Blood.cfg:5
msgid "Thin Blood"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Thin_Blood, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\d1_Thin_Blood.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Not all bloodborn grow towards their vampire side. Some lean on the human "
"side, and can stand the daylight, and use a bow, which most vampires disdain "
"as a peasant weapon. However they still have the vampires curse of blood "
"thirst on them, giving them a reason to continue to serve their lord. These "
"qualities make them a valuable support for a vampires army."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\d1_Thin_Blood.cfg:78
msgid "female^Thin Blood"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Half_Blood, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\d2_Half_Blood.cfg:5
msgid "Half Blood"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Half_Blood, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\d2_Half_Blood.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Thin Blood vampires blood grows stronger as they kill. When they are balanced"
" roughly evenly between both bloods, they are known as half bloods."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\d2_Half_Blood.cfg:78
msgid "female^Half Blood"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Day_Hunter, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\d3_Day_Hunter.cfg:5
msgid "Day Hunter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Day_Hunter, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\d3_Day_Hunter.cfg:19
msgid ""
"After heading to the halfway point, a halfblood can choose to go back. They "
"still have the strength given them by their vampire blood, but they have "
"chosen light, and no longer desire blood. Many of them will still serve "
"vampire lords, out of loyalty, and habit, and vampire lords rarely regret "
"having them in their service."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\d3_Day_Hunter.cfg:82
msgid "female^Day Hunter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Twilight_Walker, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\d3_Twilight_Walker.cfg:5
msgid "Twilight Walker"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Twilight_Walker, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\d3_Twilight_Walker.cfg:19
msgid ""
"After reaching the halfway point, a halfblood can choose to go back, but many"
" prefer not too. Those who don't are known as twilight walkers, and are among"
" a lords most trusted servants, because they could have chosen day, but did "
"not. As such they are often entrusted with poisons, and assassinations. For a"
" vampire lord will always have enemies some of which are better slain with "
"poison in the twilight, than with an army at night."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\d3_Twilight_Walker.cfg:103
msgid "female^Twilight Walker"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Gargoyle, race=AE_myh_gargoyle
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\f1_Gargoyle.cfg:5
msgid "Gargoyle"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Gargoyle, race=AE_myh_gargoyle
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\f1_Gargoyle.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Vampires can animate stone with blood. These stone creatures use the magic of"
" blood to fly. Vampires use these creatures to guard their castles, and to "
"provide air support and surveillance to their forces. They cannot see, and "
"thus fight equally well in all lights."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Marlgoyle, race=AE_myh_gargoyle
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\f2_Marlgoyle.cfg:5
msgid "Marlgoyle"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Marlgoyle, race=AE_myh_gargoyle
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\f2_Marlgoyle.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The blood magic of the gargoyle is strengthened when it kills enough. As it "
"keeps killing it will get stronger, and the stone form will continue to gain "
"strength."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Blood_Hulk, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\g2_Blood_Hulk.cfg:5
msgid "Blood Hulk"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Blood_Hulk, race=AE_myh_vampire
#: .\units\EoM_units\vampires\g2_Blood_Hulk.cfg:26
msgid ""
"These monstrous vampires gorge themselves on the blood of their victims "
"instead of turning them. Their appetite for blood is never sated, and with "
"each victim they grow in strength and size. Only talented blood mages can "
"create such monstrosities."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Shapeshifter, race=AE_myh_therian
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\a1_Shapeshifter.cfg:5
msgid "Shapeshifter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Shapeshifter, race=AE_myh_therian
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\a1_Shapeshifter.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The Therian and Warg are good neighbors; a mutual respect binds the two "
"cultures together. Some Therian find the Warg society so appealing that they "
"embrace it as their own. These Therian use their shifting powers to resemble "
"more closely those with whom they live. The Warg refer to them simply as "
"'Shapeshifters'."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\a1_Shapeshifter.cfg:33
#: .\units\ME_units\slavers\a0-slave.cfg:23
#: .\units\ME_units\slavers\a1-serf.cfg:23
#: .\units\ME_units\slavers\a2-farmhand.cfg:23
#: .\units\MiE_units\cornurs\1_Shaman.cfg:30
#: .\units\MiE_units\cornurs\2_Warlock.cfg:31
#: .\units\MiE_units\cornurs\3_Horned_Elder.cfg:32
msgid "sickle"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Changeling, race=AE_myh_therian
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\a2_Changeling.cfg:5
msgid "Changeling"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Changeling, race=AE_myh_therian
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\a2_Changeling.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Shapeshifters who have spent extended periods of time enveloped within the "
"Warg culture grow to even more strongly resemble their companions."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Wolfling, race=AE_myh_therian
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\a3_Wolfling.cfg:7
msgid "Wolfling"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Wolfling, race=AE_myh_therian
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\a3_Wolfling.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Once a Shapeshifter has become fully integrated into Warg society they are "
"known as Wolflings. They are no longer seen as a human presence within their "
"society, but as essential companions."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Stalker, race=AE_myh_warg
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\b1_Stalker.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Stalkers are the smaller of the Warg bretheren and are known for their darker"
" fur. Because of their smaller size these Warg wield a spear in combat "
"instead of their claws. Stalkers use their heightened agility to great use in"
" combat to surround their foes."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\b1_Stalker.cfg:36
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\b2_Shadow_Pelt.cfg:36
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\b3_Night_Eye.cfg:38
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\c2_Rabid_Wolf.cfg:42
msgid "tackle"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Shadow_Pelt, race=AE_myh_warg
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\b2_Shadow_Pelt.cfg:5
msgid "Shadow Pelt"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Shadow_Pelt, race=AE_myh_warg
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\b2_Shadow_Pelt.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Many stalkers who have grown more experianced, will smear certain kinds of "
"dirt and dust on their fur to make themselves harder to see. This has lead to"
" the term shadow pelt, as it gives the impression of a permanent shadow "
"resting on them."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Night_Eye, race=AE_myh_warg
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\b3_Night_Eye.cfg:5
msgid "Night Eye"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Night_Eye, race=AE_myh_warg
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\b3_Night_Eye.cfg:18
msgid ""
"After a time as a shadow pelt something about the dirt bleeds into the fur. "
"This gives a very dark shade of black that hides very well in the darkest of "
"nights."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Warrior_Wolf, race=AE_myh_warg
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\c1_Warrior_Wolf.cfg:5
msgid "Warrior Wolf"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Warrior_Wolf, race=AE_myh_warg
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\c1_Warrior_Wolf.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The low ranking warriors of the clan are know as wolves, only after proving "
"themselves are they allowed to call themselves warg."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Rabid_Wolf, race=AE_myh_warg
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\c2_Rabid_Wolf.cfg:5
msgid "Rabid Wolf"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Rabid_Wolf, race=AE_myh_warg
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\c2_Rabid_Wolf.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Some warrior wolves prefer to become more like wolves rather than choose to "
"take the name of warg. They never learn how to use weapons, but instead adapt"
" a style using their whole body, and move on all fours."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Warrior_Warg, race=AE_myh_warg
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\c2_Warrior_Warg.cfg:5
msgid "Warrior Warg"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Warrior_Warg, race=AE_myh_warg
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\c2_Warrior_Warg.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The Warg who have proven themselves worthy of the name are a force to be "
"reckoned with when defending their homeland."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Fenrir, race=AE_myh_warg
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\c3_Fenrir.cfg:7
msgid "Fenrir"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Fenrir, race=AE_myh_warg
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\c3_Fenrir.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Warg can fight quite well without weapons, as such many of their warriors "
"never become skilled with them. However the ones who do, are given the title "
"Fenrir, and are warriors to be feared."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Moon_Blade, race=AE_myh_warg
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\c3_Moon_Blade.cfg:5
msgid "Moon Blade"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Moon_Blade, race=AE_myh_warg
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\c3_Moon_Blade.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The warg revere the moon, and sometimes the moon blesses devout warriors with"
" strange powers. These warg are marked with white fur, and wield swords like "
"slivers of the moon."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=melee
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\c3_Moon_Blade.cfg:29
msgid "Moon Sword"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Pack_Leader, race=AE_myh_warg
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\c3_Pack_Leader.cfg:5
msgid "Pack Leader"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Pack_Leader, race=AE_myh_warg
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\c3_Pack_Leader.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The individual packs, and clans each have a leader chosen from their "
"warriors, for his wisdom and prowess."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Garou, race=AE_myh_warg
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\c4_Garou.cfg:5
msgid "Garou"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Garou, race=AE_myh_warg
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\c4_Garou.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Most warg don't live to be very old. However the leaders that live to be very"
" old are revered by freinds, and feared by foes."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Wolf_Cub, race=wolf
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\d0_Wolf_Cub.cfg:5
msgid "Wolf Cub"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Wolf_Cub, race=wolf
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\d0_Wolf_Cub.cfg:20
msgid ""
"The warg can catch and train real wolves to aid them in war. They do it by "
"capturing wolf cubs, and starting the training while they are very young. "
"Wolves make good scouts as they can move even faster than the warg can."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Wolf, race=wolf
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mie_thelian_wolf, race=wolf
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\d1_Wolf.cfg:6
#: .\units\MiE_units\wolves\1_Wolf.cfg:5
msgid "Wolf"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Wolf, race=wolf
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\d1_Wolf.cfg:21
msgid "Full grown wolves are rather swift, and accurate with their jaws."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Dire_Wolf, race=wolf
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mie_thelian_dire_wolf, race=wolf
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\d2_Dire_Wolf.cfg:6
#: .\units\MiE_units\wolves\2_Dire_Wolf.cfg:5
msgid "Dire Wolf"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Dire_Wolf, race=wolf
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\d2_Dire_Wolf.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Something about the warg bleeds into the wolves they tame, causing them to "
"grow larger, and stronger. These wolves, known as dire wolves provide swift "
"sure firepower to the wargs arsenal."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Fire_Sprite, race=AE_myh_dryad, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\e1_Fire_Sprite.cfg:5
msgid "Fire Sprite"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Fire_Sprite, race=AE_myh_dryad, gender=female
#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Flame_Sprite, race=AE_myh_dryad, gender=female
#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Flame_Spirit, race=AE_myh_dryad, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\e1_Fire_Sprite.cfg:18
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\e2_Flame_Sprite.cfg:18
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\e3_Flame_Spirit.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Fire Sprites are tiny faerie creatures who get their name from being able to "
"somewhat control the element of fire. Living in the forest, these creatures "
"use their powers primarily to prevent their homes from burning down. Sharing "
"a respect for the woods, they have become great allies with the Warg."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\e1_Fire_Sprite.cfg:24
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\e2_Flame_Sprite.cfg:24
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\e3_Flame_Spirit.cfg:25
msgid "sprite punch"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\e1_Fire_Sprite.cfg:33
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\e2_Flame_Sprite.cfg:33
msgid "sapphire flame"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Flame_Sprite, race=AE_myh_dryad, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\e2_Flame_Sprite.cfg:5
msgid "Flame Sprite"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Flame_Spirit, race=AE_myh_dryad, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\e3_Flame_Spirit.cfg:5
msgid "Flame Spirit"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\e3_Flame_Spirit.cfg:34
msgid "spirit fire"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Blackfur, race=AE_myh_warg
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\f1_Blackfur.cfg:5
msgid "Blackfur"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Blackfur, race=AE_myh_warg
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\f1_Blackfur.cfg:17
msgid ""
"There is a rare breed of warg with black fur and a slight build. Although not"
" as physicaly strong as the normal kind, foes have learned to fear the sudden"
" death that could await in any dark shadow."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Black_Hunter, race=AE_myh_warg
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\f2_Black_Hunter.cfg:5
msgid "Black Hunter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Black_Hunter, race=AE_myh_warg
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\f2_Black_Hunter.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The blackfur hunt at night for the concealment it gives, and are quite adept "
"at hunting any kind of quarry."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Water_Dryad, race=AE_myh_dryad, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\g1_Water_Dryad.cfg:5
msgid "Water Dryad"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Water_Dryad, race=AE_myh_dryad, gender=female
#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Water_Nymph, race=AE_myh_dryad, gender=female
#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Water_Shyde, race=AE_myh_dryad, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\g1_Water_Dryad.cfg:20
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\g2_Water_Nymph.cfg:19
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\g3_Water_Shyde.cfg:22
msgid ""
"In any wetland area you may find a Dryad calling the place her home. Dryads "
"are not combatitive in nature and instead will control surrounding plant life"
" to ensnare her enemies and slow them down until help arrives."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Water_Nymph, race=AE_myh_dryad, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\g2_Water_Nymph.cfg:5
msgid "Water Nymph"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Water_Shyde, race=AE_myh_dryad, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\wargs\g3_Water_Shyde.cfg:5
msgid "Water Shyde"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Courier, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\a1_Courier.cfg:5
msgid "female^Courier"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Courier, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\a1_Courier.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Unlike most other peoples, the Windsong possess neither domesticated beasts "
"of burden or mechanical transports. The former due to the icy conditions of "
"their homeland, and the latter due to their distaste for machines. Instead, "
"some girls devote themselves to learning the levitation ciphers. There are "
"many benefits to this, rough terrain poses little impediment, as does ice and"
" water, and delicate loads can be carried quickly. Their devotion to "
"levitation denies them access to the more directly dangerous ciphers, so they"
" carry a bow and hit their opponents with small rocks if they come too close."
" Their skill at manipulating gravity makes their arrows uncannily accurate."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Emissary, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\a2_Emissary.cfg:5
msgid "female^Emissary"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Emissary, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\a2_Emissary.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Those Couriers who show themselves to be intelligent and reliable are "
"elevated to the position of Emissary. They are entrusted with transporting "
"documents, precious artefacts and sometimes even Windsong council members. "
"Freed from the physical and mental burden of maintaining large loads, an "
"Emissary is much more agile. This allows her to wield a sword which she uses "
"to slash at enemies in a flurry of charges. Such tactics are dangerous, so "
"Emissaries prefer to use their original weapons if possible."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Reaver, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\a2_Reaver.cfg:5
msgid "female^Reaver"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Reaver, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\a2_Reaver.cfg:18
msgid ""
"While Couriers in peacetime are rarely of a martial bent, war brings out "
"hidden abilities in everyone, and some have recently chosen to bring back a "
"covenant long lost: the order of the Reavers. Used for the heaviest assaults "
"and sieges in ancient wars, they exchange their lightweight stones for great "
"iron blades, crushing any who stand in the path of the Windsong."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Dreadnought, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\a3_Dreadnought.cfg:5
msgid "female^Dreadnought"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Dreadnought, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\a3_Dreadnought.cfg:24
msgid ""
"The records concerning the master Reavers for whom the title of Dreadnought "
"was created tell not only of their heroic deeds in battle, of the courage "
"with which they hurled themselves against hordes of foes, but also of their "
"darker deeds, of cities razed to the ground and armies laid waste before "
"their unstoppable advance. These legends have long since been forgotten by "
"all but the Windsong themselves, but with the revival of their order, it is "
"certain that new ones will soon be written."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Sky_Shard, race=AE_myh_abstraction
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\b0_Sky_Shard.cfg:5
msgid "Sky Shard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Sky_Shard, race=AE_myh_abstraction
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\b0_Sky_Shard.cfg:31
msgid ""
"In an age long forgotten by the rest of the world, when the Windsong first "
"took up their watch, they realized that it would be impractical to carry out "
"their duty of balancing without becoming dangerously numerous themselves. The"
" Windsong needed servants who could become numerous in times of balancing and"
" quickly decrease in times of hiding. Servants who could be trusted utterly, "
"could travel quickly and were able to perform a variety of tasks. The cipher,"
" the only power used by the Windsong, was capable of carving such servants "
"from The Raw and binding them into reality. But this required the full "
"attention of an Ascendant to maintain even a handful of these Shards. And so "
"the Windsong gathered the most powerful Cryptographers (those who use "
"ciphers) to the Foundation, and had them construct an artifact of "
"unimaginable, though very defined, power to do it for them. It took centuries"
" to create, but with it the Windsong were finally complete.\n"
"\n"
"Shards are bound to the will of whoever controls 'The Mandate'. As they are "
"barely present in reality, they can teleport between areas of high cipher "
"activity (friendly towns). Also a consequence of this is their immunity to "
"Drain, Poison and Plague. Shards are crystalline in nature and so have "
"unusual resistances. Shards are never destroyed, they are merely 'pushed out'"
" of reality."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=melee
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\b0_Sky_Shard.cfg:42
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\b1_Sky_Crystal.cfg:43
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\c1_Weaver.cfg:36
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\c2_Envoy.cfg:32
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\c3_Herald.cfg:33
msgid "purge"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Sky_Crystal, race=AE_myh_abstraction
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\b1_Sky_Crystal.cfg:5
msgid "Sky Crystal"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Sky_Crystal, race=AE_myh_abstraction
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\b1_Sky_Crystal.cfg:32
msgid ""
"A Sky Crystal is a Shard that has emerged further into reality and so has a "
"firmer physical presence.\n"
"\n"
"Crystals are bound to the will of whoever controls 'The Mandate'. As they are"
" barely present in reality, they can teleport between areas of high cipher "
"activity (friendly towns). Also a consequence of this is their immunity to "
"Drain, Poison and Plague. Crystals are crystalline in nature and so have "
"unusual resistances. Crystals are never destroyed, they are merely 'pushed "
"out' of reality."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Weaver, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\c1_Weaver.cfg:5
msgid "female^Weaver"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Weaver, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\c1_Weaver.cfg:23
msgid ""
"While most Windsong are able to devote themselves to only one or two aspects "
"of the cipher, there are those who are able to access many. When such a child"
" is born, a spirit from The Raw appears and binds to them. To best make use "
"of their gifts, these 'Weavers' (for they can intertwine their ciphers) are "
"given the best education and training that the Council can provide.\n"
"\n"
"Once they reach adulthood, Weavers fill a number of different roles in "
"Windsong society: they are the healers, the planners, the diviners, and the "
"military leaders. They pursue the art of archery, viewing it as a form of "
"meditation, and are aided in both everyday life and battle by their "
"accompanying spirit.\n"
"\n"
"The first lessons a Weaver-born learns are the arts of healing, though she "
"cannot yet cure poison."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Envoy, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\c2_Envoy.cfg:5
msgid "female^Envoy"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Envoy, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\c2_Envoy.cfg:21
msgid ""
"The Windsong know how dangerous unadvised action can be. Their limited "
"resources means that even one mistake could threaten the Eternal Watch. To "
"guard against this, some Weavers focus their attention on the Sky Shards, "
"learning to emulate the Shard's detachment from reality. Once submersed in "
"The Raw, they can move long distances just as the Shards can. The Council "
"relies on these Envoys to asses operations or be the field advisers in an "
"emergency. This amazing power comes at the cost of their studies in other "
"areas like healing and battle, so while they can advise and coordinate field "
"agents, they cannot lead them in battle or heal them afterwards. Furthermore,"
" to remain in The Raw for more than an instant is dangerous, so Envoys cannot"
" use it to protect themselves in the same way as the Shards.\n"
"\n"
"Envoys can move instantly between areas of high cipher activity (friendly "
"towns). Envoys cannot heal anymore."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Prophetess, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\c2_Prophet.cfg:23
msgid ""
"There are many among the Windsong who could successfully lead an army, or "
"plan a battle, as the council has all children trained to the best of their "
"ability. So, for the Windsong, knowing when to act is more important. The Raw"
" is affected by all events, both past and future, and is fluidic as these "
"possibilities change. Through her accompanying spirit, some Weavers learn to "
"interpret flows in The Raw as predictions for future events. With time and "
"experience, her predictions become more accurate and dependable. Eventually, "
"if she is of quality, she will be invited to join the ranks of the Prophets. "
"Unlike the farseers of other peoples, the Windsong Prophets do not 'witness' "
"events so much as apply an expanded form of cause and effect. Knowing all "
"flows are open to interpretation, Prophets are discouraged from making "
"predictions without the council of her peers.\n"
"\n"
"Unlike Envoys, Prophets have much time to study the arts of leadership and "
"healing, and she has now learned to cure poison. Such is the respect of the "
"Windsongs for the Prophets, that any direction given by them will be obeyed "
"immediately and without question."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Ascendant, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\c3_Ascendant.cfg:5
msgid "female^Ascendant"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Ascendant, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\c3_Ascendant.cfg:24
msgid ""
"Few Weavers and Prophets reach the rank of Ascendant. Not just because of the"
" difficult in reaching this goal, but also because of the danger and "
"sacrifice necessary. The path to becoming an Ascendant begins when a "
"Weaver-born binds themselves to their accompanying spirit in the same manner "
"that the spirit bound itself to her on her birth. A successful binding will "
"slowly, over the course of two years, pull her body into The Raw. If the "
"Ascending fails, she faces a slow death. As the Spirit cares for her "
"wellbeing above all else, it will reject the binding unless she can convince "
"it that she is powerful enough to Ascend. If successful, her physical form "
"will slowly be converted into The Raw itself, granting her immortality and "
"great, though not infallible, insight into the nature of events, both current"
" and of those to come.\n"
"\n"
"Any who reach this pinnacle of the Weaver-born automatically becomes a full "
"member of the Council. Though most Ascendants were Prophets, it is "
"technically possible for Envoys and Heralds to Ascend. However, Envoys have "
"experienced the dangers of passing through The Raw and the idea of entering "
"unprotected shakes even the bravest woman's confidence.\n"
"\n"
"Because an Ascendant's body is being transformed into The Raw, most damage "
"they take simply speeds the process (They heal as if in a village every "
"turn). They know powerful healing ciphers and those around them revere them, "
"obeying them with fervor."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Windsong_Herald, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\c3_Herald.cfg:22
msgid ""
"As children, Weavers learn to communicate with their accompanying spirit via "
"a special type of cipher. The spirit will only ever respond to the girl it "
"bound itself to, and has a very basic mind. As an Envoy, dealing with "
"unexpected and often dangerous situations, she has learned how useful this "
"spirit can be. Those who dedicate long hours to the understanding and "
"training of their accompanying spirit gain a powerful ally who will guide "
"their bow and empower their purges. Those who achieve this link join the "
"elite ranks of the Heralds, responsible directly to the Council.\n"
"\n"
"Heralds can move instantly between areas of high cipher activity (friendly "
"towns)."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Seeker, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\d1_Seeker.cfg:5
msgid "female^Seeker"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Seeker, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\d1_Seeker.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The name given to the Seekers comes from their role in the legend of the "
"Windsong's first appearance: they were tasked with searching the world over "
"for a suitable place to build the first Foundation.\n"
"\n"
"This tradition of exploration continues unabated, and the Seekers' great "
"speed and agility are easily put to use in times of war."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\d1_Seeker.cfg:29
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\d2_Pathfinder.cfg:27
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\d2_Pathfinder.cfg:39
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\d2_Skyrunner.cfg:35
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\d3_Farstrider.cfg:28
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\d3_Farstrider.cfg:40
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\d3_Stormbringer.cfg:36
msgid "polearm"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Pathfinder, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\d2_Pathfinder.cfg:5
msgid "female^Pathfinder"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Pathfinder, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\d2_Pathfinder.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Capable of racing through the toughest terrain with uncanny speed, those "
"known as Pathfinders serve as the vanguards of the Windsong armies. They have"
" devoted themselves to developing their own agility, and long practice has "
"granted them an almost inhuman speed. And, when they deem it necessary, their"
" fluid grace and skill with their polearms allows them to strike like the "
"thunder they wield, catching distracted foes unawares."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Skyrunner, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\d2_Skyrunner.cfg:5
msgid "female^Skyrunner"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Skyrunner, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\d2_Skyrunner.cfg:26
msgid ""
"One of the few warrior groups to survive the Age of Patience, the Skyrunners,"
" choose to sacrifice the immense speed of the Pathfinders in favor of "
"equipping themselves with more substantial armor - though this is still "
"exceptionally light by most standards. In times of peace, their relative "
"strength and skill with the lightning cipher won them a place as the honor "
"guard to the members of the Council, but now they take up once again the old "
"mantle of war."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Farstrider, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\d3_Farstrider.cfg:5
msgid "female^Farstrider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Farstrider, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\d3_Farstrider.cfg:19
msgid ""
"One of the oldest tales that have come down from the wars of the ancients "
"tells of a great battle between the Windsong and their old nemeses, the "
"elves. Each side sent their fastest runner to call for reinforcements, and "
"though the elves felt assured of their agile messenger's victory over his "
"frail human opponent, in the end, the elf fell behind, cursing his weary "
"feet. The Farstrider, on the other hand, ran with the speed and endurance of "
"the wind, and when the Windsong reinforcements arrived two days early, the "
"elves were forced to surrender."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Stormbringer, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\d3_Stormbringer.cfg:5
msgid "female^Stormbringer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Stormbringer, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\d3_Stormbringer.cfg:27
msgid ""
"The name Stormbringer was obviously appended to these great warriors for "
"their ability to shatter enemy ranks with furious bolts of lightning, but "
"seems doubly apt when one witnesses the way in which they lead the Windsong "
"into battle. Spinning past their foes like dancers despite their heavy armor,"
" the presence of a Stormbringer on the front lines can turn the most "
"carefully prepared defence into a chaotic rout in seconds."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Gatekeeper, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\e1_Gatekeeper.cfg:5
msgid "female^Gatekeeper"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Gatekeeper, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\e1_Gatekeeper.cfg:33
msgid ""
"The Windsong Foundation, though hidden far in the arctic northern seas, still"
" represents too great a target to be left unguarded. The Gatekeepers have "
"kept their cousins safe throughout the Age of Patience, and they have no "
"intention of ceasing their vigilance now.\n"
"\n"
"Devoting themselves to the study of combat, they have created a unique, "
"unarmed style which allows them to fight without removing their ceremonial "
"blindfolds."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Heretic, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\e2_Heretic.cfg:5
msgid "female^Heretic"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Heretic, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\e2_Heretic.cfg:36
msgid ""
"The Windsong Council preaches the importance of patience and pacifism, that "
"one should not give in to anger and instead think carefully about every "
"decision. It is this belief that has kept the Windsong out of conflict for so"
" long.\n"
"\n"
"There is a faction, however, that believes that the balance of the world can "
"only be brought about by action, and thus espouses a more active role for the"
" Windsong, pushing constantly for war and the expansion of the Windsong's "
"influence in the outside world.  Though they are known as Heretics, their "
"opinions are nonetheless valued, and those Gatekeepers who follow the "
"philosophy are allowed to train themselves in the forbidden arts of swordplay"
" and fire magic."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\e2_Heretic.cfg:53
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\e3_Harbinger.cfg:65
msgid "sunburst"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Lorekeeper, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\e2_Lorekeeper.cfg:7
msgid "female^Lorekeeper"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Lorekeeper, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\e2_Lorekeeper.cfg:37
msgid ""
"The Great Library, the enormous complex that forms the heart of the Windsong "
"Foundation, is the home of what may the oldest texts still existing in the "
"world, many of which have been copied down by generations of Scribes as their"
" original bindings dissolved into dust. Most of the Windsong are forbidden "
"from entering its hallowed halls, and only the most loyal and skilled "
"Gatekeepers are allowed to join the ranks of the Lorekeepers and become its "
"guards."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Harbinger, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\e3_Harbinger.cfg:5
msgid "female^Harbinger"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Harbinger, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\e3_Harbinger.cfg:37
msgid ""
"Stunningly powerful warriors, Harbingers epitomize the warlike path of the "
"Heretic. Their command of the forbidden flame cipher, as well as the "
"bloodthirsty furor they unleash upon their opponents, make them the terror of"
" their allies as much as of their enemies. Yet even the peaceful Windsong "
"realize that such power must be put to use, and they are often selected to "
"lead groups of their fellow Heretics into battle."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Oathkeeper, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\e3_Oathkeeper.cfg:5
msgid "female^Oathkeeper"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Oathkeeper, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\e3_Oathkeeper.cfg:36
msgid ""
"Until recently, it was believed that the Oathkeeper caste had, like many "
"others, vanished with time, made unnecessary by long years of peace. It was "
"not until the deepest vaults opened and they marched forth to do battle that "
"it became clear that the Oathkeeper title had not only survived, but that the"
" mantle had been passed down from generation to generation through the "
"millenia. Those few who are offered membership are inevitably among the most "
"skilled warriors ever to walk the world, and capable of holding back entire "
"armies singlehandedly."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Scribe, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\f1_Scribe.cfg:5
msgid "female^Scribe"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Scribe, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\f1_Scribe.cfg:28
msgid ""
"The scribes of the Windsong are those engaged in studying, as well as "
"contributing to, the vast libraries kept at the Foundation.\n"
"\n"
"With the coming of the Great Balancing, they have proven their worth in "
"combat, employing against their enemies an ancient -- and very effective -- "
"brand of magic known as the Cipher."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\f1_Scribe.cfg:36
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\f2_Savant.cfg:34
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\f3_Arbiter.cfg:42
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\f4_Librarian.cfg:44
msgid "cipher"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Savant, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\f2_Savant.cfg:5
msgid "female^Savant"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Savant, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\f2_Savant.cfg:28
msgid ""
"The savants teach the scribes more about using Ciphers and revise the "
"contributions made by the scribes to the Great Library. In combat, though "
"they may lack the skill needed to wield weapons, their magic compensates well"
" for the drawback."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Arbiter, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\f3_Arbiter.cfg:5
msgid "female^Arbiter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Arbiter, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\f3_Arbiter.cfg:28
msgid ""
"The head mistress among the Savants is known as the Arbiter. Possessing vast "
"knowledge on the Great Library and the Cipher, these maidens also wield "
"scythes for protection from close range."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Runeforger, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\f3_Runeforger.cfg:5
msgid "female^Rune Forger"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Runeforger, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\f3_Runeforger.cfg:33
msgid ""
"Instead of becoming Arbiters, some Savants may chose to master all forms of "
"the Cipher. The Rune Forgers are experienced in all forms of the Cipher and "
"they can use this knowledge to inflict catastrophic damage to the enemies who"
" were foolish enough to cross paths with the Windsong."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=ranged
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\f3_Runeforger.cfg:54
msgid "sorrow"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=ranged
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\f3_Runeforger.cfg:68
msgid "memory"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\f3_Runeforger.cfg:81
msgid "death"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_myh_Librarian, race=AE_myh_windsong, gender=female
#: .\units\EoM_units\windsong\f4_Librarian.cfg:5
msgid "female^Librarian"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_stf_eltireans_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\eltireans.cfg:9
msgid "race^Eltirean"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_stf_eltireans_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\eltireans.cfg:10
msgid "race^Eltireans"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_stf_eltireans_race
#. [race], id=AE_stf_free_saurians
#. [race], id=AE_stf_triththa_cuttlefish
#. [race], id=AE_stf_race_wind_elemental
#: .\units\EOS_units\eltireans.cfg:12
#: .\units\EOS_units\saurians.cfg:9
#: .\units\EOS_units\_units.cfg:19
#: .\units\EOS_units\_units.cfg:32
msgid ""
"This race is from The Era of Strife. Its coding and art were done by Jami, "
"AI, Elrias, Lizard, Quietus, Espreon, Neorice and Various others."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Gnoll_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\gnolls.cfg:9
msgid "race^Gnoll"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Gnoll_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\gnolls.cfg:10
msgid "race^Gnolls"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Gnoll_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\gnolls.cfg:13
msgid ""
"This race is from The Era of Strife. Its coding and art were done by Jami, "
"AI, Elrias, Lizard, Quietus, Espreon, Neorice and Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Gnolls are humanoid hyenas which live in the swamps of the Silver Lands. They"
" are known for their aptitude in the fine art of archery and for their "
"ability to conceal themselves in swampy terrain. Gnolls are often associated "
"with the Minotaurs, mainly due to the fact Minotaurs often hire Gnolls as "
"mercenaries."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs.cfg:4
msgid "race^Minotaur"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs.cfg:5
msgid "race^Minotaurs"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs.cfg:8
msgid ""
"This race is from The Era of Strife. Its coding and art were done by Jami, "
"AI, Elrias, Lizard, Quietus, Espreon, Neorice and Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Minotaurs are fearful creatures which are of ancient origin, they used to"
" be humans which lived in the ancient times on the Great Continent, but a "
"curse was placed upon the ancient civilization of these humans due to their "
"disobedience towards their deity and creator. However some of the cursed ones"
" prayed to their deity for forgiveness and therefore were rewarded with the "
"inability to die by aging and therefore could only be killed by other means.\n"
"\n"
"A minotaur's body is basically a fusion between that of a bull and a human. "
"They also possess immense strength and some possess magical abilities granted"
" by a higher relationship with their deity. The minotaurs even without a "
"greater relationship with their deity are very magical creatures due to their"
" prayers for forgiveness. This magic is manifested as the inability to die by"
" aging and therefore the minotaurs' bodies heal very quickly.\n"
"\n"
"Minotaurs fight well in forests and mountains but fight poorly in open "
"fields, and especially in water and most of them are very slow but sturdy."
msgstr ""

