#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Gnoll_Sharpeye, race=AE_stf_minotaurs_Gnoll_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\gnolls\a3-Sharpeye.cfg:4
msgid "Sharpeye"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Gnoll_Sharpeye, race=AE_stf_minotaurs_Gnoll_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\gnolls\a3-Sharpeye.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from The Era of Strife. Its coding and art were done by Jami, "
"AI, Elrias, Lizard, Quietus, Espreon, Neorice and Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Gnoll Sharpeyes have perfected their grand art of archery and have become"
" somewhat adept in the use of thier swords. Eventhough most of the Gnolls "
"spend most of their time attacking in the swamps the Sharpeyes sometimes "
"participate in battle outside of the swamps. Nonetheless, these creatures "
"take pride in their art, especially when using it to kill."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Behemoth, race=AE_stf_minotaurs_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_highlanders_Behemoth, race=AE_mrc_highlanders_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Behemoth.cfg:5
#: .\units\ME_units\highlanders\e3-behemoth.cfg:5
msgid "Behemoth"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Behemoth, race=AE_stf_minotaurs_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Behemoth.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from The Era of Strife. Its coding and art were done by Jami, "
"AI, Elrias, Lizard, Quietus, Espreon, Neorice and Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Behemoths were minotaurs who committed crimes that are so severe (i.e. "
"blasphemy), that not even death would be harsh enough to punish them. The "
"process of turning something into an abomination such as this is so dark and "
"secret that only the Elders, the goddess of the minotaurs, and a few people "
"sneaky enough to witness the process without being caught know about it. It "
"is rumored that the crystals are used in this process.\n"
"\n"
"Nonetheless, the Behemoths have been obviously driven into a state of supreme"
" insanity, therefore only one adept in the magic of the minotaurs, or a "
"person to whom the behemoth has been ordered to obey is able to control them."
" In addition, due to the modifications caused by the ritual, the Behemoths "
"tend to move more swiftly than the rest of their brethren."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Behemoth.cfg:29
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Behemoth_Ancient.cfg:30
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Crusher.cfg:47
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Mauler.cfg:48
msgid "maul"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Ancient_Behemoth, race=AE_stf_minotaurs_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Behemoth_Ancient.cfg:5
msgid "Ancient Behemoth"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Ancient_Behemoth, race=AE_stf_minotaurs_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Behemoth_Ancient.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from The Era of Strife. Its coding and art were done by Jami, "
"AI, Elrias, Lizard, Quietus, Espreon, Neorice and Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Over time, the powerful, arcane magic which distorted the minotaur that "
"became a Behemoth further distorts the minotaur. This distortion causes the "
"Behemoth to grow, gain more strength and become much more insane. After a "
"certain degree of distortion, the Behemoth becomes known as an Ancient "
"Behemoth, which references the amount of time spent to become that distorted."
" An Ancient Behemoth is so mentally unstable, that it takes an Elder to "
"safely give it commands and/or orders to obey certain people.\n"
"\n"
"Since an Ancient Behemoth is extremely dangerous, they are oft kept in "
"enormous holding cells until needed; these cells are kept on the outskirts of"
" minotaur cities for further safety measures. Also, they are kept there so "
"that they can easily be used as an anti-siege weapon."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Boar_Cataphract, race=AE_stf_minotaurs_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Boar_Cataphract.cfg:36
msgid ""
"This unit is from The Era of Strife. Its coding and art were done by Jami, "
"AI, Elrias, Lizard, Quietus, Espreon, Neorice and Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Cataphracts are the elite of the boar-riding forces of the minotaur forces; "
"they have a practically perfect bond with their companion which the rider "
"often considers it to be his best friend. Even though Cataphracts use their "
"spears effectively, their true power still lies in their companion. It is "
"unknown how a sentient and non-sentient creature such as a boar could have "
"such a powerful bond and have effective communications. These qualities make "
"the Cataphracts a terrifyingly powerful force to be reckoned."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Boar_Knight, race=AE_stf_minotaurs_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Boar_Knight.cfg:5
msgid "Boar Knight"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Boar_Knight, race=AE_stf_minotaurs_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Boar_Knight.cfg:35
msgid ""
"This unit is from The Era of Strife. Its coding and art were done by Jami, "
"AI, Elrias, Lizard, Quietus, Espreon, Neorice and Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Boar Riders who know how to use their companions to their full potential are "
"promoted to Boar Knights. While Boar Knights carry regular weapons, their "
"real potential lies in the strength of their companion, due to their "
"evergrowing bond."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Boar_Rider, race=AE_stf_minotaurs_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Boar_Rider.cfg:5
msgid "Boar Rider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Boar_Rider, race=AE_stf_minotaurs_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Boar_Rider.cfg:35
msgid ""
"This unit is from The Era of Strife. Its coding and art were done by Jami, "
"AI, Elrias, Lizard, Quietus, Espreon, Neorice and Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Boar Riders mainly serve as scouts for the minotaur forces; however, they "
"also work well in battle. Boar Riders attack by trying to impale their "
"enemies or by using their enormous companions to crush them."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Gore, race=AE_stf_minotaurs_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Gore.cfg:5
msgid "Gore"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Gore, race=AE_stf_minotaurs_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Gore.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from The Era of Strife. Its coding and art were done by Jami, "
"AI, Elrias, Lizard, Quietus, Espreon, Neorice and Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Gores are basically new recruits in the minotaur infantry or simply "
"militia defending their territory."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Overlord, race=AE_stf_minotaurs_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Gore_Overlord.cfg:24
msgid ""
"This unit is from The Era of Strife. Its coding and art were done by Jami, "
"AI, Elrias, Lizard, Quietus, Espreon, Neorice and Various others.\n"
"\n"
"A minotaur that has been recognized for their skill, leadership ability and "
"intelligence is bestowed the title of 'overlord'. Basically the overlord rank"
" is the minotaur equivalent to the human rank of general. Overlords plan all "
"the battle strategies and whatnot, and unlike human generals, overlords "
"sometimes willingly participate directly in battle in order to further "
"inspire their comrades to perform their best. In addition, overlords wield "
"crossbows in order to strike enemies from afar, especially enemies about to "
"kill a comrade. These amazing qualities make these elites majestic sights to "
"behold."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Rouser, race=AE_stf_minotaurs_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Gore_Rouser.cfg:5
msgid "Rouser"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Rouser, race=AE_stf_minotaurs_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Gore_Rouser.cfg:22
msgid ""
"This unit is from The Era of Strife. Its coding and art were done by Jami, "
"AI, Elrias, Lizard, Quietus, Espreon, Neorice and Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Rousers are the elite of the minotaur infantry who seek either "
"generalship or executionership; their bravery is derived from the desire to "
"obtain higher ranks in minotaur society."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Savage, race=AE_stf_minotaurs_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Savage, race=orc
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mie_vampire_savage, race=AE_mie_vampire
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Gore_Savage.cfg:5
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Savage.cfg:4
#: .\units\MiE_units\vampires\1_Savage.cfg:5
msgid "Savage"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Savage, race=AE_stf_minotaurs_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Gore_Savage.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from The Era of Strife. Its coding and art were done by Jami, "
"AI, Elrias, Lizard, Quietus, Espreon, Neorice and Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Unlike the rousers, savages have decided to take on a reputation of fear "
"rathern than leadership. The reason savages are dreaded is because it appears"
" that savages have reverted to their primal instincts which are absolutely "
"terrifying in the eyes of those who do not know about the minotaurs well. "
"These frightening aspects appear to affect the enemy in a negative manner "
"which will actually physically weaken them."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Cutthroat, race=AE_stf_minotaurs_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_mercenaries_Cutthroat, race=AE_mrc_mercenaries_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Kusarigama_Cutthroat.cfg:6
#: .\units\ME_units\mercenaries\d2-Cutthroat.cfg:5
msgid "Cutthroat"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Cutthroat, race=AE_stf_minotaurs_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Kusarigama_Cutthroat.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from The Era of Strife. Its coding and art were done by Jami, "
"AI, Elrias, Lizard, Quietus, Espreon, Neorice and Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Kusarigamas are noble and highly useful weapons that are difficult to master."
" The cutthroats have gazed upon the power of a kusarigama master and they "
"wish to achieve such mastery. Although cutthroats lack experience with their "
"weapon they can still make some use of it."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#. [attack], type=impact, range=ranged
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Kusarigama_Cutthroat.cfg:28
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Kusarigama_Cutthroat.cfg:39
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Kusarigama_Executioner.cfg:33
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Kusarigama_Executioner.cfg:46
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Kusarigama_Slayer.cfg:32
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Kusarigama_Slayer.cfg:43
msgid "kusarigama"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Executioner, race=AE_stf_minotaurs_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Executioner, race=AE_mrc_mutant_race, gender=male
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_tribe_Executioner, race=AE_mrc_tribe_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Kusarigama_Executioner.cfg:5
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\a3-executioner.cfg:5
#: .\units\ME_units\tribe\f3-executioner.cfg:5
msgid "Executioner"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Executioner, race=AE_stf_minotaurs_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Kusarigama_Executioner.cfg:24
msgid ""
"This unit is from The Era of Strife. Its coding and art were done by Jami, "
"AI, Elrias, Lizard, Quietus, Espreon, Neorice and Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Executioners are masters of the kusarigama, they have their own style of "
"wielding it; instead of wielding it like a scythe, they prefer to wield it "
"like a claw. Even though these powerful warriors will kill most of the "
"enemies they face, they like to play it safe by poisoning their weapon. Most "
"foolhardy archers think they can easily defeat an Executioner, however they "
"likely have not been acquainted with the weight and chain that makes the "
"kusarigama such an effective weapon."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Slayer, race=AE_stf_minotaurs_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Kusarigama_Slayer.cfg:23
msgid ""
"This unit is from The Era of Strife. Its coding and art were done by Jami, "
"AI, Elrias, Lizard, Quietus, Espreon, Neorice and Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Learning how to properly and effectively wield a kusarigama is pure drudgery;"
" however that does not stop those eager to eventually gain the power and "
"skill of a master. Since slayers are still learning how to have near-perfect "
"control of their weapon they choose not to use poison like the executioners "
"do. Slayers are not quite masters yet; however they are still quite skilled "
"with their kusarigamas; therefore, slayers are not to be underestimated.."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Elder, race=AE_stf_minotaurs_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Mage_Elder.cfg:5
msgid "Elder"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Elder, race=AE_stf_minotaurs_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Mage_Elder.cfg:22
msgid ""
"This unit is from The Era of Strife. Its coding and art were done by Jami, "
"AI, Elrias, Lizard, Quietus, Espreon, Neorice and Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Elders are incredibly powerful mages who represent the minotaur's goddess"
" in the physical world, in addition they carry out her will. Their power "
"comes from their incredible aura combined with the divine crystals which they"
" wield. These crystals are very powerful and very different from the ones "
"wielded by the Warlocks, as they can be used to summon and create different "
"powers... they can even distort living beings. These powerful orcacles "
"sacrificed their sight in order to gain the ability to see their goddess as "
"she is invisible to most creatures. Although they cannot see through their "
"eyes the can see through a newly acquired sense which is obtained through the"
" ritual in which they lost their original sight."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Mage_Elder.cfg:40
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Mage_Mystic.cfg:47
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Mage_Shaman.cfg:42
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Mage_Warlock.cfg:40
msgid "aura blast"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Mystic, race=AE_stf_minotaurs_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Mage_Mystic.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from The Era of Strife. Its coding and art were done by Jami, "
"AI, Elrias, Lizard, Quietus, Espreon, Neorice and Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Although the Warlocks and the Elders are more famous for their very lofty "
"role, more powerful magic and the mysterious crystals which they wield, the "
"Mystics are superior to the Warlocks and the Elders in a few ways. First they"
" can levitate, such an ability is very useful in battle; second they are "
"physically stronger than their counterparts; third they possess healing "
"abilities. All these qualities make the Mystics a terrifying force on the "
"battle field, therefore they should not be taken lightly."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Shaman, race=AE_stf_minotaurs_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Mage_Shaman.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from The Era of Strife. Its coding and art were done by Jami, "
"AI, Elrias, Lizard, Quietus, Espreon, Neorice and Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Minotaur Shamans hold a lofty position in minotaur society, they either "
"pursue the quest as representatives of the minotaur's goddess or they pursue "
"the amazing ability to levitate and healing. Even though these mages are "
"lacking a bit of experience they are still powerful."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_minotaurs_Warlock, race=AE_stf_minotaurs_race
#: .\units\EOS_units\minotaurs\Mage_Warlock.cfg:21
msgid ""
"This unit is from The Era of Strife. Its coding and art were done by Jami, "
"AI, Elrias, Lizard, Quietus, Espreon, Neorice and Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Minotaur Warlocks are very powerful mages that have a very important role"
" in minotaur society; that role is to serve as conveyers of their goddess' "
"words and to serve as her hands. Their vast power comes from their powerful "
"aura combined with the crystals they wield."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_free_saurians_Brave, race=AE_stf_free_saurians
#: .\units\EOS_units\saurians\Brave.cfg:4
msgid "Saurian Brave"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_free_saurians_Brave, race=AE_stf_free_saurians
#: .\units\EOS_units\saurians\Brave.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from The Era of Strife. Its coding and art were done by Jami, "
"AI, Elrias, Lizard, Quietus, Espreon, Neorice and Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Saurian tribes rarely maintain anything resembling a standing army, fighting "
"primarily with hit-and-run raiding tactics by the tribe's hunters and scouts."
" The largest and strongest saurians are often designated to defend the "
"village and serve as shock troops in time of war. Being the closest thing the"
" tribe has to dedicated soldiers, they generally prefer the club over the "
"traditional saurian hunting spear, making them all the more effective in "
"battles against rival tribes."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_free_saurians_Champion, race=AE_stf_free_saurians
#: .\units\EOS_units\saurians\Champion.cfg:4
msgid "Saurian Champion"
msgstr ""

