#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_free_saurians_Warchief, race=AE_stf_free_saurians
#: .\units\EOS_units\saurians\Warchief.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from The Era of Strife. Its coding and art were done by Jami, "
"AI, Elrias, Lizard, Quietus, Espreon, Neorice and Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Lacking military training or discipline, the rare ocassions when saurians "
"choose to fight a pitched battle tend to be savage and frenzied affairs. Left"
" to their own devices the saurians' battle lines rapidly devolve into a "
"number of individual melees. Here distinction is earned not through "
"leadership or tactical ability, but sheer strength and fierceness, and the "
"saurians' war chiefs earn their positions through feats of personal prowess "
"rather than any sort of command ability. Although this leaves saurian "
"warbands deficient tactically, the power and ferociousness of their champions"
" is not to be underestimated."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_fut_brungar_race
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar.cfg:5
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar.cfg:7
msgid "race^Brungar"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_fut_brungar_race
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar.cfg:9
msgid ""
"This race is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
" \n"
"The Brungar are dwarves who grew tired of the caves in ages past and thus "
"ventured forth from their mighty empires in search of a different life. They "
"settle in the rock of lakes and oceans and eventually, after living centuries"
" in and out of the water, evolved gills and thus were able to create great "
"underwater caverns, rivalled by only their ancestors mountain realms. The "
"Brungar have not left all of their dwarven traits behind them however for "
"they still continue to make great contraptions that have helped in the making"
" of their underwater fortress and also in hunting and protecting their "
"caverns.\n"
"\n"
"The Brungar have, as is often found with dwarves, a king of great stature, "
"for a dwarf, but also they have a grand council. The king has ultimate power "
"but the council has some power of its own so having a position on this "
"council is a position of great respect through out the Brungar society. They "
"worship the god of the sea, as they call him, and never fail to pay homage "
"through sacrifice of a 15th of their entire earnings from the hunts. To fail "
"to sacrifice is punishable by death or forever banishment from the sea.\n"
"\n"
"The society of the Brungar is often misunderstood do to the difference "
"between them and that of conventional dwarves. The Brungar long for jewels "
"yes, but they do not bet all they have on them, or use them for money. They "
"do, however, use them for adorning their precious artifacts or weapons. The "
"king also is given a tribute of jewels every year as thanks for the great "
"leadership that he is giving to them. They spend their time hunting for both "
"game and jewels for they are dwarves after all. The smithies of the Brungar "
"are still as great as the smithies of old. They work in drained rooms in the "
"underwater caverns and create some of the best arms and weapons available "
"away from the mountains. Due to their need for speed they often use spears or"
" harpoons  rather then axes. But axes are not totally uncommon for those that"
" venture forth from the sea."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_fut_race_Nordhris
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris.cfg:4
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris.cfg:6
msgid "race^Nordhris"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_fut_race_Nordhris
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris.cfg:8
msgid ""
"The people now known as the Nordhris were once citizens of the peaceful "
"southern lands. Fearing that the decadence and folly they saw in their "
"brethren would be their undoing as well, they wandered northward, away from "
"long lazy summers and the trappings of civilization.\n"
"Their new unforgiving home has hardened their bodies and purified their "
"spirits, allowing them to tap into the primal spirit of the White Lands. By "
"their self-inflicted ordeal were they changed, skin becoming rougher, hair "
"more pronounced; the value of gold and gems dimmed in their eyes, for what "
"was required for survival was the family, the clan, and the cooperation of "
"the band – the Pack.\n"
"\n"
"Hunting, herding and foraging for subsistence, or raiding the spoiled humans "
"of the lowlands, the Nordhris are a people close to nature, which is "
"reflected in their tools and attire – leather, fur and wood is worn for "
"protection from the cold and the blows of enemies. Horn, stone and wood are "
"the primary material for weapons, with metal being used mainly for spear and "
"axeheads.\n"
"In summer, their people roam far and wide in search of bounty and adventure, "
"dwelling in large rotund tents they can fold and erect in a matter of "
"minutes, while for winter, they return to fortified settlements to share "
"tales, arrange weddings, and celebrate in the fires‘ glow.\n"
"\n"
"Men and womanfolk have widely separated duties and privileges in the Nordhric"
" society; while males have say over matters of the hunt, war, some crafts, "
"and are deemed connected to the spirits of beasts, women have say over "
"matters of the hearth, such as marriage, and tend to many crafts including "
"that of the brewer, tending the grounds, midwives, and seeing to the smaller "
"fortifications of the winter fortress; theirs is the connection to the Earth "
"and all that grows from her body.\n"
"While worldy matters are decided by the war leader, the Horn-Crowned "
"patriarch chosen by a gathering of grown males, and by the Summer, Autumn, "
"and Winter Queens, three women, a maiden, a mother and a crone, in times of "
"crisis the people look to the Shamans, who are privy to the deepest mysteries"
" of the spirits and act as keepers of lore and of the Law. While they watch "
"the observance of law by others, the shamans are subject to a harsh law "
"themselves – should they fail in their duties, or abuse the law for their "
"gain, they will be found dead one morning, frightened to death by the spirits"
" of the ancestors.\n"
"Disputes are settled by individuals or small proxy forces at most; warfare "
"between the clans is considered taboo. Trials will be held at the height of "
"winter, when breath freezes right in front of the mouth. Men will do combat "
"practically naked, armed but with ritual iron blades; the last man standing –"
" or holding the knife – has justice on his side. Most often, one contestant "
"will throw away the blade beforehand, as the icy iron is excruciatingly "
"painful to the touch.\n"
"\n"
"The Nordhris are a feral people, deliberately so. Their prime focus is upon "
"retaining and emphasizing what makes them human, and to that end, they live "
"every day to the fullest. Willingly and intentionally have they rejected the "
"trappings of civilization, and with them greed, treachery and decadence; "
"their system of taboos reflects this. Even today, when someone presents a "
"member of a clan with a written contract to sign, he can expect to have his "
"arms ripped out of the sockets."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin.cfg:4
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin.cfg:6
msgid "race^Welkin"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin.cfg:8
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
" \n"
"The Welkin are a form of woodland elves that had evolved over many periods of"
" time. The Welkin share many things in common with normal elves, specifically"
" physical features. However, these adapted elves have many inhabitants that "
"have wings. These wings enable them to fly and fight from above.The Welkin "
"left the forest because of the difficulty to fly in search of better suited "
"terrain. They populate mostly mountainous areas, along with hills. Dwarves "
"are usually competing for land with the Welkin, which leads to distrust and "
"wars. The Welkin sometimes ally trolls if needed during wars, since they have"
" a common enemy.\n"
"\n"
"The way of life for the Welkin is fairly different from many other cultures. "
"Everyone must learn magic from a certain age, during a period similar to "
"human's teenage years. They choose what path they wish to follow, the path of"
" Aten, the sun, the path of Thoth, the moon, or the path of the wind. The "
"path of the wind is the most complicated of all, and very few choose to "
"follow it. Some, however, choose to follow both Thoth and Aten, where they "
"study how to combine the powers to heal others. This path is not highly "
"accepted in society, and most that follow the two paths are outcasts.\n"
"\n"
"Welkin are known for their hunting skills. They hunt birds, woodland "
"creatures, and even occasionally gryphons. The hunters are very skilled, and "
"use a weapon similar to a spear. The queen or king divide the hunted food "
"evenly between all people, And therefore all must work to earn their food. "
"The monarchs only give what is neceessary. The Welkin are very independent "
"from other lands because they are also farmers, weapon smiths, as well as "
"armor smiths. Because of this, the Welkin must be very dependent upon their "
"own kind. Therefore if everyone doesn't play their part, their whole society "
"falters. It is looked on very dimly when lazyness or personal gain is held "
"higher then the community. The Welkin do not trade often because of their "
"independence of other nations and this leads to having few allies."
msgstr ""

