" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"Any Brungar that would willingly use an alligator as a mount is usually "
"considered to be a fool. This is due to the unforunate fact that the fatality"
" rate among the alligator riders is the highest of any profession-even the "
"Hunters. Even the practice of taming the alligators enough for them to allow "
"a rider is a task frought with peril. Despite this, some do decide to pursue "
"this course, and those that survive are undoubtably some of the most skilled,"
" cunning, and lucky dwarves to have ever lived."
