#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Sea_Turtle.cfg:35
msgid "Jaws"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=ranged
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Baby_Sea_Turtle.cfg:41
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Giant_Sea_Turtle.cfg:48
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Sea_Turtle.cfg:45
msgid "Water Jet"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Council_Elder, race=AE_fut_brungar_race
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Council_Elder.cfg:5
msgid "Council Elder"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Council_Elder, race=AE_fut_brungar_race
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Council_Elder.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"The next ring up from the Council Member, the Council Elders are wiser and "
"stronger then their lesser brothers. They have proven themselves either in "
"battle or in trade to obtain their highstanding position. They hold higher "
"standings in both the eyes of the king and the eyes of the common folk. "
"Because of their higher position they are granted both better armaments and "
"bigger weapons to signify their position. Still a wonder to the outside world"
" is how the Elder's armor can be so strong while being light enough that he "
"does not sink while in battle among the great seas."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Council_Member, race=AE_fut_brungar_race
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Council_Member.cfg:4
msgid "Council Member"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Council_Member, race=AE_fut_brungar_race
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Council_Member.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"In the government of the Brungar, the king is the final power, but he his not"
" without his ring of advisors, the Tri-Point Council makes up this ring. All "
"are mighty warriors and carry a trident to signify their prestigeous position"
" upon the council. While the Council Member is among the lower ring of the "
"Council, they are still leaders among the Brungar community and are often "
"seen leading their troops into battle in seek of honor and glory, both for "
"themselves and to gain greater position on the council."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Crab, race=monster
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Crab.cfg:5
msgid "Crab"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Crab, race=monster
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Crab.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"Although most crabs of the Brungar forces are as large as the trolls of "
"ancient times, some council members are simply impatient. Not bothering to "
"wait for the crustacean to reach its full size and combat capability, they "
"deploy crabs at the average size, which is admittedly still quite large by "
"human standards. A crab's exoskeleton can rival steel in strength, and has "
"the added benefit of being much lighter, which makes them extremely effective"
" in melee combat. When faced with a warrior attacking from distance, the crab"
" can launch streams of water. In the wild, these crabs usually survive by "
"ambushing unsuspecting humans on beaches."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Crab.cfg:29
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Giant_Crab.cfg:30
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Overgrown_Crab.cfg:29
