msgid "Claw"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Crocodile, race=monster
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Crocodile.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
" \n"
"It's a giant Crocodile. They are more vicious than Alligators and they eat "
"lots more."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Crocodile_Rider, race=AE_fut_brungar_race
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Crocodile_Rider.cfg:5
msgid "Crocodile Rider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Crocodile_Rider, race=AE_fut_brungar_race
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Crocodile_Rider.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"The Brungar that have proven their aptitude for handling their alligator are "
"eventually given crocodiles to be their new mounts. Despite the fact that "
"crocodiles are both larger and stronger than alligators, the fatalities due "
"to the transition are surprisingly few. This is because any dwarf that has "
"managed to survive this long has proven themsleves to be one of the most "
"cunning and deadly of all the dwarvish riders."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Crystal_Master, race=AE_fut_brungar_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Crystal_Master.cfg:5
msgid "Crystal Master"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Crystal_Master, race=AE_fut_brungar_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Crystal_Master.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"The Crystal Masters are very few, but legends of their power are still "
"widespread. It is said that a single Crystal Master and a few of his "
"strongest disciples were able to destroy an army of several hundred all by "
"themselves. While their mighty hammers are hard to weild in the waters by "
"normal Brungar, due to the runes on the hammer as well as the magical power "
"that runs through the veins of the Crystal Master, this Brungar has very "
"little trouble crushing skulls both in the deep caverns of the ocean and on "
"the dry plains."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Crystal_Master.cfg:40
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Astral_Ranger.cfg:31
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Shadow_Raider.cfg:61
msgid "Ice Hammer"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Crystal_Master.cfg:50
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Ice_Apprentice.cfg:49
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Ocean_Apprentice.cfg:35
msgid "Ice Shard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Dwarvish_Hunter, race=AE_fut_brungar_race
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Dwarvish_Hunter.cfg:5
msgid "Dwarvish Hunter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Dwarvish_Hunter, race=AE_fut_brungar_race
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Dwarvish_Hunter.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
" \n"
"The Hunter class was one of the first to be established after the Brungar "
"separated from their knalgan ancestors. As such, they have become the "
"backbone of the Brungar and act both as their primary source of food and as "
"the backbone of their military. While the Dwarvish Hunters are still novices "
"in the art of hunting, they are eager to better learn from their master how "
"to hunt, so that they may have more food for their family. They yearn for the"
" day when they will be skilled enough to fell cuttlefish single-handedly and "
"sacrifice the mighty beast to their god."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Dwarvish_Huntsman, race=AE_fut_brungar_race
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Dwarvish_Huntsman.cfg:5
msgid "Dwarvish Huntsman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Dwarvish_Huntsman, race=AE_fut_brungar_race
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Dwarvish_Huntsman.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"After much experience in the wild hunting prey for food, and also in the "
"great battles of the Brungar. Dwarvish Hunstman are far more skilled then the"
" novice hunters they once were. They have discovered that through the use of "
"many long blades of dried sea weed strung together they can create a net that"
" helps to slow down their prey making it easier to slaughter. While Hunters "
"may be the main force of the Brungar army, gaining enough experience to "
"consider them to be Huntsman is a very difficult task since speed of hunting "
"prey is needed rather then bulky brawn which slows them down, yet also makes "
"them prime tagets for hard hitting foes."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Dwarvish_HuntsMaster, race=AE_fut_brungar_race
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Dwarvish_HuntsMaster.cfg:5
msgid "Dwarvish HuntsMaster"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Dwarvish_HuntsMaster, race=AE_fut_brungar_race
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Dwarvish_HuntsMaster.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"Attaining the title HuntsMaster is the highest achievement that any Dwarvish "
"Hunter can hope to achieve-and few enough do. Most Hunters simply do not "
"possess the skill necessary or stamina to be awarded this title. With their "
"mighty spears and strong nets, HuntMasters are the pride of any community and"
" many tales are told of their perils, some of which are immensely tall, while"
" others bear great truth."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Experienced_Tamer, race=AE_fut_brungar_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Experienced_Tamer.cfg:5
msgid "Experienced Tamer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Experienced_Tamer, race=AE_fut_brungar_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Experienced_Tamer.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"After they have managed to capture, tame, and train a fierce creature to "
"fight beside them, Amateur Tamers are called Experienced Tamers, for as their"
" name says, they are experienced. They can put their training to the test and"
" set out to conquer the creatures of legend that caused many to join their "
"ranks. The glory of capturing mighty beasts is looked down upon by none, and "
"great rewards and honors are bestowed upon those that manage to do so."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Expert_Tamer, race=AE_fut_brungar_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Expert_Tamer.cfg:5
msgid "Expert Tamer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Expert_Tamer, race=AE_fut_brungar_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Expert_Tamer.cfg:21
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"The stories of the Expert Tamers are legendary! These are the Brungar who "
"have not only managed to capture and train one of the lesser beasts to fight "
"alongside them, but also the mighty beasts. Be it the water serpent or cuttle"
" fish, these Brungar have managed to train them to do their bidding. The "
"ranks of the Brungar army swells with the catches of these wonderous "
"warriors. It was the Expert tamers of old which first brought the creatures "
"like the sea turtle and the crab to fight alongside themselves. Often will "
"the Expert tamers turn the tide of the battle with their precisional whips "
"and army of beasts."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Giant_Crab, race=monster
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Giant_Crab.cfg:5
msgid "Giant Crab"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Giant_Crab, race=monster
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Giant_Crab.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"The Brungar use an unknown magic to haste the growth of the crabs into beasts"
" of destruction; upon the complete growth of such a behemoth, the army uses "
"it for defense and hunting. These titanic arthropods are often used as living"
" siege engines in wartime, capable of cleaving through an army of enemies "
"without so much of a scratch due to their natural armor. Their skill in using"
" water blasts has become as deadly as the most accurate elven snipers."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Giant_Sea_Turtle, race=monster
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Giant_Sea_Turtle.cfg:5
msgid "Giant Sea Turtle"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Giant_Sea_Turtle, race=monster
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Giant_Sea_Turtle.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"A legend states that once, in the old days of Wesnoth, an island appeared out"
" of nowhere off the coast of a certain wealthy baron. Intrigued, the baron "
"deployed a fleet to investigate the appearing. Three moons later, the humans "
"realized that the Island was getting no closer. When the boats accelerated, "
"the Island turned around and attacked the boats. The one boat that managed to"
" get back to the coast relayed his tale of a huge turtle, apparently "
"millennia old and the size of an island. Encouraged by these and similar "
"fables, the Brungar have strived to use magic for the enlargement of turtles "
"to gargantuan sizes, and in doing so turning them into monsters of war, able "
"to smash the strongest battleship to splinters."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Harpoonier, race=AE_fut_brungar_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Harpoonier.cfg:5
msgid "Harpoonier"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Harpoonier, race=AE_fut_brungar_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Harpoonier.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
" \n"
"Having descended below the waves, the Brungar left their gunpowder weapons "
"behind - yet the blue depths house many thick-skinned terrors best brought "
"down from afar. To that end, crafty dwarven hands created the harpoon gun, "
"capable of hurling heavy spears with astounding force and speed, be it "
"underwater or on dry land. The harpooniers form a prestigious part of the "
"Brungar forces, toting their heavy guns with abundant machismo and elitism; "
"their marksmanship and hunting contests attract much public attention, and "
"the winners become celebrities amongst their peers."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Harpoonier.cfg:26
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Harpoon_Guard.cfg:27
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Harpoon_Specialist.cfg:28
msgid "Harpoon Spear"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Harpoonier.cfg:35
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Harpoon_Guard.cfg:37
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Harpoon_Specialist.cfg:37
msgid "Harpoon Cannon"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Harpoon_Guard, race=AE_fut_brungar_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Harpoon_Guard.cfg:5
msgid "Harpoon Guard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Harpoon_Guard, race=AE_fut_brungar_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Harpoon_Guard.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
" \n"
"The mounted heads of a myriad of creatures, from sea serpents to orc "
"chieftains, adorn the walls of the abodes of the most experienced "
"harpooniers. In their decades of service, they have faced the most dreaded "
"foes and brought them down with the impressive power of their weapons. These "
"have been customized to the point where only their owners knows how to "
"maintain and use them, finely tuned for the best possible performance. To the"
" young Brungar, the Big Game Hunters are like figures of legend - their aim "
"supernatural, their trophy-adorned armor awe-inspiring, even the simple act "
"of carrying their colossal guns a heroic feat on its own."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Harpoon_Specialist, race=AE_fut_brungar_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Harpoon_Specialist.cfg:5
msgid "Harpoon Specialist"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Harpoon_Specialist, race=AE_fut_brungar_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Harpoon_Specialist.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
" \n"
"Nobody can teach you to use the heavy and fickle harpoon gun to its full "
"potential - it is an acquired skill that takes years to master. The Harpoon "
"Specialists are elite Harpooniers, the creme de la creme; few can discern the"
" effects of currents and the target's movements on the shot better.\n"
"Each is also a tinkerer in his own right, modifying his weapon for greater "
"reliability, accuracy and power whenever he can; the veterans trade "
"improvement tricks like a valuable commodity.\n"
"Meanwhile, the foes of the Brungar have learnt to fear the view of rows of "
"large-bore muzzles pointed their way - at least those who have had the "
"opportunity to learn from their mistakes."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Herbalist, race=AE_fut_brungar_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Herbalist.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"The compassion and empathy that are necessary for a responsible practice of "
"medicine do not come easily to the gruff and taciturn dwarves; those who "
"display these rare attributes join the ranks of the Herbalists, harvesting "
"the abundant and varied underwater flora for natural remedies and brewing "
"wondrous concoctions under the stern supervision of their elders. Following a"
" strict moral code, most herbalists reject notions of personal gain and "
"dedicate their lives to the pursuit of knowledge, their prestige based upon "
"the number and potency of miraculous brews they have mastered. With little "
"stomach for combat and lacking the martial skills that come only from long "
"hours of drill, the Herbalists still venture out to the battlefield to save "
"lives where they can, heedless of the danger - for in the most crucial cases,"
" every second matters."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Herbicider, race=AE_fut_brungar_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Herbicider.cfg:5
msgid "Herbicider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Herbicider, race=AE_fut_brungar_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Herbicider.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"Those Brungar who excell in the working of poisonous vegetation deem to be "
"called Herbicidiers. Unlike their Herbalist brothers, Herbicidiers hunger for"
" battle, armed with their infamous poison tipped spear and vial of fatal "
"toxins. Due to their thirst for battle, they have equipped themselves with "
"better armor both to defend themselves from their enemies as well as their "
"deadly concotions. Although they are not very numerous among the ranks of the"
" Brungar, they are a contingent which are feared by all who are affected by "
"their toxins."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Herbicider.cfg:26
msgid "Toxic Spear"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Herbicider.cfg:39
msgid "Poison Spray"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_High_Council_Elder, race=AE_fut_brungar_race
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\High_Council_Elder.cfg:5
msgid "High Council Elder"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_High_Council_Elder, race=AE_fut_brungar_race
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\High_Council_Elder.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"The rank of High Council Elder is without doubt the pinnacle achievement of "
"any Brungar's lifetime, for the task of even being considered for this post "
"is a laborious and time consuming process. Their deeds in battle are "
"unfathomable and are often great lords who are given the task of looking over"
" great sections of the king's domain. Their armor and great trident are made "
"from the strongest metal found in their seas and tinted red to make their "
"presence on the battlefield easily discovered and to spread fear throughout "
"the enemy ranks. Although they are usually higher in age then the members of "
"the lower rings of the council, they are still great sturdy Brungar whose "
"leadership capabilities are exceeded by none."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_High_Council_Member, race=AE_fut_brungar_race
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\High_Council_Member.cfg:5
msgid "High Council Member"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_High_Council_Member, race=AE_fut_brungar_race
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\High_Council_Member.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"Nearly at the top of the Tri-Point Council are the High Council Members. All "
"members of the High Council are undoubtably some of the most skilled of their"
" generation, in both the use of a trident as well as in politics. These "
"overlords take on a great weight of responsibility when they are given their "
"first real chance to prove their true leadership capabilites for they are "
"given a small lake town or ocean village to reign over. To both lead their "
"armies in times of war, and lead them to prosper in times of peace."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Ice_Apprentice, race=AE_fut_brungar_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Ice_Apprentice.cfg:5
msgid "Ice Apprentice"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Ice_Apprentice, race=AE_fut_brungar_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Ice_Apprentice.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"Some Ocean Apprentices choose to go a different path. The Ice Apprentices are"
" the more militant of their fellow mages, since they make the water into a "
"weapon by freezing and then sharpening the ice until it is as deadly as most "
"metallic weapons. However, many who oppose the Ice Apprentice don't realize "
"the skill involved in making their weapons for before they can take a gander "
"as to what is being done, spikes of ice are impaling their bodies. Only the "
"incredibly fleet of foot and mind can avoid their deadly weapons, and even "
"they have trouble doing so for very long."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Ice_Apprentice.cfg:39
msgid "Ice Staff"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Leviathan, race=monster
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Leviathan.cfg:5
msgid "Leviathan"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Leviathan, race=monster
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Leviathan.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"Most ancient creatures are eldritch horrors, ancient antediluvians, the "
"culminations of legends. Monsters that stalk the night. Behemoths whom no "
"sane being has ever encountered, and survived mentally intact to relate his "
"story. Avatars of destruction, older than time itself, living only for the "
"chaos it creates. Mysterious creatures whose origins and motivations are "
"alike unknown. The Leviathan is not any one of the above categories. "
"Leviathans, despite their imposing size, power, and name, are quite a gentle "
"and trustworthy caste of turtles. The Brungar tamers that are held "
"responsible for maintaining the creature's health understand, and know, the "
"build and mindset of the creature, from each scratch of the Leviathan's "
"imposing, nigh-impenetrable shell to all of its ancient, slow considerations "
"floating through its cranium. The Leviathans are always the focal point of "
"work in the Brungar culture, only the best of food, purified water, herbal "
"accelerators of growth, and other consumables go toward these treasured war "
"machines. Indeed, the newest tenders of the Leviathans find that the "
"creatures, though majestic, are something of a thousand-ton bother in the "
"subjects of hygiene and clinical need. Leviathans, though extremely difficult"
" to care for due to their size, are deadly on the battlefield, as one would "
"probably expect from a siege engine of their size. Their flippers, though "
"admittedly not of much use propelling them on land, can shatter the strongest"
" of fortifications with one sweeping blow, the armored plates that compose "
"its shell can withstand the strongest of physical and magical attacks. They "
"are a sight to be feared by all who would dare to stand in the path of such a"
" behemoth. The creature, when at sea, is easily mistaken for an island, this "
"attribute gives them a useful advantage in stealth, for they have been known "
"to ferry thousands of their stout masters across an unforgiving sea, to "
"vanquish all enemies before them."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=ranged
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Leviathan.cfg:49
msgid "Aqua Blast"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Ocean_Apprentice, race=AE_fut_brungar_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Ocean_Apprentice.cfg:5
msgid "Ocean Apprentice"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Ocean_Apprentice, race=AE_fut_brungar_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Ocean_Apprentice.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"Some Brungar decide that they would rather learn how to control their "
"surroundings-the liquid water-rather than a mount. The Ocean Apprentice is "
"the most basic of this, utilizing compressed jets of water to knock their "
"opponents into submission. If their enemies happen to come to close to them, "
"they rely on their fists to knock them back to where their powerful water "
"jets can blast them back. As they learn more and more about the water around "
"them, they come closer to deciding to use water to its fullest, or converting"
" it to another deadly weapon."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=ranged
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Ocean_Apprentice.cfg:47
msgid "water jet"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Overgrown_Crab, race=monster
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Overgrown_Crab.cfg:5
msgid "Overgrown Crab"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Overgrown_Crab, race=monster
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Overgrown_Crab.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"The Brungar use their skill in taming by growing the crab to abnormal sizes. "
"These crabs have begun to exceed the norm size of their cousins, and can move"
" faster and faster than the regular crabs. Most Overgrown Crabs have been "
"trained and used by the navy for long periods of time; through their tenure "
"as beasts of war, they have been trained in the elegant and fine arts of "
"slicing humans in half with sharp pincers. The water-launching capabilities "
"of the crabs have also become more efficient due to experience."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Practitioner, race=AE_fut_brungar_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Practitioner.cfg:5
msgid "Practitioner"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Practitioner, race=AE_fut_brungar_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Practitioner.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"Having treated hundreds of patients, the Practitioners have a knowledge as "
"broad as it is deep; well-acquaintened with a plethora of maladies, they "
"spend as much time teaching their successors and delving deeper into the "
"secrets of the healing art, as they do treating the sick and wounded. A high "
"Practitioner does not have to worry about base matters such as gold, for his "
"hard-earned acclaim and respect from all social classes means the mighty and "
"the wealthy compete to show him their appreciation and goodwill; for it is so"
" that a high Practitioner decides over life and death simply by choosing who "
"is worthy to recieve the services of his precious few apprentices, and who "
"shall go without aid. Having spent their lives in scholarly pursuit, the "
"Practitioners never trained in the arts of combat, yet can use their "
"knowledge of the body's workings to great effect, reluctantly so.Having "
"treated hundreds of patients, the Practitioners have a knowledge as broad as "
"it is deep; well-acquaintened with a plethora of maladies, they spend as much"
" time teaching their successors and delving deeper into the secrets of the "
"healing art, as they do treating the sick and wounded. A high Practitioner "
"does not have to worry about base matters such as gold, for his hard-earned "
"acclaim and respect from all social classes means the mighty and the wealthy "
"compete to show him their appreciation and goodwill; for it is so that a high"
" Practitioner decides over life and death simply by choosing who is worthy to"
" recieve the services of his precious few apprentices, and who shall go "
"without aid. Having spent their lives in scholarly pursuit, the Practitioners"
" never trained in the arts of combat, yet can use their knowledge of the "
"body's workings to great effect, reluctantly so."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Sea_Turtle, race=monster
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Sea_Turtle.cfg:5
msgid "Sea Turtle"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Sea_Turtle, race=monster
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Sea_Turtle.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"These turtles, full grown and capable of decapitating a small human in one "
"bite, have proven themselves in battle. The same magics used to accelerate "
"the growth of the crabs are also used on these reptiles, growing them until "
"they are easily mistaken for buildings. This is seen as the peak of "
"achievement by the turtles, and all who achieve this honor become the most "
"vigilant guardians of the Brungar."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Sting_Ray, race=monster
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Sting_Ray.cfg:5
msgid "Sting Ray"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Sting_Ray, race=monster
#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Sting_Ray_Deep, race=monster
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Sting_Ray.cfg:18
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Sting_Ray_Deep.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"Training a stingray to be of any use in battle is a challenging, and "
"dangerous, task. However, it is very rewarding if it is completed. The "
"stingray is one of the the most deadly creatures in the Brungar's arsenal if "
"fought in the water, since they can often not only out-manuever their "
"opponents, but are quite strong with the use of their natural poisonous "
"stinger. Although the Herbicidiers could use Sting Ray posion in their vile "
"concoctions, the death toll of those extracting the venom was catastrophicly "
"higher then those that they used the poison on. Needless to say, the Sting "
"Rays are a force to be reckoned with, and are never truly tame."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Sting_Ray.cfg:29
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Sting_Ray_Deep.cfg:30
msgid "Bash"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Sting_Ray_Deep, race=monster
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Sting_Ray_Deep.cfg:5
msgid "Deep Sting Ray"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Toxin_Specialist, race=AE_fut_brungar_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Toxin_Specialist.cfg:5
msgid "Toxin Specialist"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Toxin_Specialist, race=AE_fut_brungar_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Toxin_Specialist.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"Toxin Specialists are extremely rare, partially due to the time and "
"dedication that it takes to achieve their vast knowledge of deadly poisons, "
"but mostly because they are killed by the very poisons that they sought to "
"understand. Those with the brains to avoid their own concotions are guarded "
"well and strike only at the oppertune time. Their great spear drips with the "
"poison from their vial as they await the impalement of their next victim, "
"often slightly to eagerly."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Toxin_Specialist.cfg:33
msgid "Poison Spear"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Toxin_Specialist.cfg:46
msgid "Toxic Cloud"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Undecided_Student, race=AE_fut_brungar_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Undecided_Student.cfg:5
msgid "Undecided Student"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Undecided_Student, race=AE_fut_brungar_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Undecided_Student.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"'Only though adversity does a dwarf grow.' The Brungar have taken this saying"
" to heart, and rarely is it more true than for those who try to master the "
"fickle runes to command the waves. When faced with the terrors of war and "
"reality of combat, the grain is separated from the chaff, and those who "
"emerge from their first trial successful can join the ranks of the scholars "
"under the tutelage of a revered master of herb lore or water magic. The "
"Undecided Student has not been given runes and thus has no magic at his "
"command, but strives with proverbial dwarven tenacity, beating at the "
"dwarves' enemies with fists and rocks if it need be. Yet some would rather "
"cure the damage of combat rather than join in it so they seek to learn of the"
" herbs of the land and sea. While they may be rather frail, he will no let "
"anyone stop him from joining the fray, for that is the furnace where dwarves "
"are made; it will not take long for them to prove their worth."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=ranged
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Undecided_Student.cfg:35
#: .\units\ME_units\refugees\0-refugee.cfg:34
#: .\units\ME_units\refugees\f1-rabble.cfg:35
#: .\units\MiE_units\treefolk\1_Bark_Guise.cfg:45
#: .\units\MiE_units\treefolk\2_Bark_Elder.cfg:49
#: .\units\MiE_units\treefolk\3_Sentry_Bark.cfg:50
msgid "rock"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Wave_Master, race=AE_fut_brungar_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Wave_Master.cfg:5
msgid "Wave Master"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Wave_Master, race=AE_fut_brungar_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Wave_Master.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"Those who advance to the rank of Wave Masters are true masters of their "
"environment, and as such, they can summon huge waves that can crush their "
"opponents simply by the sheer wieght of the water. They owe much of their "
"success to the one who discovered the benefits of place water runes on "
"paddles. For with the use of these runic paddles they can manipulate the "
"waves almost with ease. And to keep from crushing themselves with their own "
"waves, the Wave Master continues to use his harpoon if an enemy gets to "
"close."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Wave_Master.cfg:27
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Wave_Rider.cfg:26
#: .\units\ME_units\tribe\e2-fishingboat.cfg:59
msgid "Harpoon"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=ranged
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Wave_Master.cfg:37
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Wave_Rider.cfg:36
msgid "Wave"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Wave_Rider, race=AE_fut_brungar_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Wave_Rider.cfg:5
msgid "Wave Rider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_brungar_Wave_Rider, race=AE_fut_brungar_race, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\brungar\Wave_Rider.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"After a Brungar gains a high level of control over the water, they advance to"
" the rank of Wave Rider. They are able to summon large, fast-moving waves to "
"slam into any opponent that enters into their domain. They now also wield a "
"harpoon instead of their fists, because it better serves its dual "
"purpose-hunting food and hunting intruders. The Wave Riders are often among "
"entertainers as well as soldiers for them riding the waves on their runic "
"paddles is truly an awe-inspiring sight and thrills many to the bone."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_Nordhris_Apprentice, race=AE_fut_race_Nordhris, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Apprentice.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"In the harsh cold of the north, simply staying alive is a challenge. This is "
"why the Nordhris have learned to combine herbal remedies, though herbs are "
"scarce in the arctic weather, with magical healing. Apprentices have only "
"just begun to learn the healing arts, and, though they are not the most "
"effective healers, know how to use herbs to their maximum potency. This lets "
"them be reduce the cost of ingredients. Apprentices are also much in tune "
"with the cold of the north, and can call down violent gusts of arctic wind "
"upon their enemies, even in the warmest and calmest atmospheres. Apprentices "
"and their masters are the most used to cold weather, and are comfortable "
"enough to walk barefoot in the snow."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Apprentice.cfg:35
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Warlock.cfg:37
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Witch_Doctor.cfg:35
msgid "Frost"
msgstr ""

