msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_Nordhris_Northern_Fighter, race=AE_fut_race_Nordhris, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Northern_Fighter.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"Only the truly lucky or the truly skilled survive even a few battles as a "
"Braveheart, however, those who do are automatically given a position of "
"leadership among their peers. Their responsibilities range from training new "
"recruits in the time in between battles to making sure that the Bravehearts "
"are given adequate (sp?) food and weapons. Despite these responsibilities, "
"the simple fact that they survived this long is enough to inspire their "
"company to fight harder in the hope that they too could survive longer than a"
" couple years."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_Nordhris_Greatbow, race=AE_fut_race_Nordhris
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Northern_Greatbow.cfg:5
msgid "Northern Greatbow"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_Nordhris_Strongbow, race=AE_fut_race_Nordhris
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Northern_Strongbow.cfg:5
msgid "Northern Strongbow"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_Nordhris_Northern_Warlord, race=AE_fut_race_Nordhris, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Northern_Warlord.cfg:5
msgid "Northern Warlord"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_Nordhris_Northern_Warlord, race=AE_fut_race_Nordhris, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Northern_Warlord.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"Wolfhearts are the few have managed to survive and thrive through decades of "
"service in the most dangerous part of the Nordhris military. As a reward for "
"their unwavering loyalty, devotion, and skill these former peasants are now "
"given command of their own army, as well as a place of honor among even the "
"highest echelons of Nordhris society. Despite their age, these warriors are "
"never content to sit back and let others do all the work for them. They will "
"instead charge into the front lines of battle and proceed to cut down any "
"enemy foolish enough to stand in their path. Their ferocity acts as a beacon "
"of hope for their fellow warriors, all of whom would willingly give their "
"lives to protect their leader, in even the most hopeless of battles."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_Nordhris_Northern_Warrior, race=AE_fut_race_Nordhris, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Northern_Warrior.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"With relentless training and combat having weeded out any who had managed to "
"survive on luck alone, those who still remain alive and in the service of the"
" military are given the rank of Feralheart. Once a Braveheart has reached "
"this rank they are given some land of their own, which distinctively marks "
"their rise in the social hierarchy of the Nordhris - they are now among the "
"low ranking nobility. As such, it is no longer their duty to directly "
"supervise the Bravehearts. They are now responsible for more important tasks "
"such as coordinating strategic efforts with other military leaders on the "
"field and evaluating the performance of their men. This lifestyle does not "
"suit many former Bravehearts, and as a result Feralhearts can often be seen "
"fighting alongside their troops despite their new rank. While some deride "
"this as classic examples of why peasants shouldn't be allowed to join the "
"noble class, a Feralheart's presence does give noticeable benefits on the "
"battlefield in the form of harder fighting and more loyal troops. This causes"
" some generals to covertly encourage Feralhearts to join the battle, and they"
" are rarely disappointed with the results."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_Nordhris_Northguard, race=AE_fut_race_Nordhris, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Northguard.cfg:5
msgid "Northguard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_Nordhris_Northguard, race=AE_fut_race_Nordhris, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Northguard.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
" \n"
"Northguards are the elite of the northmen. northguards are the vanguard of "
"the Nordhis army, and are often sent forwards to lead weaker troops in battle"
" because of their combat experience. Since the fatality rate in northguards "
"is lower than that of northmen, some northguards go into the false assumption"
" that their superior armor will keep them safe and that their troops are duty"
" bound to protect them, and fall into a false sense of security. These are "
"normally the first to be killed in combat. All northguards aspire towards the"
" day that they are granted the title of warlord, when they will be given "
"command of a larger portion of the Nordhis army, and admitted into the "
"Nordhis council."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Northguard.cfg:36
msgid "Superb Bow"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_Nordhris_Northman, race=AE_fut_race_Nordhris, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Northman.cfg:5
msgid "Northman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_Nordhris_Northman, race=AE_fut_race_Nordhris, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Northman.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
" \n"
"When the leaders of the Nordhis call their people to arms, every able bodied "
"man picks up a weapon. Those that have no great skill in magic, healing or "
"archery, those that have no exceptional stealth and those not brave or "
"foolish enough to throw themselves into the head of the battle, that weapon "
"is the sword. Dubbed by their enemies as northmen, because of the direction "
"from which they tend to attack, these warriors are more at home on the snowy "
"tundra than they are on a grassy plain. The wolf pelts they customarily wear "
"are used for warmth as well as to intimidate their enemies. Stronger than "
"most bravehearts, these soldiers are some of the most resilient recruits in a"
" Nordhis army, but are less eager to fight than their courageous and "
"occasionally foolish counterparts and thus demand more money for their "
"service. Though less skilled than most warriors from other cultures, northmen"
" tend to be more numerous, and use strength in numbers to overwhelm their "
"enemy. Northmen fight with a sword in hand and somewhat proficient with the "
"hunting bow, which is used to hunt down large game during peacetime."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Northman.cfg:36
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Slaughterer.cfg:59
msgid "Hunting Bow"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_Nordhris_Oathsworn, race=AE_fut_race_Nordhris, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Oathsworn.cfg:5
msgid "Oathsworn"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_Nordhris_Oathsworn, race=AE_fut_race_Nordhris, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Oathsworn.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"Once a northguard has served for several years,and are admitted into the "
"Nordhis council, they have to take an oath taken in blood that they will do "
"whatever they can to protect the Nordhis people. Even close to death they'd "
"so try to defend their people by increasing the ferocity of their attacks. "
"Only death will stop those brave soldiers from fulfilling their oaths."
msgstr ""

#. [attacks]
#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Oathsworn.cfg:37
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Savage.cfg:47
msgid "frenzy"
msgstr ""

#. [attacks]
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Oathsworn.cfg:38
msgid "The more wounded this unit is the more attacks he gets"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Oathsworn.cfg:45
msgid "Majestic Bow"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_Nordhris_Poacher, race=AE_fut_race_Nordhris, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Poacher.cfg:5
msgid "Poacher"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_Nordhris_Poacher, race=AE_fut_race_Nordhris, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Poacher.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"Prowlers are the hunters-in-training of the Nordhris, as they have yet to "
"master the customary hunting style of those who kill wild game. Their hunting"
" style is rather unusual by the standards of most outsiders: they prefer to "
"attack their prey directly instead of taking it down with a bow from a "
"distance. In order to accomplish this, the Prowlers are in the process of "
"learning how to completely conceal their presence from the animals around "
"them so that they may ambush and kill their prey with ease. Still, many have "
"laughed at this saying that it changes nothing when compared to the ease of "
"hunting with a bow, that is until they stop laughing and realize that they "
"are apparently alone in the middle of an open tundra."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_Nordhris_Prowler, race=AE_fut_race_Nordhris, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Prowler.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"After sufficient training, an Arctic Prowler will be allowed to take a test "
"of their hunting and survival skills to determine if they are worthy to be "
"recognized as a master hunter. The test itself is simple and and "
"straightforward: They must go into the wilderness alone and survive for one "
"month. After one month has passed, they must return with at least 40 animal "
"hides taken from animals they have killed with their own weapons. However, "
"there is a catch. If they are unable to survive for a whole month, come back "
"more than a week afterwards, or return without at least 40 hides, they are "
"assigned to their master as an apprentice for the next 10 years and will not "
"be allowed to advance beyond apprenticeship until that time has passed. The "
"repercussions of failure, while harsh, assure that only those who are truly "
"prepared are able to become master hunters. As for those who do pass the "
"test, it is traditional for the family to hold a celebration in his or her "
"honor with an animal caught by the new Ravager. In the mean time, the former "
"Prowler gets to enjoy their new found prestige as well as adjust to their "
"role in society."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_Nordhris_Reaver, race=AE_fut_race_Nordhris, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Reaver.cfg:5
msgid "Reaver"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_Nordhris_Reaver, race=AE_fut_race_Nordhris, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Reaver.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"Of all the available positions in the Nordhris army, reavers are perhaps the "
"hardest to qualify for. To become a reaver, one must be almost as fast as a "
"snowrunner and as stealthy and strong as an arctic prowler. Most importantly,"
" however, reavers must master the kusari, a hand scythe with a ball and chain"
" attached. In combat, reavers have two roles: hiding in the dark behind the "
"enemy to prevent a retreat, and chasing after those who do succeed in "
"fleeing. A favorite reaver tactic is to entangle an enemy from afar using the"
" ball and chain end of their weapon, and then slicing them to ribbons with "
"the bladed side."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_Nordhris_Slaughterer, race=AE_fut_race_Nordhris, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Slaughterer.cfg:5
msgid "Slaughterer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_Nordhris_Slaughterer, race=AE_fut_race_Nordhris, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Slaughterer.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"Those scouts who stay behind enemy lines, or are cut off from the main army "
"become slaughterers - one man army. Preying on enemies who venture dep into "
"the woods, they also don't need to run as much as was required by their "
"former occupation so they have lost their ability to run like other Northern "
"scouts. They also become more beast-like due to the environment they have to "
"live in to survive. They rely on surprise attacks and getting the first hit."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Slaughterer.cfg:47
msgid "Hunting Spear"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_Nordhris_Snowrunner, race=AE_fut_race_Nordhris, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Snowrunner.cfg:5
msgid "Snowrunner"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_Nordhris_Snowrunner, race=AE_fut_race_Nordhris, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Snowrunner.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
" \n"
"Not many can move swiftly with all the snow, slush and ice that accumulates "
"across the land, but the Snowrunners, as their title suggests, can run over "
"these elements swiftly and with ease. With their spear in hand and the bow "
"only an arms reach away the snow runners can just as easily plug a hole in "
"the lines or kill of an enemy as take a message miles in just a few hours."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_Nordhris_Tribal_Sage, race=AE_fut_race_Nordhris, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Tribal_Sage.cfg:5
msgid "Tribal Sage"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_Nordhris_Tribal_Sage, race=AE_fut_race_Nordhris, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Tribal_Sage.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"After a frenetic shaman has reached a certain level of skill and power, they "
"are deemed worthy of the title 'Sage'. These sages are the both the most "
"devoted and the most powerful of their shaman brethren, and have continued "
"their training to the exclusion of nearly everything else. As such, they are "
"now easily capable of taking down nearly any undead that they come across be "
"it the minions or their master. This single-mindedness has cost them though, "
"as they are rather easily killed by any opponent who is not undead. Despite "
"this weakness, they are highly respected within Nordhris society and are "
"given the dual tasks of educating new recruits - and executing any found to "
"be experimenting with the dark arts."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_Nordhris_Warlock, race=AE_fut_race_Nordhris, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Warlock.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"This is the story of Sodd, a swordsman. In the midst of battle with the "
"Nordhris, Sodd somehow managed to break through enemy ranks. He caught sight "
"of the injured enemy commander, unguarded, except for his healer. Sodd rushed"
" forwards to deliver the finishing blow, when, suddenly a snowstorm "
"surrounded him. Sodd could see neither friend nor foe through the thick "
"flurry of flakes, but still pressed forwards towards his target. After what "
"felt like hours, frostbitten Sodd saw a figure in the distance. Rushing "
"towards what he thought was the enemy leader, he slashed at the figure, "
"missed, and was killed by a staff blow to the head. Sodd was unlucky enough "
"to happen across a fully realized Nordhris healer, known as a warlock, "
"healing his troop leader. Not only are warlocks master healers, but they can "
"also conjure up miniature blizzards that can freeze their enemies to death. "
"Warlocks also have some experience using their staves in melee combat, and "
"can wield them surprisingly well."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_Nordhris_Wildheart, race=AE_fut_race_Nordhris
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Wildheart.cfg:5
msgid "Wildheart"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_Nordhris_Wildheart, race=AE_fut_race_Nordhris
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Wildheart.cfg:18
msgid ""
"After having fought several battles due to the constant pressure, some "
"bravehearts fall in a trance of battle. They become intoxicated from the view"
" and smell of blood. They stop caring for their own safety, throw away their "
"wooden shields and focus on their fierce attacks.\n"
"\n"
""
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_Nordhris_Wiseman, race=AE_fut_race_Nordhris, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Wiseman.cfg:5
msgid "Wiseman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_Nordhris_Wiseman, race=AE_fut_race_Nordhris, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Wiseman.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"The rank of Wiseman is the highest honor that can be attained, and despite "
"the honor and glory that this title bestows, there are few enough that manage"
" to attain it. The sheer amount of time needed to acquire the necessary skill"
" is hard enough, but the most common reason for not attaining this honor is "
"quite simple: they died before they could be considered for the title. "
"However, those few who do manage to survive will achieve such power and "
"mastery over their art that they can make even a lich's bones rattle with "
"fear."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_Nordhris_Witch_Doctor, race=AE_fut_race_Nordhris, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\Nordhris\Witch_Doctor.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"When an apprentice has gone through many years of training, and proven "
"themselves worthy in combat as warriors who can heal their comrades in arms "
"even in the heat of battle, they are granted the title of witch doctors, and "
"allowed to take on their own apprentices. The name originated when an "
"extremely talented apprentice went south with a Nordhris war tribe, to raid "
"the humans in the warmer regions. While looting, he came across herbs the "
"likes of which where never seen in the arctic. When he returned home, the "
"apprentice used his new herbs to heal so well, he was declared a witch. A "
"common witch doctor philosophy is that experience is the best teacher, and "
"where better to find injured people to cure than in the middle of a "
"battleground? Though, of course, witch doctors aren't often seen in combat: "
"when the councilors request a healer for war, this is the argument they use "
"to convince their apprentices to go. Witch doctors normally work in Nordhris "
"villages, where they heal the injured and the sick, for a price, of course. "
"Witch doctors can both heal better and summon storms better than their "
"apprentices, and are sometimes hired by richer warriors as private physicians"
" in combat."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_Nordhris_Wolfheart, race=AE_fut_race_Nordhris
