#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Battle_Seer, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Battle_Seer.cfg:5
msgid "Battle Seer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Battle_Seer, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Battle_Seer.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"With their strength growing with each battle, the Battle Seer's are one of "
"the deadliest foes in the great Welkin Army. But because their time is spent "
"more in training with their physical weapons instead of practicing the art of"
" healing, Aten and  Thoth have taken away much of their magic as well as the "
"ability to use the Power of Thoth as effectively as they once could. They  "
"can still cure ailments such as poison but they cannot heal wounded soldiers "
"as they once did. The Battle Seers, however,  do not fret over their loss, "
"instead they fight on to win great honor and valor! With their power of "
"healing taken away and  their great glory on the battlefield, some of these "
"Welkin have become somewhat arrogant and are often avoided by other  Welkin."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Battle_Seer.cfg:30
msgid "female^Battle Seer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Deadeye, race=AE_fut_welkin
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_refugees_Deadeye, race=AE_mrc_refugees_race
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Deadeye.cfg:5
#: .\units\ME_units\refugees\h3-deadeye.cfg:5
msgid "Deadeye"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Deadeye, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Deadeye.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
" As the only ones to continue to use a bow in the Army of Thoth, the Deadeye "
"are the greatest marksman of their kind. With the eyes of the elves these "
"Welkin can pinpoint precisely where they wish to strike and hit it with "
"little difficulty. They have not forsaken their god though and continue to "
"follow Thoth with devotion and prayer. As a result, they have grown quite "
"skillful at using the Power of Thoth. Although not as powerful as the Astral "
"Ranger and not nearly as powerful as the Doyens, the Deadeyes are a foe to be"
" reckoned with."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Deadeye.cfg:25
msgid "female^Deadeye"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Doyen, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Doyen.cfg:5
msgid "Doyen"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Doyen, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Doyen.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"With the wisdom aquired through their studying and practice, the Doyen's "
"healing power is strong. However, their skill in the Power of Thoth has also "
"greatly increased as they strive for the peak of the road to Thoth. These  "
"Welkin are ever seeking to become Patriarchs of their gods. They fight "
"bravely for their people and have been the wisest advisors of their king or "
"queen. Since they still follow both Thoth and Aten, they are looked on with "
"distain. However, because of their great power and wisdom, they are not "
"shunned as the lesser sages of their order are."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Doyen.cfg:27
msgid "female^Doyen"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Elder_Sage, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Elder_Sage.cfg:5
msgid "Elder Sage"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Elder_Sage, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Elder_Sage.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"As the Sage's ability grows and his wisdom exceeds that of the other sage's "
"he will have approached the point of becoming an Elder Sage. These Welkin "
"study hard and have learned ways to twist and manipulate water that most find"
" inconceivable. Though a healer, the Elder Sage can be a fierce foe. These "
"Welkin, though an imposing threat on the field of battle, are best left  out "
"of the fray because of the frailty of their body. When they are not in "
"battle, they are often found healing those who have fought in battles or "
"curing the ailments of those with diseases."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Elder_Sage.cfg:28
msgid "female^Elder Sage"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Flurry, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Flurry.cfg:5
msgid "Flurry"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Flurry, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Flurry.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"The Welkin who are called Flurrys have been given their name due to their "
"amazing speed and power over the surrounding air. One of the oddest of the "
"Welkin, they follow the sun but have chosen a different path than most. In "
"order to harness the power of the air as either a weapon or a method of "
"transportation, Flurries must be able to use their hands. As such, they are "
"equipped with claws that allow full use of the hands but also give Flurries "
"another method of attack and defence. Holding true to their heritage, they "
"use their speed and stay away from a fight whenever possible. However, with "
"enough experience these Welkin are still to be feared and are not to be "
"underestimated."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Flurry.cfg:24
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Dust_Faerie.cfg:44
msgid "female^Flurry"
msgstr ""

