#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Lord.cfg:84
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Mentor.cfg:83
msgid "Sunburst"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Golden_Guard, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Golden_Guard.cfg:5
msgid "Golden Guard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Golden_Guard, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Golden_Guard.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
" \n"
"Considered to be the most steadfast soldier in the entire Army of Aten, the "
"Golden Guard has amassed enough strength as to be able to wield two maces. "
"And since the Golden Guards can't use their wings anyway, they are equipped "
"with impressive  armor that is almost impenetrable without decreasing their "
"already limited mobility. They are not usually found on the front lines, due "
"to their restricted mobility, but rather they are usually found as Honor "
"Guards or protecting precious convoys."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Grand_Flyer, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Grand_Flyer.cfg:5
msgid "Grand Flyer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Grand_Flyer, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Grand_Flyer.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
" \n"
"The Grand Flyer is one of the deadliest warriors in the entire Army of Aten. "
"As a master in the art of the ring blade, the Grand Flyer turns even the "
"mightiest warriors blood cold and strikes terror into all those that look "
"upon him. These Welkin have an advantage over most of their enemies due to "
"their impressive speed and incredible power. In order to achieve this power, "
"increased training is required, but through this the Grand Flyer has achieved"
" great strength and honor."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Grand_Flyer.cfg:29
msgid "female^Grand Flyer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Guardian_of_Day, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Guardian_of_Day.cfg:5
msgid "Guardian of Day"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Guardian_of_Day, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Guardian_of_Day.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
" \n"
"The Guardian of Day's great dexterity contradicts the popular thought that "
"all Welkin are frail. Trained to use a mace these Welkin epitomize power. "
"with the agility of the Welkin, and the strength from their training, these "
"Guardians are a force to be reckoned with. although these Welkin possess "
"amazing strength, they are also quite agile, however are also so heavy that "
"their wings cannot hold them aloft. Like their counterparts, the Luna "
"Protectors, the Guardians of Day keep their wings in their armor to keep them"
" from being damaged. Due to the limited reach of the mace, they have been "
"trained in the art of the sun, granted to them from Aten, to ward of distant "
"enemies."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Hierarch_of_Aten, race=AE_fut_welkin, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Hierarch_of_Aten.cfg:5
msgid "Hierarch of Aten"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Hierarch_of_Aten, race=AE_fut_welkin, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Hierarch_of_Aten.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"The Hierarchs are the highest possible position to hold for those who follow "
"Aten. They show no outward flame but rather carry a great staff that "
"signifies the unity of the Welkin in their worship of both Aten and Thoth. "
"This does not grant any strange power but is merely symbolism to show that "
"their sociecties can connect. Although rarely found on the field of battle, "
"the Hierarchs of Aten possess tremendous power and are greatly feared. The "
"king therefore often uses Hierarchs not only as advisors but also as "
"diplomats or messengers, hoping to use this intimidation to his advantage."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Hierarch_of_Aten.cfg:62
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\High_Pyroation.cfg:84
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Neophyte.cfg:46
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Pyroation.cfg:54
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Solar_Empyrean.cfg:80
msgid "Flare"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_High_Pyroation, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\High_Pyroation.cfg:5
msgid "High Pyroation"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_High_Pyroation, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\High_Pyroation.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"High Pyroations are the first in their order to take with them a staff for "
"use in battle. It is often thought by younger more immature Welkin that the "
"High Pyroation takes a staff to help him walk due to his age. This, however, "
"is merely a myth. These followers of Aten have also learned that with the "
"controlling of their temper they can better control the fire that rages "
"within them, which allows them to be more articulate and to better advise "
"their Lords. They still study and pray to Aten, not so that they might gain "
"power or honor, but rather because of their wonderous devoutness to their "
"god. These Welkin are still quite frail and cannot withstand the great "
"ferocity of the battlefield but if well protected, they can help change the "
"tide of any battle."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\High_Pyroation.cfg:28
msgid "female^High Pyroation"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Lord, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Lord.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"The Lords of the Welkin are powerful both in standing with the King and "
"strength on the battlefield. They stand as a shining pillar of might to rally"
" the troops and lead them into the fray. Never cowering away from a fight, "
"Lord's are excellent generals. Although not always a general, in order to "
"have the title you must have accumulated enough wealth and power to be "
"granted this name. Therefore one knows that if they fight a Lord, they fight "
"one who has worked long and hard on attaining their standing."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Lord.cfg:25
msgid "female^Lord"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Luna_Protector, race=AE_fut_welkin, gender=female
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Luna_Protector.cfg:5
msgid "Luna Protector"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Luna_Protector, race=AE_fut_welkin, gender=female
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Luna_Protector.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"These are Welkin who have sworn to give their lives to protect the honor of "
"Thoth, and if that means fighting during the day, then so be it. Luna "
"Protectors, unlike the rest of their brethren, have taken the spear as their "
"main weapon and use the power of the moon to attack enemies who are too "
"frightened to approach them. Because of how much training is necessary to "
"fight equally during both night and day, the Luna Protectors are trained from"
" a very young age, before they grow their wings. Because of this they do not "
"fully know how to use their wings and thus cannot fly. Since they do not need"
" their wings they keep them concealed under their armor to prevent them from "
"becoming a weakness."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Mentor, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Mentor.cfg:5
msgid "Mentor"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Mentor, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Mentor.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"Known on the Battlefield to be Welkin of Prowess and for keeping the soldiers"
" under them stern and battle ready, a Mentor is always urging his soldiers on"
" to fight for their god and their queen. These Welkin have taken "
"responsibility over personal ability. With both their progressed skills with "
"the ring blade, the Fire of Aten, and the ability to inspire his troops to a "
"greater level then they ever thought possible, a Mentor is always a great "
"asset to the Army of Aten."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Mentor.cfg:24
msgid "female^Mentor"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Midnight_Stalker, race=AE_fut_welkin, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Midnight_Stalker.cfg:5
msgid "Midnight Stalker"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Midnight_Stalker, race=AE_fut_welkin, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Midnight_Stalker.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"Those that have proven their worth and stealth have been promoted to Midnight"
" Stalker. These Welkin are the 'underground' of the Army of Thoth. They fight"
" from the shadows and have learned when best to strike a fatal blow on a foe."
" The Midnight Stalkers should not be generalized as just spies for they can "
"hold their own on the battlefield, both with the sword and the Power of "
"Thoth. Midnight Stalkers not only fight from the shadows, they become the "
"shadows. If a foe comes across one of these Welkin in the night they very "
"well may be the last thing they see, if they see them at all."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Moonlight_Glider, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Moonlight_Glider.cfg:5
msgid "Moonlight Glider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Moonlight_Glider, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Moonlight_Glider.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"Any Welkin that shows a propensity for stealth and espionage are entered into"
" the order of the Moonlight Gliders. These are the Welkin who are willing "
"forgo the traditional views of honor and valor on the battlefield and instead"
" kill their enemy by any means necessary, whether that be open combat on the "
"battlefield or infiltrating enemy lines and assassinating enemy officers."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Moonlight_Glider.cfg:24
msgid "female^Moonlight Glider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Neophyte, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Neophyte.cfg:5
msgid "Neophyte"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Neophyte, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Neophyte.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"The Neophyte are Welkin that honor Aten. These Welkin take no weapons to "
"battle, save that which was bestowed upon them due to their homage to the "
"sun. These Welkin are, as is common among Welkin, frail and therefore cannot "
"withstand the tumult and the turmoil of the bloody Wesnothian battlefield. "
"Despite their lack of Strength and might, Neophytes surely are a sight to "
"see. With their flaring red hair and red robe, they truly praise Aten as a "
"beacon for the sun!"
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Neophyte.cfg:24
msgid "female^Neophyte"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Patriarch, race=AE_fut_welkin, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Patriarch.cfg:5
msgid "Patriarch"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Patriarch, race=AE_fut_welkin, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Patriarch.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"There is no more honor for a follower of Thoth then to me one of his "
"Patriarchs. Patriarchs carry a great staff that signifies the unity of the "
"Welkin in their worship of both Thoth and Aten, for the staff fits flushly on"
" the staff of the Hierarchs of Aten. This does not grant any strange power "
"but is mearly symbolism to show that their sociecties can connect. Granted "
"with the great Power of Thoth, these Welkin are incredibly powerful "
"adversaries and, although they can do great damage to their enemies, it is "
"unwise to leave them unprotected. Though less deadly then they're "
"counterparts, the Hierarchs, the Patriarchs are often found to be more "
"intimidating than them, probably due to the fact that they have continued to "
"keep their faces shaded. They too are called by their king to be diplomats, "
"messengers, as well as advisors."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Pyroation, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Pyroation.cfg:5
msgid "Pyroation"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Pyroation, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Pyroation.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"These Welkin follow Aten so devoutly that they don't waste time trying to "
"learn the art of a hand weapon but instead spend their time praying and "
"studying. Through their deep devotion to Aten they have been granted the "
"privilege of a slight embodiment of fire from the sun and let it rain from "
"their hands in battle making the carven flee. Pyroations must go through "
"rigorous training so they can learn to control the power which is to be "
"bestowed upon them and so have little time for pleasantries. It is rare to "
"find a charismatic Pyroation due to how ill-tempered most are because of a "
"lack of sleep from late night studies and devotions."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Pyroation.cfg:32
msgid "female^Pryoation"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Quickdraw, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Quickdraw.cfg:5
msgid "Quickdraw"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Quickdraw, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Quickdraw.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"These Welkin are those which epitomize the characteristical elvish swiftness."
" They are Welkin that have excelled in their skill with the bow. They have "
"rid themselves of all other weapons so as to have a better knowledge and "
"skill of both the bow and the power of Thoth. These Welkin move swiftly and "
"take out their enemy from a distance, but cannot protect themselves if an "
"enemy manages to get close enough for a melee attack."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Quickdraw.cfg:24
msgid "female^Quickdraw"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Sage, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Sage.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"A Welkin who has decided to follow both Aten and Thoth. Because of his "
"decision, however, a sage is forced to live a life of solitude lest he be "
"subjugated to the insults of the people. But because of the knowledge of "
"recieving these insults before becoming a Sage, most are very strong in their"
" faith and do great works for their king and queen. As a follower of both the"
" sun and the moon, a sage has discovered that through the manipulation of the"
" purging effect of the fire and the soothing effect of the water a healing "
"effect is created."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Sage.cfg:24
msgid "female^Sage"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Sentinel_of_the_Moon, race=AE_fut_welkin, gender=female
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Sentinel_of_the_Moon.cfg:5
msgid "Sentinel of the Moon"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Sentinel_of_the_Moon, race=AE_fut_welkin, gender=female
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Sentinel_of_the_Moon.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"The Sentinels of the Moon are known and revered for their strength and "
"prowess during battle. Still they protect Thoth and still they grow stronger."
" When attacked these soldiers have been trained to destroy the enemy at any "
"and all costs! These Welkin are so loyal to Thoth that they continue to fight"
" during the hours of the day, and have acquired so much strength that there "
"is no difference in their fighting capabilities in battle during the day or "
"night."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Shadow_Raider, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Shadow_Raider.cfg:5
msgid "Shadow Raider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Shadow_Raider, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Shadow_Raider.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"A great fighter for the army of Thoth, the Shadow Raider is quite a powerful "
"enemy. He wields an ice hammer, which he creates with the skill in the art of"
" the moon. Yet they are still able to fight their distant enemies with the "
"Power of Thoth. Shadow Raider's have abandoned the bow for the way of the "
"moon which is why they were granted with such awe inspiring power. These "
"Welkin, however, have grown slow due to their constant study and so are not "
"as quick as they once were."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Shadow_Raider.cfg:28
msgid "female^Shadow Raider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Solar_Empyrean, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Solar_Empyrean.cfg:5
msgid "Solar Empyrean"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Solar_Empyrean, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Solar_Empyrean.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"These elves are those which are, if possible, even more devout and have spent"
" more time in their effort to please Aten then any others of their order. In "
"response to this great sacrifice, Aten has greatly increased the embodiment "
"of his  power. The Solar Empyreans glow with his radiance and at the touch of"
" their hands his flame is ignited. These Welkin have no need of staff or "
"material weapon for the Power of Aten flows through their veins. They are a "
"sight to behold on the battlefield, glowing like a small sun during the day "
"or shining like a star during the night, drawing the army towards them like a"
" beacon."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Solar_Empyrean.cfg:30
msgid "female^Solar Empyrean"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Star_Shooter, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Star_Shooter.cfg:5
msgid "Star Shooter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Star_Shooter, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Star_Shooter.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"The most versatile of the Welkin, the Star Shooter is a follower of the moon "
"who's training exceeds that of any other recruit in the Welkin army. These "
"Welkin have undergone a massive amount of rigorous training so that they are "
"able to wield a sword and bow, but still be capable of using the Power of "
"Thoth as well. Though their ability to use the sword and bow is great it is "
"not to be compared to that of their power to control the art of the  moon. "
"This Welkin is not one to be underestimated and is ready for anything that is"
" thrown at him."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Star_Shooter.cfg:24
msgid "female^Star Shooter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Talon_Hero, race=AE_fut_welkin, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Talon_Hero.cfg:5
msgid "Talon Hero"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Talon_Hero, race=AE_fut_welkin, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Talon_Hero.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"These elves train with the claw. They have become the quickest assassins in "
"the land. However, they do not stalk around like assasins, rather, they move "
"proudly toward their foes making their enemies fear them for their battle "
"prowess. They are not to be picked off either, for if you miss they can blast"
" their enemy away with their power of wind. The Talon Warriors are the first "
"of their order to equip themselves with armor. They wear a breastplate for "
"protection but this decreases their speed. However, their speed is so great "
"that this extra wieght does not decrease their fighting  prowess in the "
"slightest."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Talon_Warrior, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Talon_Warrior.cfg:5
msgid "Talon Warrior"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Talon_Warrior, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Talon_Warrior.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"The Flurry's which have chosen the strength over spirit are those of the "
"Talon Order. They train hard so as to be able to wield their claw blades to "
"their greatest capabilities, while still maintaining their twister of wind "
"which allows them to fly. Although they are not as prevalent in the art of "
"the wind, these Welkin are still a deadly force from a distance. However, if "
"one does attack a Talon Warrior from a distance, they are the lucky ones for "
"their true power lies in their claws."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Talon_Warrior.cfg:24
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Dust_Twist.cfg:45
msgid "female^Talon Warrior"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Thoth_s_Bulwark, race=AE_fut_welkin, gender=female
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Thoths_Bulwark.cfg:5
msgid "Thoth's Bulwark"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Thoth_s_Bulwark, race=AE_fut_welkin, gender=female
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Thoths_Bulwark.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"Thoth's Bulwarks are Sentinels of whom contain immense strength, might, and "
"prowess both on the battlefield and off it. They defend their god with their "
"lives, and as their title states, they protect Thoth as a bulwark. Continuing"
" to fight both night and day, these stout defenders are fearless and deadly."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Tornado, race=AE_fut_welkin, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Tornado.cfg:5
msgid "Tornado"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Tornado, race=AE_fut_welkin, gender=male
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Tornado.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"These Welkin are elves which have sought out the great power of the wind and "
"they praise Aten with their incredible skill. They are still equipped with "
"the claw and are quite deadly with them, however, their speed and skill with "
"wind is awe inspiring. Unlike the Talon Heros the Tornados do not wear armor "
"because it slows them down. The Tornado's rely on their speed because of "
"their lack of melee power and they are often royal messengers due to their "
"high rank and speed."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Twilight_Slayer, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Twilight_Slayer.cfg:5
msgid "Twilight Slayer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Twilight_Slayer, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Twilight_Slayer.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
" \n"
"The Twilight Slayers have, unlike others that had also chosen to be Star "
"Shooters, given up the study of the moon for the training to become the "
"masters of the sword . These Welkin have studied the sword so as to find out "
"all the capabilities of the incredibly versitile weapon. These elves not only"
" use the sword in melee combat but also hurl their swords as a lesser Welkin "
"would throw a dagger. This intimidatation makes their foe reluctanct to face "
"them."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Twilight_Slayer.cfg:36
msgid "female^Twilight Slayer"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=ranged
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Twilight_Slayer.cfg:101
msgid "Thrown Sword"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Whirlwind, race=AE_fut_welkin
#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Whirlwind, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Whirlwind.cfg:5
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Whirlwind.cfg:5
msgid "Whirlwind"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_fut_welkin_Whirlwind, race=AE_fut_welkin
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Whirlwind.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Era of the Future. Its coding, art, and ideas were done"
" by Turuk, Mirion147, Huston, Pentarctagon, Wesfreak, Xandria, and Zerovirus.\n"
"\n"
"Whirlwinds are Flurries that have excelled in their ability to control the "
"surrounding air and have increased their power considerably which, in "
"addition to the trademark claw weapon of the Flurry, makes them formidable "
"opponents yet still swift enough to be the main scout of the army of Aten. "
"The main desire of the Whirlwinds is to bring glory and honor to Aten through"
" their skill and power, they take no credit for their work but give it all to"
" their god."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\EotF_units\welkin\Whirlwind.cfg:24
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Dust_Whirlwind.cfg:46
msgid "female^Whirlwind"
msgstr ""

