msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Blazer, race=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarf
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Blazer.cfg:4
msgid "Blazer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Blazer, race=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarf
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Blazer.cfg:21
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Blazers focus more on the power of their alchemical creations than their "
"actually duties. Many are despised as pyromaniacal, but, on the fields of "
"battle, the massive explosions they summon from flasks whose size belie their"
" power earn them respect in the eyes of their fellows and foes alike."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Gas_Baron, race=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarf
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Gas_Baron.cfg:4
msgid "Gas Baron"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Gas_Baron, race=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarf
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Gas_Baron.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"These former miasmists are as coldblooded as the contraptions, a necessary "
"attribute of one who commonly melts his foes into a pile of liquefied flesh. "
"In the tank on a Gas Baron's back, there is a chemical, the composition of "
"which is known to none but him. Thus, each brutally kills his foe in a "
"different method, but all do so with an inscrutable steely glint in their "
"eyes."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Gas_Baron.cfg:29
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\General.cfg:26
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Marshal.cfg:25
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Miasmist.cfg:28
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Soldier.cfg:22
msgid "clockwork blade"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Gas_Baron.cfg:38
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Miasmist.cfg:37
msgid "miasma"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_General, race=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarf
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\General.cfg:4
msgid "General"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_General, race=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarf
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\General.cfg:21
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The swish, click, swish, click of a clockwork general's mechanical boots is "
"feared by all non-dwarves. His metallic armor makes him as strong as two men,"
" and he uses his widgets to deadly effect. He is a master of battlefield "
"construction, and stories are told of generals who, having lost their blades,"
" fashion a new weapon out of their armor."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Greaser, race=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarf
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Greaser.cfg:4
msgid "Greaser"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Greaser, race=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarf
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Greaser.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"To keep the myriad of dwarvish devices oiled and running, the clockwork "
"dwarves hire greasers. Greasers are not manual laborers, but skilled "
"repairmen. They carry an array of toils, not least among them being "
"inflammable concoctions. If caught on the battlefield in the act of repair, "
"greasers are far from defenseless - in fact, they are some of the most deadly"
" dwarven recruits."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Gunner, race=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarf
#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_dark_legion_Gunner, race=human
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Gunner.cfg:4
#: .\units\misc_units\dark_legion\Dark_Gunner.cfg:4
msgid "Gunner"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Gunner, race=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarf
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Gunner.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Over time, dwarves equipped with 'guns', as they call them, become "
"sufficiently adept at operating their weapons that they can reload and fire "
"exceedingly quickly. These gunners spray their enemies with their metal "
"insects of death, pushing back whole battalions in a single round of firing."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Itinerant, race=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarf
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Itinerant.cfg:4
msgid "Itinerant"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Itinerant, race=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarf
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Itinerant.cfg:26
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Many ramblers forsake their lives of roving and return to a hold. Some do "
"not. An itinerant is a dwarf whose wanderlust has made him an eternal "
"outcast. He not only wanders, but avoids almost all mannish company, They "
"bear flags on their great lances that warn all to stay away unless "
"approached, lest the itinerant slay him in a fit of sociopathic rage."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Itinerant.cfg:35
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Rambler.cfg:33
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Wanderer.cfg:31
msgid "clockwork lance"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Marshal, race=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarf
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Marshal.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"A clockwork marshal is a former soldier who has been chosen to lead his "
"fellow warriors. He is fitted with clockwork devices in addition to his sword"
" that augment his strength and speed."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Miasmist, race=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarf
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Miasmist.cfg:4
msgid "Miasmist"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Miasmist, race=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarf
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Miasmist.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Clockwork soldiers either specialize in leadership, or in slaughter. A "
"miasmist chooses the latter, and as such is equipped with deadly gases that "
"he sprays forth, disfiguring the flesh of the foe until he simultaneously "
"suffocates and burns to death."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Oiler, race=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarf
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Oiler.cfg:4
msgid "Oiler"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Oiler, race=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarf
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Oiler.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Oilers are simply more experienced greasers- they are proficient in more "
"methods of repair, and, as such, are permitted to use more dangerous but "
"effective elixirs to perform their duties. Thus, they have more powerful "
"methods of defense on the battlefield, and can even hurl flaming globes of a "
"gelatinous substance at their foes, wreaking great havoc."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Rambler, race=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarf
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Rambler.cfg:4
msgid "Rambler"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Rambler, race=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarf
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Rambler.cfg:24
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Ramblers are the more experienced wanderers; they are wise in the ways of the"
" world, and travel across the lands of every race. They commonly enhance both"
" their legs and their lances according to the necessities of a life dedicated"
" to rambling."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Soldier, race=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarf
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Soldier.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The soldiers of the clockwork dwarves are not remarkable in and of their "
"skill of arms, per se, but in their remarkable ability to use their advanced "
"and complex equipment. Each is equiped with a clockwork blade, a blade that "
"can fold into a dagger, telescope into a two-handed sword, or be curved into "
"any sort of scimitar or similar curved instrument of combat. Needless to say,"
" their foes are bewildered by the dwarves clever usage of their equipment's "
"odd nature."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Steel_Eagle, race=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarf
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Steel_Eagle.cfg:4
msgid "Steel Eagle"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Steel_Eagle, race=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarf
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Steel_Eagle.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The sight of a Steel Eagle hovering over the field strikes the enemy with "
"fear and wonder. How any device - let alone a mass of metal and gears - can "
"be made to fly remains a mystery to other races. But while their means of "
"flight is unknown, their means of attack are well-known; armed with the "
"'guns' characteristic of the dwarves, they dart hither and thither, spraying "
"their enemies with metal slugs."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Triggerman, race=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarf
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Triggerman.cfg:4
msgid "Triggerman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Triggerman, race=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarf
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Triggerman.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The dwarves, partial to clockwork, developed a new kind of ranged warfare "
"technology. The triggermen do not use the crossbows or thundersticks of their"
" ancestors, but devices similar to thundersticks but much more complex. None "
"save the dwarves themselves can comprehend the inner-workings of their tubes,"
" but few can hold their ground when confronted with the buzzing cylinders "
"that issue forth from them, in much larger numbers than from their "
"predecessor’s weapons."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Wanderer, race=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarf
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Wanderer.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"These shiftless vagabonds are fringe members of dwarven society. They do have"
" a hold to call their home, but rove far and wide across the world seeking to"
" exorcise their wanderlust. Dwarves make poor wanderers, however, as they "
"avoid horses and boats, and their legs cannot carry them far or fast. Thus, "
"wanderers equip themselves with giant mechanical legs, which they control "
"with their own. These massive devices eventually become as one with the "
"dwarf, and after years of wandering, a wanderer is inseparable from his legs."
" When he must fight, a wanderer wields a lance-not a long, smooth lance like "
"that of the humans, but a machinery-covered pole that can be folded into a "
"pocket."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Wooden_Bird, race=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarf
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Wooden_Bird.cfg:4
msgid "Wooden Bird"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Wooden_Bird, race=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarf
#: .\units\feudal_units\dwarves-clockwork\Wooden_Bird.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The so-called 'wooden birds' are some of the most amazing devices built by "
"the dwarves. They fly over the ground, moving with considerable speed, and "
"rain down death on their enemies without fear of retribution."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Archer, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\a1-Archer.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The elves' keen senses lend themselves well to the pursuit of archery. High "
"Elven archers combine their inherent dexterity and strength with rigid "
"discipline and training, giving them astonishing capabilities on the "
"battlefield. Even their rank-and-file bowmen, armed with light yew bows, are "
"capable of loosing volley after volley into enemy ranks, each arrow striking "
"its mark with deadly force."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Chasseur, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\a2-Chasseur.cfg:4
msgid "Chasseur"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Chasseur, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\a2-Chasseur.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The High Elves pride themselves on the skill of their archers, and while "
"other menn may deride them as arrogant, they would still admit that High "
"Elven archers posess incredible skill. The veterans, known as chasseurs, "
"constitute a formidable force; their prowess is gained through years upon "
"years of fighting and training. No human, orc or dwarf can equal the power "
"and rapidity of their shooting."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Tireur_d_Elite, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\a3-Tireur_dElite.cfg:4
msgid "Tireur d'Elite"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Tireur_d_Elite, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\a3-Tireur_dElite.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The finest of High Elven archers are posessed of skills that seem incredible "
"to other menn. They consider themselves a class apart from their brethren, it"
" is said that among their number are warriors who voyaged across the northern"
" ice and fought alongside the first Issaelfr lords, or even Vanimaro himself."
" These tales do not seem unlikely given their amazing prowess; though they "
"train almost constantly, it is easy to believe that only centuries of war "
"could produce such mastery."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Charger, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_equestrians_Charger, race=AE_mrc_equestrians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\b1-Charger.cfg:4
#: .\units\ME_units\equestrians\b1-charger.cfg:5
msgid "Charger"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Charger, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\b1-Charger.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The elves have always recognised the value of cavalry in battle, but until "
"they came to inhabit Silvia they had little opportunity to use them. When the"
" High Elves did move south, however, they soon started to train horsemen. "
"These chargers are well known for their bravery and skill; like many elves, "
"they wield only spears, but use these simple weapons to great effect."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Cavalier, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_dark_legion_Cavalier, race=human
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\b2-Cavalier.cfg:4
#: .\units\misc_units\dark_legion\Dark_Cavalier.cfg:4
msgid "Cavalier"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Cavalier, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\b2-Cavalier.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The High Elven cavaliers represent a kind of fighter that humans have "
"attempted to create throughout history - a cavalrymann who can fight well in "
"a melee and can also hold his own at range - but they are almost certainly "
"the most successful of these attempts. Abandoning the spear for a finely "
"crafted backsword, they are a match for any Ceresian knight at close "
"quarters; for combat at a distance, they carry crossbows, shooting left and "
"right with astonishing skill."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Cuirassier, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\b2-Cuirassier.cfg:4
msgid "Cuirassier"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Cuirassier, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\b2-Cuirassier.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Any High Elf, if asked about human knights, would describe them as a pale "
"imitation of their own cuirassiers. While this is really conceit on the part "
"of the elves, it is undeniable that the elves produce the finer horsemenn. "
"Complementing their spears with swords of elven steel, they are more "
"versatile than lanciers, having considerable worth in defence as well as in "
"the charge."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Lancier, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\b2-Lancier.cfg:4
msgid "Lancier"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Lancier, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\b2-Lancier.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The most daring chargers often choose to continue fighting with lances alone."
" While this is a dangerous tactic - a failed charge leaves few survivors - it"
" is terrifically effective when used propery. Lanciers can run down an enemy "
"without their foes being able to strike a single blow."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Cataphract, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\b3-Cataphract.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The High Elven cataphracts are without doubt the finest horsemenn of this "
"world - as they themselves will gladly admit. They are clad in glittering "
"mail, armed with the finest weapons that elven craftsmannship can produce, "
"and mounted on horses of mighty strength and build - a combination which, "
"combined with their incredible skill, makes them near unassailable in combat."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Escrimeur, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\b3-Escrimeur.cfg:4
msgid "Escrimeur"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Escrimeur, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\b3-Escrimeur.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The ideal of the all-purpose cavalrymann - the ideal that has eluded humans "
"for so long - is embodied by the escrimeurs. While not as devastating in the "
"charge as a gendarme, they are as versatile and deadly as any cavalrymann "
"could hope to be. Their skills with horse, sword, and crossbow seem "
"incredible to other races, and are held in high regard even by their fellow "
"elves."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Gendarme, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\b3-Gendarme.cfg:4
msgid "Gendarme"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Gendarme, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\b3-Gendarme.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Lanciers' preferred method of attack - a single, head-on charge - is so risky"
" that most are killed in battle before they can perfect their skills. Those "
"that survive to become veterans are inevitably masters of fighting and "
"horsemanship. Known as gerdarmes, these menn are among the most terrifying "
"opponents that can ever be met in battle; their charges are nigh-on "
"unstoppable, causing untold devastation when they strike."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Faerie_Warrior, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\c1-Faerie_Warrior.cfg:4
msgid "Faerie Warrior"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Faerie_Warrior, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\c1-Faerie_Warrior.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The High Elves derive most of their tactics from Issaelfr tradition. However,"
" the Faerie Warriors are a continuation of the Sidhe ways, deriving from the "
"War Mages of old. They combine powerful magic with considerable "
"swordsmannship to create a unique class of warrior."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\c1-Faerie_Warrior.cfg:40
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\c3-Sylvanus.cfg:43
msgid "faerie lightning"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Feyblade, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\c2-Feyblade.cfg:4
msgid "Feyblade"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Feyblade, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\c2-Feyblade.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"The more powerful of the High Elven magi become feyblades, adept with both "
"sword and the lightning they call from the sky."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\c2-Feyblade.cfg:69
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\c3-Sylvanus.cfg:30
msgid "fey sword"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Sylvanus, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\c3-Sylvanus.cfg:4
msgid "Sylvanus"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Sylvanus, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\c3-Sylvanus.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Master of both sword and magic, a Sylvanus is a warrior whose heritage "
"reaches back to the days of Vanimaro himself. The sight of one on the "
"battlefield will never fail to terrify his foes; they are much feared for "
"their ability to call down lightning, without warning, from a cloudless sky."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Horse_Archer, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\d1-Horse_Archer.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The High Elves developed a number of types of cavalry during their early "
"years in Silvia. One of the most straightforward of these is the horse "
"archer: a rider equipped with a bow and a short sword, intended for speed and"
" agility in hit-and-run attacks. These warriors make no pretense of "
"compromise - they are weak in melee, and a disciplined force of knights or "
"pikemen presents them with a serious problem - but when striking against an "
"unprepared foe, they are deadly indeed."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Coutillier, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\d2-Coutillier.cfg:4
msgid "Coutillier"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Coutillier, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\d2-Coutillier.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Coutilliers are, like so many of the High Elven cavalry, a refinement of an "
"ancient idea. Exchanging their bows for heavy javelins, they also devote more"
" time to swordsmanship than the savaris. The result is a fast rider capable "
"of shock attacks either at range or at close quarters."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Savari, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\d2-Savari.cfg:4
msgid "Savari"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Savari, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\d2-Savari.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"High Elven horse archers who continue their martial pursuits are known as "
"savaris. Years of training with the bow have given these elves a level of "
"skill that no other race can rival. While their effectiveness in melee is "
"still poor compared to other cavalry, they are rightly feared in battle; they"
" can rain down arrows on the enemy ranks before retreating suddenly, out of "
"range of any retribution."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Chevauleger, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\d3-Chevauleger.cfg:4
msgid "Chevauleger"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Chevauleger, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\d3-Chevauleger.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The chevaulegers are the finest of their kind - the culmination of decades "
"training with sword and javelin. Taking a different tactic to the slower, "
"heavier escrimeurs, they are superb scouts, having the speed and daring to "
"attempt - and succeed in - the most dangerous of raids and sorties."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Voltigeur, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\d3-Voltigeur.cfg:4
msgid "Voltigeur"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Voltigeur, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\d3-Voltigeur.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The zenith of mounted archery is represented by the voltigeurs. No other race"
" can equal their mastery of the bow while mounted; few could match it even on"
" foot. They have fought in countless battles, striking quickly and "
"mercilessly, darkening the skies with arrows, filling their enemies' hearts "
"with fear."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Sorceress, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race, gender=female
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\e1-Sorceress.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The world of faerie is far more potent than the corporeal world. Simply "
"bringing some of this world into our own can have violent results. This is "
"well-understood by the elves, although rarely used with malicious intent; "
"doing so is no easy task, and is a very ill-regarded use of their strength.\n"
"\n"
"Those able to do so are roughly titled as 'sorceresses' by other races; and "
"certainly are capable of acting the part."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Enchantress, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race, gender=female
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\e2-Enchantress.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The magic of the elves is wholly unlike that of humanity, so much so that "
"humans are almost universally incapable of understanding it, let alone using "
"it. Likewise, those who are masters of it are equally enigmatic; though it "
"can be said that they are revered by their people, very little can be said "
"about their actual function or purpose within that society."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Sylph, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race, gender=female
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\e3-Sylph.cfg:4
msgid "female^Sylph"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Sylph, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race, gender=female
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\e3-Sylph.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Rarely seen, the sage-like Sylphs are masters of both their faerie and "
"mundane natures. They are possessed of wondrous, and sometimes terrifying "
"powers. Legends concerning these have given other races a healthy fear of the"
" elves."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Spearman, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\f1-Spearman.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The spearmenn of the high elven nation wield glaives as their primary weapon,"
" allowing them to deal both bladed and piercing damage. "
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Glavier, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\f2-Glavier.cfg:4
msgid "Glavier"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Glavier, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\f2-Glavier.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Most men prefer clubs, axes, and other barbaric weapons to the spear, which "
"they view as a cheap alternative, to only be used against cavalry or due to "
"the lack of more suitable weaponry. Not so with the High Elves. Their "
"Spearmenn are equipped with glaives, a flexible and deadly cousin of the "
"spear. Those who learn to capitalize on the strengths of the glaive become "
"Glaviers, wielding their finely crafted polearms with speed that rivals that "
"of a sword. They confound enemies with the designs they weave in the air with"
" the shining tips of their great weapons, then strike with great scything "
"blows that, while powerful, are painstakingly precise."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Schiltron, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\f2-Schiltron.cfg:4
msgid "Schiltron"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Schiltron, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\f2-Schiltron.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The most agile and quick Spearmenn become Schiltrons, taking their name from "
"their formation of choice, the ring of pikes invented by the Keltoi in "
"ancient times. Though their talents may seem better suited to the more "
"flexible glaive, the Schiltrons need agility in great measure, as the pikes "
"they wield, though of High Elven manufacture, and shorter than average, are, "
"ultimately, pikes, and thus unwieldy and unbalanced. Their skill compensates "
"for this, and they strike with great speed, withdrawing and jabbing their "
"pike many times, then fading back into the impenetrable thorn bush that is "
"the schiltron."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Shieldbearer, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Shieldbearer, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\f2-Shieldbearer.cfg:4
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Shieldbearer.cfg:4
msgid "Shieldbearer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Shieldbearer, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\f2-Shieldbearer.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The lords of the High Elves lead their men with brilliance of both thought "
"and deed, and as such are often targeted by an enemy hoping that if the head "
"is cut off, the body will die. The Shieldbearers are tasked with accompanying"
" these great lords, forming an impenetrable wall to defend them from the "
"assaults of the enemy, or with securing strategic points before "
"reinforcements can arrive. Because they carry great tower shields, even "
"larger than those of the Lavinians, many a man has assumed them to be slow "
"and lumbering. Many a man has also been thrown to the ground by a "
"surprisingly quick blow from a Shieldbearer's shield."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Aegis, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\f3-Aegis.cfg:4
msgid "Aegis"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Aegis, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\f3-Aegis.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Aeges are the elite of the shieldbearers. They are everywhere known for "
"their immense strength, and rightly so, for they trudge into battle equipped "
"with the finest full plate armor and great shields of steel yet are no slower"
" for it. Like the shieldbearers, they guard the greatest of the elves, and "
"when their charge is threatened, they fight to the death, forming an "
"impenetrable wall before him - a wall bristling with glistening steel, a wall"
" of overlapping scales, a wall of might, skill, and undying loyalty."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Captain, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\f3-Captain.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Those who become true masters of the glaive will generally become Captains, "
"esteemed by all their comrades. None are trained for this role of leadership;"
" they simply acquire it through bravery, cunning, and skill with their "
"weapon. Despite this ostensible lack of tactical expertise, once they are "
"respected enough, less skilled troops will pledge themselves to the Captain's"
" banner, and the great elven sages will commence the training of the new "
"cohort. A cohort fights as one, each elf covering the next with his swirling "
"blows, the Captain at the fore, pressing the enemy back, and leading his "
"troops to victory.\n"
"\n"
"The Captains wield a weapon even more deadly and sophisticated than the "
"glaive: the dual glaive. These they spin in the air, slashing, jabbing, "
"scything through flesh, bone and steel, turning even bloodshed into an art."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Fouchardier, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\f3-Fouchardier.cfg:4
msgid "Fouchardier"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_high_elves_Fouchardier, race=AE_feu_high_elves_race
#: .\units\feudal_units\elves-high\f3-Fouchardier.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"In each schiltron, there are bound to be at least a handful of Fouchardiers. "
"These former Schiltrons are esteemed veterans, but not merely longstanding "
"members of their group.\n"
"\n"
"To become one of the honored Fouchardiers, a Schiltron must fight a battle "
"alone, without his formation. Due to difficult nature of the wielding of the "
"pike without support, many do not pass this test, instead succumbing to their"
" inexperience and fear. Oddly enough, Fouchardier are encouraged to receive "
"wounds during their test, and each has many scars. This lends itself to an "
"easy system of distributing the Fouchardier among the schiltrons: each "
"schiltron is allotted thirty scars."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Acolyte, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Acolyte.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Ceresian clergy are not generally trained as fighters, but even so, they "
"often choose to support the soldiery during wartime. They generally tend to "
"the wounded on the battlefield, but also have some knowledge of magic."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Acolyte.cfg:37
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Deacon.cfg:40
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Knight_Raetian.cfg:44
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Metropolitan.cfg:44
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Monsignor.cfg:40
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Order_Knight.cfg:41
msgid "invocation"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Arbalestier, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Arbalestier.cfg:4
msgid "Arbalestier"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Arbalestier, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Arbalestier.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The arbalest is a more powerful variant of the crossbow, built with a steel "
"prod rather than a wooden one. While it is more expensive than a normal "
"crossbow, it is a very deadly and very accurate weapon."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Cavaliero, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Cavaliero.cfg:4
msgid "Cavaliero"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Cavaliero, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Cavaliero.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Cavalieros are the finest of Ceresian light cavalry. Their speed and "
"manoeuvreability allow them to outflank any enemy and cut off any advance."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Cavalryman, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Cavalryman.cfg:4
msgid "Cavalryman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Cavalryman, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Cavalryman.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The open plains of Ceresia are ideal for cavalry tactics - and "
"unsurprisingly, the Ceresian cavalry are some of the finest in the world. "
"They are equipped with swords and plate armour, and they ride fearlessly into"
" the fray."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Champion, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Champion, race=AE_imp_nemidian_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_equestrians_Champion, race=AE_mrc_equestrians_race, gender=male
#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_dark_legion_Champion, race=human
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Champion.cfg:4
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-nemidians\Champion.cfg:5
#: .\units\ME_units\equestrians\c2-champion.cfg:5
#: .\units\misc_units\dark_legion\Dark_Champion.cfg:4
msgid "Champion"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Champion, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Champion.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The most skilled men-at-arms are known among the Ceresian nobility as "
"Champions. They are men of fearsome strength and power, viewed with awe by "
"friend and foe alike."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Condottiero, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Condottiero.cfg:4
msgid "Condottiero"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Condottiero, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Condottiero.cfg:26
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"A condottiero commands a full brigade of men. He is an experienced fighter, "
"skilled in the use of many different weapons. Often he does not owe fealty to"
" any lord, but instead sells his services to the highest bidder."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Corporal, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Corporal.cfg:4
msgid "Corporal"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Corporal, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Corporal.cfg:25
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"A corporal, as his rank implies, commands a small body of men in battle. He "
"is often a young noble, though on some occasions a free commoner is made an "
"officer."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Crossbowman, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Crossbowman.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The Ceresians rarely use conventional bows, but they make great use of the "
"crossbow. While these weapons cannot shoot as quickly as a longbow, they are "
"both powerful and easy to use."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Deacon, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Deacon.cfg:4
msgid "Deacon"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Deacon, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Deacon.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"A Ceresian priest is skilled in healing and has considerable supernatural "
"powers. He is welcomed by the army that he supports, and is always willing to"
" call upon the gods to bless his fellow men."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Espadachino, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Espadachino.cfg:4
msgid "Espadachino"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Espadachino, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Espadachino.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Espadachinos are those noble swordsmen who strive above all to be lightning "
"quick with their blades. Though they do not wear such heavy armour as their "
"compatriots, those who have seen these men fight will concede that the "
"benefits this affords are impressive."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Espadachino.cfg:30
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Rodelero.cfg:32
msgid "rapier"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Halberdier, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_dark_legion_Halberdier, race=human
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Halberdier.cfg:4
#: .\units\misc_units\dark_legion\Dark_Halberdier.cfg:4
msgid "Halberdier"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Halberdier, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Halberdier.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Halberdiers are the Elite of the common soldiery. Their halberds, though "
"requiring considerable strength and training to use, are far more versatile "
"than pikes or spears, having axe-like blades with which unwitting enemies may"
" be sliced apart."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Knight_Commander, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Knight_Commander.cfg:4
msgid "Knight Commander"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Knight_Commander, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Knight_Commander.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The most experienced knights serve their lords with unflinching loyalty. They"
" are deadly in battle, fighting skilfully with both sword and lance, and men "
"will rally to the sight of a Knight Commander at the forefront of a charge."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Knight_Errant, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Knight_Errant.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"A young noble, once knighted by his liege lord, is known as a Knight Errant. "
"He may then wear his own coat of arms, and often commands troops of his own. "
"He also carries a lance in addition to his sword; while this weapon sees most"
" use at the tilt, it is nevertheless effective on the battlefield."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Knight_Raetian, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Knight_Raetian.cfg:4
msgid "Knight Raetian"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Knight_Raetian, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Knight_Raetian.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"When Alfhelm Alfricsson sacked Lavinium, the Lavinian general Sextus Raetius "
"turned against the emperor and fought on Alfhelm's side. He did this, his "
"eponymous Order claims, in order to preserve what could be preserved of "
"Lavinian civilization - if he had not done so, the entire city would have "
"been burned to the ground. In later days, the Raetian Knights fought against "
"any who threatened their efforts to preserve and restore that civilization, "
"including their own nominal lieges."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Knight_Raetian.cfg:35
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Order_Knight.cfg:32
msgid "morningstar"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Lieutenant, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Lieutenant.cfg:4
msgid "Lieutenant"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Lieutenant, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Lieutenant.cfg:25
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Lieutenants are mid-ranking officers, drawn from the lower ranks to serve as "
"commanders' deputies. In battle they wield pikes and crossbows."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Man_at_Arms, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Man-at-Arms.cfg:4
msgid "Man-at-Arms"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Man_at_Arms, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Man-at-Arms.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Some squires choose not to ride horses into battle, instead refining their "
"skill in fighting whilst dismounted. These men-at-arms wear full armour and "
"wield longswords, and in melee combat they are formidable indeed."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Master_Arbalestier, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Master_Arbalestier.cfg:4
msgid "Master Arbalestier"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Master_Arbalestier, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Master_Arbalestier.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Master arbalestiers are renowned for their skill with their weapons. The best"
" among them boast that they can hit a gold coin at four hundred paces, every "
"time - and indeed, many enemy commanders have met their ends in the form of a"
" crossbow bolt through the skull."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Metropolitan, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Metropolitan.cfg:4
msgid "Metropolitan"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Metropolitan, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Metropolitan.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The most revered of the Ceresian clergy are the metropolitans. Often more "
"powerful than the lords whom they ostensibly serve, the metropolitans command"
" the respect and admiration of their countrymen. Though they do not often "
"fight in battle, they command impressive spiritual powers, and their "
"appearance never fails to frighten the enemy."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Monk, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Monk.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Ceresian monks are used to long voyages, often alone or through uncharted "
"waters. They have seen much of the world, and are tireless in their travels."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Monk.cfg:32
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Novice.cfg:27
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Pellegrino.cfg:42
msgid "tempest"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Monsignor, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Monsignor.cfg:4
msgid "Monsignor"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Monsignor, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Monsignor.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"'Monsignor' is the title of a senior priest, both healer and fighter. During "
"peacetime, he attends to the worship of the gods, and cares for the sick and "
"needy, but in wartime he will call upon his divine patrons to smite his "
"enemies."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Mounted_Crossbowman, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Mounted_Crossbowman.cfg:4
msgid "Mounted Crossbowman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Mounted_Crossbowman, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Mounted_Crossbowman.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Some experienced crossbowmen ride into battle on horseback. While this does "
"impair their shooting somewhat, it grants them much greater mobility, and "
"also gives them an advantage in melee combat."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Mounted_Infantryman, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Mounted_Infantryman.cfg:4
msgid "Mounted Infantryman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Mounted_Infantryman, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Mounted_Infantryman.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Some infantrymen choose to ride horses into battle, making them far more "
"mobile. While they still fight on foot and are therefore not true cavalry, "
"they nevertheless gain a great tactical advantage from their mounts."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Novice, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Novice.cfg:4
msgid "Novice"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Novice, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Novice.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Some religious-minded Ceresians choose to bring the worship of their gods to "
"distant lands. This pursuit can take many forms, from preaching to foreign "
"peoples, to living in isolated monasteries, but when these monks choose to "
"travel, they generally do so by boat."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Order_Knight, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Order_Knight.cfg:4
msgid "Order Knight"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Order_Knight, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Order_Knight.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Ceresian Order Knights are an unusual order. Instead of accepting "
"noblemen, they recruit exclusively from the clergy, selecting the most "
"zealous of the acolytes. While they are not as formidable fighters as the "
"Knights Errant alongside whom they serve, their magical powers and healing "
"skills more than make up for this deficit."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Pellegrino, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Pellegrino.cfg:4
msgid "Pellegrino"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Pellegrino, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Pellegrino.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Senior monks, whichever god they serve, are hardy and experienced men. Taking"
" the title 'Pellegrino', meaning 'Traveller', they roam freely across the "
"seas of Evrosia. Some of the most devout and determined have become legendary"
" for their incredible sea crossings."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Pikeman, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Pikeman.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Pikemen are a key part of any Ceresian infantry contingent. Their long pikes "
"allow them to fend off attacks with impunity, and when arrayed in battle "
"formation they are a fearsome foe. But while they have a number of different "
"roles, many would say that their real purpose is to protect the Ceresians' "
"renowned crossbowmen."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Rodelero, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Rodelero.cfg:4
msgid "Rodelero"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Rodelero, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Rodelero.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"A rodelero is a master of the duel: agile, experienced, and blindingly fast. "
"He can cut down an enemy in seconds, and is feared by any foe who crosses his"
" path."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Squire, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Squire.cfg:4
msgid "Squire"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Squire, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Squire.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"A squire is a young noble who has not yet been knighted by his liege lord. He"
" does not ride a horse into battle, fighting instead on foot. Eschewing "
"missile weapons, he carries a sword, and wields it with great skill."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Stradioto, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Stradioto.cfg:4
msgid "Stradioto"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Stradioto, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Stradioto.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Stradioti are the vanguard of the Ceresian armies. They are well known for "
"their audacity and daring; in hit-and-run attacks they excel, striking with "
"deadly speed and withdrawing before the foe can strike back."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Yeoman, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Yeoman.cfg:4
msgid "Yeoman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_ceresians_Yeoman, race=AE_feu_ceresians_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\human-ceresians\Yeoman.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Yeomen are the footsoldiers of the Ceresian armies. They are armed only with "
"spears, but they are staunch defenders, and many battles would have been lost"
" had it not been for the bravery of these men."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Automaton, race=mechanical
#: .\units\feudal_units\mechanical-clockwork\Automaton.cfg:4
msgid "Automaton"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Automaton, race=mechanical
#: .\units\feudal_units\mechanical-clockwork\Automaton.cfg:26
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"These are the most formidable contraptions ever faced: they have reached "
"their peak of physical prowess, and with it, they grow an extra pair of "
"limbs, which they use to scuttle like spiders, leap like frogs, and rend "
"their foes like the merciless killers they are."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Contraption, race=mechanical
#: .\units\feudal_units\mechanical-clockwork\Contraption.cfg:4
msgid "Contraption"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Contraption, race=mechanical
#: .\units\feudal_units\mechanical-clockwork\Contraption.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"These strange creatures are the primary inhabitants of the cities of the "
"clockwork dwarves; they outnumber the dwarves themselves. Close inspection "
"has revealed startling truths about these strange creatures: they have not "
"flesh and blood but gears and springs. On the field of battle, they are "
"employed by the dwarves as scouts, and their mechanical legs carry them "
"quickly and nimbly across almost any terrain."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Golem, race=mechanical
#: .\units\feudal_units\mechanical-clockwork\Golem.cfg:4
msgid "Golem"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Golem, race=mechanical
#: .\units\feudal_units\mechanical-clockwork\Golem.cfg:22
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"These are 'adult' contraptions, and as such, somewhat larger. However, they "
"do not loose the mobility of their earlier years. These bizarre animals use "
"their sticklike arms to bludgeon their foes to death, and their mercilessness"
" is feared by all."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Golem_Soldier, race=mechanical
#: .\units\feudal_units\mechanical-clockwork\Golem_Soldier.cfg:5
msgid "Golem Soldier"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\feudal_units\mechanical-clockwork\Golem_Soldier.cfg:57
msgid "rectangular shield"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Goliath, race=mechanical
#: .\units\feudal_units\mechanical-clockwork\Goliath.cfg:5
msgid "Goliath"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=ranged
#: .\units\feudal_units\mechanical-clockwork\Goliath.cfg:58
#: .\units\feudal_units\mechanical-clockwork\Iron_Golem_Soldier.cfg:57
msgid "flash cannon"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_clockwork_dwarves_Iron_Golem_Soldier, race=mechanical
#: .\units\feudal_units\mechanical-clockwork\Iron_Golem_Soldier.cfg:5
msgid "Iron Golem Soldier"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Bladesman, race=orc
#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Bladesman, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_fanatics_Bladesman, race=AE_mrc_fanatics_race, gender=male
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Bladesman.cfg:4
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Bladesman.cfg:5
#: .\units\ME_units\fanatics\a1-bladesman.cfg:5
msgid "Bladesman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Bladesman, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Bladesman.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Those orcs who excell in the use of the battle axe are informally known to "
"their bretheren as Bladesmen. Disregarding all flair or style, Bladesman "
"fight with simple and brutal strength, hacking directly at whatever stands "
"before them. Any skill gained through battle only builds on what nature has "
"already granted them."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Flanker, race=goblin
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Goblin_Flanker.cfg:4
msgid "Flanker"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Flanker, race=goblin
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Goblin_Flanker.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Some goblins have discovered that the skills gained on the hunt can be put to"
" use on the battlefield. While goblins are not overly welcome among the "
"raiding parties, they are undeniably useful and so their presence is "
"tolerated, if grudgingly."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Hunter, race=goblin
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Goblin_Hunter.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The cruel life on the steppes tends to weed out the weak early on and harden "
"those that remain. For this reason goblins are nowhere near as common on the "
"steppe as they are elsewhere. Those that do survive often make themselves "
"useful as scouts or scavengers. In hunting parties they specialise in the use"
" of barbed harpoons to lame prey, allowing an easier kill for their larger "
"orcish bretheren."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Striker, race=goblin
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Goblin_Striker.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Rather then weaken foes for others to finish off, Strikers seek the killing "
"blow themselves. However they do not possess the physique to survive long in "
"a straight fight. Instead they dart around the main forces, seeking to "
"surprise distracted enemies,having extraordinary reflexes to strike first."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Icewind_Drover, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Icewind_Drover.cfg:4
msgid "Icewind Drover"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Icewind_Drover, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Icewind_Drover.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"A Herder of sufficiant ability can become what the Steppe Orcs call a Drover,"
" the elite of the IceWind order. With age and experience in the control of "
"elemental magics. Some have claimed to be capable of summoning forth fierce "
"blizzards from a clear sky, an unlikely feat unconfirmed by outsiders. When "
"asked about the mechanics of their abilities they often answer by refering to"
" themselves as "
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Icewind_Drover.cfg:40
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Icewind_Herder.cfg:42
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Icewind_Master.cfg:40
msgid "frostwind"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Icewind_Drover.cfg:52
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Icewind_Herder.cfg:54
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Icewind_Master.cfg:52
msgid "frostshards"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Icewind_Herder, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Icewind_Herder.cfg:4
msgid "Icewind Herder"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Icewind_Herder, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Icewind_Herder.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"There is an old tale about the creation of the the IceWind order: A gang of "
"children were fishing when a very young female, hooking something bigger then"
" she could land, was dragged into the subzero waters. She did not reappear. "
"Two days later, by which time the tribe had nearly forgotton the loss, a "
"sentry witnessed an unnerving spectacle. The very same girl, delirious with "
"exhaustion and deathly pale, was spotted dragging herself from the pond.\n"
"After the incident the girl, whose name is a closely guarded secret, was "
"never the same. The tribespeople told stories of seeing her freeze a bear "
"solid, simply by looking at it, others claimed that she went out by night to "
"converse with unseen things that moved in the water. Nobody dared approch her"
" about these rumours, lest they prove to be true.\n"
"She became the founder of the IceWind order, every year she would select "
"children from the tribe to train. Whatever she taught them, it granted them a"
" mysterious influence over the elements of their habitat. The Herders "
"themselves describe this influence as "
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Icewind_Master, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Icewind_Master.cfg:4
msgid "Icewind Master"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Icewind_Master, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Icewind_Master.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Masters are a rare thing indeed, especially in a race with little aptitude "
"for magic. There is almost never more then one in each generation and, as "
"often as not, no Masters will emerge for decades. Those that do reach this "
"pinnacle of their order are often of reclusive nature, as their power "
"seperates them from the main clan. However the reasons for their estrangement"
" also grant them great respect from their brethren."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Juggernaut, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Juggernaut.cfg:4
msgid "Juggernaut"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Juggernaut, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Juggernaut.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Some of the Steppe Orcs aspiring to power realise that they actually have a "
"certain aptitude for the charge. Abandoning the pursuit of leadership, these "
"Juggernauts fling themselves on the enemy with utterly ferocious "
"recklessness. In one legendary incident, likely made greater with each "
"telling, an entire squad of elves scattered and ran at the sight of a single "
"Juggernaut bearing down on them."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Khan, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Khan.cfg:4
msgid "Khan"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Khan, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Khan.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The steppe chieftains are titled Khans, serving as both statesmen and "
"generals. They have discovered the advantages of leading from behind, urging "
"their fellows on before them. Before a battle it is customary for them to "
"mingle with the soldiers, goading them on with threats, promises, insults or "
"just primal bellows. Anything to spur them into a towering rage. Nearly "
"everyone who has fought the orcs of the steppe has spoke of the unnerving "
"roars of the orcish leaders.\n"
"Despite this, Khans are more then ready to enter the fray against any "
"especially audacious enemy that seeks to challenge them. Often, while "
"retaining their flail, they focus on using the axe as they are considered too"
" valuable an asset to risk in daredevil charges."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Massif, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Massif.cfg:4
msgid "Massif"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Massif, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Massif.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Clad in crude armour with full-face helms and swinging weapons too heavy for "
"many humans to lift, the hulking Massifs are a terrifying spectacle. They "
"invariably continue their use of the battleaxe, with fearful results."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Outcast, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Outcast.cfg:4
msgid "Outcast"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Outcast, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Outcast.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Not all initiates to the IceWind order are successful. Some lack the "
"necessary patience, others are found wanting in mental edurance. However "
"being excluded from the order cannot make them forget what they have learned.\n"
"When the Outcasts first began performing supposedly forbidden magic on their "
"own, the IceWind order raised an uproar in the tribal council. Under threat "
"of exile the Outcasts were forced to ceace their activities. But their order "
"survived, albeit in a different form. Rather then mimic their counterparts, "
"they developed a parallel sect that exists on the fringes of the tribe. The "
"magics worked by the Outcasts are undeniably crude, but have great practicle "
"use. However they are denied the mystical union with their icy home, that is "
"a right reserved for the Herders."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=melee
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Outcast.cfg:33
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Pariah.cfg:34
msgid "frigid touch"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Outcast.cfg:45
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Pariah.cfg:46
msgid "enchanted touch"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Pariah, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Pariah.cfg:4
msgid "Pariah"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Pariah, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Pariah.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Those rejects of the IceWind order who achieve veteran status in their art "
"are looked upon as akin to minor criminals. However not even the Herders can "
"deny that they are more then a little useful. Pariahs have little loyalty to "
"the clan and rarely fight except for an incentive. When they do, they "
"specialise in flushing foes from fortified positions or difficult terrain."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Rigid, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Rigid.cfg:4
msgid "Rigid"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Rigid, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Rigid.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Aptly named, the Rigid are a near unbreakable foe. They often form fall-back "
"positions behind the battle lines. Many a time the Rigid have been "
"sacrificed, delaying the enemy while the main force recovers and regroups "
"behind their unyielding wall of flesh, bone and iron. Their role is hardly a "
"glorious one and usually comes to an end jammed into a choke point against "
"hopeless odds."
msgstr ""

#. [special_note]
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Rigid.cfg:20
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Shieldbearer.cfg:20
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Stoic.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Due to their lack of weaponry this unit can not attack the enemy. When "
"attacked however, they retaliate with heavy strikes with the front of their "
"shields."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Savage, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Savage.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Unlike humans or elves, most orcs find a barbaric thrill in the chaos and "
"blood of battle. Some so much so that the experience pushes their psyche, "
"unstable and voilent at the best of times, dangerously close to the brink. "
"Teetering on the fine edge between sanity and burning instinct, they are "
"feared nearly as much by their comrades as by their enemies. Hurling "
"themselves bodily into the fray, they attack enemies solely with their fists "
"and teeth. Savages cease to use armour at all, allowing them greater speed "
"and ease of movement but sacrificing the protection it gives. Few have been "
"known to survive beyond early adulthood."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Shieldbearer, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Shieldbearer.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Some soldiers are given a special role, quite different from any of their "
"comrades. Shieldbearers carry no real weapon at all. Their unique duty is to "
"protect the wounded, patch up holes in the line and, if all looks to be lost,"
" hold off the enemy long enough to cover their retreating army. It has often "
"been said by the Steppe Orcs that while the Shieldbearers have never secured "
"victory, they have numerous times prevented utter defeat."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Skewer, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Skewer.cfg:4
msgid "Skewer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Skewer, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Skewer.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"While orcs may not be renowned for their intellectual capacity, it is well "
"within their powers of thinking to realise that a longer spear will allow "
"them to impale an enemy from greater distance. In addition, Skewers delight "
"in crafting barbed heads for their spears, further increasing their grisly "
"effectiveness."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Spearhead, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Spearhead.cfg:4
msgid "Spearhead"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Spearhead, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Spearhead.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Any Steppe Orcs wishing to lead their comrades must first show their worth in"
" battle. Spearheads lead the charge into the enemy, seeking to crash a hole "
"in the battle lines of the foe. It is a dangerous profession to say the "
"least. Their eagerness to impress frequently results in a sticky end. Their "
"crude but often effective tactics are complemented by equally crude but "
"effective weapons. A weight attached to a chain makes a perfectly servicable "
"flail."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Spearman, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Spearman.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The orcs of the steppe learnt early on that their axes were simply not "
"suitable against all foes. In accordance with this, some warriors forgo "
"further usage of the axe and take up short spears. While neccesary, the "
"change is often somewhat awkward."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Stoic, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Stoic.cfg:4
msgid "Stoic"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Stoic, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Stoic.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Stoic are embodiments of endurance, plain and simple. They are "
"characterized by sheer stubbornness and refusal to go down even under the "
"heaviest of blows. Time and again a foe has struck down a Stoic and thought "
"him dead, only to see the hardy orc lift himself from among the corpses of "
"the dead, raise his shield and reasume his position."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Vanguard, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Vanguard.cfg:4
msgid "Vanguard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Vanguard, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Vanguard.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Having proven themselves in battle, Vanguards start to assert their authority"
" others. Their experience is put to use on the battlefield, where they direct"
" the actions of their comrades. Yet often in the fracas of battle these "
"subtleties are disregarded and the Vanguards live up to their name, leading "
"by example. They have however learnt some restraint, complementing their "
"flails with a standard battleaxe similar to that used by steppe warriors."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_feu_khaganate_Warrior, race=orc
#: .\units\feudal_units\orcs-khaganate\Warrior.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The rank and file Steppe Orc soldier epitomizes the qualities of his clan. "
"Hardened, resiliant and, when necessary, desperately savage. However, while "
"loyal to their clan, they have little restraint and are often hard to "
"control. The inherent strength of their race and a harsh life of continuous "
"conflict take the place of formal training. Not known for their finesse, "
"Steppe Orcs fight with heavy two-handed battle axes."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei.cfg:11
msgid "race^Caverneus"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei.cfg:12
msgid "race+female^Cavernea"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei.cfg:13
msgid "race^Cavernei"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#. [race], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Bear
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei.cfg:14
#: .\units\imperial_units\_units.cfg:22
msgid ""
"This race is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_issaelfr_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost.cfg:11
msgid "race^Issaelf"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_issaelfr_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost.cfg:12
msgid "race+female^Issaelf"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_issaelfr_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost.cfg:13
msgid "race^Issaelfr"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_issaelfr_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost.cfg:14
msgid ""
"This race is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"This branch of the Elves lived in Alfheim, in the frigid northlands. A quiet "
"and withdrawn people, they were often falsely perceived as uncaring. This was"
" not at all true, as their allies the Marauders could attest. Rather, the "
"Frost Elves, though slow to make friends, were exceptionally steadfast and "
"loyal to the friends they had and would stand by them through thick and thin."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild.cfg:11
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild.cfg:13
msgid "race^Sidhe"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild.cfg:12
msgid "race+female^Sidhe"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild.cfg:14
msgid ""
"This race is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"When the Elves first arrived in Evrosia, they were united in one nation, led "
"by the king Vanimaro. However, upon their encounter and subsequent battles "
"with the Keltoi/Marauders, they fractured. The Issaelfr, who had taken up "
"residence in Alfheim, wanted peace, but the Sidhe would accept no such thing."
" The matter was not helped when Vanimaro was slain in combat by the "
"Marauders. Afterwards, the Sidhe dwelt in the eastern forests, their capital "
"at Mt. Stormkeep. They were extremely xenophobic, and detested, above all, "
"mankind, which they saw as a race of weaklings and traitors."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians.cfg:11
msgid "race^Arendian"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians.cfg:12
msgid "race+female^Arendian"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians.cfg:13
msgid "race^Arendians"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians.cfg:14
msgid ""
"This race is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The Arendians are the descendants of those Keltoi who did not flee from the "
"Laviniani and Dardanoi migrations. They excel at horsemanship and such."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians.cfg:11
msgid "race^Lavinian"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians.cfg:12
msgid "race+female^Lavinian"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians.cfg:13
msgid "race^Lavinians"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians.cfg:14
msgid ""
"This race is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The people of the southern hills and plains, united by Maximus the Imperator,"
" have become the Lavinian Empire. Ruled with an iron fist, but governed in "
"large part by the Senate, it seeks dominion over all the known world. They "
"learned metalworking from the Dvergken, philosophy from the Dardanoi, and "
"tactics from the Airiya. In open grassland, the terrain of their homeland, "
"they are nearly unstoppable."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_marauder_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders.cfg:11
msgid "race^Marauder"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_marauder_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders.cfg:12
msgid "race+female^Marauder"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_marauder_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders.cfg:13
msgid "race^Marauders"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_marauder_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders.cfg:14
msgid ""
"This race is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The Keltoi people have been split in two. This half, the Marauders, moved "
"further north into the great forest. These Keltoi are proud to have no "
"Dardanian or Lavinian blood flowing in their veins. (The Lavinian slur that "
"Marauders are half-orcish is, of course, false.) They now use iron weapons, "
"mainly axes and such, learned from the Lavinians and the newly arrived Elves."
" Also, now that they have been driven north by the Lavinians, they are forced"
" to spend much more energy on mere survival, making the mundane positions of "
"fisherman, hunter, and woodcutter much more important."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_nemidian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-nemidians.cfg:11
msgid "race^Nemidian"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_nemidian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-nemidians.cfg:12
msgid "race+female^Nemidian"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_nemidian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-nemidians.cfg:13
msgid "race^Nemidians"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_nemidian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-nemidians.cfg:14
msgid ""
"This race is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Before the Lavinian Empire began to rise, the Nemidians formed a separate "
"country in the desert lands to the south-east of Lavinia. They excelled in "
"the taming of wild beasts, such as horses, elephants, and hippopotamuses, but"
" they were not great craftsmen. When the Lavinians first reached out "
"southward, the Nemidians saw an opportunity, and allied themselves with the "
"new power, acting as a subservient but independent ally for eight hundred "
"years."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti.cfg:11
msgid "race^Orcei Gladiator"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti.cfg:12
msgid "race+female^Orcei Gladiator"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti.cfg:13
msgid "race^Orcei Gladiatores"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti.cfg:14
msgid ""
"This race is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The term 'Orcei Gladiatores' originally referred only to those Orcs captured "
"by the Lavinians for use in gladiatorial combat. In time, though, as various "
"gladiators escaped or won their freedom and shared their training with free "
"Orcs who had never been enslaved, this term came to be applied to all of "
"those orcs who wield the weapons of the Coliseum. The Gentes Orcorum lived "
"during the Age of the Empire."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Bear
#: .\units\imperial_units\_units.cfg:18
msgid "race^Bear"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Bear
#: .\units\imperial_units\_units.cfg:19
msgid "race+female^Bear"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Bear
#: .\units\imperial_units\_units.cfg:20
msgid "race^Bears"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Elder_Seal, race=monster
#: .\units\imperial_units\animals\Elder_Seal.cfg:4
msgid "Elder Seal"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Elder_Seal, race=monster
#: .\units\imperial_units\animals\Elder_Seal.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"When a seal slays a man in battle, it is rewarded by its elven trainer with "
"many fish, an opportunity to mate, and a small toy - for the seals are but "
"dumb animals, and if they do not expect to be rewarded, they will flee the "
"battlefield in terror, diving down to the depths of the ocean out of reach of"
" both enemy and erstwhile friend. An Elder Seal has had many feasts, many "
"offspring, and has accumulated a great many toys - though it does not play "
"with the latter so much as one might expect, for it has learnt to love "
"battle, and would rather fight than live in peace in the breeding pens of the"
" Issaelfr."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Falcon, race=falcon
#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Falcon_Lord, race=falcon
#: .\units\imperial_units\animals\Falcon.cfg:18
#: .\units\imperial_units\animals\Falcon_Lord.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Falconry."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\imperial_units\animals\Falcon.cfg:25
#: .\units\imperial_units\animals\Falcon_Lord.cfg:31
msgid "dive-bomb"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Falcon_Lord, race=falcon
#: .\units\imperial_units\animals\Falcon_Lord.cfg:4
msgid "Falcon Lord"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Fleet_Seal, race=monster
#: .\units\imperial_units\animals\Fleet_Seal.cfg:4
msgid "Fleet Seal"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Fleet_Seal, race=monster
#: .\units\imperial_units\animals\Fleet_Seal.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Though the seals are only animals, they learn from combat just as quickly as "
"men, if not quicker, and soon after their first battle they have adjusted to "
"the switch from hunting unarmed fish to attacking men armed with spear, sword"
" and bow. Their elven masters are pleased with this, and reward them well, if"
" they survive."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Ice_Bear, race=AE_imp_Sidhe_Bear
#: .\units\imperial_units\animals\Ice_Bear.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Bear"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Ice_Bear, race=AE_imp_Sidhe_Bear
#: .\units\imperial_units\animals\Ice_Bear.cfg:21
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Just a bear. A bear that could slay many men with just one swipe of its paw."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\imperial_units\animals\Ice_Bear.cfg:28
#: .\units\imperial_units\bears\Bear.cfg:25
#: .\units\imperial_units\bears\Young.cfg:25
msgid "bearhug"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Seal, race=monster
#: .\units\imperial_units\animals\Seal.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Trained seals are an important part of the military, as they enable these "
"Elves to control the seas. The use of aquatic allies is also helpful in the "
"hunt, as it provides the Issaelfr with wider access to the bounty of the "
"seas."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Bear, race=AE_imp_Sidhe_Bear
#: .\units\imperial_units\bears\Bear.cfg:5
msgid "Bear"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Bear, race=AE_imp_Sidhe_Bear
#: .\units\imperial_units\bears\Bear.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Adult bears are known for going their own way; most bears would sooner flee a"
" melee than throw themselves at risk. Some, though, for whatever reason, "
"choose not to run. These bears are a terrifying sight to behold. An adult "
"bear is a mass of muscle, claw, fur, and fury of almost unrivalled "
"proportions: even the most skilled of warriors will not look lightly on the "
"bulk of an angry, advancing bear."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Young_Bear, race=AE_imp_Sidhe_Bear
#: .\units\imperial_units\bears\Young.cfg:5
msgid "Young Bear"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Young_Bear, race=AE_imp_Sidhe_Bear
#: .\units\imperial_units\bears\Young.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"It's rare to see bears motivated enough to enter a fight in a meaningful way."
" Nevertheless, occasionally one of these enormous beasts will find some "
"motivation, whether it be danger to its territory, desperation for food, or "
"even through service to an ally. Even a juvenile bear is a fearsome sight on "
"the battlefield, rending and tearing with its claws and crushing with its "
"powerful limbs and sheer mass. Its heavy fur, thick skin, and already "
"impressive bulk defy its surprising agility in the forest."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Cavernei_Dragonguard, race=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Dragonguard.cfg:5
msgid "Dragonguard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Cavernei_Dragonguard, race=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Dragonguard.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"It is not clear why the Dragonguards are called what they are, a name given "
"by their dwarven brethren. Some speculate that the name comes from their "
"weapon of choice, these strange staves that belch fire and death. Others have"
" surmised that it is because such weapons would be a threat against even a "
"true Dragon, should such a thing be seen again in the known world. Whatever "
"the case, it is for these weapons that the guardians of the great Cavernei "
"citadels are both renowned and feared; weapons that have broken the mightiest"
" of warriors in a single blow."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Cavernei_Eagle_Master, race=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Eagle_Master.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Eagle Masters have long experience flying the Eagles, which have become an "
"extension of themselves. This special relationship makes the heart of the "
"earth-bound tremble, for these mighty pairs may strike from anywhere."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Cavernei_Eagle_Rider, race=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Eagle_Rider.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Only a few are able to bond with the mighty Eagles. Those who do may become "
"Eagle Riders, and discover the world of the skies upon the backs of these "
"flying beasts."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Cavernei_Fighter, race=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Fighter.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Cavernei Fighters wield mighty battle axes and hammers, which make them "
"feared opponents in close range combat. They are excellent in mountainous "
"terrain or underground. Though not swift, their power and endurance more than"
" compensate."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Cavernei_Guardsman, race=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Guardsman.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The most resilient dwarves sometimes join the Cavernei army as Guardsmen. "
"Slow and without a strong attack, they guard the Army's flank, soaking up a "
"lot of damage, and hurling heavy spears for defense."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Cavernei_Journeyman, race=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Journeyman.cfg:4
msgid "Journeyman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Cavernei_Journeyman, race=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Journeyman.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Journeymen are those watchers who chose to study the inscription of runes"
" on artifacts rather than their spontaneous use. They are often the ones to "
"converse with merchants and such and buy food in exchange for gold or "
"weapons, for they are more open than most of the cavernei, though they retain"
" the aura of mystery that surrounds all runic artists."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Cavernei_Lord, race=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Lord.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Clad in shining armor, these dwarves look like kings from under the "
"mountains. They wield axe and hammer with masterful skill, and can hit a "
"target with a thrown hand axe at several paces. Though slow on their feet, "
"these dwarves are a testament to the prowess of their kin."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Cavernei_Monitor, race=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Monitor.cfg:4
msgid "Monitor"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Cavernei_Monitor, race=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Monitor.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"News travels quickly underground. It is almost as if the dwarves saw "
"everything as it was happening and somehow relayed the information across "
"thousands of miles in but a few minutes. But for that to happen, the cavernei"
" would need to monitor every battlefield, every royal court, every high "
"council, and be somehow able to transport themselves instantaneously from the"
" surface world to the safety of the caverns to report the events above. Their"
" report would then somehow disseminate throughout the entire realm of the "
"dwarves in a matter of hours.\n"
"\n"
"The whole idea is, of course, absurd. Even if the dwarves do have merchants "
"spread across the continent in almost every major city, it would be simply "
"impossible for these merchants to travel to the dwarven lands and back and "
"not be noticed."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#. [attack], type=secret, range=ranged
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Monitor.cfg:37
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Monitor.cfg:49
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Observer.cfg:34
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Watcher.cfg:34
msgid "runic spell"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Cavernei_Observer, race=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_slavers_Observer, race=monster
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Observer.cfg:4
#: .\units\ME_units\slavers\e1-observer.cfg:5
msgid "Observer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Cavernei_Observer, race=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Observer.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"It has happened more than once that, on a raging battlefield, one of the "
"commanders would spot a dwarf merchant a small distance away from two sides, "
"calmly watching them fight, apparently unafraid for his life or his goods. "
"Occasionally the commander has sent his own troops to investigate. When they "
"reached the dwarf, if he was still there, which he often was not, they would "
"find him well-armed and looking surprisingly martial, but always 'just "
"passing through'. Never has anything conclusive been discovered about these "
"observers - though it is reported that once, when investigating such a "
"matter, a scout claims to have come across the dwarf sinking into the very "
"earth beneath him, leaving behind only a faint runic symbol inscribed around "
"where he supposedly vanished. This story has never been confirmed, and the "
"Cavernei, as is well known, refuse to answer the questions of the merely "
"curious."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Cavernei_Runemaster, race=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Runemaster.cfg:4
msgid "Runemaster"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Cavernei_Runemaster, race=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Runemaster.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The greatest armors and weapons, as all know, are to be found in the "
"storehouses of those who live below the surface. They gain their power not "
"only from the metallurgic skills of the cavernei, but also from the art of "
"the Runemasters; some say the two are one and the same. The Runemasters, of "
"course, save the best for themselves."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Cavernei_Sentinel, race=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Sentinel.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Sentinel, with his tower shield and great courage, refuses to yield under"
" even the strongest of enemy attacks."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Cavernei_Stalwart, race=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Stalwart.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Stalwarts, after years in battle, have fashioned new shields and strong armor"
" from the ruins of their enemies. While slow, they are feared for their "
"resilience and strength."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Cavernei_Steelclad, race=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Steelclad.cfg:5
msgid "Steelclad"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Cavernei_Steelclad, race=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Steelclad.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The more experienced Cavernei Steelclad fighters wear heavy chain mail and "
"plate armor, for which they are rightly famous."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Cavernei_Thunderer, race=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Thunderer.cfg:5
msgid "Thunderer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Cavernei_Thunderer, race=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Thunderer.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"When the Marauders first encountered the dwarves, they were mystified by the "
"power of the Cavernei Thunderers, who were able to hurl death from afar "
"through the apparatus of these strange ... 'wands' they carried into battle."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Cavernei_Thunderguard, race=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Thunderguard.cfg:5
msgid "Thunderguard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Cavernei_Thunderguard, race=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Thunderguard.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The Cavernei Thunderguards are famed for their curious weaponry, these "
"strange staves of wood and iron that make a thunderous noise in their anger. "
"The machinations behind this weaponry are a mystery, a secret taken to the "
"grave by the dwarves who wield them, and are assumed to have even forged "
"them. The most that is known are reports of dwarves pouring a strange black "
"dust into the mouth of their weapons, which some say is a food to fuel the "
"beast imprisoned within.\n"
"\n"
"Though a single shot from these 'thundersticks' can take several minutes to "
"prepare, the results are seen by the Dwarves as being well worth the wait."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Cavernei_Watcher, race=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Watcher.cfg:4
msgid "Watcher"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Cavernei_Watcher, race=AE_imp_cavernei_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\dwarves-cavernei\Watcher.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Scattered across the continent of Evrosia are certain wells that do not lead "
"down to water. Build by the hidden folk, they serve as a sort of doorbell - "
"if a surface-dweller drops something into one of these wells, the dwarves "
"will soon know of it, and will either send one of their merchants up to the "
"surface to speak with them, or not. Somehow the dwarves know before revealing"
" themselves whether or not the person on the surface is one they wish to "
"converse with. They are thought to watch the areas around where the wells are"
" found. Many suspect they watch a much broader swath of land."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Alpine_Ranger, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Alpine_Ranger.cfg:5
msgid "Alpine Ranger"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Alpine_Ranger, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Alpine_Ranger.cfg:22
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The mountains of the Issaelfr are dangerous to cross on foot, and most men "
"must take great care when doing so to avoid plummeting to their death in "
"hidden crevasses or sliding down steep and slippery embankments. The Alpine "
"Rangers, however, have such skill at mountaineering that they can move almost"
" as fast on treacherous mountains as they do on even ground."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Alpine_Ranger.cfg:37
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Alpine_Ranger.cfg:46
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Mountaineer.cfg:27
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Mountaineer.cfg:36
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Mountaineer.cfg:45
msgid "ice pick"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Archer, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Archer.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"In many areas of the Issaelfr peninsula, it is near impossible to farm or "
"raise livestock. The elves there survive by hunting the wild reindeer, and in"
" the process grow quite skilled in the use of the bow."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Bladesman, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Bladesman.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"When the elves arrived on Evrosia, they already had a long tradition of "
"swordsmanship - though never before had they fought till the death with "
"sharpened blades. This expertise, however, was primarily found in those Sidhe"
" who closely followed Vanimaro, the King of the Elves and Wielder of the "
"Thunderblade. The more independent elves who left Vanimaro and settled on the"
" northern peninsula were for the most part unskilled in the use of a sword. "
"It was a great boon to them, then, when the Marauder people agreed to an "
"exchange of hostages whereby young elven princes would learn swordsmanship in"
" the Seat of three Kings while young Marauder noblewomen would learn fey "
"magic in Alfenheim. The Marauders, upon returning home after their education,"
" found themselves unable to teach the secrets of faerie to any who had not "
"learnt from the Issaelfr, but the returning Bladesmen were more than able to "
"pass along their knowledge to the remainder of the frost elves."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Borealis, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Borealis.cfg:5
msgid "Borealis"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Borealis, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Borealis.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"It is said that, in the far north where the Issaelfr live, lamps dance in the"
" sky during winter nights, making night almost as bright as day, but not with"
" the light of the sun - it is a fey, mystical glow. Some think these lights "
"are magic, and it is from them that the northern elves draw their magic. "
"Whether or not this is true, the greatest Issaelfr archers are named for "
"them, and a Borealis does seem to hit his target more often than is really "
"natural."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Gelus, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Gelus.cfg:5
msgid "Gelus"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Gelus, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Gelus.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Elves are fascinated by the weather. In the northern lands of the Issaelfr, "
"it rains less often than it snows, and the flurries of descending snowflakes "
"are the inspiration for the Gelus, those archers who aspire to shoot arrows "
"as quickly as the snow falls. And, just as anything caught in a snowstorm is "
"unlikely to be remain untouched by every flake, the Gelus' aim is such that "
"rarely if ever does an enemy manage to dodge all of his shots."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Glaive_Master, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Glaive_Master.cfg:5
msgid "Glaive Master"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Glaive_Master, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Glaive_Master.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The glaive is a curious weapon. It is, essentially, a combination of sword "
"and spear, with a long blade and an even longer shaft. But it is more than "
"that, and only a true expert can really wield a glaive to its full potential."
" Rare is the Issaelfr who becomes one, but he who does is a force to be "
"reckoned with."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Glaive_Master.cfg:41
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Glaivier.cfg:40
msgid "azegiz"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Glaivier, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Glaivier.cfg:5
msgid "Glaivier"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Glaivier, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Glaivier.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Not all Bladesmen are alike. Some choose the path of the solitary ice roamer,"
" but many others prefer to fight in an organized fashion, lining up on the "
"field of battle with other likeminded elves against whatever enemy. These "
"elves quickly see the usefulness of the glaive, for it can act both as a "
"spear and sword, and so the Issaelfr army does not need to train and equip a "
"separate group of spearmen - the glavier can fight in the ranks alongside "
"bladesmen, then when a spear is needed, they simply use their weapon "
"differently. This great benefit is more than worth the slight inconvenience "
"of learning a new weapon."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Ice_Dancer, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Ice_Dancer.cfg:5
msgid "Ice Dancer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Ice_Dancer, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Ice_Dancer.cfg:22
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Issaelfr and Sidhe have many things in common, and among them is a love "
"for elegance. The Ice Dancer, like so many of his Sidhe brethren, makes "
"swordsmanship a thing of beauty. The Dancers, though, tend to be rather aloof"
" from Issaelfr society, and sometimes one wonders whether these elves would "
"not have preferred to live in the groves of Mount Stormkeep rather than in "
"the frigid wastes of the northern peninsula.\n"
"\n"
"This wonder, however, is quickly erased when one sees with what grace they "
"glide across the ice and snow found only in their adopted homeland."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Ice_Roamer, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Ice_Roamer.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Roamer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Ice_Roamer, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Ice_Roamer.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The most elegant of Bladesmen become Ice Roamers, and perfect the skill of "
"fighting upon frozen water with the speed of one fighting on land - and have "
"learned to move and fight on land faster than one would think possible. They "
"fight alone, and often make their way through enemy lines to strike at the "
"opponent's rear to break a hole for their slower allies to take advantage of."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Mistral_Cryomancer, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race, gender=female
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Mistral_Cryomancer.cfg:4
msgid "female^Mistral Cryomancer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Mistral_Cryomancer, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race, gender=female
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Mistral_Cryomancer.cfg:21
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"'Cryomancer' is a Lavinian term meaning magician of the ice. The Cryomancers "
"are content to be known by this; they have no name for themselves. It is an "
"apt name, in any case; the Cryomancer calls on the weather of her homeland to"
" smother the enemy in ice and snow, and more often than not, the weather "
"obliges, even when she is far from the northern winter."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Mistral_Cryomancer.cfg:39
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Mistral_Glacialist.cfg:38
msgid "ice"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Mistral_Glacialist, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race, gender=female
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Mistral_Glacialist.cfg:4
msgid "female^Mistral Glacialist"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Mistral_Glacialist, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race, gender=female
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Mistral_Glacialist.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The magic of the Mistral Magus is that of wind; that of the Glacialist is of "
"ice. She has harnessed the raw power of the weather of her adopted homeland, "
"and in doing so become more powerful in battle than many who carry more "
"inmpressive weapons than her small dagger."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Mistral_Magus, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race, gender=female
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Mistral_Magus.cfg:5
msgid "female^Mistral Magus"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Mistral_Magus, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race, gender=female
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Mistral_Magus.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"When the wife of the first Issaelf king first set foot on the northern "
"continent, she saw nothing but rock, snow, and ice and felt nothing but the "
"chill wind against her face, and she knew she had found her home. Ever since,"
" the women of the Issaelfr have harnessed the wind of their homeland against "
"any who would challenge their right to live there."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=melee
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Mistral_Magus.cfg:24
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Mistral_Rime_Castellan.cfg:28
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Mistral_Rime_Keeper.cfg:27
msgid "wand"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Mistral_Rime_Castellan, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race, gender=female
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Mistral_Rime_Castellan.cfg:5
msgid "female^Mistral Rime Castellan"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Mistral_Rime_Castellan, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race, gender=female
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Mistral_Rime_Castellan.cfg:22
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"It is rumored that the Rime Castellans have captured the wind and hold it "
"prisoner, but when asked, they deny this, saying they carry with them only "
"the power to summon the wind, not the wind itself. Either way, it is clear "
"that the Mistral Rime Castellans have immense power at their disposal, able "
"to death out life and death as they choose."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Mistral_Rime_Keeper, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race, gender=female
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Mistral_Rime_Keeper.cfg:5
msgid "Mistral Rime Keeper"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Mistral_Rime_Keeper, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race, gender=female
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Mistral_Rime_Keeper.cfg:21
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The ice and the gale can be used to restore life, and not only to take it. "
"The Rime Keeper has learned this; the sack she carries holds within it the "
"power of the wind, and when she opens it, it helps friend and destroys foe."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Mountaineer, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Mountaineer.cfg:21
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Those Archers who prove themselves worthy, and demonstrate leadership "
"ability, are promoted to the ranks of the Mountaineers. Hardy warriors who "
"can withstand the elements, and perform well in the mountains and hills as "
"well as in the ice and snow, they will do all they can to help their people "
"to survive in their harsh environment."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Yakmount_Margrave, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Yakmount_Margrave.cfg:5
msgid "Yakmount Margrave"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Yakmount_Margrave, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Yakmount_Margrave.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"When the elves settled in Alfenheim, they had never been a horse-riding "
"people - the Sidhe never adopted mounts - and so it was not with the aim of "
"finding a substitute for the no longer useful horse that the Issaelfr tamed "
"the wild yak. It was because the northernmost settlements of the Issaelfr "
"could not be supplied without a beast of burden of some kind. The Issaelfr "
"soon learned of the usefulness of mounts in battle as well, and eventually "
"the elves were experts at the use of this nontraditional cavalry."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Yak_Knight, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Yak_Knight.cfg:6
msgid "Yak Knight"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Yak_Knight, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Yak_Knight.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The wilderness of Alfenheim is hard to travel if on foot, and impossible if "
"mounted on a horse - it simply cannot keep its footing on the treacherous "
"passes of the northern mountains. The Issaelfr have solved this problem by "
"taming the yaks native to that land and riding them. They have found them "
"useful in battle, as well."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Yak_Rider, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Yak_Rider.cfg:6
msgid "Yak Rider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Issaelfr_Yak_Rider, race=AE_imp_issaelfr_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-frost\Yak_Rider.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Some Issaelfr have tamed wild yaks, native to the mountains of the northern "
"peninsula, which they use as mounts. Though other races cannot understand "
"their predilection for these odd beasts, and cannot imagine riding them, the "
"cavalry is rightly feared for its cold efficiency."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Bladespinner, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Bladespinner.cfg:5
msgid "Bladespinner"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Bladespinner, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Bladespinner.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Many men of the southern plains believed the tales of elven warriors who "
"danced with their blades were just that - tales. The Marauders, however, knew"
" all too well of the reality of the Bladespinners, whose swords would spin in"
" dizzying patterns, deflecting the much heavier human swords with ease, and "
"then cut the enemy in three places seemingly simultaneously, though the "
"Bladespinners wield only two blades."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Blizzardlord, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Blizzardlord.cfg:5
msgid "Blizzardlord"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Blizzardlord, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Blizzardlord.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The Sidhe nobility, though not accepting commoners into their ranks, "
"nonetheless pick the most skilled and loyal Snowdancers and raise them to the"
" rank of Blizzardlord, giving them authority over the Hoarfrosters and "
"Snowdancers. The expectation is that the Blizzardlords will keep their "
"fellows loyal and obedient to the nobility and train new recruits."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Blizzardlord.cfg:37
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Hoarfroster.cfg:33
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Snowdancer.cfg:33
msgid "snow wind"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Dark_Thunderblade, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Dark_Thunderblade.cfg:5
msgid "Dark Thunderblade"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Dark_Thunderblade, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Dark_Thunderblade.cfg:21
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"When Vaniyera the Shadowdancer took up the thunderblade of the west after the"
" death of Leithan, he brought together a dancer's capacity for cunning and "
"deception with the pure fey power of the storm. His possession of both of "
"these styles of magic meant that, though his title was that of Thunderblade, "
"his powers were unlike those of any other Sidhe."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Dark_Thunderblade.cfg:36
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Dark_Thunderblade.cfg:48
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Thunderblade.cfg:24
msgid "thunderblade"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Fury, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Fury.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The wild elf Furies do not wield an extraordinarily powerful weapon, but they"
" are dangerous nonetheless, for they fight as if fey, and will press the "
"battle long past when any reasonable man would have pulled back. Their "
"madness often leads to their death, but even more often it will lead to the "
"death of the enemy."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Herald, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Herald.cfg:21
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Sidhe do not fight with any battle formation; each elf is left to his own"
" devices to slay as many of the foe as possible. Nevertheless, though they "
"fight independently, they do not ignore each other during the battle. The "
"Herald is a perfect example of this. When not fighting himself, he will sing "
"out a war chant, and those other elves who are fighting will listen to it and"
" let the music guide them, inspiring them on to great deeds."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Hoarfroster, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Hoarfroster.cfg:5
msgid "Hoarfroster"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Hoarfroster, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Hoarfroster.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Some Sidhe commoners long for the prestige of their magic-using betters. They"
" try with all their might to master the art of casting lightning at their "
"foes with deadly precision, but find it is beyond them. At the last, however,"
" they discover that there is an element they can somewhat control -- frozen "
"water. This is their claim to greatness."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Raindancer, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Raindancer.cfg:5
msgid "Raindancer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Raindancer, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Raindancer.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Sidhe nobility are powerful mages. They have concentrated their powers on"
" the calling of lighting from an otherwise clear sky, and their dancing among"
" the lightning is what gave them their name of raindancers. Alas, the young "
"and brash noblemen are uninterested in study, and more likely to go practice "
"their swordplay than their magic."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Shadowdancer, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Shadowdancer.cfg:5
msgid "Shadowdancer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Shadowdancer, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Shadowdancer.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Some men accuse the Shadowdancers of the use of dark magic, and many would "
"believe it, for their ability to slip behind enemy lines and stab the foe in "
"the back is truly uncanny. Most of them deny any magical knowledge whatsoever"
" - a wise move, for in the Sidhe lands magic is reserved to the Raindancer "
"class - but some defy the Council and proudly admit to the use of what they "
"call a 'natural fey power for cunning and deception'. It is not dark magic, "
"they say, but the use of the faerie talents they naturally possess. The "
"Council, with most of its members afraid of a Shadowdancer blade finding them"
" in their sleep, does nothing about this blatant disregard for its authority."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Snowdancer, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Snowdancer.cfg:5
msgid "Snowdancer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Snowdancer, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Snowdancer.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The Sidhe nobility do not lightly accept the fact that some among their "
"subjects seek to join the ranks of the mages, but they are pragmatic and "
"acknowledge that even weak ice magic is a useful supplement to their own "
"skills, as long as its practitioners remember their place. Therefore, they "
"have established the rank of Snowdancer as a reward for Hoarfrosters who "
"excel in both skill and loyalty."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Stormlord, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Stormlord.cfg:4
msgid "Stormlord"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Stormlord, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Stormlord.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"A Stormlord has spent his entire life studying magic. He has sacrificed all "
"else for this goal - including his skill with the sword. In exchange he has "
"reached the absolute pinnacle of magical power. He can go no higher, for "
"there is nowhere higher to go. He knows, it is said, all there is to know, "
"about air, water, fire and earth. It is a shame that his wisdom manifests "
"itself on the battlefield only as a massive thunderous display of raw power -"
" but it is fitting, for it is the beauty seen in the power of the storm that "
"inspired him to study magic in the first place."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=melee
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Stormlord.cfg:24
msgid "lightning staff"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Tempest, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Tempest.cfg:5
msgid "Tempest"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Tempest, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Tempest.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Tempest aims to make his magic live up to his name. He calls down "
"lightning from the sky, using magic whose raw destructive power is almost "
"unequaled."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Thunderblade, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Thunderblade.cfg:5
msgid "Thunderblade"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Thunderblade, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Thunderblade.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"When Vanimaro, the first King of the Sidhe, died in battle, the shards of his"
" mighty sword were collected and kept preciously by the greatest wild elf "
"mages. Twelve great Thunderblades were then made, each containing a shard of "
"the original, and each containing a part of the power of the storm wielded by"
" Vanimaro. These blades were awarded to the best of the swordsmen found among"
" the Sidhe, and they were given rule over the various marches of the Sidhe "
"forests and over the armies of those marches."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Tracker, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Tracker.cfg:22
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"It would be said that Wild Elf Trackers are outcasts from Sidhe society, "
"except that there is no Sidhe society to speak of except that found at Mount "
"Stormkeep; there are no other cities, and each wild elf lives on his own or "
"with his family, banding together only when they have a common enemy. The "
"Trackers are only different in that they do not bother to settle down in any "
"one place. They roam the forests of the Sidhe, living off the land and "
"guarding it from invasion - they are often the first to respond to an "
"attacking force. They can cover as much ground in one day as an armored man "
"can cover in two, and use this to their advantage when in battle. Their "
"primary spear they coat with the sap of a certain shrub, giving it a "
"poisonous tinge, but they would consider it cowardly to do this for their "
"javelins as well."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Veiledblade, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Veiledblade.cfg:5
msgid "Veiledblade"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Veiledblade, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Veiledblade.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Wild Elves consider themselves an honorable people, and so the "
"Veiledblades are always tolerated rather uneasily - they are, it is thought, "
"merely ignoble assassins. This dislike continues up until the Veiledblades "
"are needed in battle, at which point the Sidhe proclaim that deception is a "
"natural part of war, and that Veiledblades are not assassins, but rather "
"skirmishers, a quite noble profession."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Wanderer, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Wanderer.cfg:22
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Sidhe, already a solitary race, sometimes have elves among them even more"
" so than normal who prefer the tracking and scouting to marching with the "
"general army. These are generally the same elves who refuse to settle in one "
"place, wandering the land and avoiding all contact with other elves except "
"when absolutely necessary."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Wardancer, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Wardancer.cfg:5
msgid "Wardancer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Wardancer, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Wardancer.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Wardancers are legends even among the Sidhe. The skill of a Bladespinner may "
"seem unbelievable, but he is an amateur compared to a mighty Wardancer. When "
"facing a Wardancer, a man will be killed three times over before he touches "
"the ground, and onlookers will be unable to tell in what order the two blades"
" hit, or which one struck the extra blow."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Warmage, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Warmage.cfg:5
msgid "War Mage"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Warmage, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Warmage.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Few Sidhe are capable of staying away from battle for long. The War Mages are"
" wild elf nobility who, though trained as mages, spend most of their time "
"with sword in hand. Their prowess with the sword easily equals that of a "
"warrior, and their magic is a welcome ally."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Warrior, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Warrior.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The lithe and strong Sidhe warriors are deadly swordsmen, capable of dealing "
"fast, strong blows and avoiding them just as easily. Their only weakness is "
"their frailty due to their distaste for armor."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Warsinger, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Warsinger.cfg:5
msgid "Warsinger"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Warsinger, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Warsinger.cfg:22
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Warsinger is a master of the songs of combat. A powerful warrior himself,"
" he can drive his companions into battle frenzies with his war chants, "
"driving them on to great deeds while he himself slaughters the enemy."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Whirlwind, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Whirlwind.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The speed and furocity of a Wild Elf Whirlwind is unmatched by any other "
"warrior. He throws himself into battle, slashing his sword, up and down, left"
" and right, in a cyclone of destruction, and refuses to pull back until he is"
" physically unable to continue fighting."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Wildblade, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Wildblade.cfg:5
msgid "Wildblade"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Wildblade, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Wildblade.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"A normal elf lives for thousands of years; one who decides to take the path "
"of a Wildblade has decided that this is too long. Better a short and glorious"
" life of battle, they say, than a death in old age. This conviction lends the"
" Wildblades a courage, some would say recklessness, in battle that is "
"unmatched. The lifespan of a Wildblade is short, for an elf, but those of his"
" enemies are shorter."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Windlasher, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Windlasher.cfg:5
msgid "Windlasher"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Windlasher, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Windlasher.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Those Raindancers who wish to focus all of their energy on the study of magic"
" must follow the path of the Windlasher. They do not have the master-student "
"relationship of the Thunderblades, for magic, the Sidhe believe, is best "
"learned alone. A Windlasher, who has aleady learned the fundamentals of their"
" art from the school at Mount Stormkeep, will continue his studies in "
"isolation - even if he continues living in the city at Stormkeep, he will "
"spend most of his days locked in his garden deep in contemplation."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Windrunner, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Windrunner.cfg:5
msgid "Windrunner"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Windrunner, race=AE_imp_sidhe_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\elves-wild\Windrunner.cfg:23
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"A tale floats around the swamps of Marauderdom involving a Wild Elf "
"Windrunner and the high queen of the Issaelfr. The Windrunner, who in the "
"course of his wanderings found himself in Alfenheim, challenged the queen, a "
"Mistral Rime Castellan, to a race. The winds which the Castellan carried in "
"her pouch would be unleashed and sent against him, and if they caught him, he"
" would tell the queen how to counter the poison found on the spears of the "
"Windrunners. If he managed to outrun them, the queen would grant him an "
"unnamed favor. The sidhe lost his brash wager, and that is how the Rime "
"Castellans learnt the art of curing poison.\n"
"\n"
"One version says that, anyway. Those who have seen the Windrunners in action "
"doubt the purported outcome of the race. Their primary spear they coat with "
"the sap of a certain shrub, giving it a poisonous tinge, but they would "
"consider it cowardly to do this for their javelins as well."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Archer, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Archer.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"On the vast plains of Arendia, where the horse is king, even archers fight "
"from horseback. In the hills and forests of the eastern half of that country,"
" however, horses are rarer, and there most fighters, archers and swordsmen, "
"fight on foot. The stability of having two feet on the ground gives to the "
"Arendian Archers superior power with the sword, but at the expense of the "
"great speed of the Bowriders."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Arrow_Wind, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Arrow_Wind.cfg:5
msgid "Arrow Wind"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Arrow_Wind, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Arrow_Wind.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The name 'Arrow Wind' comes from an old folk tale in which the most skilled "
"archer in all of Arendia was challenged to prove his prowess by firing arrows"
" repeatedly in an outline around his his wife, and yet not kill her. When "
"asked about this later, the wife likened the experience to a gentle breeze.\n"
"\n"
"Nowadays the appelation has come to refer to the sound of their arrows. "
"Capable of putting three arrows in the air before the first has hit the "
"target, the sound of so many arrows in flight is likened to a rushing wind of"
" death over the battlefield."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Battlear, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Battlear.cfg:4
msgid "Battlear"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Battlear, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Horseman, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Mounter_Warrior, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Battlear.cfg:17
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Horseman.cfg:17
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Mounted_Warrior.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
" "
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Boltrider, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Boltrider.cfg:5
msgid "Boltrider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Boltrider, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Boltrider.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Shooting a bow from horseback is almost guaranteed to be less effective than "
"with two feet planted firmly on the ground, but the Boltrider devotes his "
"energies to reducing the difference as much as is humanly possible. He very "
"nearly succeeds in bridging the gap - indeed, if taking as normal the poor "
"archery of his south-eastern Lavinian neighbors, he succeeds admirably."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Bowknight, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Bowknight.cfg:5
msgid "Bowknight"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Bowknight, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Bowknight.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Bowknights are usually minor lords in the west of Arendia. Here there are "
"huge tracts of barren land, land that could perhaps with great effort be "
"irrigated, but is really good only for a nomadic lifestyle of raising cattle "
"and horses. The huge swathes of land and isolation of each individual clan "
"causes several clans to go rogue, raiding their neighbors mercilessly. This "
"bandit-like behavior leads to the rogues being treated as no better than "
"outlaws, and it is the bowriders, because they are most used to hunting down "
"bandits, who are placed in charge of enforcing this law."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Bowmaster, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Bowmaster.cfg:5
msgid "Bowmaster"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Bowmaster, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Bowmaster.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Bowmasters are in many places the true lords of western Arendia, for all the "
"bowknights answer to them, to whom the bowriders answer in turn. This means "
"that, while the great plains of the west often seem ripe for conquest, if any"
" force tried to invade those lands, they would soon face a sizable army of "
"mounted archers who could lead the invaders on an exhausting goose-chase "
"before wheeling around and peppering the enemy with arrows. This tactic "
"quickly convinces all but the most determined foe that conquering western "
"Arendia is not worth the trouble, and so normally the only trouble the "
"western Arendians have is with internal banditry."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Bowrider, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Bowrider.cfg:5
msgid "Bowrider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Bowrider, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Bowrider.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Bowriders come from the western part of Arendia. There they are the hunters, "
"as a horse is the only thing which can keep up with prey in the savanna that "
"covers the area. This means that they have had great practice firing bows "
"from horseback. This experience makes them an invaluable part of Arendias "
"army, where they use hit and run tactics to weaken the enemy and constantly "
"harry their flanks."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Chief, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Chief.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The horsemen of western Arendia band into clans comprised for the most part "
"of extended families, and the chieftain of a clan is usually the eldest fit "
"male. The clan chief does not wield all the power, for the bowriders, who "
"band together, comprise half of the clan's military might, but his influence "
"should not be underestimated."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Druid, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mie_thelian_druid, race=AE_mie_thelian
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Druid.cfg:5
#: .\units\MiE_units\human-thelians\2_Druid.cfg:6
msgid "Druid"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Druid, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Mounter_Marksman, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Shaman, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Warlock, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Warlord, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Druid.cfg:20
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Mounted-Marksman.cfg:25
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Shaman.cfg:20
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Warlock.cfg:21
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Warlord.cfg:21
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
" "
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Feather_Bow, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Feather_Bow.cfg:5
msgid "Feather Bow"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Feather_Bow, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Feather_Bow.cfg:24
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"A result of a rigorous selection process, the Feather Bows are among the best"
" archers in all the land. They gain their name from the tassel of feathers "
"tied to the upper and lower parts of their bowstring, a combination of a "
"badge of office and a silencing device for the bowstring. It is also said "
"that when they fire, the sound is like that of a feather falling... until the"
" arrow strikes home. Different clans use feathers colored with different "
"dyes."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Hero, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Hero.cfg:21
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Once a wanderer has regained his honour he has usually done enough for the "
"good of the people of Arendia that he is regarded as a hero by those who once"
" scorned him. These men have fought in many a battle and usually this "
"experience is put to good use by a clan in the area, or as bodyguards to the "
"royal family. Heros are also regarded as the only people skillful enough to "
"wield double bladed swords. These agile weapons are the most deadly and sharp"
" in all of Arendia, forged by royal smiths in the forges of the capital."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Horse_Master, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Horse_Master.cfg:5
msgid "Horse Master"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Horse_Master, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Horse_Master.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
" Heaviest of all Aredian calvary is well armored againist impact attacks and "
"also crushing with ease anything that is on their way."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Horse_Master.cfg:30
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Mounted_Warrior.cfg:29
msgid "morning-star"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Hunter, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Hunter.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Hunters are an ancient cult in Arendia. These men used to go out, usually "
"with only the cloaks on their backs for protection, and hunt the dragons that"
" lived in and around Arendia. They were known as hunters for they had not yet"
" found their prey. When they did, and had single-handedly killed it, they "
"became known as slayers. The Arendians have no word for one who has found a "
"dragon and not slain him, for all such combats were required to be to the "
"death, but the closest word would be 'fodir', which translates roughly as "
"'food.'\n"
"\n"
" Of course these days there are only wyverns for them to hunt and kill, and "
"few enough of them anyway, but the hunter cult lives on as an unofficial "
"segment of Arendian clan armies. They operate as advance infantry in special "
"situations. They do not take orders, but must be asked to assist. They are "
"typically glad to wield their blades in Arendian service."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Mounter_Marksman, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Mounted-Marksman.cfg:5
msgid "Mounted Marksman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Mounter_Warrior, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Mounted_Warrior.cfg:5
msgid "Mounted Warrior"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Slayer, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Slayer.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"In the days of Dragons, when a hunter fought and single handedly killed a "
"dragon he became known as a slayer. Any slayer could be recognised as such by"
" a crimson red cloak, a colour which nobody else could wear, for they always "
"wore one cut from the dragon's wing as a token of their victory. A "
"right-handed slayer would take his cloak from the left wing, and a "
"left-handed slayer would take his from the right wing. The unused wing was "
"typically made into a tent, or a battle flag. Teeth became arrow-heads. Horns"
" became daggers or drinking horns. No part of the dragon went unused, and "
"none but a slayer could own anything crafted from the corpse.\n"
"\n"
" Today there is no man in all of Arendia that could match the old Slayers for"
" skill, simply because there are no true dragons left to practice on, only "
"wyverns. However, once a hunter is considered to be amongst the most skilled "
"of his kind, and after rigorous trials and testing, he is awarded a crimson "
"red cloak; but not a dragon one. For the last one of them is stored in the "
"palace, and was won by the first king of Arendia, when he killed the greatest"
" dragon to ever have blackened Arenida's skies."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Swordsman, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Swordsman.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The swordsmen of eastern Arendia fight on foot, the better to move through "
"the hills and forests that pervade the region - one border of the vast sea of"
" grass that stretches from the western mountains to the eastern coastline. "
"Remembering their ancestry - the first Arendians lived nomadic lives on the "
"plains, and only after they conquered the forestlands did some of them "
"dismount - they fight with only as much armor as a mounted horseman would "
"use, always prepared to swing back into the saddle and fight from horseback "
"once more. The opportunity, sadly, rarely presents itself."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Wanderer, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Wanderer.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Wanderers are outcasts from Arendian society, haveing disgraced either "
"themselves or their families. They now seek to regain their honour by "
"wandering the land and killing all who are dishonourable or evil. Often these"
" include other wanderers who have given up on this quest as these men are "
"dead to most Arendians because of their crimes and lack of remorse for them. "
"However, despite this, untill they are considered to have regained their "
"honour they are scorned and mocked by all, never to their faces, for they are"
" famous for their short tempers and deadliness with any blade, but always "
"behind their backs.\n"
"\n"
"Of course, although they, like all Arendians, are obsessed with the honour "
"that they are trying to regain, this hasn't stopped them from learning a few "
"dirty tricks along the way. Wanderers are adept at knife throwing, and have "
"been known to kill men fifty feet away in one snake like movement and flick "
"of the wrist."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Warlord, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Warlord.cfg:5
msgid "Warlord"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Arendians_Warrior, race=AE_imp_arendians_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-arendians\Warrior.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"After the rise of the Lavinians the clans on the southern edges of the plains"
" of Arendia had a problem. Most of their fighters used swords or arrows to "
"fight, as had been their tradition for centuries, however these Lavinians all"
" wore metal armour. Wearing metal as armour was not an unknown concept for "
"the arendians, but it was only worn by their close combat fighters, and their"
" best archers, it never covered their whole body because they simply did not "
"have enough, and it got in the way when fighting because it was so heavy. And"
" so, to adapt to this new threat, these clans started to train their fighters"
" to use maces instead of swords, because although maces didn't pierce the "
"armour, it could crush or crumple it, wounding the wearer."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Aquilifer, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Aquilifer.cfg:5
msgid "Aquilifer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Aquilifer, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Aquilifer.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Having a lion-skin headdress on his head, a golden eagle at the top of his "
"standard, and the red-and-gold of the Legion on his armor, the Aquilifer "
"truly is a symbol of the Empire itself. There is only one Aquilifer in each "
"legion, and he must be a bold, courageous and wise man to hold that post. By "
"carrying the Legion's Eagle, he makes himself a target for any enemy, and "
"often must fight, and die, protecting it. The Eagle serves as inspiration and"
" an object of honor for all of the Legionaires, and it will give them "
"strength in the battle even in the dead of night."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Archuballistarius, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Archuballistarius.cfg:5
msgid "Archuballistarius"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Archuballistarius, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Archuballistarius.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Lavinian Legion will often, in its conquests, come across a fortified "
"town that refuses to surrender. Instead of storming the walls of the city, "
"they simply wheel out the artillery. The town invariably falls. The "
"Archuballistarius is also effective on the battlefield, although it moves "
"rather slowly."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Auxiliary, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Auxiliary.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Although the Legionaires make up the core of the army, there is an equal "
"number of Auxilia in the Legion's ranks as well. The Auxilia do not have a "
"shield or much armor, and wield only a broadsword, but their quickness, "
"adaptability and plentifulness makes up for this. Their one hope is that, by "
"serving in the Legion for long enough, they will be granted Lavinian "
"citizenship, and all the privileges that come with that."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Field_Ballista, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Ballista.cfg:5
msgid "Field Ballista"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Field_Ballista, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Ballista.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"A Lavinian Field Ballista's primary purpose is attacking the cities that "
"oppose the Legion's expansion. However, it is also deadly against enemies on "
"the battlefield. It is small enough that transportation is possible, although"
" not exactly fast, and the ballista's controller is able to defend himself "
"with a gladius if the ballista is attacked."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Bowman, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_tribe_Bowman, race=AE_mrc_tribe_race, gender=male
#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_dark_legion_Bowman, race=human, gender=male
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Bowman.cfg:5
#: .\units\ME_units\tribe\b1-bowman.cfg:5
#: .\units\misc_units\dark_legion\Dark_Bowman.cfg:4
msgid "Bowman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Bowman, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Bowman.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Lavinian army does not consist only of Legionaires and Auxilia, although "
"those are the primary fighters. There are also archers, the Lavinian Bowman. "
"However, even these have not given up the Lavinian affinity for heavy "
"protective armor. They have given up some mobility and efficacy in combat, "
"but have made themselves nearly indestructable.\n"
"\n"
"The Bowman does not carry a sword. Although this will leave him vulnerable to"
" most enemies, it allows him to instead carry around a burning ember, which "
"he can use to light up his arrows before he sends them. The Bowman is so well"
" armored that when he is defending, he will take reduced damage from physical"
" weapons."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Centurion, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Centurion.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"A Centurion, commander of an entire Century, is well knowledged in the "
"tactics and strategy needed for such a post. He has a large red crest on his "
"helmet, and unlike a normal Legionaire carries a large spear along with his "
"gladius and pila. He is not as formidable a fighter as a Praetorian Guard, "
"but his knowledge and leadership more than make up for this."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Centurion.cfg:54
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Decurion.cfg:54
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Legionnaire.cfg:47
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Praetorian_Guard.cfg:55
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Propugnator.cfg:55
msgid "pilum"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Decurion, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Decurion.cfg:5
msgid "Decurion"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Decurion, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Decurion.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"A Decurion commands a group of ten legionnaires, leading them with expert "
"precision. The crest on his helm has been turned sideways to make him "
"recognizable to his troops in battle, and his armor is the color of gold for "
"the same reason. Although he no longer bears the heavy, rectangular shield of"
" the Legionaire, he is still a formidible opponent, and the loss of the "
"shield actually allows him to attack quicker with his gladius."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Funditor, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Funditor.cfg:5
msgid "Funditor"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Funditor, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Funditor.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The Funditor's two weapons are the gladius and the sling. Although skilled "
"with both of them, he has put most of his effort into practicing with the "
"sling, firing quick and accurate volleys in every battle. Nonetheless, he can"
" fight and win in hand-to-hand combat against a rawly recruited Legionaire. "
"The Funditor is as good as the best Lavinian archer, both due to his own "
"skill, and the Lavinian incompetence with the bow and insistence on defense, "
"rather than offense, from the Saggitarius."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Legionaire, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Legionnaire.cfg:4
msgid "Legionaire"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Legionaire, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Legionnaire.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Legionaire is the backbone of the Lavinian army. He begins training and "
"drilling at a very young age, and can serve for up to twenty-five years. His "
"main weapons are the gladius, a short stabbing sword, and the pilum, a "
"throwing spear that sticks into an enemy's shield, weighing him down and "
"often causing him to trip. Normally the Legionaires battle in formation, with"
" the Auxilia protecting the flanks, but on his own a Legionaire can still "
"fight bravely. The shield of the Legionaire is so large that it is easiest "
"for him to retaliate to melee attacks with it, rather than switching to his "
"gladius."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Light_Infantryman, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Light_Infantry.cfg:5
msgid "Light Infantryman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Light_Infantryman, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Light_Infantry.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Having taken a shine to the gladius they were originally equipped with, the "
"Lavinian Light Infantryman has kept that sword and now wears a light leather "
"shield. Alone among all members of the Lavinian army, he does not wield any "
"ranged weapon, but his relative litheness and quick feet allow him to run "
"back and forth from battle front to battle front. Also, his speed and strong "
"sword make him perfect for taking out archers after the enemy's front lines "
"have been decimated."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Praetorian_Guard, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Praetorian_Guard.cfg:4
msgid "Praetorian Guard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Praetorian_Guard, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Praetorian_Guard.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Praetorian Guard's task is to protect the Imperator and his family - or "
"simply whomever his employer is. Having been chosen from the rank and file of"
" the Legion, he now occupies an extremely prestigious position, that of "
"Imperial Bodyguard. His shield, large enough to protect both him and his "
"charge, he can also use to stun his opponent, and perhaps kill him. In "
"addition to this shield, he bears two throwing spears and a short sword. The "
"shield of the Praetorian Guard is so large that it is easiest for him to "
"retaliate to melee attacks with it, rather than switching to his gladius."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Propugnator, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Propugnator.cfg:5
msgid "Propugnator"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Propugnator, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Propugnator.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Propugnator, a skilled fighter, has chosen not to accept the rank of an "
"officer, and instead to continue fighting on the front lines. He bears a very"
" large shield with an embossed oval in the center, which he uses both to "
"protect himself exceeding well, and to smash his opponent's head with, "
"temporarily stunning him. Aside from that, his weapons are the same as an "
"ordinary Legionaire - a gladius, and two pila. The shield of the Propugnator "
"is so large that it is easiest for him to retaliate to melee attacks with it,"
" rather than switching to his gladius."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Rorarius, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Rorarius.cfg:5
msgid "Rorarius"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Rorarius, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Rorarius.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The Rorarius is as good a melee fighter as almost any member of the Legion "
"proper, simply because his lightweight shield and lack of armor allows him to"
" make much stronger stabs with his gladius. However, this offensive "
"capability comes at a price; although he deals more damage than even a "
"Praetorian, he takes more in return, and is unable to retaliate at all "
"against enemy archers. Rorarii are indeed powerful fighters, but they are "
"only support troops, and without either Legionaires or other Auxilia they are"
" ineffective against most armies."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Saggitarius, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Saggitarius.cfg:5
msgid "Saggitarius"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Saggitarius, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Saggitarius.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Saggitarii are the best archers the Lavinians have to offer - though that"
" is not as great praise as one might imagine. They have decent skill with the"
" bow, but they sacrifice power for accuracy, and speed for for "
"indestructability. When a Saggitarius hides behind his great shield, no "
"force, however, powerful, can destroy him without first destroying it. The "
"Saggitarius is so well armored that when he is defending, he will take "
"reduced damage from physical weapons."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Siege_Archer, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Siege_Archer.cfg:5
msgid "Siege Archer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Siege_Archer, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Siege_Archer.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Much of Lavinian military strategy was determined by the need, early in their"
" history, to capture the fortified cities that first opposed the rise of the "
"Empire. These towns could not be taken by marching Legionaires, and so the "
"Lavinians were forced to learn the art of the siege. Most important for a "
"successful siege was the use of ballistae and catapults, but second only to "
"that was the use of the Siege Archer. These bowmen did not shoot masses of "
"arrows into the opposing town, but rather, hiding behind massive shields that"
" acted as mobile ramparts, would carefully pick off enemy soldiers, slowly "
"but surely, until the enemy garrison was depleted and the walls could be "
"taken unopposed. The Siege Archer is so well armored that when he is "
"defending, he will take reduced damage from physical weapons."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Signifer, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Signifer.cfg:5
msgid "Signifer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Signifer, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Signifer.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The standardbearer for his Century, the Signifer holds an enviable position. "
"He does not often engage in melee combat himself, but instead helps and "
"inspires his fellow Legionaires, and helps them regroup in case of retreat. "
"His standard has all of the awards his Century has recieved lined up, and a "
"large hand at the top, serving as a point of reference for all the fighters."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Skirmisher, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Skirmisher.cfg:5
msgid "Skirmisher"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Skirmisher, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Skirmisher.cfg:23
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Skirmisher has abandoned his original weapon, the sword, in favor of a "
"spear for both close and long range. He has perfected the art of moving "
"quickly between enemy lines, and is able to hold his own against opponents of"
" both the ranged and melee variety. His main task in the Legion is providing "
"a skirmishing screen for the Legionaires, and to help funnel cavalry and "
"archers towards their more heavily armored allies."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Slinger, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Slinger.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Although the bow is often a more dangerous weapon than the sling, many "
"Lavinian auxiliaries opt for the latter, because of its rapid rate of fire "
"and the plentifulness of ammunition. Although a swiftly moving stone is not "
"all that dangerous to a fully equipped Legionaire, it is often enough to take"
" down the unarmored barbarians the Legion is usually fighting."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Velite, race=AE_imp_lavinian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-lavinians\Velite.cfg:34
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Often a member of one of the barbarian tribes which have allied with the "
"Empire, a Velite wears the wolf-skin headdress of the northern people, and is"
" clothed in green and brown; he wields a throwing spear and a small wooden "
"buckler. Not having been trained in organized combat, but rather in a form of"
" 'tactics' that the Lavinians view and primitive and chaotic, the Velite runs"
" around the battlefield, right past his opponents, until he finds someone he "
"can defeat. Then he attacks."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Axeman, race=AE_imp_marauder_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Axeman.cfg:5
msgid "Axeman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Axeman, race=AE_imp_marauder_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Axeman.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"A Marauder Axeman takes care making sure that the Marauder villages have a "
"good supply of wood during the cold winters in the Northland. He also excels "
"at building the resilient wooden walls that protect Marauder encampments. "
"Although he is not as furious a melee fighter as the Warriors, he knows how "
"to use a bow, and is often seen giving Warriors some much needed ranged "
"suppport."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Boatsman, race=AE_imp_marauder_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Boatsman.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Marauders subsist on hunted game and fish. The boatsmen among them go "
"out, on rivers or on the sea, in small coracles, light enough to carry when "
"on land. Their skills at boating do them well in wartime, when they take up "
"arms and attack their enemies from the water."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Crusher, race=AE_imp_marauder_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Crusher.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"A Marauder Crusher's only weapon is the huge iron maul he carries around. He "
"has no need for others, for he is a master at the art of berserking, which "
"requires no finess, only brute strength. He will fight until either he or his"
" opponent lies dead."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Fay, race=AE_imp_marauder_race, gender=female
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Fay.cfg:5
msgid "female^Fay"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Fay, race=AE_imp_marauder_race, gender=female
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Fay.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Marauders and Frost Elves keep the peace between them by what might be "
"termed an exchange of hostages. The Frost Elven princes live in Marauder "
"villages for the first quarter of their lives, and the Marauder noblewomen do"
" the same in Frost Elven lands. There, they learn the art of magic from the "
"Frost Elves, and when they return, they prove their worth in battle."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Fay.cfg:62
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Galdra.cfg:39
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Seeress.cfg:38
msgid "cold blast"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Galdra, race=AE_imp_marauder_race, gender=female
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Galdra.cfg:5
msgid "female^Galdra"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Galdra, race=AE_imp_marauder_race, gender=female
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Galdra.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The greatest of the Marauder seers, the Galdra, are misunderstood even by "
"their own people. The common folk see the Galdra as the warrior wives of "
"their lords. In truth, the Galdra will use their magic in battle, but their "
"true place is at the side of a Marauder thain, who will consult them for "
"advice in the wars against the Lavinians and Sidhe."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Hunter, race=AE_imp_marauder_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Hunter.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"A Hunter, in addition to providing Marauder villages with wood and shelter, "
"supplies his people with fresh meat during the cold and harsh winters. He is "
"more skilled at fighting in the forests than other Maurauders, because it is "
"there that the game he hunts lives. Hours each day spent hunting and "
"practicing has allowed him to hone his markmanship, and he is a very able "
"archer."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Jarl, race=AE_imp_marauder_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Jarl.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"A Jarl is the right-hand man of his Marauder Lord, advising him in battle and"
" away from the field and often ruling in his stead when the Lord must be "
"away. If a lord dies heirless, often it is the jarl who takes his place."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Lord, race=AE_imp_marauder_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Lord.cfg:21
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"There are few Marauders indeed that are of such skill that they receive the "
"title Lord. A Marauder Lord is the strongest amongst his kin, and his "
"fighting skills are constantly tested as many Marauders challenge his status "
"as supreme champion of his tribe. His heroic deeds and charisma inspires "
"other Marauders to fight harder for their tribe, and to battle until the "
"death. Many 'civilized' generals have underestimated the Marauder Lord's wits"
" and tactics, and paid for their mistake with their lives."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Mauler, race=AE_imp_marauder_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Mauler.cfg:5
msgid "Mauler"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Mauler, race=AE_imp_marauder_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Mauler.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Most Crushers do not survive enough raids to be given the title of Mauler. "
"One who does is truly a strong and fearsome opponent. He does not exercise "
"restraint in battle, but fights until the death - it is because of this that "
"so many die at a quite early age. Although the 'civilized' fighters think "
"this fervor is foolhardy and pointless, many a battle has been won through "
"the fury of the berserking Maulers."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Mounted_Axeman, race=AE_imp_marauder_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Mounted_Axeman.cfg:5
msgid "Mounted Axeman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Mounted_Axeman, race=AE_imp_marauder_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Mounted_Axeman.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Horses are hard to come by in Marauder culture, and are also hard to take "
"along on ocean raids across Iceswept Bay. Still, any Marauder would leap at "
"the chance to steal horse or livestock, even if only for the journey back. "
"All of the negative aspects of riding a horse into battle are forgotten once "
"a Marauder makes the first quick and powerful axe-sweep cutting down an "
"enemy, especially if the very horse he is riding was stolen from the man he "
"slays."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Mounted_Axeman.cfg:25
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Mounted_Axeman.cfg:34
#: .\units\MiE_units\cornurs\1_Valiant.cfg:25
#: .\units\MiE_units\cornurs\2_Battler.cfg:25
#: .\units\MiE_units\cornurs\3_Protector.cfg:30
msgid "battleaxe"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Pillager, race=AE_imp_marauder_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_dark_legion_Pillager, race=human
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Pillager.cfg:5
#: .\units\misc_units\dark_legion\Dark_Pillager.cfg:4
msgid "Pillager"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Pillager, race=AE_imp_marauder_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Pillager.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Marauder Warriors wield their torches out of necessity, recognizing that some"
" enemies are easier to burn than to slice in twain, but the Pillagers embrace"
" their role as arsonists. They revel in the seizing of what they can from the"
" houses of their foes, and the burning of what they cannot."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Raider, race=AE_imp_marauder_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Raider.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Only the best scouts are called Raiders. They are rumored to catch wild "
"horses singlehandedly... and by foot. These rumors are not too far from the "
"truth. The Raider's extreme quickness is of great use in battle, for he can "
"reach the front before the opponent and capture the good defensive terrain. "
"He also carried with him a net for entangling the enemy, both to slow him "
"down in battle and, if the other opponents flee, to capture him as a slave."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Sailor, race=AE_imp_marauder_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_mercenaries_Sailor, race=AE_mrc_mercenaries_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Sailor.cfg:5
#: .\units\ME_units\mercenaries\g1-Sailor.cfg:5
msgid "Sailor"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Sailor, race=AE_imp_marauder_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Sailor.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Marauder fishermen spend their whole lives around boats - even when on land, "
"they carry their coracles on their backs with them. They already know all "
"they can learn about boatsmanship, but they can indeed learn more about "
"warfare. It takes immense skill for them to wield an axe in a boat as small "
"as theirs."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Scorcher, race=AE_imp_marauder_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Scorcher.cfg:5
msgid "Scorcher"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Scorcher, race=AE_imp_marauder_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Scorcher.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Some of the most powerful and experienced Marauders choose not to take on the"
" responsibilities of being a Marauder Lord, and instead choose to be the "
"first to land and plunge into battle. They wield a torch in battle, and, as a"
" symbol of their status in Marauder society, are always given the right to "
"burn away the first civilized building during raids. Their strength and fury "
"in battle is a constant source of tales throughtout the land, and even the "
"most skilled warriors can not stand in their way for long."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Scout, race=AE_imp_marauder_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Scout.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"All marauder children are evaluated by the clan lords at the age of only "
"eight winters. All of the ones who seem extremely lithe and agile are "
"selected to become Scouts, the first to enter every battle and the last to "
"leave. Marauder chieftains usually use them almost as one would a mounted "
"warrior."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Sea_Wolf, race=AE_imp_marauder_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Sea_Wolf.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Tales are told in the villages of Arendia of the terrifying Marauder raids. "
"In the dark of night, boats will float swiftly come downstream, bearing fire "
"and death. The dreaded Sea Wolves, their ships cloaked in black, will charge "
"out onto the land, slay their victims, take their plunder, and retreat as "
"quickly as they came."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Seeress, race=AE_imp_marauder_race, gender=female
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Seeress.cfg:5
msgid "female^Seeress"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Seeress, race=AE_imp_marauder_race, gender=female
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Seeress.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The art of seid is taught to Marauder noblewomen by the Frost Elves, their "
"allies, as part of a political agreement between the two peoples. After "
"returning home from the Frost Elven lands, the Seeress has learned to use her"
" powers in battle, striking down foes with a wave of her hand."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Shieldmaiden, race=AE_imp_marauder_race, gender=female
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Shieldmaiden.cfg:5
msgid "female^Shieldmaiden"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Shieldmaiden, race=AE_imp_marauder_race, gender=female
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Shieldmaiden.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Although their training with the Frost Elves showed them how to use magic "
"with no aid or magical props, some Marauder noblewomen wish to fight with "
"true weapons as well. Using their knowledge of seid to their advantage, they "
"imbue their spears with a fey spirit, and even with no martial training they "
"can often best warriors at their own game."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Valkyrie, race=AE_imp_marauder_race, gender=female
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Valkyrie.cfg:5
msgid "female^Valkyrie"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Valkyrie, race=AE_imp_marauder_race, gender=female
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Valkyrie.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Tales float about in Lavinia of the Marauder Valkyries. They are, it is said,"
" spirits from the netherworld come to claim souls for the army that will "
"fight beside them on the last days against the legions of darkness. Those "
"they touch with their spears are destined to fall in battle that day and be "
"brought back to fight for good in the final battle at the end of time. It is "
"an intriguing story, but it is no consolation for the Legionaires who are "
"slain at the hands of a Valkyrie, who are in truth not spirits, but Marauder "
"noblemwomen who have mastered the art of seid, and who have given themselves "
"the wings of a bird - so great is their power - to better move about the "
"battlefield."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Warrior, race=AE_imp_marauder_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Warrior.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Warriors are the main fighters in the Marauder army. Very strong and faster "
"than most troops because of their light armour, they reach the front quickly,"
" and once the enemy is routed they often cannot escape the blade of these "
"swift and brutal men. The Warriors believe that if they die in battle, they "
"will live forever, drinking and feasting with the gods, it is this that gives"
" them their fearlessness when fighting."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Woodsman, race=AE_imp_marauder_race
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_highlanders_Woodsman, race=AE_mrc_highlanders_race, gender=male
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Woodsman.cfg:5
#: .\units\ME_units\highlanders\a2-woodsman.cfg:5
msgid "Woodsman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Marauders_Woodsman, race=AE_imp_marauder_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-marauders\Woodsman.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Woodsmen are well-respected in Marauder society, and their hunting and "
"forestry skills are unmatched by any man. Amongst the Marauders' numereous "
"enemies, they are avoided and greatly feared - and for good reason, as their "
"markmanship with bow and pure strength is amazing. Many of them train by "
"chopping down trees with a single blow."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Champion, race=AE_imp_nemidian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-nemidians\Champion.cfg:23
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"A Nemidian Champion is one of the most skilled horsemen to be found, either "
"in the Empire or in his homeland of Nemidia. His spear-charges are feared "
"throughout the land, as are his scimitar and javelins. He has garbed himself "
"in the Lavinian fashion, and even takes the red and golden colors of the "
"Legion. If it were not for the fact that his skin was black - burnt by the "
"sun, the Lavinians believe - he could be mistaken for a Lavinian general, "
"commanding his Legionaires from horseback."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Claimant, race=AE_imp_nemidian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-nemidians\Claimant.cfg:22
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The more skilled the riders of Nemidia grow, the faster they are able to push"
" their horses to run. A Nemidian Claimant's horse wears light armor, but it "
"still manages to go faster than that of an untrained cavalryman. In addition,"
" the Claimant now wields an additional weapon; a scimitar, which he uses when"
" he does not wish to deal or recieve instant death."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Hippopotamus, race=AE_imp_nemidian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-nemidians\Hippopotamus.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The Lavinians have a name for the fearsome river horse of the Nemidian waters"
" - 'hippopotamus'. The enemies who face them often have never heard of these "
"strange beasts, but they too have a name for them - death on four legs."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-nemidians\Hippopotamus.cfg:30
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-nemidians\River_Calf.cfg:29
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-nemidians\River_Horse.cfg:29
msgid "head-butt"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_Horseman, race=AE_imp_nemidian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-nemidians\Horseman.cfg:22
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The land of Nemidia governs itself, but it has a strong alliance with the "
"Lavinian Empire, and often sends warriors to aid in its battles. The country "
"is renowned for its skilled horsemen - so the Lavinians, instead of fielding "
"their own, simply send the cavalry of Nemidia into battle. The horseman's "
"only weapon is his spear, but his skill with it allows him to use it as a "
"projectile, as well as a melee weapon."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_River_Calf, race=AE_imp_nemidian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-nemidians\River_Calf.cfg:5
msgid "River Calf"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_River_Calf, race=AE_imp_nemidian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-nemidians\River_Calf.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The land of Nemidia is not all desert. Many rivers cut through across the "
"sands, and the greatest of these leave fertile stretches in their floodplains"
" that the Nemidians often farm. In these rivers lurk death, however, in the "
"form of the river horse. A bull hippo can crush a man underfoot with the ease"
" of a man crushing a bug. Some enterprising Nemidians capture the offspring "
"of these creatures, raising them in the hopes of riding them as a form of "
"aquatic cavalry."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_River_Horse, race=AE_imp_nemidian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-nemidians\River_Horse.cfg:5
msgid "River Horse"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Lavinians_River_Horse, race=AE_imp_nemidian_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\human-nemidians\River_Horse.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The strange appearance of the River Horse often leads the enemies of the "
"Nemidians and their Lavinian allies to laugh, believing them to be riding "
"giant pigs. The riders of these beasts have the last laugh, however, as more "
"often than not they teach their opponents that, though their hippos may look "
"like giant pigs, they are not nearly as easy to slaughter."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Bestiarius, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Bestiarius.cfg:4
msgid "Bestiarius"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Bestiarius, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Bestiarius.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"To satisfy the constant Lavinian demand for variety in bloodshed, some "
"Pugnatores trade in their clubs for spears and focus on accuracy rather than "
"speed with their whips."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Bestiarius.cfg:35
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Feral_Bestiarius.cfg:36
msgid "bullwhip"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Brutal_Paegniarius, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Brutal_Paegniarius.cfg:4
msgid "Brutal Paegniarius"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Brutal_Paegniarius, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Brutal_Paegniarius.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"A Brutal Paegniarius has finally mastered the two weapons to which he has "
"devoted his training: the club and the whip. His ferocity is legendary, hence"
" the name."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Dimacherius, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Dimacherius.cfg:4
msgid "Dimacherius"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Dimacherius, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Dimacherius.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Some Galli prefer to wield two swords and dispense with a shield. The "
"Lavinian crowds, ever thirsting for novelty, welcome the change."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Dimacherius_Fortis, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Dimacherius_Fortis.cfg:4
msgid "Dimacherius Fortis"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Dimacherius_Fortis, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Dimacherius_Fortis.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"A Dimacherius of unquestioned skill and great popularity is hailed, rightly "
"as a Dimacherius Fortis, in honor of his bravery."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Feral_Bestiarius, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Feral_Bestiarius.cfg:4
msgid "Feral Bestiarius"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Feral_Bestiarius, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Feral_Bestiarius.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Feral Bestiarius gets his name as a tribute to his animal-like instincts,"
" honed over a lifetime of training."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Gallus, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Gallus.cfg:4
msgid "Gallus"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Gallus, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Gallus.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The first Galli were member of the Galaladz tribe, sworn enemies of the "
"Samandiz. The Lavinians changed the pronunciation to suit their tastes and "
"changed the meaning to refer to any low-level gladiator that used the long "
"sword, a novel weapon to the fickle crowds, though traditional to the "
"Galaladz."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Hoplomachus, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Hoplomachus.cfg:4
msgid "Hoplomachus"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Hoplomachus, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Hoplomachus.cfg:22
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"A sturdy, steady, dependable Samnis may be selected to join the ranks of the "
"Hoplomachi, a gladiator type invented for those days when the crowds are in "
"the mood for a prolonged defensive struggle rather than a quick offensive "
"one."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Hoplomachus_Fortis, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Hoplomachus_Fortis.cfg:4
msgid "Hoplomachus Fortis"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Hoplomachus_Fortis, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Hoplomachus_Fortis.cfg:22
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"A Hoplomachus Fortis is rightly renowned for his ability to stand firm "
"against hordes of foemen."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Murmillo, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Murmillo.cfg:4
msgid "Murmillo"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Murmillo, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Murmillo.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Members of the Galaladz tribe were known for recklessly charging into battle "
"without regard for their own safety. Even in captivity, many of them "
"maintained this tradition in the Lavinian arenas, which delighted the "
"bloodthirsty crowds to no end. Such a warrior became known as a Murmillo."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Murmillo_Leonis, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Murmillo_Leonis.cfg:4
msgid "Murmillo Leonis"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Murmillo_Leonis, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Murmillo_Leonis.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"A Murmillo who has been lucky enough to survive many battles, despite his "
"reckless bravery, is rightfully hailed as a Murmillo Leonis in recognition of"
" his prowess."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Paegniarius, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Paegniarius.cfg:4
msgid "Paegniarius"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Paegniarius, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Paegniarius.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"A Paegniarius is an Orc who has become attached to the club and the whip and "
"focused his efforts on perfecting his skill with these weapons."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Provocator, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Provocator.cfg:4
msgid "Provocator"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Provocator, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Provocator.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"A Provocator may not be quite as heavily equipped as a Hoplomachus, but he "
"more than makes up for it with his skill at swordsmanship, a skill over which"
" it is not uncommon for Lavinian commoners to unabashedly fawn."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Provocator_Leonis, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Provocator_Leonis.cfg:4
msgid "Provocator Leonis"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Provocator_Leonis, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Provocator_Leonis.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"A Provocator Leonis has reached the height of skill with his longsword, and "
"is more than a match for any opponent he might expect to meet in the Lavinian"
" arenas."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Pugnator, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Pugnator.cfg:4
msgid "Pugnator"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Pugnator, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Pugnator.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Pugnatores were trained for those occasions when the Lavinian crowds demanded"
" straightforward bludgeoning rather than intricate swordplay in the games. "
"Those lucky few who have escaped Lavinian slavery continue to maintain their "
"skills and abilities, and teach them to any of their brethren as are eager to"
" learn."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Samnis, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Samnis.cfg:4
msgid "Samnis"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Samnis, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Samnis.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"One of the original types of Orcish gladiators, the first Samnes were members"
" of the Samandiz tribe. The Lavinians changed the pronunciation to suit their"
" tastes and changed the meaning to refer to any low-level gladiator that used"
" the short sword, which was not a native Orcish weapon but rather a Lavinian "
"one to which the Orcs were forced to adjust."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Secutor, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Secutor.cfg:4
msgid "Secutor"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Secutor, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Secutor.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"A Secutor is a Samnis who has chosen to perfect his skill with the "
"shortsword, much to the amusement of the Lavinian crowds."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Secutor_Leonis, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Secutor_Leonis.cfg:4
msgid "Secutor Leonis"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Secutor_Leonis, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Secutor_Leonis.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"A Secutor Leonis has perfected his skill with the shortsword to the point "
"that he can exhibit a dazzling display of technical proficiency, and kill "
"with a flourish, for which the bloodthirsty Lavinian crowds love him all the "
"more."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Secutor_Leonis.cfg:40
msgid "sun glare"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Thraex, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Thraex.cfg:5
msgid "Thraex"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Thraex, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Thraex.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"In the original Samandiz tribe, the shortsword was not used. The sickle-sword"
" was their traditional weapon. A few members of this tribe prevailed upon "
"their captors to allow them to use this blade in the arena, as long as they "
"first developed proficiency in the short sword. These gladiators became known"
" as the Thraex."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Thraex.cfg:28
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Thraex_Paratus.cfg:39
msgid "sickle-sword"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Thraex_Paratus, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Thraex_Paratus.cfg:5
msgid "Thraex Paratus"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Thraex_Paratus, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-magni\Thraex_Paratus.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"A Thraex Paratus has mastered his idiosyncratic weapon, the sickle-sword, and"
" demonstrated its usefulness in the arena, much to the amusement of the "
"novelty-hungry Lavinian crowds."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Essedarius, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti\Essedarius.cfg:5
msgid "Essedarius"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Essedarius, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti\Essedarius.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The Lavinian crowds crave variety and not just bloodshed. The Essedarius, a "
"Minutus in a fox-drawn chariot, was developed from the Latronis to satisfy "
"their whims. The greater speed and versatility provided by chariots ensures "
"that they also find a place in the armies of those who escape from Lavinian "
"slavery."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Essedarius_Vulpis, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti\Essedarius_Vulpis.cfg:5
msgid "Essedarius Vulpis"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Essedarius_Vulpis, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti\Essedarius_Vulpis.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"A successful and popular Essedarius becomes known as an Essedarius Vulpis, in"
" honor of his canine companions."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Fleet_Retiarius, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti\Fleet_Retiarius.cfg:5
msgid "Fleet Retiarius"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Fleet_Retiarius, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti\Fleet_Retiarius.cfg:27
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Some Retiarii perfect the art of running circles around their enemies, and "
"are hailed as Fleet Retiarii in recognition of their skill."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Khampsa, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti\Khampsa.cfg:5
msgid "Khampsa"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Khampsa, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti\Khampsa.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"Though popularly known as River Lizard, the true name of this beast is "
"Khampsa. But whatever the name, its bite is not to be taken lightly, for "
"which it is ever popular in the Lavinian arenas."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Khampsa_Audentis, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti\Khampsa_Audentis.cfg:5
msgid "Khampsa Audentis"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Khampsa_Audentis, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti\Khampsa_Audentis.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"A Khampsa of great ferocity becomes known as a Khampsa Audentis, the latter "
"term referring to its bold and audacious behavior."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Laquerius, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti\Laquerius.cfg:5
msgid "Laquerius"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Laquerius, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti\Laquerius.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Some Piscatores come to prefer the lasso to the net and the lance to the "
"trident. The variety is much appreciated by the Lavinian crowds they "
"entertain."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti\Laquerius.cfg:22
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti\Laquerius_Faber.cfg:28
msgid "lasso"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Laquerius_Faber, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti\Laquerius_Faber.cfg:5
msgid "Laquerius Faber"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Laquerius_Faber, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti\Laquerius_Faber.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"A Laquerius who has perfected his art becomes known as a Laquerius Faber, the"
" latter word being appended to designate his skill."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Latronis, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti\Latronis.cfg:5
msgid "Latronis"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Latronis, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti\Latronis.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The crowds in the Lavinian arenas very much enjoy watching staged hunts. The "
"Latronis was developed to be a specialist in these extravaganzas. Those "
"Latrones who escape from bondage find that their hunting skills are just as "
"useful in the real world as in the artificial environment of the Lavinian "
"public spectacles."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Piscator, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti\Piscator.cfg:5
msgid "Piscator"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Piscator, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti\Piscator.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Lavinian citizenry demands that the nobles devise ever new forms of "
"bloodsoaked entertainment. The Piscator, a Minutus who seeks to entangle his "
"foe in a net and then pierce him with a trident, was developed to meet this "
"need."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Retiarius, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti\Retiarius.cfg:5
msgid "Retiarius"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Retiarius, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti\Retiarius.cfg:22
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"A Piscator of proven worth and entertainment value is equipped with a minimal"
" amount of armor and sent back into the arena to fight another day."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_River_Lizard, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti\River_Lizard.cfg:5
msgid "River Lizard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_River_Lizard, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti\River_Lizard.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The good people of Lavinia also enjoy watching beast fights. The Orcei soon "
"developed a great affinity for one of these beasts, euphemistically known as "
"a River Lizard. They often use these beasts in the arena, and those among "
"them who escape from captivity often bring a few of their reptilian friends "
"with them."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Venator, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti\Venator.cfg:5
msgid "Venator"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Venator, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti\Venator.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"A successful Latronis is hailed by his Lavinian fans as a Venator. Those "
"Minuti who escape from bondage continue to use this title for successful "
"hunters."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Venator_Faber, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti\Venator_Faber.cfg:5
msgid "Venator Faber"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Orcei_Venator_Faber, race=AE_imp_Orcei_Gladiatores_race
#: .\units\imperial_units\orcs-minuti\Venator_Faber.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is from Imperial Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
" \n"
"The most popular, famous, and successful of the Venatores are hailed as "
"Venatores Fabri."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Ancestor, race=undead
#: .\units\imperial_units\spirit-elves\Sidhe_Ancestor.cfg:24
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"Revered warriors of old roam through the woods of the Sidhe, visible only due"
" to their shining silver maces. They are only partially present in the mortal"
" realm, and wounds close as if they had never existed. Their voice can "
"whisper in the wind words that chill the hearts of the living and bring them "
"closer to the realm of the dead."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\imperial_units\spirit-elves\Sidhe_Ancestor.cfg:39
#: .\units\imperial_units\spirit-elves\Sidhe_Forefather.cfg:40
#: .\units\imperial_units\spirit-elves\Sidhe_Warrior_Spirit.cfg:35
msgid "ancient mace"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Forefather, race=undead
#: .\units\imperial_units\spirit-elves\Sidhe_Forefather.cfg:25
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The greatest warriors of the Sidhe are far from gone. When their death chant "
"can be heard echoing through the trees, their enemies know, though it is too "
"late, that their silver maces will soon be there."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_imp_Sidhe_Warrior_Spirit, race=undead
#: .\units\imperial_units\spirit-elves\Sidhe_Warrior_Spirit.cfg:20
msgid ""
"This unit is from Feudal Era. Its coding and art were done by Turin and "
"Various others.\n"
"\n"
"The Sidhe Warriors of times past are not quite gone. Their Spirits roam "
"through the forests of their former homes, seeking to perform feats of arms "
"as they did in the past, and death is no obstacle..."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=AE_mrc_avians_race
