#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Cultist, race=AE_mrc_cult_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\a1-cultist.cfg:5
msgid "Cultist"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Cultist, race=AE_mrc_cult_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\a1-cultist.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Cultists are a group of men that usually have secret reunions, no-one is sure"
" about their real intentions, but it is true that they're commonly seen "
"fighting, weird creatures and monstrosities by their side, so cultists are "
"both feared and hated."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Covert, race=AE_mrc_mutant_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\a2-covert.cfg:5
msgid "Covert"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Covert, race=AE_mrc_mutant_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\a2-covert.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Coverts are mysterious people with traits of an unknown non human race, there"
" is not that much information about them apart that people consider them as "
"traitors of humanity because of fighting by the side of unknown monsters and "
"becoming one of them"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Overt, race=AE_mrc_cult_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\a2-overt.cfg:5
msgid "Overt"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Overt, race=AE_mrc_cult_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\a2-overt.cfg:21
msgid ""
"The difference between overt and covert is that coverts kept their humanity "
"and didn't want genetic experiments over themselves. Those seems of not "
"needing genetic alterations and brainwashing to remain loyal to the cult."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Cleaner, race=AE_mrc_cult_race, gender=male
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_refugees_Cleaner, race=AE_mrc_refugees_race
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\a3-cleaner.cfg:5
#: .\units\ME_units\refugees\a1-cleaner.cfg:5
msgid "Cleaner"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Cleaner, race=AE_mrc_cult_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\a3-cleaner.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Similar case of Executioners if you question their actions they just refer "
"themselves as Cleaners... they don't provide a very developed argument for "
"their actions, avoiding details or reasons ... they maybe are hidding their "
"truth goals."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Executioner, race=AE_mrc_mutant_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\a3-executioner.cfg:22
msgid ""
"They're named Executioners just because if you question them why they are "
"doing those genocides they will just say 'for the common good' which is "
"strange coming from a genocidal... inquietant... but there is a question... "
"What do these people want exactly? And what are their reasons for the genetic"
" manipulation even on themselves, assassinations and immoral acts."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Spy, race=AE_mrc_mutant_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\a3-spy.cfg:5
msgid "Spy"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Spy, race=AE_mrc_mutant_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\a3-spy.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Spies are the most mysterious of all cultists, he's probably watching the "
"human society disorders and refusing his human nature past... maybe this "
"allows him to acomplish the factions goals... who knows if they were mentally"
" right or not before the genetic manipulation ... but sure thing is that "
"there is no regret in any of its actions"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\a3-spy.cfg:50
msgid "Needle"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Exile, race=AE_mrc_cult_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\b1-exile.cfg:5
msgid "Exile"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Exile, race=AE_mrc_cult_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\b1-exile.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Exiled are men that used to be in the human society like any good man, but "
"because of differences in belief or because of a misunderstanding those men "
"ended being exiled. After living for some time in the wild, those men found a"
" cultist and after a long talking the cultist persuaded them to fight for "
"their cause. Letting us  think that a good man can easily join the cause of "
"cultists."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\b1-exile.cfg:36
#: .\units\ME_units\holy_order\f1-officer.cfg:31
#: .\units\ME_units\holy_order\f2-justice.cfg:32
#: .\units\ME_units\holy_order\f3-law.cfg:35
msgid "Trudgeon"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Banished, race=AE_mrc_cult_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\b2-banished.cfg:5
msgid "Banished"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Banished, race=AE_mrc_cult_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\b2-banished.cfg:21
msgid ""
"After some time, Banished are hated like cultists, which doesn't matter to "
"the banished, completely used to being rejected by the society but not by the"
" cultists. He probably became arrogant and more immoral than he used to be."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Lonewolf, race=AE_mrc_cult_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\b2-lonewolf.cfg:5
msgid "Lonewolf"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Lonewolf, race=AE_mrc_cult_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\b2-lonewolf.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Some exiled prefer to stay in wild rather than going for cultists goals. Cult"
" has no problems with that and they gift him wolves claws in one of his two "
"hands. They trust that when he is called for fighting for the cult he will "
"participate."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Condemned, race=AE_mrc_cult_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\b3-condemned.cfg:5
msgid "Condemned"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Condemned, race=AE_mrc_cult_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\b3-condemned.cfg:22
msgid ""
"It's said that if the society finds these individuals they would be condemned"
" to death ... the reasons are varied, but it looks like that those men were "
"brainwashed and irreconcilable."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Freak, race=AE_mrc_mutant_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\c1-freak.cfg:5
msgid "Freak"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Freak, race=AE_mrc_mutant_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\c1-freak.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Freaks are weird green humanoid creatures with hard skin, that are clumsy. "
"No-one knows their exact origin, but it's sure it's not human being. It's "
"probably the result of a wrong experiment that was left to die."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Miscreation, race=AE_mrc_mutant_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\c2-miscreation.cfg:5
msgid "Miscreation"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Miscreation, race=AE_mrc_mutant_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\c2-miscreation.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Miscreation has grown unnaturally fast. Unexpected to live that long... Now "
"it has claws in one of the 2 hands, being not symetrical. Looks like it's "
"genetically designed for fighting ... but why was it left to die earlier? "
"This shows us that cultists have an oddly good knowledge of genetics."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Montrosity, race=AE_mrc_mutant_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\c3-monstrosity.cfg:5
msgid "Monstrosity"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Montrosity, race=AE_mrc_mutant_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\c3-monstrosity.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Monstrosity is the final result of a creature that fought for its life in a "
"hostile world. After all, the failed experiment wasn't a failure, but wasn't "
"probably what cultists wanted in the beginning. Looks like cultists now "
"appreciate this creature. But ... what were cultists trying to do that ended "
"in such a horrible creature? We could say that freaks were the hardest of "
"their experiments and that ended with unwanted results."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Lookout, race=AE_mrc_cult_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\d1-lookout.cfg:5
msgid "Lookout"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Lookout, race=AE_mrc_cult_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\d1-lookout.cfg:21
msgid "Apart from being more swift than usual, they are not unlike regular humans."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Sentry, race=AE_mrc_cult_race, gender=male
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_refugees_Sentry, race=AE_mrc_refugees_race
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\d2-sentry.cfg:5
#: .\units\ME_units\refugees\h1-sentry.cfg:5
msgid "Sentry"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Sentry, race=AE_mrc_cult_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\d2-sentry.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Sentry, similar to lookout, are swift. These men are given the task to watch "
"and warn if their camps are being attacked. Apart of their unusual swiftness,"
" those men need less sleep to accomplish their function."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\d2-sentry.cfg:60
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\d3-beacon.cfg:60
msgid "Fire Arrow"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Beacon, race=AE_mrc_cult_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\d3-beacon.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Beacon has now a weight more similar to regular humans, but he's still as "
"fast. They're completely sane, being used to living with that lot of "
"monsters, miscreations and cultists doing immoral experiments. These men "
"shine for a solid emotional and mental health unlike most of their "
"companions. It's said that some beacon leaves the cult for days to live in "
"the society and then comes back to the cult, but probably with no of "
"intention of betrayal."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Recruit, race=AE_mrc_cult_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\e1-recruit.cfg:5
msgid "Recruit"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Recruit, race=AE_mrc_cult_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\e1-recruit.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Cultists often recruit mercenaries that fight for anyone's cause for some "
"coins. Those men have no idea in what their life will turn..."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Rebel, race=AE_mrc_cult_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\e2-rebel.cfg:5
msgid "Rebel"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Rebel, race=AE_mrc_cult_race, gender=male
#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Subverter, race=AE_mrc_cult_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\e2-rebel.cfg:21
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\e3-subverter.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Rebels and Subverters after fighting some time for the cultist they're still "
"figting for the cult, but unlike recruits they oppose society and do not "
"fight just for coins. They still have no real idea about the meanings of the "
"cult, but they don't seem to be brainwashed, just uninformed."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Transformation, race=AE_mrc_mutant_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\e2-transformation.cfg:5
msgid "Transformation"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Transformation, race=AE_mrc_mutant_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\e2-transformation.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Transformation used to be human ... it's not known what kind of process "
"occurred to them... but it looks like cult is capable of corrupting the "
"genetic data of already born living. The question is ... what kind of "
"technique they use for those genetic manipulations... creepy... also, does it"
" still think like an human; also which would be reasons of why those men "
"allowed themselves to be the product of such experiments."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Mutant, race=AE_mrc_mutant_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\e3-mutant.cfg:5
msgid "Mutant"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Mutant, race=AE_mrc_mutant_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\e3-mutant.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Mutant is starting to lose its human features, even its personality as human."
" Looks like that it's not just genetic corruption, it's now conscience "
"corruption too. It is just becoming into killing machine ... also, it's said "
"that recruits that chose the genetics modifications were men that wanted to "
"forget their past and that were better informed about the cult itself."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Subverter, race=AE_mrc_cult_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\e3-subverter.cfg:5
msgid "Subverter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Inhuman, race=AE_mrc_mutant_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\e4-inhuman.cfg:5
msgid "Inhuman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Inhuman, race=AE_mrc_mutant_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\e4-inhuman.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Inhuman no longer has human characteristics. It has an incredible feast for "
"killing (not just humans). Still it's hard to make those things talk, also it"
" can still can maintain a conversation, though its vocal chords will make it "
"difficult to talk, apart of decrease of inteligence from a regular human, "
"still, if it were persuaded it could tell us a lot about of the cult ... "
"sadly, it's too loyal to them."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Survivor, race=AE_mrc_mutant_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\f1-survivor.cfg:5
msgid "Survivor"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Survivor, race=AE_mrc_mutant_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\f1-survivor.cfg:21
msgid ""
"The survivor is a real accomplishment of the cultist's genetics. If we look, "
"all cultists are men or asexual, but never female. They consider the male "
"gender as the superior gender and they do not consider the female gender "
"because of their genetics knowledge."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Outlaster, race=AE_mrc_mutant_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\f2-outlaster.cfg:5
msgid "Outlaster"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Outlaster, race=AE_mrc_mutant_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\f2-outlaster.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Outlaster can outlast about any extreme climatic situation and is capable of "
"living alone in the wild. It's unknown why cultists wanted so resistant and "
"long lived creation, unlike most of theirs. Meaning the cult have long time "
"goals..."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Remnant, race=AE_mrc_mutant_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\f3-remnant.cfg:5
msgid "Remnant"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Remnant, race=AE_mrc_mutant_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\f3-remnant.cfg:21
msgid ""
"After decades of long long living, looks like he's stronger than ever. In his"
" actual age any human would feel weak, ancient or sick, but Remnant is more "
"healthy than ever. Some remnant tried to have sons with regular women to try "
"to build a genetically superior humanity, but for their surprise they're not "
"fertile. At this point they start understanding that the cult goals aren't "
"completely good for human race and at a point they just start fighting for "
"their ownselves."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\f3-remnant.cfg:51
msgid "Inner Strength"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Primordial, race=AE_mrc_mutant_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\f4-primordial.cfg:5
msgid "Primordial"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_cult_Primordial, race=AE_mrc_mutant_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\f4-primordial.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Primordial is the success of eugenics. Primordial proved to be immortal, "
"being stronger the older he is. His cells instead of deteriorating over time,"
" improve over the pass of time. It's not known if this process has a limit, "
"but the few silver mages that studied this kind of men said he has an "
"expected life of at least 900 years but no more than 2000 years because the "
"process consumes certain energy from the environment that grows gradually "
"over time, to a point, when the primordial would die because there wouldn't "
"be enough food (or better said, food with the energy requirements) to "
"maintain this process in the current world, even at the conclusion of an "
"hypothetical case in which even if he spends his whole life eating he would "
"still die due to inanition. If it wasn't due this fact, he would be "
"completely immortal... fact that of course, cultist will never know."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\ME_units\cult\f4-primordial.cfg:47
msgid "Ancient Strength"
msgstr ""

