#: .\units\ME_units\holy_order\c2-inquisition.cfg:19
msgid ""
"When the leaders of oppositions are caught, they are sent to an inquisitor. "
"Inquisitors have many more methods that they use than a normal interrogator, "
"and although less people live through a session with an inquisitor, they do "
"enjoy their job."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_holy_order_Torturer, race=AE_mrc_holy_order_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\holy_order\c3-torturer.cfg:5
msgid "Torturer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_holy_order_Torturer, race=AE_mrc_holy_order_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\holy_order\c3-torturer.cfg:20
msgid ""
"When the holy order catches foreign enemies, they are sent to the torturers. "
"While no one comes out of a torturers dungeon, very few actually die from the"
" torturers actions. By the end of the first week the prisoners pray to gods "
"other than their own, as long as they give them their last wish: a quicker "
"death."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_holy_order_Judiciary, race=AE_mrc_holy_order_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\holy_order\d1-judiciary.cfg:5
