msgid "Judgement"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_holy_order_Supreme, race=AE_mrc_holy_order_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\holy_order\d3-supreme_judge.cfg:5
msgid "Supreme Judge"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_holy_order_Supreme, race=AE_mrc_holy_order_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\holy_order\d3-supreme_judge.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Supreme Judges are the law of the land. Only the Pope himself can overturn a "
"decision of a Supreme Judge. If a charge is ever held against a religious "
"figure, a Supreme Judge is called in to settle the matter."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_holy_order_Mounted_Officer, race=AE_mrc_holy_order_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\holy_order\e1-mountedofficer.cfg:5
msgid "Mounted Officer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_holy_order_Mounted_Officer, race=AE_mrc_holy_order_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\holy_order\e1-mountedofficer.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Mounted officers are the patrols of the officer force. They patrol the "
"streets looking for any signs of trouble. At the first sign of wrongdoing "
"they find the nearest officer and lead him to the perpetrator with their keen"
" eyes and quick steeds. If there are no officers in the area, the mounted "
"officers will subdue the perpetrator with their trusty spear, although they "
"prefer not to because most of these officers have been given their job "
"because of their notable cowardice."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_holy_order_Listener, race=AE_mrc_holy_order_race, gender=male
