#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_oracles_Beholder, race=monster, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\oracles\l1-beholder.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Through years of studying the summoning art, summoners have been able to "
"concoct hundreds of creatures. Beholders, while physically frail and not "
"combat worthy, were found useful by the headmasters of the Oracles "
"facilities. They were originally used to scout out areas large and isolated "
"enough for schools to be built on. Though when a single unwanted person might"
" stumble upon a university of magic, beholders are sent out to find and "
"eliminate them by staring the life out of them, or strangulating them with "
"their tentacles.\n"
" \n"
"Beholders are evil creations of a really twisted warlock. Usually beholders "
"feed of birds and bats, hunting them with strikes of stare at far, once the "
"prey is at close range the tentacle finishes the job. Beholders's evil "
"appearance indicates that they are seething to anything else, but for some "
"curious reason it's calm next to humanoid presence. Curiously, beholder "
"understands most of the orders given to it even with no training at all, "
"meaning that probably it has a kind of mental connection with anyone that the"
" creator authorized."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#. [attack], type=secret, range=ranged
#: .\units\ME_units\oracles\l1-beholder.cfg:44
#: .\units\ME_units\oracles\l2-evileye.cfg:46
#: .\units\ME_units\oracles\l2-evileye.cfg:59
msgid "Stare"
msgstr ""

