#: .\units\ME_units\oracles\l2-evileye.cfg:5
msgid "Evileye"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_oracles_Evileye, race=monster, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\oracles\l2-evileye.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Once beholder has grown out and gained some experience at fighting, the eyes "
"become from blue to red differentiating them from regular beholders quickly "
"apart of the size. It's said that evileyes are almost as loyal as a trained "
"bird if not saying equally loyal. With that new size it can hunt owls and "
"maybe eagles in weird circunstances."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_oracles_Blindman, race=AE_mrc_oracles_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\oracles\m1-blindman.cfg:5
msgid "Blindman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_mrc_oracles_Blindman, race=AE_mrc_oracles_race, gender=male
#: .\units\ME_units\oracles\m1-blindman.cfg:19
msgid ""
"For some reason Oracles usually have more men, which can make predictions "
"about the future than almost any other race, but it's true as well that more "
"of them born without being capable to see anything even if it's in front of "
"their noses. Also, being blind their other senses are considerably improved "
"likely the hearing and mostly the touch. Not being capable of seeing the "
"opponent he has in the front, they have not good properties to be warriors, "
"apart they cannot see that well the environment in which he is fighting which"
" decreases considerably his agility. Still, he can react very accurately, if "
"someone strikes him with weapons at close range and the damage he will deal "
"in retaliation is unexpectedly high. If facing him, it's better to use a "
"ranged weapon negating his only strength in a fight."
msgstr ""

