#. [race], id=AE_dep_deep_elf
#: .\units\misc_units\deep-elves.cfg:104
msgid ""
"The Deep Elves live in a place called the Underearth, that is located in the "
"realms of the far east, a land, where both sun and moon never set and day "
"equals night. The Underearth is a huge earthly dome within the depths of the "
"far east. Its vastness has often lead people to saying that the Underearth "
"itself is an own world. Lonesome wanderers often report about seeing "
"wandering stars inside the caves of the Underearth, but what do they know "
"about a place, where the sky's the earth?\n"
"\t\t\n"
"\t\tThe beings living inside these darkest depths are of elvish origin, yet "
"their prolonged exposure to the darkness led to various adaptations: while "
"some adapted to the darkness, becoming the shadows themselves, the body of a "
"few former elves resisted against the influence of the darkness, which "
"resulted in them emerging light.\n"
"\t\t\n"
"\t\tThe elves that once descended into the depths had lost their faith in "
"nature, believing that nature is just as influenced by the great things "
"beyond as the elves themselves. Searching for exactly these things beyond, "
"the ancestors of the Deep Elves discovered the works and scriptures of an "
"ancient perished civilisation. Great vaults built by the Deep Elves are since"
" then gracing the darkest depths, inside are shrines of Shassagoth - a being "
"described in those scriptures and whose return they are awaiting."
msgstr ""

