#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Archer, race=elf, gender=male
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Archer.cfg:5
msgid "Desert Archer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Archer, race=elf, gender=male
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Archer.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Desert Archers are trained from youth in archery, and so skilled in "
"long-range combat. Though their bows are cruder and their arrows less "
"plentiful than their elvish ancestors, they fight with ferocity that does "
"credit to their race."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Archer.cfg:220
msgid "female^Desert Archer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Avenger, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Avenger.cfg:4
msgid "Desert Avenger"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Avenger, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Avenger.cfg:31
msgid ""
"Desert Avengers are extremely skillful and extremely quick, powerful in all "
"forms of combat. Like their kin, they prefer the sword to the bow and are "
"adept at sneaking around and backstabbing their enemies."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Avenger.cfg:155
msgid "female^Desert Avenger"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Captain, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Captain.cfg:4
msgid "Desert Captain"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Captain, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Captain.cfg:28
msgid ""
"Skilled in commanding other elves, Desert Captains provide a bonus to all "
"level 1 units on adjacent hexes. Desert Captains prefer engaging the enemy in"
" melee combat, but are trained in archery as well."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Champion, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Champion.cfg:4
msgid "Desert Champion"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Champion, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Champion.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Desert Champions are awesome masters of swordsmanship, inflicting grievous "
"wounds in close combat. Master fighters, they are also skilled with the bow, "
"able to inflict damage on their enemies from both near and far."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Druid, race=elf, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Druid.cfg:4
msgid "female^Desert Druid"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Druid, race=elf, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Druid.cfg:27
msgid ""
"Desert Druids are powerful masters of the sands. Brilliant at ensnaring "
"unwary opponents, they use their vast knowledge of the plants of the desert "
"to heal allies. Druids are excellent supporting units in any group of elves."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Fighter, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Fighter.cfg:5
msgid "Desert Fighter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Fighter, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Fighter.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Desert Fighters make up the bulk of the Quenoth warriors. They are trained in"
" both sword and bow, though like most of their kin, they prefer swordplay to "
"archery. These Elves are deft of foot, and fight best in the open sands."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Hero, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Hero.cfg:4
msgid "Desert Hero"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Hero, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Hero.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Desert Heroes focus on individual performance on the battlefield, having "
"tweaked their combat skills to the very maximum. Desert Heroes prefer "
"fighting at close range with the sword, but also have some skill with the "
"bow."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Horseman, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Horseman.cfg:4
msgid "Desert Horseman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Horseman, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Horseman.cfg:36
msgid ""
"Trading speed for heavier arms and armament, Elvish Horsemen delight in "
"riding into danger instead of away from it. The open sands are much more "
"suited towards mounted combat than their old forests were, and through the "
"generations the Elves have greatly increased their equestrian skills."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Hunter, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Hunter.cfg:5
msgid "Desert Hunter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Hunter, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Hunter.cfg:24
msgid ""
"Desert Hunters are trained to scour the sands for prey and enemies. They can "
"quickly entangle others with their bolas and then finish them off with their "
"swords."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Hunter.cfg:146
msgid "female^Desert Hunter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Marksman, race=elf, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Marksman.cfg:4
msgid "Desert Marksman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Marksman, race=elf, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Marksman.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Desert Marksman are expert in use of the bow. Though their bows and arrows "
"are not as fine as those of their ancestors, they continue to hone their "
"skill. This great skill with the bow compensates for their lack of skill in "
"melee combat."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Marksman.cfg:174
msgid "female^Desert Marksman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Marshal, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Marshal.cfg:4
msgid "Desert Marshal"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Marshal, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Marshal.cfg:29
msgid ""
"Desert Marshals are master commanders, able to inspire confidence in any "
"level 1 or 2 unit in adjacent hexes, causing them to fight with increased "
"skill. Desert Marshals prefer engaging the enemy in melee combat, but are "
"trained in archery as well."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Outrider, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Outrider.cfg:4
msgid "Desert Outrider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Outrider, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Outrider.cfg:30
msgid ""
"Riding like the wind, Desert Outriders breeze across the sands to strike at "
"weaker units and exposed flanks. Skilled in the sword, and trained in the "
"bow, they strike hard before flying off into the sands to evade response."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Prowler, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Prowler.cfg:4
msgid "Desert Prowler"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Prowler, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Prowler.cfg:30
msgid ""
"Desert Prowlers sneak across the sands, searching out enemies and protecting "
"their people. They are trained to slip past enemies unnoticed and flank them."
" The combination of their bolas and blades allows them to cripple and kill "
"opponents with alarming ease."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Prowler.cfg:132
msgid "female^Desert Prowler"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Ranger, race=elf, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Ranger.cfg:4
msgid "Desert Ranger"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Ranger, race=elf, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Ranger.cfg:30
msgid ""
"Desert Rangers are quick and powerful. Skilled in both short and long-range "
"combat, Rangers are truly all-round fighters. Like their kin, they prefer the"
" sword to the bow and are adept at sneaking around and backstabbing their "
"enemies."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Ranger.cfg:154
msgid "female^Desert Ranger"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Rider, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Rider.cfg:4
msgid "Desert Rider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Rider, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Rider.cfg:27
msgid ""
"Swift riders, Desert Riders are fast in the open desert. They can use a bow "
"from horseback, but prefer to engage in melee combat when necessary."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Scout, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Scout.cfg:5
msgid "Desert Scout"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Scout, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Scout.cfg:28
msgid ""
"Desert Scouts move swiftly across the sands. Their skill on horseback is "
"virtually unmatched, although they do lack power in combat."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Sentinel, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Sentinel.cfg:4
msgid "Desert Sentinel"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Sentinel, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Sentinel.cfg:26
msgid ""
"Desert Sentinels patrol the sands; they are trained to avoid enemies when it "
"is advantageous. They can cripple opponents with their bolas and are deadly "
"with their swords.\n"
"\n"
"The skirmish ability allows the rogue to ignore enemy units' zones of control"
" and thus move unhindered around them."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Sentinel.cfg:114
msgid "female^Desert Sentinel"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Shaman, race=elf, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Shaman.cfg:5
msgid "female^Desert Shaman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Shaman, race=elf, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Shaman.cfg:27
msgid ""
"Desert Shamans focus on less violent ways to hinder the enemy. Their "
"entangling attack slows enemies down and reduces by one the number of times "
"they may attack. Shamans also possess basic healing abilities."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Sharpshooter, race=elf, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Sharpshooter.cfg:4
msgid "Desert Sharpshooter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Sharpshooter, race=elf, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Sharpshooter.cfg:23
msgid ""
"The most elite archers among the elves, Desert Sharpshooters use the best "
"bows and arrows available, which makes them just as deadly as their "
"ancestors. Desert Sharpshooters are incredibly accurate, even when firing "
"very quickly, which makes them excellent at picking off entrenched enemies."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Sharpshooter.cfg:155
msgid "female^Desert Sharpshooter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Shyde, race=elf, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Shyde.cfg:4
msgid "female^Desert Shyde"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Shyde, race=elf, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Shyde.cfg:29
msgid ""
"Desert Shydes are elves that are devoted to nature and their faerie side. "
"Dragonfly wings sprout from their backs and change them into beautiful "
"creatures. They are capable of gliding unencumbered across almost any "
"terrain."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Shyde, race=elf, gender=female
#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Star, race=elf, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Shyde.cfg:29
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Star.cfg:37
msgid "This unit can fly across any terrain except deep water."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Star, race=elf, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Star.cfg:4
msgid "female^Desert Star"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Star, race=elf, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Star.cfg:37
msgid ""
"Desert Stars are Shydes that have becomes so powerful and holy that they "
"shine forth the light of Eloh, even in the darkest places. They are living "
"testaments to the power and glory of Eloh. Like Shydes, they are capable of "
"gliding unencumbered across almost any terrain. Eloh's power also reduces the"
" wounds that Desert Stars suffer when attacked."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_Star, race=elf, gender=female
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Desert_Star.cfg:37
msgid "It also gains a 10% bonus to resistance from all attacks."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_dust_faerie, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Dust_Faerie.cfg:5
msgid "Dust Faerie"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_dust_faerie, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Dust_Faerie.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is an adaptation of Flurry from the Era of the Future, designed to "
"fill a missing role in AE Desert elves.\n"
"\n"
"The presence of Dusk Faeries is still a mystery, still it's very well known "
"that faeries in desert show a different conduct compared to forest ones. "
"First to notice is that they often enjoy more of loneliness and second is "
"that they don't hesitate about acting violent in times it's required to. Not "
"wholesome beings as forest faeries but are reliable friends specially in "
"times to fight."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=ranged
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Dust_Faerie.cfg:99
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Dust_Twist.cfg:100
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Dust_Vengance.cfg:62
msgid "Dust Tornado"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_dust_twist, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Dust_Twist.cfg:5
msgid "Dust Twist"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_dust_twist, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Dust_Twist.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This unit is an adaptation of Talon Warrior from the Era of the Future, "
"designed to fill a missing role in AE Desert elves.\n"
"\n"
"After some time in the battlefield, these faeries are named dust twist. Now "
"are much more skilled at casting more and larger tornadoes which can cause a "
"lot of harm."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_dust_vengeance, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Dust_Vengance.cfg:5
msgid "Dust Vengeance"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_dust_vengeance, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Dust_Vengance.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This unit is an adaptation of PYR's Dust Devil combined with Flurry from the "
"Era of the Future, designed as an extra by IPS for Ageless Era's Desert "
"Elves.\n"
"\n"
"\tFor real unknown reasons, some dust faeries have an endless thirst of "
"vengeance because of the death of various of their friends in the "
"battlefield. Spinning faster than all other dust faeries it's extremely hard "
"to harm them using cutting or piercing weapons, still everything else seems "
"to be effective against them."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=melee
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Dust_Vengance.cfg:49
msgid "twister"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=ranged
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Dust_Vengance.cfg:75
msgid "sand storm"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_dust_Whirlwind, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Dust_Whirlwind.cfg:5
msgid "Dust Whirlwind"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_agl_desert_elves_dust_Whirlwind, race=elf
#: .\units\misc_units\desert-elves\Dust_Whirlwind.cfg:19
msgid ""
"This unit is an adaptation of Whirlwind (but lv3) from the Era of the Future,"
" designed to fill a missing role in AE Desert elves.\n"
"\n"
"Dust Whirlwind are the dust faeries are between all beings that are known to "
